title: FairyTale: A True Story
text: In 1917, two children take a photograph, which is soon believed by some to be the first scientific evidence of the existence of fairies.

title: Phantoms
text: In the peaceful town of Snowfield, Colorado something evil has wiped out the community. And now, its up to a group of people to stop it, or at least get out of Snowfield alive.

title: Swept from the Sea
text: The story of Russian emigrant Yanko Goorall and servant Amy Foster in the end of nineteenth century. When Yanko enters a farm, sick and hungry after a shipwreck, everyone is afraid of him, except for Amy.

title: Life Less Ordinary, A
text: Upon being fired, a desperate guy kidnaps a daughter of his former boss. Two angels are sent to Earth to check if love is possible in this case.

title: Hurricane Streets
text: A teenage petty criminal dreams of escaping his increasingly unlawful lifestyle when he meets a sweet girl who hopes to one day travel to Alaska.

title: Eve's Bayou
text: What did little Eve see--and how will it haunt her? Husband, father and womanizer Louis Batiste is the head of an affluent family, but it's the women who rule this gothic world of secrets, lies and mystic forces.

title: Switchback
text: An FBI agent tries to catch a serial killer who kidnapped his son.

title: Gang Related
text: After murdering an undercover DEA agent, two corrupt cops scramble to cover up what they've done.

title: Stripes
text: Two friends who are dissatisfied with their jobs decide to join the army for a bit of fun.

title: Bean
text: The bumbling Mr. Bean travels to America when he is given the responsibility of bringing a highly valuable painting to a Los Angeles museum.

title: Mad City
text: A distraught man inadvertently takes a group of children hostage in a museum while a hungry, seasoned reporter tries to resurrect his career covering the story.

title: Welcome to Sarajevo
text: Journalist Flynn from the U.S., Michael Henderson from the U.K., and their teams meet at the beginning of the Bosnian war in Sarajevo. During their reports, they find an orphanage run by the devoted Mrs. Savic near the frontline. Henderson gets so involved in the kids' problems, that he decides to take one of the children, Emira, illegally back to England. He is assisted by American aid worker Nina.

title: Deceiver
text: A hooker is found cut in two. Two cops give polygraph tests to the only suspect, James Wayland , an unstable genius. After some time, the roles change.

title: Rainmaker, The
text: An underdog lawyer takes on a fraudulent insurance company.

title: Boogie Nights
text: Back when sex was safe, pleasure was a business and business was booming, an idealistic porn producer aspires to elevate his craft to an art when he discovers a hot young talent.

title: Witness
text: When a young Amish boy is sole witness to a murder, policeman John Book goes into hiding in Amish country to protect him until the trial.

title: Incognito
text: Harry Donovan is an art forger who paints a fake Rembrandt picture for five hundred thousand dollars. Marieke, the woman he meets in Paris and gets into bed with, turns out to be the art expert whom Harry's clients are using to check the counterfeit picture he painted.

title: Starship Troopers
text: Humans in a fascist, militaristic future wage war with giant alien bugs.

title: Critical Care
text: A hospital resident is put in the middle of a legal battle between two half-sisters on whether to pull their comatose dad's life support. But more seems to be at stake than dad's life - his inheritance.

title: Joy Luck Club, The
text: The life histories of four East Asian women and their daughters reflect and guide each other.

title: Chairman of the Board
text: A surfer becomes the head of a major company.

title: Sliding Doors
text: A London woman's love life and career both hinge, unknown to her, on whether or not she catches a train. We see it both ways, in parallel.

title: Mortal Kombat: Annihilation
text: A group of martial arts warriors have only six days to save the Earth from an extra-dimensional invasion.

title: Truman Show, The
text: An insurance salesman discovers his whole life is actually a reality TV show.

title: Wings of the Dove, The
text: An impoverished woman who has been forced to choose between a privileged life with her wealthy aunt and her journalist lover, befriends an American heiress. When she discovers the heiress is attracted to her own lover and is dying, she sees a chance to have both the privileged life she cannot give up and the lover she cannot live without.

title: Mrs. Dalloway
text: In 1923 London, socialite Clarissa Dalloway's  well-planned party is overshadowed by the return of an old suitor she had known thirty-three years earlier.

title: I Love You, I Love You Not
text: Prep school student Daisy and her European-born grandmother Nana share the sad stories of their lives: Daisy tells Nana of her romance with young Ethan and problems in school because she's Jewish
column9: and Nana tells of her young years under Nazis when she was sent to ghetto and then to concentration camp.

title: Red Corner
text: An American attorney on business in China is wrongfully arrested and put on trial for murder, with a female defense lawyer from the country the only key to proving his innocence.

title: Jackal, The
text: An imprisoned I.R.A. fighter is freed to help stop a brutal, seemingly "faceless" assassin from completing his next job.

title: Anastasia
text: The last surviving child of the Russian Royal Family joins two con men to reunite with her grandmother, the Dowager Empress, while the undead Rasputin seeks her death.

title: Man Who Knew Too Little, The
text: Wallace Ritchie is mistaken for a spy and must stop a plot to assassinate international leaders at a banquet.

title: Alien: Resurrection
text: 200 years after her death, Ellen Ripley is revived as a powerful human/alien hybrid clone. Along with a crew of space pirates, she must again battle the deadly aliens and stop them from reaching Earth.

title: Amistad
text: In 1839, the revolt of Mende captives aboard a Spanish owned ship causes a major controversy in the United States when the ship is captured off the coast of Long Island. The courts must decide whether the Mende are slaves or legally free.

title: Apostle, The
text: After his happy life spins out of control, a preacher from Texas changes his name, goes to Louisiana and starts preaching on the radio.

title: Artemisia
text: Artemisia Gentileschi  was one of the first well-known female painters. The movie tells the story of her youth, when she was guided and protected by her father, the painter Orazio Gentileschi. Her professional curiosity about the male anatomy, forbidden for her eyes, led her to the knowledge of sexual pleasure. But she was also well known because in 1612 she had to appear in a courtroom because her teacher, Agostino Tassi, was suspected of raping her. She tried to protect him, but was put in the thumb screws...

title: Bent
text: In 1930s Berlin, a gay Jew is sent to a concentration camp under the Nazi regime.

title: Butcher Boy, The
text: The antisocial son of an alcoholic father and a bipolar mother grows up in 1960s Ireland.

title: Deconstructing Harry
text: Suffering from writer's block and eagerly awaiting his writing award, Harry Block remembers events from his past and scenes from his best-selling books as characters, real and fictional, come back to haunt him.

title: Flubber
text: An absent-minded professor discovers "flubber," a rubber-like super-bouncy substance.

title: For Richer or Poorer
text: An unhappily married Manhattan socialite couple flee from the I.R.S. and end up in Amish country where they pretend to be visiting relatives.

title: Good Will Hunting
text: Will Hunting, a janitor at M.I.T., has a gift for mathematics, but needs help from a psychologist to find direction in his life.

title: Home Alone 3
text: Alex Pruitt, an 8-year-old boy living in Chicago, must fend off international spies who seek a top-secret computer chip in his toy car.

title: Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil
text: A visiting city reporter's assignment suddenly revolves around the murder trial of a local millionaire, whom he befriends.

title: Mouse Hunt
text: Two stumblebum inheritors are determined to rid their antique house of a mouse who is equally determined to stay where he is.

title: Scream 2
text: Two years after the first series of murders, as Sidney acclimates to college life, someone donning the Ghostface costume begins a new string of killings.

title: Stranger in the House
text: A botched diamond burglary and a dead publishing company executive set off a string of murders and betrayal in this suspensful, nonstop thriller!

title: Sweet Hereafter, The
text: A bus crash in a small town brings a lawyer to the town to defend the families, but he discovers that everything is not what it seems.

title: Titanic
text: A seventeen-year-old aristocrat falls in love with a kind but poor artist aboard the luxurious, ill-fated R.M.S. Titanic.

title: Tomorrow Never Dies
text: James Bond sets out to stop a media mogul's plan to induce war between China and the UK in order to obtain exclusive global media coverage.

title: Postman, The
text: A nameless drifter dons a postman's uniform and bag of mail as he begins a quest to inspire hope to the survivors living in post-apocalyptic America.

title: Horse Whisperer, The
text: The mother of a severely traumatized daughter enlists the aid of a unique horse trainer to help the girl's equally injured horse.

title: Jackie Brown
text: A flight attendant with a criminal past gets nabbed by the FBI for smuggling. Under pressure to become an informant against the drug dealer she works for, she must find a way to secure her future without getting killed.

title: Kundun
text: From childhood to adulthood, Tibet's fourteenth Dalai Lama deals with Chinese oppression and other problems.

title: Mr. Magoo
text: The myopic millionaire defeats jewel smugglers in his usual bumbling manner.

title: Big Lebowski, The
text: Jeff "The Dude" Lebowski, mistaken for a millionaire of the same name, seeks restitution for his ruined rug and enlists his bowling buddies to help get it.

title: Afterglow
text: A handyman with marital problems meets a housewife with the same.

title: My Life in Pink
text: Ludovic is an innocent seven-year-old child who provokes horror in his community when he dresses in girls clothes and insists he's a girl.

title: Great Expectations
text: Modernization of Charles Dickens' classic story finds the hapless Finn as a painter in New York City pursuing his unrequited and haughty childhood love.

title: 3 Ninjas: High Noon On Mega Mountain
text: The three unstoppable Ninja brothers fight to save their hero  and Mega Mountain Amusement Park from the vicious kid-hating Medusa .

title: Senseless
text: A student gets his senses enhanced by an experimental drug. But abuse is not an option.

title: Wag the Dog
text: Shortly before an election, a spin-doctor and a Hollywood producer join efforts to fabricate a war in order to cover up a Presidential sex scandal.

title: Dark City
text: A man struggles with memories of his past, which include a wife he cannot remember and a nightmarish world no one else ever seems to wake up from.

title: Hard Rain
text: The partner and nephew of an armored-truck driver tries to prevent three million dollars from being taken by a gang during a catastrophic flooding caused by a severe storm.

title: Half Baked
text: The story of three not so bright men who come up with a series of crazy schemes to get a friend out of jail.

title: Fallen
text: Homicide detective John Hobbes witnesses the execution of serial killer Edgar Reese. Soon after the execution, the killings start again, and they are very similar to Reese's style.

title: Shooting Fish
text: Two con artists' plan to steal enough for a house are twisted when a pretty girl enters the picture.

title: Fallen Angels
text: This Hong Kong-set crime drama follows the lives of a hitman, hoping to get out of the business, and his elusive female partner.

title: Four Days in September
text: Brazillian urban guerrilla fighters kidnap the American Ambassador. Now, the diplomat's life hangs in the balance - helplessly caught between a government unwilling to cooperate - and his fear of the captors themselves.

title: Spice World
text: World famous pop group the Spice Girls zip around London in their luxurious double decker tour bus having various adventures and performing for their fans.

title: Deep Rising
text: A group of heavily armed hijackers board a luxury ocean liner in the South Pacific Ocean to loot it, only to do battle with a series of large-sized, tentacled, man-eating sea creatures who had already invaded the ship.

title: Music From Another Room
text: A man's search for his one true love whose birth he assisted in as a five-year-old.

title: Replacement Killers, The
text: A troubled hitman seeks aid from a forger to help him get papers to China. However, the drug lord has hired replacements to finish the job, and kill the hitman.

title: B. Monkey
text: A young woman attempts to end her criminal career. But she needs love to make it.

title: Night Flier
text: A reporter is on the trail of a vampiric murderer who travels by plane.

title: Blues Brothers 2000
text: Elwood must reunite the old band, with a few new members, and go on another "Mission from God."

title: Wedding Singer, The
text: Robbie, a singer, and Julia, a waitress, are both engaged, but to the wrong people. Fortune intervenes to help them discover each other.

title: Sphere
text: A spaceship is discovered under three hundred years' worth of coral growth at the bottom of the ocean.

title: Palmetto
text: A recently released ex-con gets involved in a fake kidnapping scheme that turns very real.

title: As Good as It Gets
text: A single mother and waitress, a misanthropic author, and a gay artist form an unlikely friendship after the artist is assaulted in a robbery.

title: King of New York
text: A drug kingpin is released from prison and seeks to take total control of the criminal underworld in order to give back to the community.

title: Twilight
text: A retired detective accepts a simple task, unaware that it will tear open old, forgotten, but deadly wounds.

title: U.S. Marshals
text: U.S. Marshal Samuel Gerard and his team of Marshals are assigned to track down Sheridan, who has been accused of a double-murder.

title: Welcome to Woop-Woop
text: A con artist escapes a deal gone wrong in New York and winds up in the Aussie outback in a strange town whose inhabitants are an oddball collection of misfits.

title: Love and Death on Long Island
text: Giles De'Ath  is a widower who doesn't like anything modern. He goes to movies and falls in love with movie star Ronnie Bostock . He then investigates everything about the movie and Ronnie. After that, he travels to Long Island City, where Ronnie lives, and meets him, pretending that Ronnie is a great actor, and that's why Giles admires him.

title: Everest
text: An international team of climbers ascends Mt. Everest in the spring of 1996. The film depicts their lengthy preparations for the climb, their trek to the summit, and their successful return to Base Camp. It also shows many of the challenges the group faced, including avalanches, lack of oxygen, treacherous ice walls, and a deadly blizzard.

title: Hush
text: Newlyweds move to the family thoroughbred horse ranch, where the husband's obsessive mother resolves to get rid of her new daughter-in-law.

title: Suicide Kings
text: A group of youngsters kidnap a respected Mafia figure.

title: Man in the Iron Mask, The
text: The cruel King Louis XIV of France has a secret twin brother whom he keeps imprisoned. Can the twin be substituted for the real king?

title: Newton Boys, The
text: The story of the Newton gang, the most successful bank robbers in history, owing to their good planning and minimal violence.

title: Wild Things
text: A police detective uncovers a conspiracy behind a case involving a high-school guidance counselor when accusations of rape are made against him by two female students.

title: Paulie
text: Paulie, a talking parrot, recounts his travels looking for his original owner to a Russian janitor who helps him to the end of his journey.

title: Cool, Dry Place, A
text: Russell, single father balances his work as a lawyer with the care of his five-year-old son, after his wife abandoned them. When she reappears creating turmoil, he must deal with his new love interest and a job opportunity of a lifetime.

title: Fireworks
text: Nishi leaves the police in the face of harrowing personal and professional difficulties. Spiraling into depression, he makes questionable decisions.

title: Primary Colors
text: A man joins the political campaign of a smooth-operator candidate for President of the U.S.

title: Wide Awake
text: A 10-year-old boy goes on a search for God after his grandfather dies.

title: Two Girls and a Guy
text: 2 girls wait outside a young actor's door and find out he's had them both as "only" girlfriend the last 10 months. They wait inside after breaking in. When Blake comes home he just can't stop lying but they stay.

title: Object of My Affection, The
text: A pregnant New York City social worker begins to develop romantic feelings for her gay best friend, and decides she'd rather raise her child with him, much to the dismay of her overbearing boyfriend.

title: Homegrown
text: 3 marijuana farmhands see their boss killed, ending their peaceful existence in NW California. They decide to harvest, process and sell the crop themselves. Crime bosses, corrupt cops, killer pilot, greed etc. ensue.

title: The Players Club
text: A woman must contend with rival strippers and her boss in an attempt to make a legitimate living.

title: Chorus Line, A
text: Hopefuls try out before a demanding director for a part in a new musical.

title: Beat Street
text: An aspiring DJ, from the South Bronx, and his best friend, a promoter, try to get into show business by exposing people to hip-hop music and culture.

title: Breakin' 2: Electric Boogaloo
text: A developer tries to bulldoze a community recreation center. The local breakdancers try to stop it.

title: Breakin'
text: A struggling young jazz dancer meets up with two break-dancers. Together they become the sensation of the street crowds.

title: Laputa: Castle in the Sky
text: A young boy and a girl with a magic crystal must race against pirates and foreign agents in a search for a legendary floating castle.

title: High Society
text: With socialite Tracy Lord about to remarry, her ex-husband - with the help of a sympathetic reporter - has 48 hours to convince her that she really still loves him.

title: Kiss Me Kate
text: An ex-husband and wife team star in a musical version of 'The Taming of the Shrew'; off-stage, the production is troublesome with ex-lovers' quarrels and two gangsters looking for some money owed to them.

title: Matrix Reloaded, The
text: Freedom fighters Neo, Trinity and Morpheus continue to lead the revolt against the Machine Army, unleashing their arsenal of extraordinary skills and weaponry against the systematic forces of repression and exploitation.

title: Down with Love
text: In 1962 New York City, love blossoms between a playboy journalist and a feminist advice author.

title: Cinemania
text: This documentary about the culture of intense cinephilia in New York City reveals the impassioned world of five obsessed movie buffs. The filmmakers expose this delightfully deranged cult by capturing the daily lives of its members. Interviews in movie houses, on the street and in the homes of the subjects tell the story of each individual. Many cannot hold a job, or choose not to. All of them have demoted the importance of the real world, giving all of their attention to the fantasy world of the movies. These human encyclopedias of cinema see two to five films a day, and from 600 to 2,000 films per year. Many have no physical sex lives, living instead in a world of romance with stars like James Dean or Audrey Hepburn. In Cinemania, Hollywood's biggest fans become the true stars. This is the story of their lives, their memories, their unbending habits and the films they love.

title: Spanish Apartment, The
text: A strait-laced French student moves into an apartment in Barcelona with a cast of six other characters from all over Europe. Together, they speak the international language of love and friendship.

title: Pokémon Heroes
text: Two thieves take control of an ancient weapon designed to defend the canal city of Altomare.

title: Bruce Almighty
text: A guy who complains about God too often is given almighty powers to teach him how difficult it is to run the world.

title: In-Laws, The
text: Right before his daughter's wedding, a mild-mannered foot doctor discovers that his future son-in-law's father is a free-wheeling international spy.

title: Gigantic
text: Documentary about the music group They Might Be Giants.

title: Respiro
text: On an impoverished Italian island, a free-spirited woman is accused of madness by townspeople fed up with her antics.

title: Finding Nemo
text: After his son is captured in the Great Barrier Reef and taken to Sydney, a timid clownfish sets out on a journey to bring him home.

title: Italian Job, The
text: After being betrayed and left for dead in Italy, Charlie Croker and his team plan an elaborate gold heist against their former ally.

title: Wrong Turn
text: Chris and a group of five friends are left stranded deep in the middle of the woods after their cars collide. As they venture deeper into the woods, they face an uncertain and bloodcurdling fate.

title: Capturing the Friedmans
text: Documentary on the Friedmans, a seemingly typical, upper-middle-class Jewish family whose world is instantly transformed when the father and his youngest son are arrested and charged with shocking and horrible crimes.

title: Together
text: A violin prodigy and his father travel to Beijing, where the father seeks the means to his son's success while the son struggles to accept the path laid before him.

title: 2 Fast 2 Furious
text: Former cop Brian O'Conner is called upon to bust a dangerous criminal and he recruits the help of a former childhood friend and street racer who has a chance to redeem himself.

title: Whale Rider
text: A contemporary story of love, rejection and triumph as a young Maori girl fights to fulfill a destiny her grandfather refuses to recognize.

title: Nevada Smith
text: A half-American Indian and half-white teenager evolves into a hardened killer as he tracks down his parents' murderers.

title: Once a Thief
text: A romantic and action packed story of three best friends, a group of high end art thieves, who come into trouble when a love-triangle forms between them.

title: Silk Stockings
text: A musical remake of Ninotchka: After three bumbling Soviet agents fail in their mission to retrieve a straying Soviet composer from Paris, the beautiful, ultra-serious Ninotchka is sent to complete their mission and to retrieve them. She starts out condemning the decadent West, but gradually falls under its spell with the help of Steve Canfield, an American movie producer.

title: Crazies, The
text: The military attempts to contain a manmade combat virus that causes death and permanent insanity in those infected, as it overtakes a small Pennsylvania town.

title: Murder on a Sunday Morning
text: Oscar-winning documentary that documents a murder trial in which a 15-year-old African-American is wrongfully accused of a 2000 murder in Jacksonville, Florida.

title: Siam Sunset
text: A British man with a peculiar curse goes on a low-rent bus tour in Australia.

title: Treasure Island
text: The treasure seeking adventures of young Jim Hawkins and pirate captain Long John Silver.

title: Walk, Don't Run
text: During the housing shortage of the Summer Olympic Games in 1964, two men and a woman share a small apartment in Tokyo, and the older man soon starts playing Cupid to the younger pair.

title: Animals are Beautiful People
text: Hilarious documentary on the wildlife of the Namib Desert.

title: Car Wash
text: A comedic take on the daily life of car-wash employees, chronicling their hopes, fears, joys, dreams, and tribulations, and meeting some eccentric customers along the way.

title: Destry Rides Again
text: Deputy sheriff Destry tames the town of Bottle Neck, including saloon singer Frenchy.

title: Intervista
text: Federico Fellini accepts the request of a television crew to be interviewed about his career, narrating memories, dreams, realities and fantasies.

title: Live Wire
text: After A US senator is killed, A Bomb Disposal Expert is brought in to investigate the deadly explosive and must uncover the terrorists plan.

title: Shenandoah
text: During the Civil War, a Virginia farmer and his family vow to remain neutral, but one of the sons is captured by Union soldiers, sending the farmer to his rescue.

title: Oscar
text: A gangster attempts to keep the promise he made to his dying father: that he would give up his life of crime and "go straight".

title: 6th Man, The
text: A college athlete returns from the dead to help his brother's basketball team win the NCAA title.

title: Railway Children, The
text: After the enforced absence of their father, three children move with their mother to Yorkshire, where during their adventures they attempt to discover the reason for his disappearance.

title: Two Mules for Sister Sara
text: Nun Sara  is on the run in Mexico and is saved from cowboys by Hogan , who is preparing for a future mission to capture a French fort. The pair become good friends, but Sara never does tell him the true reason behind her being outlawed.

title: Winchester '73
text: A cowboy's obsession with a stolen rifle leads to a bullet-ridden odyssey through the American West.

title: Man with the Movie Camera, The
text: A man travels around a city with a camera slung over his shoulder, documenting urban life with dazzling invention.

title: Objective, Burma!
text: A platoon of special ops are tasked to parachute into the remote Burmese jungle and destroy a strategic Japanese radar station, but getting out isn't as easy.

title: This Boy's Life
text: The story about the relationship between a rebellious 1950s teenager and his abusive stepfather, based on the memoirs of writer and literature Professor Tobias Wolff.

title: Barton Fink
text: A renowned New York playwright is enticed to California to write for the movies and discovers the hellish truth of Hollywood.

title: Belle époque
text: A 1931 Spanish military deserter finds himself on a lonely farm until the farmer's four daughters pay a visit and he falls for all of them.

title: Flight of the Phoenix, The
text: After a plane crash in the Sahara, one of the survivors says he's an airplane designer and they can make a flyable plane from the wreckage.

title: From the Terrace
text: An ambitious young executive chooses a loveless marriage and an unfulfilling personal life in exchange for a successful Wall Street career.

title: Long, Hot Summer, The
text: Accused barn burner and conman Ben Quick arrives in a small Mississippi town and quickly ingratiates himself with its richest family, the Varners.

title: Man of Aran
text: In this blend of documentary and fictional narrative from pioneering filmmaker Robert Flaherty, the everyday trials of life on Ireland's unforgiving Aran Islands are captured with attention to naturalistic beauty and historical detail.

title: Music Box
text: A lawyer defends her father accused of war crimes, but there is more to the case than she suspects.

title: Trial, The
text: An unassuming office worker is arrested and stands trial, but he is never made aware of his charges.

title: Unforgiven, The
text: The neighbors of a frontier family turn on them when it is suspected that their adopted daughter was stolen from the local Kiowa tribe.

title: Good Burger
text: A dim-witted teenager and his new coworker try to save the old burger joint they work for from failing after the opening of a brand new burger restaurant across the street, which's planning to put them out of business.

title: Jubilee
text: Queen Elisabeth I travels 400 years into the future to witness the appalling revelation of a dystopian London overrun by corruption and a vicious gang of punk guerrilla girls led by the new Monarch of Punk.

title: Mississippi Masala
text: An ethnic Indian family is expelled from Idi Amin's Uganda in 1972 and lives in Mississippi 17 years later. The dad sues Uganda to get his property back. The grown daughter falls in love with a black man.

title: Shattered
text: After a horrific car wreck leaves him an amnesiac, a man slowly begins to unravel his shocking past.

title: Song of Bernadette, The
text: 14-year-old Bernadette Soubirous, living in a small town in the south of 1850s France, claims to have seen a divine vision, prompting extreme skepticism, concern from her family, and religious and political turmoil.

title: Thoroughly Modern Millie
text: Millie Dillmount comes to town in the roaring twenties to encounter flappers, sexuality, and white slavers.

title: Dumb and Dumberer: When Harry Met Lloyd
text: Set back in the 80s when Harry met Lloyd in high school where they cross paths with a mean principal and a bunch of other outcasts much like themselves.

title: From Justin to Kelly
text: A waitress from Texas and a college student from Pennsylvania meet during spring break in Fort Lauderdale, Florida and come together through their shared love of singing.

title: Hollywood Homicide
text: Two LAPD detectives who moonlight in other fields investigate the murder of an up-and-coming rap group.

title: Alex and Emma
text: A writer must turn out a novel in thirty days or face the wrath of loan sharks.

title: 28 Days Later
text: Four weeks after a mysterious, incurable virus spreads throughout the UK, a handful of survivors try to find sanctuary.

title: Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle
text: The Angels investigate a series of murders which occur after the theft of a witness protection profile database.

title: Fulltime Killer
text: Two very different hitmen find themselves to be in each other's way. They use all their skill to solve the problem.

title: Ali: Fear Eats the Soul
text: A lonely widow meets a much younger Arab worker in a bar during a rainstorm. They fall in love, to their own surprise and to the outright shock of their families, colleagues, and drinking buddies.

title: Bodies, Rest & Motion
text: A fired TV salesman in Arizona decides to move to Butte, MT, in his car with his girlfriend. She meets a single housepainter.

title: Ring of Terror
text: A group of medical students undertake some silly and frightening endeavors in order to pledge a fraternity.

title: You Only Live Once
text: The public defender's secretary and an ex-convict get married and try to make a life together, but a series of disasters sends their lives spiraling out of control.

title: Anastasia
text: An opportunistic businessman tries to pass off a mysterious impostor as the Grand Duchess Anastasia, and she is so convincing that even the biggest skeptics believe her.

title: Babe, The
text: Babe Ruth becomes a baseball legend but is unheroic to those who know him.

title: Mr. Baseball
text: Jack Elliot, once a great baseball player, is forced to play in Japan where his brash, egotistical ways cause friction with his new teammates and friends.

title: Scaramouche
text: In France during the late 18th Century, a man sets out to avenge the death of his friend at the hands of a master swordsman.

title: Start the Revolution Without Me
text: Two mismatched sets of identical twins, one aristocrat, one peasant, mistakenly exchange identities on the eve of the French Revolution.

title: Tenant, The
text: A bureaucrat rents a Paris apartment where he finds himself drawn into a rabbit hole of dangerous paranoia.

title: What's Up, Doc?
text: The accidental mix-up of four identical plaid overnight bags leads to a series of increasingly wild and wacky situations.

title: Hulk
text: Bruce Banner, a genetics researcher with a tragic past, suffers an accident that causes him to transform into a raging green monster when he gets angry.

title: Legally Blonde 2: Red, White & Blonde
text: Elle Woods heads to Washington, D.C. to join the staff of a Representative in order to pass a bill to ban animal testing.

title: Sinbad: Legend of the Seven Seas
text: The sailor of legend is framed by the goddess Eris for the theft of the Book of Peace and must travel to her realm at the end of the world to retrieve it and save the life of his childhood friend Prince Proteus.

title: Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines
text: A machine from a post-apocalyptic future travels back in time to protect a man and a woman from an advanced robotic assassin to ensure they both survive a nuclear attack.

title: Swimming Pool
text: A British mystery author visits her publisher's home in the South of France, where her interaction with his unusual daughter sets off some touchy dynamics.

title: Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl
text: Blacksmith Will Turner teams up with eccentric pirate "Captain" Jack Sparrow to save his love, the governor's daughter, from Jack's former pirate allies, who are now undead.

title: League of Extraordinary Gentlemen, The
text: In an alternate Victorian Age world, a group of famous contemporary fantasy, science fiction, and adventure characters team up on a secret mission.

title: Cuckoo, The
text: In WWII, a Finnish sniper is left chained to a rock by German soldiers, while a captain of the Red Army, en route to his court martial, is almost blown up by Russian planes. A Lapp woman gives a shelter to both of them at her farm.

title: I Capture the Castle
text: A love story set in 1930s England that follows 17-year-old Cassandra Mortmain, and the fortunes of her eccentric family, struggling to survive in a decaying English castle.

title: Northfork
text: Set in 1955, the residents of a small Montana community are forced to move their homes to make way for a new dam.

title: Bad Boys II
text: Two loose-cannon narcotics cops investigate the flow of Ecstasy into Florida from a Cuban drug cartel.

title: How to Deal
text: A teenager , disillusioned by too many examples of love gone wrong, refuses to believe that true love exists. Then this new guy  comes along...

title: Johnny English
text: After a sudden attack on MI5, Johnny English, Britain's most confident, yet unintelligent spy, becomes Britain's only spy.

title: Anarchist Cookbook, The
text: A dramedy that centers on a self-procalimed anarchist and his like-minded friends.

title: Dirty Pretty Things
text: Irregular migrants Okwe and Senay work at a posh London hotel and live in constant fear of deportation. One night Okwe stumbles across evidence of a bizarre murder setting off a series of events that could lead to disaster or freedom.

title: Embalmer, The
text: A solitary embalmer meets a charming and unemployed waiter who becomes his assistant, but the two get involved in a morbid and unhealthy professional and personal relationship.

title: Garage Days
text: The story of a young garage band in Sydney, Australia trying to make it big.

title: Born to Be Wild
text: Margaret teaches a gorilla sign language etc. When the gorilla owner takes it back to make money from shows, Margaret's rebellious teenage son steals it. They're off on a road trip to the Canadian border.

title: Curly Sue
text: A homeless man and his young companion, who survive by conning people, meet a woman who may need them even more than they need her.

title: Little Giants
text: Misfits form their own opposing team to an elite peewee football team, coached by the elite team coach's brother.

title: Loose Cannons
text: An unconventional cop who doesn't take any bull, is paired up with an amazing detective to capture some powerful criminals but the cop soon realizes that his by the book partner has split personality disorder.

title: Mouse That Roared, The
text: An impoverished backward nation declares a war on the United States of America, hoping to lose, but things don't go according to plan.

title: Masked & Anonymous
text: A singer, whose career has gone on a downward spiral, is forced to make a comeback to the performance stage for a benefit concert.

title: Lara Croft Tomb Raider: The Cradle of Life
text: Adventurer Lara Croft goes on a quest to save the mythical Pandora's Box, before an evil scientist finds it, and recruits a former Marine turned mercenary to assist her.

title: Seabiscuit
text: True story of the undersized Depression-era racehorse whose victories lifted not only the spirits of the team behind it but also those of their nation.

title: Spy Kids 3-D: Game Over
text: Carmen's caught in a virtual reality game designed by the Kids' new nemesis, the Toymaker. It's up to Juni to save his sister, and ultimately the world.

title: Buffalo Soldiers
text: A criminal subculture operates among U.S. soldiers stationed in West Germany just before the fall of the Berlin wall.

title: Camp
text: After a series of Broadway flops, songwriter Bert Hanley  goes to work at a musical camp for young performers. Inspired by the kids, he finds an opportunity to regain success by staging an altogether new production.

title: Mondays in the Sun
text: This is the story of those who live as if every day was a constant Sunday, those who spend their Mondays in the sun. The story of people who worked in a dockyard but are now unemployed.

title: Scorched
text: By chance 3 employees rob their bank the same weekend.

title: Avanti!
text: A successful businessman goes to Italy to arrange for the return of his tycoon father's body only to discover dad died with his long-time mistress.

title: Eve of Destruction
text: A terrorist hunter is hired by a scientist to deactivate her android double, a walking, talking, murderous nuclear bomb which has gone amok in the big city and is about to explode.

title: Kickboxer 2: The Road Back
text: David's brother, Kurt, defeats Po in Kickboxer . A year after Po kills Kurt, David, who has a kickboxing gym in LA, is manipulated into a match against Po.

title: Kiss Me, Stupid
text: Jealous piano teacher Orville Spooner sends his beautiful wife, Zelda, away for the night while he tries to sell a song to famous nightclub singer Dino, who is stranded in town.

title: One, Two, Three
text: In West Berlin during the Cold War, a Coca-Cola executive is given the task of taking care of his boss' socialite daughter.

title: Private Life of Sherlock Holmes, The
text: When a bored Holmes eagerly takes the case of Gabrielle Valladon after an attempt on her life, the search for her missing husband leads to Loch Ness and the legendary monster.

title: Remo Williams: The Adventure Begins
text: An officially "dead" cop is trained to become an extraordinary unique assassin in service of the US President.

title: Blood of Heroes, The
text: In a future where most of mankind and technology is wiped out, six people travel from place to place playing a brutal form of football with a dog skull. They hope one day to play in the league in a city.

title: What's Up, Tiger Lily?
text: In Woody Allen's directorial debut, he took the Japanese action film Kokusai himitsu keisatsu: Kagi no kagi  and re-dubbed it, changing the plot to make it revolve around a secret egg salad recipe.

title: American Wedding
text: It's the wedding of Jim and Michelle and the gathering of their families and friends, including Jim's old friends from high school and Michelle's little sister.

title: Gigli
text: Larry Gigli is assigned by a crime boss to kidnap the brother of a prominent district attorney. A beautiful woman known only as Ricki is sent to stay with him to make sure he doesn't mess up the job.

title: And Now... Ladies and Gentlemen...
text: A jazz singer and a British jewel thief are brought together by their mutual desire to forget the past.

title: Magdalene Sisters, The
text: Three young Irish women struggle to maintain their spirits while they endure dehumanizing abuse as inmates of a Magdalene Sisters Asylum.

title: Secret Lives of Dentists, The
text: An introspective dentist's suspicions about his wife's infidelity stresses his mental well being and family life to the breaking point.

title: Freaky Friday
text: An overworked mother and her daughter do not get along. When they switch bodies, each is forced to adapt to the other's life for one freaky Friday.

title: S.W.A.T.
text: An imprisoned drug kingpin offers a huge cash reward to anyone that can break him out of police custody, and only the L.A.P.D.'s Special Weapons and Tactics team can prevent it.

title: Divorce, Le
text: French vs. American social customs and behaviors are observed in a story about an American visiting her Frenchman-wed sister in Paris.

title: Princess Blade, The
text: Raised by assassins, Yuki is the last of the Takemikazuchi royal bloodline. A deadly weapon in her own right, she learns the gruesome truth about the death of her beloved mother and joins forces with a mysterious rebel leader.

title: Step Into Liquid
text: Surfers and secret spots from around the world are profiled in this documentary.

title: Double Life, A
text: A celebrated actor struggles to distinguish his own life from that of his most recent stage role, Othello.

title: Hawks and Sparrows
text: Totò and his son Ninetto are drifting on a road in Italy when they meet a speaking crow.

title: Gospel According to St. Matthew, The
text: The life of Jesus Christ according to the Gospel of Matthew. Pasolini shows Christ as a Marxist avant-la-lettre and therefore uses half of the text of Matthew.

title: Umberto D.
text: An elderly man and his dog struggle to survive on his government pension in Rome.

title: Brother's Keeper
text: This compelling documentary details the strange-but-true murder trial of Delbert Ward, accused of the mercy killing of his brother in rural upstate NY. This real-life murder mystery won the Audience Award at Sundance.

title: I Love You to Death
text: Joey Boca  owns a pizza parlor, and is married to Rosalie . He's also a serial womanizer. Rosalie goes to extremes when she finds he has been cheating.

title: Freddy vs. Jason
text: Freddy Krueger and Jason Voorhees return to terrorize the teenagers of Elm Street. Only this time, they're out to get each other, too.

title: Grind
text: Four skaters follow their idol on his summer tour in an attempt to get noticed, get sponsored, and become stars themselves.

title: Open Range
text: A former gunslinger is forced to take up arms again when he and his cattle crew are threatened by a corrupt lawman.

title: Shaolin Soccer
text: A young Shaolin follower reunites with his discouraged brothers to form a soccer team using their martial art skills to their advantage.

title: Uptown Girls
text: A grown-up woman who kept her childish instincts and behavior starts working as the nanny of an 8-year-old girl who actually acts like an adult. But everything ends right-side up.

title: American Splendor
text: An original mix of fiction and reality illuminates the life of comic book hero everyman Harvey Pekar.

title: Agent Cody Banks
text: A government agent trains Cody Banks in the ways of covert operations that require younger participants.

title: Camp Nowhere
text: A group of junior high kids don't want to go to summer camps chosen by their parents. They make their own adult-free camp and "hire" an ex drama teacher to help.

title: Hot Dog... The Movie
text: Harkin Banks heads to skiing championships in California. A teen runaway tags along as he parties and competes with friends and foes.

title: House of Wax
text: An associate burns down a wax museum with the owner inside, but he survives only to become vengeful and murderous.

title: Man's Best Friend
text: A genetically engineered dog escapes from the science facility where it was created. A family takes it in unaware of its deadly instincts which soon emerge. The scientist who created the dog tries to find it before its too late.

title: Sure Thing, The
text: Walter Gibson is a university freshman going through a dry spell. His old buddy arranges a "sure thing" for him in California. Gibson and his classmate Allison then take a long road trip out to Cali, and both foil each other's plans.

title: Valley Girl
text: Julie, a girl from the valley, meets Randy, a punk from the city. They are from different worlds and find love. Somehow they need to stay together in spite of her trendy, shallow friends.

title: Wait Until Dark
text: A recently blinded woman is terrorized by a trio of thugs while they search for a heroin-stuffed doll they believe is in her apartment.

title: Tokyo Story
text: An old couple visit their children and grandchildren in the city, but receive little attention.

title: Green Ray, The
text: It's July, and Delphine has nowhere to go for the summer. She feels very bored and "empty", but this won't last; one day she accidently meets someone who seems to be totally made for her...

title: THX 1138
text: In the 25th century, a time when people have designations instead of names, a man, THX 1138, and a woman, LUH 3417, rebel against their rigidly-controlled society.

title: Kind Hearts and Coronets
text: A distant poor relative of the Duke D'Ascoyne plots to inherit the title by murdering the eight other heirs who stand ahead of him in the line of succession.

title: Atragon
text: When an ancient underground civilization and their snake-like guardian plots to reclaim the surface world, those of the surface fights back.

title: Attack of the Puppet People
text: Lonely, deranged puppet-master designs a machine that shrinks people.
A Hollywood composer goes through a mid-life crisis and becomes infatuated with a sexy, newly married woman.

title: Tremors
text: Natives of a small isolated town defend themselves against strange underground creatures which are killing them one by one.

title: Red Shoes, The
text: A young ballet dancer is torn between the man she loves and her pursuit to become a prima ballerina.

title: Pink Panther, The
text: The bumbling Inspector Clouseau travels to Rome to catch a notorious jewel thief known as "The Phantom" before he conducts his most daring heist yet: a princess' priceless diamond with one slight imperfection, known as "The Pink Panther".

title: Pink Panther Strikes Again, The
text: Charles Dreyfus , who has finally cracked over Inspector Jacques Clouseau's  antics, escapes from a mental institution and launches an elaborate plan to get rid of Clouseau once and for all.

title: Commando
text: A retired Special Forces colonel tries to save his daughter, who was abducted by his former subordinate.

title: Dracula
text: In 1913, the charming, seductive and sinister vampire Count Dracula travels to England in search of an immortal bride.

title: Discreet Charm of the Bourgeoisie, The
text: A surreal, virtually plotless series of dreams centered around six middle-class people and their consistently interrupted attempts to have a meal together.

title: Waco: The Rules of Engagement
text: A reassessment of the tragedy at Waco that left 76 members of the Branch Davidian religious sect dead.

title: Road Home, The
text: Prompted by the death of his father and the grief of his mother, a man recalls the story of how they met in flashback.

title: Ikiru
text: A bureaucrat tries to find meaning in his life after he discovers he has terminal cancer.

title: Comic Book Villains
text: A guy dies after collecting comic books for decades. His mom inherits them and she ain't selling. Owners of 2 comic book stores want the collection. Their scheming gets ever more desperate.

title: Angel at My Table, An
text: Janet Frame was a brilliant child who, as a teen, was misdiagnosed with schizophrenia. Explore Janet's discovery of the world and her life in Europe as her books are published to acclaim.

title: Handmaid's Tale, The
text: Under a dystopian religious tyranny, most women cannot conceive children. Those young women who can live in a form of sexual slavery to provide children for influential families.

title: Revolution OS
text: While Microsoft may be the biggest software company in the world, not every computer user is a fan of their products, or their way of doing business. While Microsoft's Windows became the most widely used operating system for personal computers in the world, many experts took issue with Microsoft's strict policies regarding licensing, ownership, distribution, and alteration of their software. The objections of many high-profile technology experts, most notably Richard Stallman, led to what has become known as "the Open Source Movement," which is centered on the belief that computer software should be free both in the economic and intellectual senses of the word. Eventually, one of Stallman's admirers, Linus Torvalds, created a new operating system called Linux, a freely distributed software which many programmers consider to be markedly superior to Windows. Revolution OS is a documentary that examines the genesis of the Open Source Movement, and explores and explains the technical and intellectual issues involved in a manner understandable to computer aficionados and non-techheads alike.

title: Death in Venice
text: While recovering in Venice, sickly composer Gustav von Aschenbach becomes dangerously fixated with teenager Tadzio.

title: Medallion, The
text: A Hong Kong detective suffers a fatal accident involving a mysterious medallion and is transformed into an immortal warrior with superhuman powers.

title: My Boss's Daughter
text: After a man is asked to house sit for his boss, he becomes determined to get closer to the boss's daughter, but events keep unfolding that stop him from achieving his goal.

title: Autumn Spring
text: Faced with a looming death, an aging prankster makes the most of his remaining life.

title: Battle of Shaker Heights, The
text: Two high school boys, reenacting historic battles, use learned strategy and team up for war on a school bully. One falls for the other's sister.

title: Dust
text: A New York thief, a tough-as-nails hundred-year-old woman, two brothers from the Wild West, a Macedonian revolutionary and a beautiful pregnant woman, all cross paths in a tale that spans two continents and three centuries.

title: Stoked: The Rise and Fall of Gator
text: A documentary exploring the rise and fall of 80s skateboard legend Mark "Gator" Rogowski.

title: Jeepers Creepers 2
text: Set a few days after the original, a championship basketball team's bus is attacked by The Creeper, the winged, flesh-eating terror, on the last day of his 23-day feeding frenzy.

title: Bollywood/Hollywood
text: A wealthy East Indian man gives an apparently non-East Indian woman a crash course in his culture, so he can marry her with his family's approval.

title: Once Upon a Time in the Midlands
text: After seeing his ex-girlfriend  turn down a nationally televised marriage proposal, a small-time crook  returns to his hometown to try and win back her heart.

title: Dickie Roberts: Former Child Star
text: A thirty-something former child star hires a foster family to re-create the childhood he never had.

title: Party Monster
text: Based on the true story of Michael Alig, a Club Kid party organizer whose life was sent spiraling down when he bragged on television about killing his drug dealer and roommate.

title: Taking Sides
text: After the end of World War II, a famous German conductor is accused of loyalty to the Nazi regime. He argues that art and politics are separate. An investigator thinks otherwise.

title: Cabin Fever
text: Five college graduates rent a cabin in the woods and begin to fall victim to a horrifying flesh-eating virus, which attracts the unwanted attention of the homicidal locals.

title: Matchstick Men
text: A phobic con artist and his protégé are on the verge of pulling off a lucrative swindle when the former's teenage daughter arrives unexpectedly.

title: Once Upon a Time in Mexico
text: Hitman "El Mariachi" becomes involved in international espionage involving a psychotic CIA agent and a corrupt Mexican general.

title: Dummy
text: An ex-office worker becomes a ventriloquist, leading to a date with his unemployment counselor; but his quirky family and a gauche female friend may thwart his new career and love life.

title: Lost in Translation
text: A faded movie star and a neglected young woman form an unlikely bond after crossing paths in Tokyo.

title: Millennium Actress
text: A TV interviewer and his cameraman meet a former actress and travel through her memories and career.

title: Children of the Night
text: A schoolteacher teams up with with a priest to stop a town being overrun by vampires.

title: Gotcha!
text: Jonathan plays Gotcha with fellow college students, testing ability as assassin or mark, using paintball guns on campus. He flies to Paris on vacation and, with a woman taking his virginity, on to Berlin, where the game/ammo gets real.

title: Kuffs
text: George Kuffs, 21, leaves a pregnant girlfriend. He visits his brother Brad to bum money off him. Brad's shot and George IDs the killer at SFPD but to no avail. He inherits Brad's patrol district. He keeps it to get the killer.

title: Once Upon a Time in China
text: Late 1800s Foshan, Guangdong: Wong Fei Hung/Jet Li trains men in martial arts to help defend against foreign powers already holding Hong Kong and Macau. He looks after cute 13th Aunt, who's just returned from England. Lots of fight scenes.

title: Once Upon a Time in China II
text: Arriving by train in Guangzhou, 1895, the trio fight off White Lotus followers, who want to kill all foreigners and the cute, European dressed 13th Aunt. It's not kung fu master Dr. Wong's  last fight.

title: Once Upon a Time in China III
text: Master Wong and his disciples enroll in the 'Dancing Lion Competition' to stop an assassination plot and to battle an arrogant, deceitful opponent.

title: Paper Moon
text: During the Great Depression, a con man finds himself saddled with a young girl who may or may not be his daughter, and the two forge an unlikely partnership.

title: Day of the Dead
text: As the world is overrun by zombies, a small group of scientists and military personnel dwelling in an underground bunker in Florida must determine whether they should educate, eliminate or escape the undead horde.

title: Hello, Dolly!
text: Matchmaker Dolly Levi travels to Yonkers to find a partner for "half-a-millionaire" Horace Vandergelder, convincing his niece, his niece's intended, and his two clerks to travel to New York City along the way.

title: Memoirs of an Invisible Man
text: After a freak accident, a company executive turns completely invisible, goes on the run and becomes hunted by a treacherous CIA official, whilst trying to cope with his new reality.

title: Once Bitten
text: A vampire Countess needs to drink the blood of a virgin in order to keep her eternal beauty. It seems that all is hopeless, until she bumps into Mark Kendall.

title: Squirm
text: A storm causes some power lines to break and touch the ground, drawing millions of man-eating worms out of the earth, and into town where they quickly start munching on the locals.

title: Brood, The
text: A man tries to uncover an unconventional psychologist's therapy techniques on his institutionalized wife, amidst a series of brutal murders.

title: Anything Else
text: Jerry Falk learns a lesson the hard way when he falls in love with the beautiful but flighty Amanda.

title: Cold Creek Manor
text: A family relocates from the city to a dilapidated house in the country that was once a grand estate. As they begin renovations, they discover their new home harbors a secret and may not be completely free of its former inhabitant.

title: Fighting Temptations, The
text: A New York advertising executive travels to a small Southern town to collect an inheritance but finds he must create a gospel choir and lead it to success before he can collect.

title: Secondhand Lions
text: A coming-of-age story about a shy, young boy sent by his irresponsible mother to spend the summer with his wealthy, eccentric uncles in Texas.

title: Underworld
text: Selene, a vampire warrior, is entrenched in a conflict between vampires and werewolves, while falling in love with Michael, a human who is sought by werewolves for unknown reasons.

title: Bubba Ho-tep
text: Elvis Presley and a black "JFK" stay in a nursing home where nothing happens - until a wayward Egyptian mummy comes and sucks out the old people's souls thru their a-holes. The two decide to fight back.

title: In This World
text: A refugee family is trying to reach more peaceful lands illegally inside trucks.

title: Duplex
text: A young couple has a chance to move into a gorgeous duplex in the perfect New York neighborhood. All they have to do is bump off the current tenant, a cute little old lady.

title: Rundown, The
text: A tough aspiring chef is hired to bring home a mobster's son from the Amazon but becomes involved in the fight against an oppressive town operator and the search for a legendary treasure.

title: Under the Tuscan Sun
text: A writer impulsively buys a villa in Tuscany in order to change her life.

title: Luther
text: During the early sixteenth century, idealistic German monk Martin Luther, disgusted by the materialism in the Catholic Church, begins the dialogue that will lead to the Protestant Reformation.

title: Mambo Italiano
text: The son of Italian immigrants to Canada struggles to find the best way to reveal to his parents that he's gay.

title: My Life Without Me
text: A young woman conceals the fact of her terminal cancer to live her life with a passion she never had before.

title: To Be and to Have
text: A documentary portrait of a one-room school in rural France, where the students  are educated by a single dedicated teacher.

title: Triplets of Belleville, The
text: When her grandson is kidnapped during the Tour de France, Madame Souza and her beloved pooch Bruno team up with the Belleville Sisters--an aged song-and-dance team from the days of Fred Astaire--to rescue him.

title: Videodrome
text: A programmer at a TV station that specializes in adult entertainment searches for the producers of a dangerous and bizarre broadcast.

title: Life and Debt
text: Documentary look at the effects of globalization on Jamaican industry and agriculture.

title: Judgment at Nuremberg
text: In 1948, an American court in occupied Germany tries four Nazis judged for war crimes.

title: Brief History of Time, A
text: A film about the life and work of the cosmologist, Stephen Hawking, who despite his near total paralysis, was one of the great minds of all time.

title: Leningrad Cowboys Go America
text: Siberian rock band Leningrad Cowboys go to the USA in pursuit of fame.

title: Rules of the Game, The
text: A bourgeois life in France at the onset of World War II, as the rich and their poor servants meet up at a French chateau.

title: Seven Brides for Seven Brothers
text: In 1850 Oregon, when a backwoodsman brings a wife home to his farm, his six brothers decide that they want to get married too.

title: Kiss of the Spider Woman
text: A gay man and a political prisoner are together in a prison. The gay man narrates the stories of two fake movies and his own life.

title: All the President's Men
text: "The Washington Post" reporters Bob Woodward and Carl Bernstein uncover the details of the Watergate scandal that leads to President Richard Nixon's resignation.

title: Angie
text: Angie lives in Bensonhurst Brooklyn, and dreams of a better life. When she finds out she's pregnant - by her boyfriend, Vinnie, she decides she'll have the baby; but not Vinnie as a husband. This turns the entire close-knit neighborhood upside-down and starts Angie on a journey of self-discovery. On her way, she meets a new love interest.

title: Apartment, The
text: A recently engaged man sees a former lover and becomes obsessed with meeting her again.

title: Avalon
text: In a dystopian world, a woman spends her time playing an illegal and dangerous game, hoping to find meaning in her world.

title: Babette's Feast
text: During the late 19th century, a strict religious community in a Danish village takes in a French refugee from the Franco-Prussian War as a servant to the late pastor's daughters.

title: Beethoven
text: A slobbering St. Bernard becomes the center of attention for a loving family, but must contend with a dog-napping veterinarian and his henchmen.

title: Beethoven's 2nd
text: Beethoven, the St. Bernard dog, becomes a father, but his girlfriend Missy is dognapped, and his puppies are in danger of the same fate.

title: Boyz N the Hood
text: Follows the lives of three young males living in the Crenshaw ghetto of Los Angeles, dissecting questions of race, relationships, violence, and future prospects.

title: Bugsy
text: The story of how Benjamin "Bugsy" Siegel started Las Vegas.

title: Bugsy Malone
text: The classic gangster story of Bugsy Malone told with an all-child cast.

title: Cobra
text: A tough-on-crime street cop must protect the only surviving witness to a strange murderous cult with far-reaching plans.

title: Phenomena
text: A young girl who has an amazing ability to communicate with insects is transferred to an exclusive Swiss boarding school, where her unusual capability might help solve a string of murders.

title: Crimewave
text: A pair of whacked-out cartoon-like exterminator/hitmen kill the owner of a burglar-alarm company, and stalk the partner who hired them, his wife, and a nerd framed for the murder, who tells the story in flashback from the electric chair.

title: Monty Python's The Meaning of Life
text: The comedy team takes a look at life in all of its stages in their own uniquely silly way.

title: Where Eagles Dare
text: Allied agents stage a daring raid on a castle where the Nazis are holding American brigadier general George Carnaby prisoner, but that's not all that's really going on.

title: Tightrope
text: New Orleans single dad and cop Wes Block  goes after a serial rapist-killer, but when he gets too close to the target, the hunter suddenly becomes the hunted.

title: Sleeping with the Enemy
text: A young woman fakes her own death in an attempt to escape her nightmarish marriage, but discovers it is impossible to elude her controlling husband.

title: PCU
text: A high school senior visits college for the weekend, and stays at the wildest house on campus.

title: Rookie, The
text: A veteran detective is assigned a rookie partner after his previous partner is killed by a car theft gang. He is determined to apprehend those responsible for his friend's death but his new partner isn't really up to the task.

title: City Heat
text: Slick Private Investigator Mike Murphy  and tough Police Lieutenant Speer , once partners, now bitter enemies, reluctantly team up to investigate a murder.

title: Three O'Clock High
text: A nerd gets himself in hot water with the new bully, a quiet bad boy who challenges him to fight on the grounds of their high school after the day's end.

title: White Hunter, Black Heart
text: A thinly fictionalized account of a legendary movie director, whose desire to hunt down an animal turns into a grim situation with his movie crew in Africa.

title: Come and See
text: After finding an old rifle, a young boy joins the Soviet resistance movement against ruthless German forces and experiences the horrors of World War II.

title: Ginger Snaps
text: Two death-obsessed sisters, outcasts in their suburban neighborhood, must deal with the tragic consequences when one of them is bitten by a deadly werewolf.

title: More American Graffiti
text: College graduates deal with Vietnam and other issues of the late 1960s.

title: It's Pat
text: The comedic misadventures of a person of indeterminate gender.

title: Regarding Henry
text: After being shot, a lawyer loses his memory and must relearn speech and mobility, but he has a loving family to support him.

title: Alien Contamination
text: A former astronaut helps a government agent and a police detective track the source of mysterious alien pod spores, filled with lethal flesh-dissolving acid, to a South American coffee plantation controlled by alien pod clones.

title: Amazing Transparent Man, The
text: A crazed scientist invents an invisibility formula. He plans to use the formula to create an army of invisible zombies.

title: Love Affair
text: A French playboy and an American former nightclub singer fall in love aboard a ship.

title: Scrooge
text: A musical retelling of Charles Dickens' classic novel about an old bitter miser taken on a journey of self-redemption, courtesy of several mysterious Christmas apparitions.

title: Leap of Faith
text: Fake faith healer Jonas Nightingale is stranded in a small town where he finds he can't fool all of the people all of the time.

title: Gas, Food, Lodging
text: A waitress lives with her two teen daughters in a trailer park in New Mexico. They all want a boyfriend.

title: In Cold Blood
text: Two ex-cons murder a family in a robbery attempt, before going on the run from the authorities. The police try to piece together the details of the murder in an attempt to track down the killers.

title: Campus Man
text: Todd Barret is an aspiring businessman. He's got what it takes, but what he doesn't have is enough money to stay in college. So he cooks up a plan to make the first ever all male sports calendar. He eventually convinces Cactus Jack, a very shadowy and tough loan shark, to give him enough money to make the deal. Todd makes enough to pay for his education, but what about the money he owes Cactus Jack?

title: Yankee Doodle Dandy
text: The life of the renowned musical composer, playwright, actor, dancer, and singer George M. Cohan.

title: Ninja Scroll
text: A vagabond swordsman is aided by a beautiful ninja girl and a crafty spy in confronting a demonic clan of killers - with a ghost from his past as their leader - who are bent on overthrowing the Tokugawa Shogunate.

title: Knife in the Water
text: A couple pick up a hitchhiker on the way to their yacht. The husband invites the young man to come along for their day's sailing. As the voyage progresses, the antagonism between the two men grows. A violent confrontation is inevitable.

title: Mobsters
text: From start to finish, it's a story of friendship between four street-wise males who don't mind using violence to achieve the lives that they want. They trust no one but each other, which is vital to their success as mobsters.

title: Out of Time
text: A Florida police chief must solve a vicious double homicide before he himself falls under suspicion.

title: School of Rock
text: After being kicked out of his rock band, Dewey Finn becomes a substitute teacher of an uptight elementary private school, only to try and turn his class into a rock band.

title: Station Agent, The
text: When his only friend dies, a man born with dwarfism moves to rural New Jersey to live a life of solitude, only to meet a chatty hot dog vendor and a woman dealing with her own personal loss.

title: Wonderland
text: In the police investigation of a brutal crime scene, one man was at the center of it all: legendary porn star John Holmes.

title: Bus 174
text: On June 12, 2000, a young man with a gun took the passengers aboard Bus 174 in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil hostage. This documentary examines the event itself, the resulting media frenzy, the police response, and the perpetrator's background.

title: Mystic River
text: The lives of three men who were childhood friends are shattered when one of them has a family tragedy.

title: House of the Dead, The
text: A group of college students travels to a mysterious island to attend a rave, which is soon taken over by bloodthirsty zombies.

title: Intolerable Cruelty
text: A beautiful gold digger matches wits with a shrewd Beverly Hills divorce lawyer who is increasingly attracted to her.

title: Kill Bill: Vol. 1
text: After awakening from a four-year coma, a former assassin wreaks vengeance on the team of assassins who betrayed her.

title: Runaway Jury
text: A juror on the inside and a woman on the outside manipulate a court trial involving a major gun manufacturer.

title: Texas Chainsaw Massacre, The
text: After picking up a traumatized young hitchhiker, five friends find themselves stalked and hunted by a deformed chainsaw-wielding loon and his family of equally psychopathic killers.

title: Pieces of April
text: A wayward daughter invites her dying mother and the rest of her estranged family to her apartment for Thanksgiving dinner.

title: Returner
text: A young woman from the future forces a local gunman to help her stop an impending alien invasion which will wipe out the human race.

title: Sylvia
text: Story of the relationship between poets Edward James "Ted" Hughes  and Sylvia Plath .

title: Veronica Guerin
text: An Irish journalist writes a series of stories about drug dealers.

title: In the Cut
text: New York City writing professor, Frannie Avery, has an affair with a police detective who is investigating the murder of a beautiful young woman in her neighborhood.

title: Beyond Borders
text: The world's cruelty is confronted with the love of two different people who try to save mankind from poverty and war.

title: Radio
text: The story of a high school coach and the developmentally challenged man who he took under his wing.

title: Scary Movie 3
text: Cindy must investigate mysterious crop circles and video tapes, and help the President in preventing an alien invasion.

title: Brother Bear
text: When a young Inuit hunter needlessly kills a bear, he is magically changed into a bear himself as punishment with a talkative cub being his only guide to changing back.

title: Elephant
text: Several ordinary high school students go through their daily routine as two others prepare for something more malevolent.

title: Italian Job, The
text: Comic caper movie about a plan to steal a gold shipment from the streets of Turin by creating a traffic jam.

title: Sweet Sixteen
text: Determined to have a normal family life once his mother gets out of prison, a Scottish teenager from a tough background sets out to raise the money for a home.

title: Alien from L.A.
text: A young woman with a childish voice travels to Africa looking for her missing archaeologist father, and stumbles into a strange subterranean civilization.

title: Interstate 60
text: Neal Oliver, a very confused young man and an artist, takes a journey of a lifetime on a highway I60 that doesn't exist on any of the maps, going to the places he never even heard of, searching for an answer and his dreamgirl.

title: Eye, The
text: A blind girl gets a cornea transplant so that she will be able to see again. She gets more than she bargained for upon realizing she can also see ghosts.

title: Jolson Story, The
text: This movie shows the idealized career of the singer Al Jolson, a little Jewish boy who goes against the will of his father in order to be in showbiz. He becomes a star, falls in love with a non-Jewish dancer, and marries her. In the end he chooses success on the stage.

title: You'll Never Get Rich
text: In order to cover up his philandering ways, a married Broadway producer sets one of his dancers up on a date with a chorus girl for whom he had bought a gift, but the two dancers fall in love for real.

title: Unvanquished, The
text: Following his father's death, a boy leaves home to study in Calcutta, while his mother must face a life alone.

title: Cercle Rouge, Le
text: After leaving prison, master thief Corey crosses paths with a notorious escapee and an alcoholic former policeman. The trio proceed to plot an elaborate heist.

title: Human Stain, The
text: When a disgraced former college dean has a romance with a mysterious younger woman haunted by her dark, twisted past, he is forced to confront a shocking fact about his own life that he has kept secret for fifty years.

title: Shattered Glass
text: The story of a young journalist who fell from grace when it was discovered he fabricated over half of his articles from the publication The New Republic magazine.

title: Matrix Revolutions, The
text: The human city of Zion defends itself against the massive invasion of the machines as Neo fights to end the war at another front while also opposing the rogue Agent Smith.

title: Revolution Will Not Be Televised, The
text: In April 2002, an Irish film crew is making a documentary about Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez, when a coup from the opposition is made.

title: Elf
text: Raised as an over-sized elf, a human travels from the North Pole to NYC to meet his biological father who doesn't know he exists and is in desperate need of some Christmas spirit.

title: Billabong Odyssey
text: Action sports documentary that follows the industry's best big wave surfers as they travel the world searching for the largest waves that nature has to offer. The journey spanned 18 months, 6 continents and produced up to 70 foot waves.

title: Gloomy Sunday
text: Follows three men who are in love with a most beautiful waitress: An intellectual restaurant owner, a mysterious musician and an erratic businessman; taking place during the WWII.

title: Love Actually
text: Follows the lives of eight very different couples in dealing with their love lives in various loosely interrelated tales all set during a frantic month before Christmas in London, England.

title: Father of the Bride
text: With his oldest daughter's wedding approaching, a father finds himself reluctant to let go.

title: My Architect: A Son's Journey
text: Director Nathaniel Kahn searches to understand his father, noted architect Louis Kahn, who died bankrupt and alone in 1974.

title: Looney Tunes: Back in Action
text: The Looney Tunes search for a man's missing father and the mythical Blue Monkey diamond.

title: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
text: During the Napoleonic Wars, a brash British captain pushes his ship and crew to their limits in pursuit of a formidable French war vessel around South America.

title: Tupac: Resurrection
text: Home movies, photographs, and recited poetry illustrate the life of Tupac Shakur, one of the most beloved, revolutionary, and volatile hip-hop M.Cs. of all time.

title: Big Empty, The
text: John Person is an actor with little work, and no money, who suddenly finds himself with an opportunity to make some quick cash by delivering a suitcase to the middle of nowhere.

title: Missing, The
text: In 1885 New Mexico, a frontier medicine woman forms an uneasy alliance with her estranged father when her daughter is kidnapped by an Apache brujo.

title: Cat in the Hat, The
text: Two bored children have their lives turned upside down when a talking cat comes to visit them.

title: Gothika
text: A depressed psychiatrist wakes up as a patient in the asylum where she worked, with no memory of why she is there or what she has done.

title: 21 Grams
text: A freak accident brings together a critically ill mathematician, a grieving mother, and a born-again ex-con.

title: Barbarian Invasions, The
text: During his final days, a dying man is reunited with old friends, former lovers, his ex-wife, and his estranged son.

title: Bad Santa
text: A miserable conman and his partner pose as Santa and his Little Helper to rob department stores on Christmas Eve. But they run into problems when the conman befriends a troubled kid.

title: Haunted Mansion, The
text: A realtor and his wife and children are summoned to a mansion, which they soon discover is haunted, and while they attempt to escape, he learns an important lesson about the family he has neglected.

title: Timeline
text: A group of archaeologists become trapped in the past when they go there to retrieve a friend. The group must survive in 14th-century France before they can escape back to the twenty-first century.

title: Damage
text: A member of Parliament falls passionately in love with his son's fiancée despite the dangers of discovery.

title: OT: Our Town
text: Dominguez High, in the infamous Compton, CA, has not produced a play in over twenty years. With no money and no stage, two teachers and twenty-four students attempt to produce Thornton Wilder's American Classic OUR TOWN.

title: Devil's Playground
text: Amish teenagers experience and embrace the modern world as a rite-of-passage before deciding which life they will choose.

title: Journeys with George
text: A documentary about George W. Bush's 2000 campaign for the White House.

title: Darkman
text: A brilliant scientist left for dead returns to exact revenge on the people who burned him alive.

title: Dead of Night
text: The guests invited to weekend in the country share their supernatural stories, beginning with Walter Craig , who senses impending doom as his half-remembered recurring dream turns into reality.

title: Dernier Combat, Le
text: In a post-apocalyptic future where no one is able to speak, the few remaining humans fight over resources in order to survive.

title: Desk Set
text: Two extremely strong personalities clash over the computerization of a television network's research department.

title: Europa
text: Just after W.W.II, an American takes a railway job in Germany, but finds his position politically sensitive with various people trying to use him.

title: Final Analysis
text: A psychiatrist becomes romantically involved with the sister of one of his patients, but the influence of her controlling gangster husband threatens to destroy them both.

title: Freshman, The
text: An N.Y.C. film school student accepts a job with a local mobster who resembles a famous cinema godfather and who takes the young man under his wing, after demanding total loyalty.

title: Funny Games
text: Two violent young men take a mother, father, and son hostage in their vacation cabin and force them to play sadistic "games" with one another for their own amusement.

title: Slacker
text: A day in the life of Austin, Texas as the camera roams from place to place and provides a brief look at the overeducated, the social misfits, the outcasts and the oddballs.

title: WarGames
text: A young man finds a back door into a military central computer in which reality is confused with game-playing, possibly starting World War III.

title: Ordet
text: Follows the lives of the Borgen family, as they deal with inner conflict, as well as religious conflict with each other, and the rest of the town.

title: Forbidden Games
text: A young French girl orphaned in a Nazi air attack is befriended by the son of a poor farmer, and together they try to come to terms with the realities of death.

title: Jane Eyre
text: After a harsh childhood, orphan Jane Eyre is hired by Edward Rochester, the brooding lord of a mysterious manor house, to care for his young daughter.

title: Tale of Two Cities, A
text: A pair of lookalikes, one a former French aristocrat and the other an alcoholic English lawyer, fall in love with the same woman amongst the turmoil of the French Revolution.

title: Passion of Joan of Arc, The
text: In 1431, Jeanne d'Arc is placed on trial on charges of heresy. The ecclesiastical jurists attempt to force Jeanne to recant her claims of holy visions.

title: Ben-Hur: A Tale of the Christ
text: A Jewish prince seeks to find his family and revenge himself upon his childhood friend who had him wrongly imprisoned.

title: Cabinet of Dr. Caligari, The
