text: Hypnotist Dr. Caligari uses a somnambulist, Cesare, to commit murders.

title: Gorky Park
text: A Moscow police officer investigates a vicious triple homicide and stumbles upon a high-level international political conspiracy.

title: The Great Train Robbery
text: England, 1850s. A master criminal aims to rob a train of a large sum of gold. Security is incredibly tight and the task seems an impossible one. However, he has a plan and just the right people to carry it out.

title: Guarding Tess
text: A former U.S. First Lady wants a particular Secret Service agent to head her bodyguard detail, even though he can't stand her.

title: Hannah and Her Sisters
text: Between two Thanksgivings two years apart, Hannah's husband falls in love with her sister Lee, while her hypochondriac ex-husband rekindles his relationship with her sister Holly.

title: Hard Way, The
text: An action movie star researching a role is allowed to tag along with a hardboiled New York City policeman, who finds him superficial and irritating.

title: Highlander II: The Quickening
text: In the future, Highlander Connor MacLeod must prevent the destruction of Earth under an anti-ozone shield.

title: Hoffa
text: The story of the notorious American labor union figure Jimmy Hoffa, who organizes a bitter strike, makes deals with members of the organized crime syndicate and mysteriously disappears in 1975.

title: House of Cards
text: A widow tries to find out why her daughter's strange behavior, a reaction to her father's death, is progressively worsening.

title: Housesitter
text: Con artist Gwen moves into Newton's empty home without his knowledge and begins setting up house, posing as his new wife.

title: Hudson Hawk
text: A cat burglar is forced to steal Da Vinci works of art for a world domination plot.

title: Invasion of the Body Snatchers
text: When strange seeds drift to earth from space, mysterious pods begin to grow and invade San Francisco, California, where they replicate the residents into emotionless automatons one body at a time.

title: Kindergarten Cop
text: A tough cop must pose as a kindergarten teacher in order to locate a dangerous criminal's ex-wife, who may hold the key to putting him behind bars.

title: King Ralph
text: A regular guy from America becomes king of England after a royal wipe-out puts him next in line.

title: Last Boy Scout, The
text: A private detective's protected female witness is murdered, prompting him and the victim's boyfriend to investigate the crime that leads to a corrupt politician and a crooked football team owner.

title: Last Tango in Paris
text: A young Parisian woman meets a middle-aged American businessman who demands their clandestine relationship be based only on sex.

title: Lorenzo's Oil
text: Lorenzo Odone, a Virginia 5-year-old, develops a degenerative nerve disease so rare that nobody is working on a cure, so his parents decide to immerse themselves in research and tackle the problem themselves.

title: Lover, The
text: In 1929 French Indochina, a French teenage girl embarks on a reckless and forbidden romance with a wealthy, older Chinese man, each knowing that knowledge of their affair will bring drastic consequences to each other.

title: Mr. Destiny
text: Unhappy Larry Burrows sees what his life could've been like, had he made that winning home run as a teenager.

title: Night of the Hunter, The
text: A religious fanatic marries a gullible widow whose young children are reluctant to tell him where their real daddy hid the $10,000 he'd stolen in a robbery.

title: Only the Lonely
text: A Chicago cop must balance loyalty to his overbearing mother and a relationship with a shy funeral home worker.

title: Over the Top
text: Tough trucker Lincoln Hawk is determined to win back his son and triumph at the world arm wrestling championships.

title: Passenger 57
text: An airline security expert must take action when he finds himself trapped on a passenger jet when terrorists seize control of it.

title: Presumed Innocent
text: As a lawyer investigates the murder of a colleague, he finds himself more connected to the crime than anyone else.

title: Project X
text: An Air Force pilot joins a top secret military experiment involving chimps, but begins to suspect there might be something more to the mysterious "Project X".

title: Proof
text: The life of a blind photographer who is looked after by a housekeeper is disrupted by the arrival of an agreeable restaurant worker.

title: Battle Royale
text: In the future, the Japanese government captures a class of ninth-grade students and forces them to kill each other under the revolutionary "Battle Royale" act.

title: Wedding Banquet, The
text: To satisfy his nagging parents, a gay landlord and a female tenant agree to a marriage of convenience, but his parents arrive to visit and things get out of hand.

title: Salo, or The 120 Days of Sodom
text: In World War II Italy, four fascist libertines round up nine adolescent boys and girls and subject them to 120 days of physical, mental, and sexual torture.

title: Midnight Clear, A
text: This WW2 psychological drama plays out at Christmas. US GIs hold an isolated cabin in the Ardennes against a handful of Germans cut off from their main force. Combat-weary and short of rations, both sides are determined to survive.

title: Summer School
text: Freddy the gym teacher has to teach remedial English in summer  school, if he wants tenure. As he can only teach gym and his students want fun, emphasis is on "field trips" - until he's fired unless all his students pass the test.

title: Silverado
text: A misfit bunch of friends comes together to right the injustices which exist in a small town.

title: Quick Change
text: Three thieves successfully rob a New York City bank, but making the escape from the city proves to be almost impossible.

title: Radio Flyer
text: A father recounts a dark period of his childhood when he and his little brother lived in the suburbs.

title: Real McCoy, The
text: A woman is released from prison, an expert bank robber who wants to settle down and go straight, but her parole officer and her former employer try to get her to pull one more heist.

title: Revenge
text: A retired US Navy pilot comes to Mexico, where he falls in love with the wife of a powerful businessman. The consequences will be cruel and unforeseen.

title: Secret of My Succe$s, The
text: A talented young man can't get an executive position without rising through the ranks, so he comes up with a shortcut, which also benefits his love life.

title: Show Me Love
text: Two teenage girls in small-town Sweden. Elin is beautiful, popular, and bored with life. Agnes is friendless, sad, and secretly in love with Elin.

title: Teen Wolf
text: An ordinary high school student discovers that his family has an unusual pedigree when he finds himself turning into a werewolf.

title: High Heels
text: A singer returns after 15 years abroad to perform in Madrid and finds her 27 y.o. daughter married to one of her mom's ex-lovers.

title: Things You Can Tell Just by Looking at Her
text: Five California women struggle with personal problems as their own paths unwind in unexpected ways.

title: To Live and Die in L.A.
text: A fearless Secret Service agent will stop at nothing to bring down the counterfeiter who killed his partner.

title: Trapped in Paradise
text: Residents of a friendly Pennsylvania town foil three brothers' plan to rob a bank on Christmas Eve.

title: Wild at Heart
text: Young lovers Sailor and Lula run from the variety of weirdos that Lula's mom has hired to kill Sailor.

title: Witches, The
text: A young boy stumbles onto a witch convention and must stop them, even after he has been turned into a mouse.

title: Witches of Eastwick, The
text: Three single women in a picturesque village have their wishes granted, at a cost, when a mysterious and flamboyant man arrives in their lives.

title: Year of the Dragon
text: A police detective cracks down on organized crime in Chinatown after the murders of Triad and Mafia leaders.

title: Nothing to Lose
text: Nick's wife's in bed with his boss. He later gets a gun to his head by a carjacker but steps on the gas pedal. They end up friends after adventures together - holdups, burglary, reckless driving, revenge etc. Twists follow.

title: Flying Down to Rio
text: A bandleader woos a Latin flame who is already engaged to his employer.

title: Follow the Fleet
text: A Navy sailor tries to rekindle a romance with the woman he loves while on liberty in San Francisco.

title: What's New, Pussycat
text: A playboy who refuses to give up his hedonistic lifestyle to settle down and marry his true love seeks help from a demented psychoanalyst who is having romantic problems of his own.

title: Mary of Scotland
text: The recently widowed Mary Stuart returns to Scotland to reclaim her throne but is opposed by her half-brother and her own Scottish lords.

title: Roberta
text: An American jazzman and his buddy woo a Russian princess and a fake countess in Paris.

title: Little Women
text: The four daughters of a New England family fight for happiness during and after the Civil War.

title: Swing Time
text: Roguish gambler/dancer "Lucky" Garnett is challenged by his fiance's father to come up with $25,000 to prove he's worthy of her hand. But after he falls in love with a dance instructor, Lucky'll do anything to keep from earning the bucks.

title: Public Enemy, The
text: An Irish-American street punk tries to make it big in the world of organized crime.

title: Midsummer Night's Dream, A
text: Two couples and a troupe of actors have an encounter with some mischievous fairies in the forest.

title: Life with Father
text: A straitlaced turn-of-the-century father presides over a family of boys and the mother who really rules the roost.

title: National Velvet
text: A jaded former jockey helps a young girl prepare a wild but gifted horse for England's Grand National Sweepstakes.

title: Jesus Christ Superstar
text: Film version of the musical stage play, presenting the last few weeks of Christ's life told in an anachronistic manner.

title: Dark Victory
text: A young socialite is diagnosed with an inoperable brain tumor, and must decide whether or not she'll meet her final days with dignity.

title: Birdman of Alcatraz
text: A surly convicted murderer held in permanent isolation redeems himself when he becomes a renowned bird expert.

title: Aguirre: The Wrath of God
text: In the 16th century, the ruthless and insane Don Lope de Aguirre leads a Spanish expedition in search of El Dorado.

title: Beauty and the Beast
text: A beautiful young woman takes her father's place as the prisoner of a mysterious beast, who wishes to marry her.

title: Chorus Line, A
text: After his proposal to sail west to the East Indies is rejected by Portugal, Columbus overcomes court intrigue in Spain to gain support for his expedition.

title: Beat Street
text: A mans voyeurism lands him in the middle of a murder case.

title: Birth of a Nation, The
text: The Stoneman family finds its friendship with the Camerons affected by the Civil War, both fighting in opposite armies. The development of the war in their lives plays through to Lincoln's assassination and the birth of the Ku Klux Klan.

title: Juliet of the Spirits
text: Visions, memories, and mysticism all help a 40-something woman to find the strength to leave her cheating husband.

title: Macbeth
text: A ruthlessly ambitious Scottish lord seizes the throne with the help of his scheming wife and a trio of witches.

title: Red River
text: Dunson leads a cattle drive, the culmination of over 14 years of work, to its destination in Missouri. But his tyrannical behavior along the way causes a mutiny, led by his adopted son.

title: Woman Under the Influence, A
text: Although wife and mother Mabel is loved by her husband Nick, her mental illness places a strain on the marriage.

title: Stagecoach
text: A group of people traveling on a stagecoach find their journey complicated by the threat of Geronimo and learn something about each other in the process.

title: Shot in the Dark, A
text: Inspector Jacques Clouseau investigates the murder of Mr. Benjamin Ballon's driver at a country estate.

title: Navigator, The
text: Two spoiled rich people find themselves trapped on an empty passenger ship.

title: Court Jester, The
text: A hapless carnival performer masquerades as the court jester as part of a plot against an evil ruler who has overthrown the rightful King.

title: Bullitt
text: An all-guts, no-glory San Francisco cop becomes determined to find the underworld kingpin that killed the witness in his protection.

title: Jezebel
text: In 1850s Louisiana, a free-spirited Southern belle loses her fiancé due to her stubborn vanity and pride, and vows to win him back.

title: Hunchback of Notre Dame, The
text: In 15th-century France, a gypsy girl is framed for murder by the infatuated Chief Justice, and only the deformed bellringer of Notre Dame Cathedral can save her.

title: 42nd Street
text: When the leading lady of a Broadway musical breaks her ankle, she is replaced by a young unknown actress, who becomes the star of the show.

title: That Touch of Mink
text: A rich businessman and a young woman are attracted to each other, but he only wants an affair while she wants to save herself for marriage.

title: Sweet Dreams
text: The story of Patsy Cline, the velvet-voiced country music singer who died in a tragic plane crash at the height of her fame.

title: Play It Again, Sam
text: A neurotic film critic obsessed with the movie Casablanca  attempts to get over his wife leaving him by dating again with the help of a married couple and his illusory idol, Humphrey Bogart.

title: Send Me No Flowers
text: A hypochondriac believes he is dying and makes plans for his wife which she discovers and misunderstands.

title: Pygmalion
text: A phonetics and diction expert makes a bet that he can teach a cockney flower girl to speak proper English and pass as a lady in high society.

title: Passage to India, A
text: Cultural mistrust and false accusations doom a friendship in British colonial India between an Indian doctor, an Englishwoman engaged to marry a city magistrate, and an English educator.

title: Black Orpheus
text: A retelling of the Orpheus and Eurydice myth, set during the time of the Carnaval in Rio de Janeiro.

title: Amarcord
text: A series of comedic and nostalgic vignettes set in a 1930s Italian coastal town.

title: Hero
text: A defense officer, Nameless, was summoned by the King of Qin regarding his success of terminating three warriors.

title: Horse Feathers
text: Quincy Adams Wagstaff, the new president of Huxley University, accidentally hires bumblers Baravelli and Pinky to help his school win the big football game against the rival Darwin University.

title: Anna Karenina
text: The married Anna Karenina falls in love with Count Vronsky despite her husband's refusal to grant a divorce, and both must contend with the social repercussions.

title: Front Page, The
text: A ruthless editor tries to get his top reporter to cover one more crime story before retirement.

title: Rivers and Tides
text: Portrait of Andy Goldsworthy, an artist whose specialty is ephemeral sculptures made from elements of nature.

title: Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind
text: Warrior and pacifist Princess Nausicaä desperately struggles to prevent two warring nations from destroying themselves and their dying planet.

title: Doc Hollywood
text: A young doctor on his way across the country to a job interview crashes his car in a small town and is sentenced to work for several days at the town hospital.

title: Dragnet
text: The equally-straight-laced and "by the book" nephew of Joe Friday must work with his more laid-back partner to solve a mystery.

title: Madhouse
text: The luxurious villa of yuppie couple Mark and Jessie Bannister is overrun by loads of uninvited guests who turn the house upside-down and nearly destroy it.
Hysterical Californians prepare for a Japanese invasion in the days after Pearl Harbor.

title: Foul Play
text: A shy San Francisco librarian and a bumbling cop fall in love as they solve a crime involving albinos, dwarves, and the Catholic Church.

title: Crime Story
text: A Special Agent is assigned to protect a wealthy business magnate. However, when the businessman is kidnapped in a daring ambush, he teams up with a seasoned detective to crack the case. But soon he discovers the case isn't that simple.

title: Beyond the Clouds
text: Four stories about short or long relationships between men and women in Italy and France.

title: Collector, The
text: A man kidnaps a woman and holds her hostage just for the pleasure of having her there.

title: Deep Red
text: A jazz pianist and a wisecracking journalist are pulled into a complex web of mystery after the former witnesses the brutal murder of a psychic.

title: Diabolique
text: The wife and mistress of a loathed school principal plan to murder him with what they believe is the perfect alibi.

title: Leprechaun
text: An evil, sadistic Leprechaun goes on a killing rampage in search of his beloved pot of gold.

title: Wings of Honneamise
text: In an alternative Earth, a young astronaut participates in a controversial fledgling space program.

title: Adam's Rib
text: Domestic and professional tensions mount when a husband and wife work as opposing lawyers in a case involving a woman who shot her husband.

title: King of Hearts
text: During World War I, a British private, sent ahead to a French town to scout for enemy presence, is mistaken for a King by the colorful patients of an insane asylum.

title: Naked Lunch
text: After developing an addiction to the substance he uses to kill bugs, an exterminator accidentally kills his wife, and becomes involved in a secret government plot being orchestrated by giant bugs in a port town in North Africa.

title: Grass
text: The history of the American government's war on marijuana in the 20th century.

title: Spring Forward
text: An ex convict befriends an elderly coworker as they both try to find meaning in life and forgiveness for their past.

title: Run
text: When a law student accidentally kills the son of a mob boss in a fight, he finds himself relentlessly pursued by the mob and the police.

title: Summer Place, A
text: A self-made businessman rekindles a romance with a former flame while their two teenage children begin a romance of their own with drastic consequences for both couples.

title: Night at the Opera, A
text: A sly business manager and the wacky friends of two opera singers in Italy help them achieve success in America while humiliating their stuffy and snobbish enemies.

title: Element of Crime, The
text: A cop in a dystopian Europe investigates a serial killings suspect using controversial methods written by his now disgraced former mentor.

title: Cooler, The
text: In an old school Las Vegas casino, its top gambling jinx breaks his curse when he falls in love, much to his boss' consternation.

title: In America
text: A family of Irish immigrants adjust to life on the mean streets of Hell's Kitchen while also grieving the death of a child.

title: My Flesh and Blood
text: Documentary following Susan Tom of Fairfield, California and her 11 adopted special needs children.

title: Honey
text: Honey is a sexy, tough music video choreographer who shakes up her life after her mentor gives her an ultimatum: sleep with him or be blacklisted within their industry.

title: Last Samurai, The
text: An American military advisor embraces the Samurai culture he was hired to destroy after he is captured in battle.

title: Big Fish
text: A frustrated son tries to determine the fact from fiction in his dying father's life.

title: Something's Gotta Give
text: A swinger on the cusp of being a senior citizen with a taste for young women falls in love with an accomplished woman closer to his age.

title: Stuck on You
text: Conjoined twins from Martha's Vineyard move to Los Angeles so that one of them can pursue an acting career.

title: Girl with a Pearl Earring
text: A young peasant maid working in the house of painter Johannes Vermeer becomes his talented assistant and the model for one of his most famous works.

title: Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King, The
text: Gandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Sauron's army to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam as they approach Mount Doom with the One Ring.

title: Mona Lisa Smile
text: A free-thinking art professor teaches conservative 1950s Wellesley girls to question their traditional social roles.

title: Calendar Girls
text: A Women's Institute chapter's fundraising effort for a local hospital by posing nude for a calendar becomes a media sensation.

title: Fog of War: Eleven Lessons from the Life of Robert S. McNamara, The
text: The story of America as seen through the eyes of the former Secretary of Defense under President John F. Kennedy and President Lyndon B. Johnson, Robert McNamara.

title: House of Sand and Fog
text: An abandoned wife is evicted from her house and starts a tragic conflict with her house's new owners.

title: Monster
text: Based on the life of Aileen Wuornos, a Daytona Beach prostitute who became a serial killer.

title: Cheaper by the Dozen
text: With his wife doing a book tour, a father of twelve must handle a new job and his unstable brood.

title: Cold Mountain
text: In the waning days of the American Civil War, a wounded soldier embarks on a perilous journey back home to Cold Mountain, North Carolina to reunite with his sweetheart.

title: Paycheck
text: What seemed like a breezy idea for an engineer to net him millions of dollars, leaves him on the run for his life and piecing together why he's being chased.

title: Peter Pan
text: The Darling family children receive a visit from Peter Pan, who takes them to Never Never Land where an ongoing war with the evil Pirate Captain Hook is taking place.

title: Company, The
text: Ensemble drama centered around a group of ballet dancers, with a focus on one young dancer who's poised to become a principal performer.

title: Japanese Story
text: Against the background of an Australian desert, Sandy, a geologist, and Hiromitsu, a Japanese businessman, play out a story of human inconsequence in the face of the blistering universe. The end of the journey leaves no one capable of going back to where they started from.

title: Chasing Liberty
text: Anna wants to be like other girls her age : date a guy etc. but she's the US president's daughter and always guarded. In Prague he breaks his promise of only 2 agents following her to a concert and she runs away with Ben to see Europe.

title: Aileen: Life and Death of a Serial Killer
text: Nick Broomfield's second documentary about serial killer Aileen Wuornos, focusing on her mental state on death row.

title: Along Came Polly
text: A buttoned-up newlywed finds his strictly organized life descend into chaos when he falls in love with an old classmate.

title: Torque
text: A biker returns from Thailand to set things straight with his girlfriend. One gang leader wants him for delivery of 2 motorbikes filled with crystal meth and another gang leader wants him for murdering his brother.

title: Crimson Gold
text: An Iranian pizza delivery man sees the worst of corruption and social unbalance in his city and is driven to crime.

title: Osama
text: After the rise of the Taliban in Afghanistan and the restriction of women in public life, a pre-teen girl is forced to masquerade as a boy in order to find work to support her mother and grandmother.

title: Great Gatsby, The
text: A Midwesterner becomes fascinated with his nouveau riche neighbor, who obsesses over his lost love.

title: Wuthering Heights
text: A man becomes obsessed with vengeance when his soul mate marries another man.

title: Ship of Fools
text: A varied group of passengers boarding a ship bound for pre-WWII Germany represents a microcosm of early 1930s society.

title: This Property is Condemned
text: The dramatic love story of small-town Mississippi girl Alva Starr and railroad official Owen Legate, set during the Great Depression.

title: Jane Eyre
text: Jane Eyre is an orphan, sent to Lowood school, and eventually becomes a governess at Thornfield hall to a girl named Adele. While she is there, many strange things happen and eventually she and Edward Rochester, owner of Thornfield and Adele's guardian, fall in love. Suddenly, when Jane is about to win the happiness she deserves, a dark secret comes to light, and it will take all of her courage, love and understanding to triumph.

title: Blame It on the Bellboy
text: Several strangers converge on a hotel in Venice, Italy, where a bellboy's bad English sets them up to clash against each other in a hilarious case of mistaken identity.

title: Only the Strong
text: Ex-Special Forces soldier Louis Stevens returns to Miami to find his former high school overrun by drugs and violence. A master of the Brazilian martial art, capoeira, Stevens pledges to straighten out a dozen of the school's worst students by teaching them this demanding and highly-disciplined fighting style. Slowly, his program begins to work, giving the students new hope and purpose. But the local drug lord, himself a martial arts expert, vows to stop Stevens' positive influence. Now Stevens must fight to save his own life, as well as the lives of his rebellious young students.

title: Adventures of Ford Fairlane, The
text: A vulgar private detective is hired to find a missing groupie and is drawn into a mystery involving a series of murders tied to the music industry.

title: Beyond Re-Animator
text: After 13 years in prison, the mad scientist from Re-Animator  gets a new chance to experiment with the arrival of a young prison doctor, who secretly hopes to learn to reanimate dead people. Good intentions turn to horror.

title: Wind and the Lion, The
text: A Berber chieftain triggers an international incident, drawing the involvement of Theodore Roosevelt, when he kidnaps an American widow and her children in 1900s Morocco.

title: Mon Oncle
text: Monsieur Hulot visits the technology-driven world of his sister, brother-in-law, and nephew, but he can't quite fit into the surroundings.

title: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde
text: Dr. Jekyll allows his dark side to run wild when he drinks a potion that turns him into the evil Mr. Hyde.

title: M. Hulot’s Holiday
text: Monsieur Hulot comes to a beachside hotel for a vacation and accidentally, but good-naturedly, causes havoc.

title: People Will Talk
text: Dr. Noah Praetorius falls in love with Debra, a student who finds out that she is pregnant by her old boyfriend.

title: I Was a Male War Bride
text: After marrying an American lieutenant with whom he was assigned to work in post-war Germany, a French captain attempts to find a way to accompany her back to the States under the terms of the War Bride Act.

title: To Have and Have Not
text: During World War II, American expatriate Harry Morgan helps transport a French Resistance leader and his beautiful wife to Martinique while romancing a sensuous lounge singer.

title: High Sierra
text: After being released from prison, notorious thief Roy Earle is hired by his old boss to help a group of inexperienced criminals plan and carry out the robbery of a California resort.

title: Dark Passage
text: A man convicted of murdering his wife escapes from prison and works with a woman to try and prove his innocence.

title: Ox-Bow Incident, The
text: When a posse captures three men suspected of killing a local farmer, they become strongly divided over whether or not to lynch the men.

title: They Drive by Night
text: When one of two truck-driving brothers loses an arm, they both join a transport company where the other is falsely charged as an accessory in the murder of the owner.

title: Reefer Madness
text: Cautionary tale features a fictionalized take on the use of marijuana. A trio of drug dealers lead innocent teenagers to become addicted to "reefer" cigarettes by holding wild parties with jazz music.

title: D.O.A.
text: Frank Bigelow, told he's been poisoned and has only a few days to live, tries to find out who killed him and why.

title: Pumping Iron
text: Arnold Schwarzenegger and Lou Ferrigno face off in a no-holds-barred competition for the title of Mr. Olympia in this critically-acclaimed film that made Schwarzenegger a household name.

title: Cool World
text: When Jack Deebs was behind bars he found escape by creating Cool World, a cartoon series featuring a vixen named Holli Would. The flesh proves weaker than ink, however, as Holli takes human form in Las Vegas.

title: Strada, La
text: A care-free girl is sold to a traveling entertainer, consequently enduring physical and emotional pain along the way.

title: Ichi the Killer
text: As sadomasochistic yakuza enforcer Kakihara searches for his missing boss he comes across Ichi, a repressed and psychotic killer who may be able to inflict levels of pain that Kakihara has only dreamed of achieving.

title: Boy and His Dog, A
text: A young man and his telepathic dog wander a post-apocalyptic wasteland.

title: Ashes and Diamonds
text: As WWII and the German occupation ends, the Polish resistance and the Russian forces turn on each other in an attempt to take over leadership in Communist Poland.

title: Intolerance: Love's Struggle Throughout the Ages
text: The story of a poor young woman, separated by prejudice from her husband and baby, is interwoven with tales of intolerance from throughout history.

title: Tormented
text: A man lets a former flame fall to her death rather than let her interfere with his new relationship, but her ghost returns to disrupt his impending nuptials.

title: Chitty Chitty Bang Bang
text: A down-on-his-luck inventor turns a broken-down Grand Prix car into a fancy vehicle for his children, and then they go off on a magical fantasy adventure to save their grandfather in a far-off land.

title: Suriyothai
text: During the 16th century, as Thailand contends with both a civil war and Burmese invasion, a beautiful princess rises up to help protect the glory of the Kingdom of Ayothaya. Based on the life of Queen Suriyothai.

title: Where the Day Takes You
text: King is a young man, but he's already a veteran of life on the streets of Los Angeles. The leader of a group of runaways, King acts as a mentor to troubled kids such as gay hustler Little J and junkie Greg.

title: The Butterfly Effect
text: Evan Treborn suffers blackouts during significant events of his life. As he grows up, he finds a way to remember these lost memories and a supernatural way to alter his life by reading his journal.

title: Win a Date with Tad Hamilton!
text: A small-town girl wins a date with a male celebrity through a contest. When the date goes better than expected, a love triangle forms between the girl, the male celebrity, and the girl's best friend.

title: Touching the Void
text: The true story of two climbers and their perilous journey up the west face of Siula Grande in the Peruvian Andes in 1985.

title: Big Bounce, The
text: A small-time con artist and a Hawaiian real estate developer's mischevious, enterprising mistress team up for a potential $200,000 score.

title: Perfect Score, The
text: Six high school seniors decide to break into the Princeton Testing Center so they can steal the answers to their upcoming SAT tests and all get perfect scores.

title: You Got Served
text: In order to achieve their dream of opening a recording studio, two friends  must first win their city's dance contest -- a fierce competition that pits them against a group of tough street dancers.

title: Latter Days
text: A promiscuous gay party animal falls for a young Mormon missionary, leading to crisis, cliché, and catastrophe.

title: Barbershop 2: Back in Business
text: The owner of an historic South Side Chicago barbershop is pressured to sell out to a land developer, but must face the impact this would have on his close-knit community.

title: Catch That Kid
text: A girl and her two friends raid a bank, looking for the money needed for financing the cure of her dying father.

title: Miracle
text: The true story of Herb Brooks, the player-turned-coach who led the 1980 U.S. Olympic hockey team to victory over the seemingly invincible Soviet squad.

title: An Amazing Couple
text: In the first installment in director Belvaux's trilogy, Alain's eccentric behavior causes his wife, Cecile, to hire a detective to follow his every move -- which yields unexpected results.

title: Dreamers, The
text: A young American studying in Paris in 1968 strikes up a friendship with a French brother and sister. Set against the background of the '68 Paris student riots.

title: Lost Skeleton of Cadavra, The
text: A bad scientist and wife, a mad scientist and skeleton, two aliens and their escaped pet are all searching for the elusive element "atmospherium".

title: Hip Hop Witch, Da
text: 5 white kids get lost in the hood looking for da hip hop witch, a year later their footage was found.

title: Thirteen
text: A thirteen-year-old girl's relationship with her mother is put to the test as she discovers drugs, sex, and petty crime in the company of her cool but troubled best friend.

title: Best Defense
text: A military weapons engineer struggles to do his job responsibly, while a hapless tank commander has to live with the consequences in combat years later.

title: 50 First Dates
text: Henry Roth is a man afraid of commitment until he meets the beautiful Lucy. They hit it off and Henry think he's finally found the girl of his dreams until discovering she has short-term memory loss and forgets him the next day.

title: Welcome to Mooseport
text: A US president who has retired after two terms in office returns to his hometown of Mooseport, Maine and decides to run for Mayor against another local candidate.

title: Kitchen Stories
text: A scientific observer's job of observing an old cantankerous single man's kitchen habits is complicated by his growing friendship with him.

title: Monsieur Ibrahim
text: In Paris, a Turkish shop owner befriends a Jewish boy in his mid-teens.

title: Diary of a Country Priest
text: A young priest taking over the parish at Ambricourt tries to fulfill his duties even as he fights a mysterious stomach ailment.

title: Thief of Bagdad, The
text: A recalcitrant thief vies with a duplicitous Mongol ruler for the hand of a beautiful princess.

title: The Diary of Anne Frank
text: During World War II, a teenage Jewish girl named Anne Frank and her family are forced into hiding in the Nazi-occupied Netherlands.

title: Allegro non troppo
text: An enthusiastic filmmaker thinks he's come up with a totally original idea: animation set to classical music! When he is informed that some American named "Prisney"  has already done it, he decides to do his own version, using an orchestra comprising mostly old ladies and an animator he's kept locked in a dungeon. Several different classical pieces are animated, while the animator plots his escape.

title: Black Widow
text: A federal investigator tracks down a gold-digging woman who moves from husband to husband to kill them and collect the inheritance.

title: Herod's Law
text: Mexico, 1949. The fable of a janitor turned Mayor on a little town lost in the Mexican desert, who gradually realizes how far his new acquainted power and corruption can get him.

title: Flesh & Blood
text: In medieval Europe, a young girl from a noble family is obsessed with her captors - commoners.

title: King Solomon's Mines
text: Fortune hunter Allan Quatermain teams up with a resourceful woman to help her find her missing father lost in the wilds of 1900s Africa while being pursued by hostile tribes and a rival German explorer.

title: Raw Deal
text: A former FBI agent turned small-town sheriff agrees to help the FBI chief infiltrate the Chicago mafia when the FBI chief's son is killed by them.

title: Goodbye, Mr. Chips
text: An aged teacher and former headmaster of a boarding school recalls his career and his personal life over the decades.

title: Follow Me, Boys!
text: A man settles down in a small town and becomes the scoutmaster.

title: Against the Ropes
text: A fictional story inspired by North America's most famous female boxing promoter, Jackie Kallen. Her struggle to survive and succeed in a male dominated sport.

title: Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen
text: A teenage girl is convinced that her home city revolves around her until her family packs up and moves to the suburbs, where she finds herself competing for attention.

title: EuroTrip
text: Dumped by his girlfriend, a high school grad decides to embark on an overseas adventure in Europe with his friends.

title: Passion of the Christ, The
text: Depicts the final twelve hours in the life of Jesus of Nazareth, on the day of his crucifixion in Jerusalem.

title: Club Dread
text: When a serial killer interrupts the fun at the swanky Coconut Pete's Coconut Beach Resort--a hedonistic island paradise for swingers--it's up to the club's staff to stop the violence...or at least hide it.

title: Dirty Dancing: Havana Nights
text: High school senior Katey moves to Havana in November 1958, when her dad gets a promotion at Ford. She meets a local waiter, who introduces her to sensual Cuban music/dance. They enter a big dance contest for the prize when he gets fired.

title: Twisted
text: Jessica, whose father killed her mother and committed suicide, is a police officer. While investigating a murder, she finds herself in the center of her own investigation, when her former lovers start being murdered.

title: Good bye, Lenin!
text: In 1990, to protect his fragile mother from a fatal shock after a long coma, a young man must keep her from learning that her beloved nation of East Germany as she knew it has disappeared.

title: Hidalgo
text: In 1890, a down-and-out cowboy and his horse travel to Arabia to compete in a deadly cross desert horse race.

title: Starsky & Hutch
text: Two streetwise cops bust criminals in their red and white Ford Gran Torino, with the help of a police snitch called "Huggy Bear".

title: Reckoning, The
text: A priest on the lam takes up with a traveling band of actors, who then discover a murder has occurred and try to solve it by recreating the crime in a play.

title: Persona
text: A nurse is put in charge of a mute actress and finds that their personae are melding together.

title: Passion of Anna, The
text: A recently divorced man meets an emotionally devastated widow and they begin a love affair.

title: Corbeau, Le
text: A French village doctor becomes the target of poison-pen letters sent to village leaders, accusing him of affairs and practicing abortion.

title: Pickup on South Street
text: A pickpocket unwittingly lifts a message destined for enemy agents and becomes a target for a Communist spy ring.

title: Damned, The
text: The dramatic collapse of a wealthy, industrialist/Junker family during the reign of the Third Reich.

title: Just One of the Guys
text: Terry feels discriminated against when the summer jobs at Sun Tribune go to 2 guys. She decides to do something about it. She dresses like a guy and gets a haircut. Will students at the other high school notice? Girls notice "him".

title: Wrong Arm of the Law, The
text: In London, when Australian gangsters disguised as "Bobbies" rob British criminals, the panicked British mobsters seek an alliance with Scotland Yard in order to eliminate the foreign competition and return things to "normal".

title: Agent Cody Banks 2: Destination London
text: With all-new gadgets, high-flying action, exciting chases and a wisecracking new handler, Derek , Cody has to retrieve the device before the world's leaders fall under the evil control of a diabolical villain.

title: Girl Next Door, The
text: A teenager's dreams come true when a former porn star moves in next door and they fall in love.

title: Secret Window
text: A successful writer in the midst of a painful divorce is stalked at his remote lake house by a would-be scribe who accuses him of plagiarism.

title: Spartan
text: The investigation into a kidnapping of the daughter of a high-ranking US government official.

title: Broken Wings
text: Daphne and her four children try to cope with the abrupt death of husband/father. As the family seems to fall apart, a sudden incident gives them a chance to heal their 'broken wings'.

title: Wilbur Wants to Kill Himself
text: The chronically suicidal Wilbur and his good-hearted big brother Harbour are in their thirties, when their father dies, leaving them with nothing but a worn down second-hand bookshop in Glasgow.

title: Mad Dog and Glory
text: When shy, soft-spoken Chicago detective Wayne "Mad Dog" Dobie inadvertently saves the life of local gangster Frank Milo, he's the reluctant recipient of an unusual one week "thank you" gift - a beautiful bartender named Glory.

title: Peyton Place
text: A peaceful New England town hides secrets and scandals.

title: Dawn of the Dead
text: A nurse, a policeman, a young married couple, a salesman and other survivors of a worldwide plague that is producing aggressive, flesh-eating zombies, take refuge in a mega Midwestern shopping mall.

title: Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind
text: When their relationship turns sour, a couple undergoes a medical procedure to have each other erased from their memories.

title: Taking Lives
text: An FBI profiler is called in by French Canadian police to catch a serial killer who takes on the identity of each new victim.

title: Intermission
text: A variety of losers in Dublin have harrowingly farcical intersecting stories of love, greed and violence.

title: Jersey Girl
text: A widower must look after his precocious daughter and rebuild his life and career after he's sidelined by an unexpected tragedy and a personal blowup.

title: Ladykillers, The
text: An eccentric, if not charming Southern professor and his crew pose as a classical ensemble in order to rob a casino, all under the nose of his unsuspecting but sharp old landlady.

title: Never Die Alone
text: A drug kingpin's return home touches off a turf war.

title: Scooby-Doo 2: Monsters Unleashed
text: The Mystery Inc. gang must save Coolsville from an attack of their past monsters brought to life by an evil masked figure trying to take down the gang.

title: Dogville
text: A woman on the run from the mob is reluctantly accepted in a small Colorado community in exchange for labor, but when a search visits the town she finds out that their support has a price.

title: Ned Kelly
text: An innocent man becomes one of the most wanted criminals the world has ever known.

title: Hellboy
text: A demon, raised from infancy after being conjured by and rescued from the Nazis, grows up to become a defender against the forces of darkness.

title: Prince & Me, The
text: At college Paige meets Eddie, a fellow student from Denmark, whom she first dislikes but later accepts, likes, and loves; he proves to be Crown Prince Edvard. Paige follows him to Copenhagen, and he follows her back to school with a plan.

title: Walking Tall
text: A former U.S. soldier returns to his hometown to find it overrun by crime and corruption, which prompts him to clean house.

title: United States of Leland, The
text: A young man's experience in a juvenile detention center that touches on the tumultuous changes that befall his family and the community in which he lives.

title: The Alamo
text: Based on the 1836 standoff between a group of Texan and Tejano men, led by Davy Crockett and Jim Bowie, and Mexican dictator Santa Anna's forces at the Alamo in San Antonio Texas.

title: Ella Enchanted
text: Ella is under a spell to be constantly obedient, a fact she must hide from her new stepfamily in order to protect the prince of the land, her friend for whom she's falling.

title: Whole Ten Yards, The
text: Jimmy the Tulip's  quiet new life is shaken up by his old pal Oz , whose wife  has been kidnapped by a Hungarian mob. The Tulip and his wife Jill  spring into action.

title: I'm Not Scared
text: A young boy accidentally discovers a deep hole in the ground, where another boy is kept prisoner.

title: Ten Commandments, The
text: Moses, an Egyptian Prince, learns of his true heritage as a Hebrew and his divine mission as the deliverer of his people.

title: Dawn of the Dead
text: Following an ever-growing epidemic of zombies that have risen from the dead, two Philadelphia S.W.A.T. team members, a traffic reporter, and his television executive girlfriend seek refuge in a secluded shopping mall.

title: Prey for Rock & Roll
text: Prey For Rock & Roll is the story of Jacki and her all-girl rock and roll band, Clam Dandy, who are trying to make it in the LA club scene of the late 1980s. After ten years of being ignored by record producers, Jacki and the band find hope in one producer who promises to see them play and consider them for a contract. Jacki resolves to play this one last gig and then throw in the towel if she does not find success. Personal tragedies, however, threaten to rip the band apart, rocking the foundation of friendship and trust the women have built together. Ultimately, the band must find its strength in the music that is their passion and the thread that holds them together, inspiring them to prevail.

title: Those Magnificent Men in Their Flying Machines
text: Hoping to push Britain to the forefront of aviation, a London publisher organizes an international air race across the English Channel, but must contend with two entrants vying for his daughter, as well as national rivalries and cheating.

title: Cheaper by the Dozen
text: Myrna Loy plays the wife of the persnickety father of her 12 children, Clifton Webb, who has uniquely humorous methods for dealing with the ordeals such an unwieldy family undoubtedly encounters.

title: Scenes From a Marriage
text: Ten years within the marriage of Marianne and Johan.

title: Munchies
text: Simon Watterman, a space archaeologist, discovers the "Munchies" in a cave in Peru. Cecil Watterman, Simon's evil twin brother and snack food entrepreneur, kidnaps the creature. What Cecil does not know is that the creature, when chopped up, regenerates into many new creatures -- and are they mean!

title: Going in Style
text: Three friends living on the dole decide to rob a bank.

title: After Hours
text: An ordinary word processor has the worst night of his life after he agrees to visit a girl in Soho who he met that evening at a coffee shop.

title: Kill Bill: Vol. 2
text: The Bride continues her quest of vengeance against her former boss and lover Bill, the reclusive bouncer Budd, and the treacherous, one-eyed Elle.

title: Punisher, The
text: An undercover FBI agent becomes a vigilante and sets out to unleash his wrath upon the corrupt businessman who slaughtered his entire family at a reunion.

title: Paper Clips
text: As a part of their study of the Holocaust, the children of the Whitwell, TN Middle School try to collect 6 million paper clips representing the 6 million Jews killed by the Nazis, and grows to include millions of others killed.

title: This So-Called Disaster
text: Director Michael Almereyda's documentary on the weeks just prior to Sam Shepard's stage production of his play "The Late Henry Moss."

title: 13 Going on 30
text: A girl makes a wish on her thirteenth birthday, and wakes up the next day as a thirty-year-old woman.

title: Man on Fire
text: In Mexico City, a former CIA operative swears vengeance on those who committed an unspeakable act against the family he was hired to protect.

title: Envy
text: A man becomes increasingly jealous of his friend's newfound success.

title: Godsend
text: A couple agree to have their deceased son cloned, under the supervision of an enigmatic doctor, but bizarre things start to happen several years after his rebirth.

title: Laws of Attraction
text: Amidst a sea of litigation, two New York City divorce lawyers find love.

title: Mean Girls
text: Cady Heron is a hit with The Plastics, the A-list girl clique at her new school, until she makes the mistake of falling for Aaron Samuels, the ex-boyfriend of alpha Plastic Regina George.

title: Van Helsing
text: The famed monster hunter is sent to Transylvania to stop Count Dracula, who is using Dr. Frankenstein's research and a werewolf for nefarious purposes.

title: Mudge Boy, The
text: The film follows the story of Duncan, a fourteen-year-old misfit farm boy trying to fill the void and alleviate the numbness left by his mother's passing. Unable to let her go quite yet, Duncan mimics his dead mother. He talks in her voice at the dinner table and wears her fur coat to bed. Edgar, Duncan's distant sixty-year-old father, doesn't understand the strange manifestations of his son's mourning. Why can't Duncan grieve like a normal person? Macho mate Perry Foley, who has it physically even harder on his dad's farm, usually comforts Duncan and defends his 'wimpiness' to their cocky ruffian mates Travis, Scotty and Brent. But although clearly attracted to gentle Duncan himself, the socially unacceptable suggestion of 'sissy' homosexuality makes Perry over-react and turn on his friend.

title: Breakin' All the Rules
text: Inspired by his fiancée , a man publishes a break-up hand-book for men, becoming a best-selling author in the process.

title: Troy
text: An adaptation of Homer's great epic, the film follows the assault on Troy by the united Greek forces and chronicles the fates of the men involved.

title: Carandiru
text: Brazilian MD Drauzio Varella starts AIDS prevention in Brazil's largest prison, Carandiru in São Paulo, where the population is nearly double its 4,000 maximum. Doc learns from experience and the tragic stories of hideous crimes which landed scum there and passionate dramas adding otherwise decent people. Just when he believes to leave the prisoners happy with a soccer tournament, a silly clothing-line argument kick-starts a politically opportune revolt repression.

title: Coffee and Cigarettes
text: A series of vignettes that all have coffee and cigarettes in common.

title: Eye See You
text: A lead detective being stalked by a serial killer is asked to check into a clinic treating law enforcement officials who can't face their jobs.

title: Watch on the Rhine
text: A German-born engineer, his American wife and their children travel from Mexico to the United States to visit her family but their plans are complicated by a Romanian count.

title: Enemy Mine
text: During a long space war, the lives of two wounded enemies become dependent on their ability to forgive and to trust.

title: Enter the Dragon
text: A secret agent comes to an opium lord's island fortress with other fighters for a martial-arts tournament.

title: Happy Together
text: A couple take a trip to Argentina but both men find their lives drifting apart in opposite directions.

title: Henry & June
text: Anaïs Nin meets the American writer, Henry Miller, in Paris in 1931. She keeps a diary of her sexual awakening which includes Henry and his wife, June.

title: Martin
text: A young man, who believes himself to be a vampire, goes to live with his elderly and hostile cousin in a small Pennsylvania town where he tries to redeem his blood-craving urges.

title: Three Faces of Eve, The
text: A doctor treats a woman suffering from Multiple Personality Disorder.

title: 100 Girls
text: Matt spends the night with a girl in an elevator during power outage in a girls' college dorm. He never sees her. Waking up in the morning, panties are all that's left of her. How does he find her in a building with 100 girls?

title: Fail-Safe
text: A technical malfunction sends American planes to Moscow to deliver a nuclear attack. Can all-out war be averted?

title: Paperhouse
text: A young girl lost in the loneliness and boredom of reality finds solace in an ill boy, whom she can visit in a surreal dream world that she drew in her school composition book.

title: Dobermann
text: Dobermann is the world's most ruthless bank robber and with his gang rob bank after bank, now in Paris. What can the police do but to let the mad, morally bankrupt police commissioner loose on him?

title: Kwaidan
text: A collection of four Japanese folk tales with supernatural themes.

title: 28 Up
text: Director Michael Apted interviews the same group of British-born adults after a 7 year wait as to the changes that have occurred in their lives during the last seven years.

title: You Only Live Twice
text: Secret Agent James Bond and the Japanese Secret Service must find and stop the true culprit of a series of space hijackings, before war is provoked between Russia and the United States.

title: Octopussy
text: A fake Fabergé egg, and a fellow Agent's death, lead James Bond to uncover an international jewel-smuggling operation, headed by the mysterious Octopussy, being used to disguise a nuclear attack on N.A.T.O. forces.

title: Wit
text: A renowned professor is forced to reassess her life when she is diagnosed with terminal ovarian cancer.

title: Never Say Never Again
text: A S.P.E.C.T.R.E. Agent has stolen two American nuclear warheads, and James Bond must find their targets before they are detonated.

title: Pride and Prejudice
text: The arrival of wealthy bachelors in town causes an uproar when families with single daughters aggressively seek engagements, including the Bennet family, with five eligible daughters.

title: Fountainhead, The
text: An uncompromising, visionary architect struggles to maintain his integrity and individualism despite personal, professional and economic pressures to conform to popular standards.

title: Woman of the Year
text: Rival reporters Sam and Tess fall in love and get married, only to find their relationship strained when Sam comes to resent Tess' hectic lifestyle.

title: Samouraï, Le
text: After professional hitman Jef Costello is seen by witnesses his efforts to provide himself an alibi drive him further into a corner.

title: Oklahoma!
text: In Oklahoma, several farmers, cowboys and a traveling salesman compete for the romantic favors of various local ladies.

title: Desert Hearts
text: While waiting for her divorce papers, a repressed professor of literature is unexpectedly seduced by a carefree, spirited young lesbian.

title: Body Double
text: A young actor's obsession with spying on a beautiful woman who lives nearby leads to a baffling series of events with drastic consequences.

title: Chaplin
text: An elderly Charlie Chaplin discusses his autobiography with his editor, recounting his amazing journey from his poverty-stricken childhood to world-wide success after the ingenious invention of the Little Tramp.

title: Miracle Worker, The
text: The story of Anne Sullivan's struggle to teach the blind and deaf Helen Keller how to communicate.

title: Monster in a Box
text: This is the story of Spalding Gray and his attempt to write a novel. It is a first person account about writing and living, and dealing with success while trying to be successful.

title: School Ties
text: Set in the 1950s, a star-quarterback is given an opportunity to attend an elite preparatory school but must conceal the fact that he is Jewish.

title: Raising Cain
text: The oncologist wife of a prominent child psychologist suspects her husband has an unhealthy scientific obsession with their child, unaware of what - or who - is really going on inside his head.

title: Rose Red
text: A group of people with psychic powers are invited to spend the night in a haunted house.

title: Noises Off...
text: A travelling theater group find so much action going on behind-the-scenes, they almost ruin the performances.

title: Babylon 5: In the Beginning
text: Emperor Londo Mollari of the Centauri Republic tells the story of the Earth-Minbari War that almost destroyed humanity and later inspired its last best, hope for peace.

title: Witchfinder General
text: A young soldier seeks to put an end to the evils caused by a vicious witch-hunter when the latter terrorizes his fiancée and kills her uncle.

title: Versus
text: There are 666 portals that connect this world to the other side. These are concealed from all human beings. Somewhere in Japan exists the 444th portal.... The forest of resurrection.

title: Pride and Prejudice
text: While the arrival of wealthy gentlemen sends her marriage-minded mother into a frenzy, willful and opinionated Elizabeth Bennet matches wits with haughty Mr. Darcy.

title: China Syndrome, The
text: A reporter finds what appears to be a cover-up of safety hazards at a nuclear power plant.

title: Wages of Fear, The
text: In a decrepit South American village, four men are hired to transport an urgent nitroglycerine shipment without the equipment that would make it safe.

title: Look Who's Talking Too
text: This time, a new baby is on the way, and it's a girl. Wrapped together with the standard conflict between mother and father, Mikey engages in a bit of sibling rivalry with his new sister.

title: Bells of St. Mary's, The
text: At a big city Catholic school, Father O'Malley and Sister Benedict indulge in friendly rivalry, and succeed in extending the school through the gift of a building.

title: Delta Force, The
text: After a plane is hijacked by terrorists, The Delta Force is sent in to resolve the crisis.

title: Pat and Mike
text: Pat is a women's sports sensation unless her fiancé is around. Her new shady manager Mike keeps them apart and develops feelings for her.

title: Animal Crackers
text: Mayhem and zaniness ensue when a valuable painting goes missing during a party in honor of famed African explorer Captain Spaulding.

title: He Said, She Said
text: TV viewers love seeing the two reporters with opposing views on the show "He Said, She Said". Womanizer Dan and Lorie fall for each other. Love?

title: Bedazzled
text: A hapless loser sells his soul to the Devil in exchange for seven wishes, but has trouble winning over the girl of his dreams.

title: Cat People
text: An American man marries a Serbian immigrant who fears that she will turn into the cat person of her homeland's fables if they are intimate together.

title: Camelot
text: The story of the marriage of England's King Arthur to Guinevere. The plot of illegitimate Mordred to gain the throne and Guinevere's growing attachment to Sir Lancelot, threaten to topple Arthur and destroy his "round table" of knights.

title: Lonely Guy, The
text: A writer for a greeting card company discovers the struggles and tribulations of living alone after breaking up with his unfaithful girlfriend.

title: Four Musketeers, The
text: The Four Musketeers defend the queen and her dressmaker from Cardinal Richelieu and Milady de Winter.

title: Protocol
text: A woman  saves life of Emir of Ohtar  in Washington.

title: Postman Always Rings Twice, The
text: A married woman and a drifter fall in love, then plot to murder her husband.

title: Matinee
text: A small-time film promoter releases a kitschy horror film during the Cuban Missile Crisis.

title: Baxter
text: A white Bull Terrier named Baxter is given to an elderly woman by her daughter. As time passes, the dog develops aggressive and murderous behavior in order to be adopted by another family.

title: Explorers
text: A boy obsessed with '50s sci-fi movies about aliens has a recurring dream about a blueprint of some kind, which he draws for his inventor friend. With the help of a third kid, they follow it and build themselves a spaceship. Now what?

title: Scent of Green Papaya, The
text: A Vietnamese servant girl, Mui, observes lives within two different Saigon families: the first, a woman textile seller with three boys and a frequently absent husband; the second, a handsome young pianist with his fiancée.

title: Pierrot le fou
text: Pierrot escapes his boring society and travels from Paris to the Mediterranean Sea with Marianne, a girl chased by hit-men from Algeria. They lead an unorthodox life, always on the run.

title: Weekend
text: A surreal tale of a married couple going on a road trip to visit the wife's parents with the intention of killing them for the inheritance.

title: Tuesdays with Morrie
text: A journalist finds himself questioning his own life when his best friend, a dying man, offers him some very powerful wisdom and advice for coping in relationships, careers and society.

title: Alexander Nevsky
text: The story of how a great Russian prince led a ragtag army to battle an invading force of Teutonic Knights.

title: Jason and the Argonauts
text: The legendary Greek hero leads a team of intrepid adventurers in a perilous quest for the legendary Golden Fleece.

title: Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy
text: In the bleak days of the Cold War, espionage veteran George Smiley is forced out of semi-retirement to uncover a Soviet Agent within MI6's echelons.

title: Throne of Blood
text: A war-hardened general, egged on by his ambitious wife, works to fulfill a prophecy that he would become lord of Spider's Web Castle.

title: Best of Youth, The
text: An Italian epic that follows the lives of two brothers, from the 1960s to the 2000s.

title: Undercurrent
text: Middle-aged bride Ann Hamilton soon begins to suspect that her charming husband is really a psychotic who plans to murder her.

title: Bang, Bang, You're Dead
text: Trevor is a troubled high school student, thanks to the effects of bullying. This is the story of his fight to break free.

title: Twister
text: Delusional and spoiled Maureen and her eccentric brother Howdy decide to track down and meet their estranged mother, all while the drama of dysfunctional relationships, disastrous weather conditions and a dark family secret ensue.

title: Sniper
text: A US Marine sniper is partnered with a SWAT member to take out rebel leaders in the jungles of Panama.

title: Genghis Blues
text: San Francisco bluesman and composer, Paul Peña makes a musical pilgrimage to the land of Tuva.

title: 11'09"01 - September 11
text: The effects of the 9/11 terrorist attacks are told from different points of view around the world.

title: Parallax View, The
text: An ambitious reporter gets in way-over-his-head trouble while investigating a senator's assassination which leads to a vast conspiracy involving a multinational corporation behind every event in the world's headlines.

title: Warriors, The
text: In the near future, a charismatic leader summons the street gangs of New York City in a bid to take it over. When he is killed, The Warriors are falsely blamed and now must fight their way home while every other gang is hunting them down.

title: Babylon 5: A Call to Arms
text: The Drakh, allies of the Shadows, seek revenge against humanity after the Second Shadow War.

title: Babylon 5: The River of Souls
text: A group of Soul Hunters come to Babylon 5 demanding the return of something that was stolen from them.

title: Babylon 5: Thirdspace
text: The crew of Babylon 5 discover an ancient artifact floating in hyperspace.

title: True Stories
text: A small but growing Texas town, filled with strange and musical characters, celebrates its sesquicentennial and converge on a local parade and talent show.

title: Virgin Spring, The
text: In 14th-century Sweden, an innocent yet pampered teenage girl and her family's pregnant and jealous servant set out from their farm to deliver candles to church, but only one returns from events that transpire in the woods along the way.

title: Mogambo
text: On a Kenyan safari, white hunter Victor Marswell has a love triangle with seductive American socialite Eloise Kelly and anthropologist Donald Nordley's cheating wife Linda.

title: Secret Life of Walter Mitty, The
text: A clumsy daydreamer gets caught up in a sinister conspiracy.

title: Another Thin Man
text: An explosives manufacturer suspects a young man is out to kill him. He calls in new parents Nick and Nora to sort things out.

title: Thin Man Goes Home, The
text: Nick and Nora Charles visit Nicks parents in Nick's hometown of Sycamore Springs. The town is a very peaceful and law-abiding one but Nick soon has a murder case on his hands.

title: Shadow of the Thin Man
text: A jockey has been shot dead at the race track. Famous detective Nick Charles and his wife Nora happen to be on the scene and Lt. Abrahams asks for Nick's expert help.

title: After the Thin Man
text: Private detective Nick Charles and his wealthy wife Nora are back home at last and hoping for a quiet New Year when Nora's brother-in-law is murdered. The obvious suspect is his wife, Nora's sister, Selma.

title: Song of the Thin Man
text: Nick and Nora Charles are on a gambling boat when someone is murdered. The two main suspects are at large and come to Nick for help. Nick turns them into the police but then sets out to figure out the mystery.

title: Love Crazy
text: A wife suspecting infidelity starts divorce proceedings, so the husband pretends to be insane in order to delay the divorce and clear up the misunderstanding.

title: Gunga Din
text: In 19th century India, three British soldiers and a native waterbearer must stop a secret mass revival of the murderous Thuggee cult before it can rampage across the land.

title: Children of Dune
text: The twins of Paul "Muad'dib" Atreides become embroiled in the political landscape of Arrakis  and the rest of the universe.

title: Dune
text: A three-part miniseries on politics, betrayal, lust, greed and the coming of a Messiah. Based on Frank Herbert's classic science fiction novel.

title: Lammbock
text: Stefan and Kai have good going business, self-grown cannabis screened as pizza delivering service. For now they only have to deal with aphids.

title: Legend, The
text: This Hong Kong martial-arts extravaganza tells of evil emperors and true love. The secret Red Lotus Flower Society is committed to the overthrow of the evil Manchu Emperor and his minions. One of his Governors is sent on a mission to retrieve a list of members of that secret society. Meanwhile, Canton kung fu practitioner Fong Sai-Yuk falls in love with the beautiful daughter of a rich merchant, recently moved to Canton. Her father, in an attempt to gain influence in the region and thus improve his business, offers his daughter in marriage to the winner of a kung-fu contest. Some interesting gender role-reversals take place during a 'comedy of errors.'

title: Tremors II: Aftershocks
text: Earl Bassett, now a washed-up ex-celebrity, is hired by a Mexican oil company to eradicate a Graboid epidemic that's killing more people each day. However, the humans aren't the only one with a new battle plan.

title: Tremors 3: Back to Perfection
text: The now famous Burt Gummer returns to his hometown of Perfection, Nevada for the first time in years, but the deadliest Graboid evolution yet forces him to save the town he swore to protect.

title: Notorious C.H.O.
text: A film of Margaret Cho's one-woman stand-up show, in which she presents her take on modern sexual topics and minority issues.

title: The Plague of the Zombies
text: Young workers are dying because of a mysterious epidemic in a little village in Cornwall. Doctor Thompson is helpless and asks professor James Forbes for help. The professor and his daughter Sylvia travel to Thomson. Terrible things happen soon, beyond imagination or reality. Dead people are seen near an old, unused mine. Late people seem to live suddenly. Professor Forbes presumes that black magic is involved and someone has extraordinary power. He doesn't know how close he is: the dead become alive because of a magic voodoo-ritual, and so they must serve their master as mindless zombies...

title: I Walked with a Zombie
text: A nurse is hired to care for the wife of a sugar plantation owner, who has been acting strangely, on a Caribbean island.

title: Highway 61
text: A small-town barber goes on a road trip from Thunder Bay to New Orleans with an unpredictable woman and a coffin.

title: How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying
text: Armed with the titular manual, an ambitious window washer seeks to climb the corporate ladder.

title: Pat Garrett and Billy the Kid
text: Pat Garrett is hired as a lawman on behalf of a group of wealthy New Mexico cattle barons to bring down his old friend Billy the Kid.

title: Last Man on Earth, The
text: When a disease turns all of humanity into the living dead, the last man on earth becomes a reluctant vampire hunter.

title: Duck, You Sucker
text: A low-life bandit and an I.R.A. explosives expert rebel against the government and become heroes of the Mexican Revolution.

title: Bring Me the Head of Alfredo Garcia
text: An American barroom pianist and his prostitute girlfriend go on a trip through the Mexican underworld to collect the bounty on the head of a dead gigolo.

title: Ride the High Country
text: An ex-union soldier is hired to transport gold from a mining community through dangerous territory. But what he doesn't realize is that his partner and old friend is plotting to double-cross him.

title: Master of the Flying Guillotine
text: After his students are killed by the One Armed Boxer, a vengeful and blind Kung Fu expert travels to a village where a martial arts contest is being held and vows to behead every one armed man he comes across.

title: Frankenstein Must Be Destroyed
text: Baron Frankenstein, with the aid of a young doctor and his fiancée, kidnaps the mentally sick Dr. Brandt in order to perform the first brain transplant operation.

title: Gidget
text: A young girl discovers surfing and love  during one transitive summer.

title: Desperate Living
text: A neurotic society woman murders her husband with the help of her maid and, on the lam, escape to Mortville, a homeless community ruled over by a fascist queen.

title: Stray Dog
text: During a sweltering summer, a rookie homicide detective tries to track down his stolen Colt pistol.

title: Hidden Fortress, The
text: Lured by gold, two greedy peasants unknowingly escort a princess and her general across enemy lines.

title: High and Low
text: An executive of a Yokohama shoe company becomes a victim of extortion when his chauffeur's son is kidnapped by mistake and held for ransom.

title: People Under the Stairs, The
text: Two adults and a juvenile break into a house occupied by a brother and sister and their stolen children. There, they must fight for their lives.

title: Dark Days
text: A cinematic portrait of the homeless population who live permanently in the underground tunnels of New York City.

title: Zelig
text: "Documentary" about a man who can look and act like whoever he's around, and meets various famous people.

title: Shame
text: In the midst of a civil war, former violinists Jan and Eva Rosenberg, who have a tempestuous marriage, run a farm on a rural island. In spite of their best efforts to escape their homeland, the war impinges on every aspect of their lives.

title: Silence, The
text: Two estranged sisters, Ester and Anna, and Anna's 10-year-old son travel to the Central European country on the verge of war. Ester becomes seriously ill and the three of them move into a hotel in a small town called Timoka.

title: Winter Light
text: A small-town priest struggles with his faith.

title: Through a Glass Darkly
text: Recently released from a mental hospital, Karin rejoins her emotionally disconnected family in their island home, only to slip from reality as she begins to believe she is being visited by God.

title: The Magician
text: A traveling magician and his assistants are persecuted by authorities in Sweden of the 19th century. Their captures, however, didn't bring victory to those in power.

title: Killers, The
text: Hit men kill an unresisting victim, and investigator Reardon uncovers his past involvement with beautiful, deadly Kitty Collins.

title: Night of the Iguana, The
text: A defrocked Episcopal clergyman leads a bus-load of middle-aged Baptist women on a tour of the Mexican coast and comes to terms with the failure haunting his life.

title: Nightbreed
text: A troubled young man is drawn to a mythical place called Midian where a variety of friendly monsters are hiding from humanity. Meanwhile, a sadistic serial killer is looking for a patsy.

title: Ken Park
text: Ken Park is about several Californian skateboarders' lives and relationships with and without their parents.

title: Monterey Pop
text: A film about the greatest pre-Woodstock rock music festival.

title: Bridge Too Far, A
text: Operation Market Garden, September 1944: The Allies attempt to capture several strategically important bridges in the Netherlands in the hope of breaking the German lines.

title: Infernal Affairs
text: A story between a mole in the police department and an undercover cop. Their objectives are the same: to find out who is the mole, and who is the cop.

title: Tale of Two Sisters, A
text: A family is haunted by the tragedies of deaths within the family.

title: Broadway Danny Rose
text: In his attempts to reconcile a lounge singer with his mistress, a hapless talent agent is mistaken as her lover by a jealous gangster.

title: From Beyond
text: A group of scientists have developed the Resonator, a machine which allows whoever is within range to see beyond normal perceptible reality. But when the experiment succeeds, they are immediately attacked by terrible life forms.

title: Robot Jox
text: In the distant future, mankind has forsaken global wars for battles of single combat. The world has been divided into two opposing super powers, with each side represented by trained champions.

title: Dolls
text: A dysfunctional family of three stop by a mansion during a storm -- father, stepmother, and child. The child discovers that the elderly owners are magical toy makers and have a haunted collection of dolls.

title: Space Truckers
text: A space trucker and his cute fiancee are on their way from a space station to Earth with an unknown cargo. When space pirates hijack them, 5000 disintegrator robots are found in the cargo.

title: Death Race 2000
text: In a dystopian future, a cross country automobile race requires contestants to run down innocent pedestrians to gain points that are tallied based on each kill's brutality.

title: Bucket Of Blood, A
text: A dim-witted busboy finds acclaim as an artist for a plaster-covered dead cat that is mistaken as a skillful statuette. The desire for more praise soon leads to an increasingly deadly series of works.

title: Brigadoon
text: Two Americans on a hunting trip in Scotland become lost. They encounter a small village, not on the map, called Brigadoon, in which people harbor a mysterious secret, and behave as if they were still living two hundred years in the past.

title: Power of One, The
text: An English boy, living in Africa during World War II, through his boxing prowess, becomes a symbol of hope, in a time of war.

title: Weather Underground, The
text: The remarkable story of The Weather Underground, radical activists of the 1970s, and of radical politics at its best and most disastrous.

title: Kikujiro
text: A young, naive boy sets out alone on the road to find his wayward mother. Soon he finds an unlikely protector in a crotchety man and the two have a series of unexpected adventures along the way.

title: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter... and Spring
text: A boy is raised by a Buddhist monk in an isolated floating temple where the years pass like the seasons.

title: Phantom Tollbooth, The
text: Milo is a boy who is bored with life. One day he comes home to find a toll booth in his room. Having nothing better to do, he gets in his toy car and drives through - only to emerge in a world full of adventure.

title: Getaway, The
text: A recently-released ex-con and his loyal wife go on the run after a heist goes awry.

title: Dark Water
text: A mother and her 6 year old daughter move into a creepy apartment whose every surface is permeated by water.

title: Thing Called Love, The
text: A group of newcomers to the country music business seek love and stardom.

title: The Thief
text: A woman meets a man who isn't the right man for her - but she hasn't realised it yet...

title: How to Steal a Million
text: The daughter of an art forger teams up with a burglar to steal one of her father's forgeries and protect his secret.

title: Stendhal Syndrome, The
text: A young policewoman slowly goes insane while tracking down an elusive serial rapist/killer through Italy when she herself becomes a victim of the brutal man's obsession.

title: Mean Streets
text: A small-time hood tries to keep the peace between his friend Johnny and Johnny's creditors.

title: Jack the Bear
text: Danny DeVito is John Leary, a professional clown, whose wife's death in a car accident has left him to care for his two young boys.

title: I Am a Fugitive from a Chain Gang
text: Wrongly convicted James Allen serves in the intolerable conditions of a southern chain gang, which later comes back to haunt him.

title: Hamburger Hill
text: A very realistic interpretation of one of the bloodiest battles of the Vietnam War.

title: Sweet Bird of Youth
text: A drifter and a faded film star, both traumatized by Hollywood, arrive to the guy's hometown, where the old bitter memories revive again.

title: Frankenstein Unbound
text: The ultimate weapon, which was meant to be safe for humankind, produces global side-effects, including time slides and disappearances. The scientist behind the project and his car are transported from the year 2031 to 1817's Switzerland, where he finds Dr. Victor Frankenstein and his contemporaries.

title: Shiri
text: South Korean agents Ryu and Lee are tracking a female assassin from North Korea who has mysteriously disappeared. With new killings and the theft of a deadly bomb, time is running out to catch her.

title: Bad Day at Black Rock
text: A one-armed stranger comes to a tiny town possessing a terrible past they want to keep secret, by violent means if necessary.

title: In China They Eat Dogs
text: Two brothers, one cold and ruthless, the other sensitive and reluctant, and their brutal misadventures.

title: Delta Force 2
text: When DEA agents are taken captive by a ruthless South American kingpin, the Delta Force is reunited to rescue them in this sequel to the 1986 film.

title: Crossroads
text: A wanna be blues guitar virtuoso seeks a long lost song by legendary musician, Robert Johnson.

title: Seducing Doctor Lewis
text: A much-needed boost, in the form of a new factory, is promised to the residents of the tiny fishing village St. Marie-La-Mauderne, provided they can lure a doctor to take up full-time residency on the island. Inspired, the villagers devise a scheme to make Dr. Christopher Lewis a local.

title: Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans
text: A sophisticated urban woman seduces a farmer in the hopes that he will murder his neglected wife and join her in the city, but he soon finds himself rekindling his romance with the latter when she discovers their scheme.

title: Shock Corridor
text: Bent on winning a Pulitzer Prize, a journalist commits himself to a mental institution to solve a strange and unclear murder.

title: Au revoir les enfants
text: A French boarding school run by priests seems to be a haven from World War II until a new student arrives. He becomes the roommate of the top student in his class. Rivals at first, the roommates form a bond and share a secret.

title: Pursuit of Happiness
text: An advertising executive fails to realize that the woman of his dreams is his best friend since first grade, now married to his cheating co-worker.

title: Gladiator
