title: Better Tomorrow, A
text: A reforming ex-gangster tries to reconcile with his estranged policeman brother, but the ties to his former gang are difficult to break.

title: Decalogue, The
text: Ten television drama films, each one based on one of the Ten Commandments.

title: G.I. Joe: The Movie
text: The heroic G.I. Joe action force must oppose the ruthless Cobra organization that has secretly allied with a subterranean reptilian people who were their founders.

title: Hell Comes to Frogtown
text: After a worldwide nuclear war, where 68% of the male population was wiped out and virile men becoming a rarity, Sam Hell, a scavenger and a highly virile man, is assigned to help rescue a group of fertile women kidnapped by humanoid frogs.

title: Law of Desire
text: A gay filmmaker becomes involved with an obsessive fan while still pining for his absent true love. Meanwhile, he shares a close but complex relationship with his trans sister, an actress.

title: Prince of Darkness
text: A group of graduate students and scientists uncover an ancient canister in an abandoned church, but when they open the container, they inadvertently unleash a strange liquid and an evil force on all humanity.

title: Chinese Ghost Story, A
text: After a string of bad luck, a debt collector has no other choice than to spend the night in a haunted temple, where he encounters a ravishing female ghost and later battles to save her soul from the control of a wicked tree demon.

title: Better Tomorrow II, A
text: A restauranteur teams up with a police officer and his ex-con brother to avenge the death of a friend's daughter.

title: Bourne Identity, The
text: An injured, unconscious man washes ashore in a small French town. As he recovers, it becomes quite clear, someone is trying to kill him.

title: Dominick and Eugene
text: Dominick and Eugene are twins, but Dominick is a little bit slow due to an accident in his youth. They live together, with Dominick working as garbage man to put Eugene through medical school. Their relationship becomes strained when Eugene must decide between his devotion to his brother, or his need to go away to complete his training. Things are also not helped by Dominick's co-worker, or Eugene's budding romance.

title: Killer Klowns from Outer Space
text: Aliens who look like clowns come from outer space and terrorize a small town.

title: Moonwalker
text: Anthology movie by, and starring, Michael Jackson in his prime, combining a number of music videos from his bestselling "Bad" album with a fantasy tale of Michael's confrontation with a ruthless drug dealer known as Mr. Big.

title: Alice
text: A surrealistic revision of Alice in Wonderland.

title: Life Is a Long Quiet River
text: A revengeful nurse switches a girl and a boy at birth. They are raised in two radically different families. When the switch is revealed many years later, the now teenagers and families need to cope with their new environments.

title: Lonesome Dove
text: Two former Texas Rangers renew their spirit of adventure as they and several other residents of a small Texas town join a cattle drive to the Montana Territory.

title: Kiki's Delivery Service
text: A young witch, on her mandatory year of independent life, finds fitting into a new community difficult while she supports herself by running an air courier service.

title: Almost an Angel
text: A small-time crook becomes convinced he is an angel after a traumatic incident and resolves to perform the work of one.

title: Cry-Baby
text: In 1950s Baltimore, a bad boy with a heart of gold wins the love of a good girl, whose boyfriend sets out for revenge.

title: Bullet in the Head
text: When three close friends escape from Hong Kong to war-time Saigon to start a criminal's life, they all go through a harrowing experience which totally shatters their lives and their friendship forever.

title: Ghost Dad
text: A widowed father tries to support his children after he becomes a ghost in an accident.

title: It
text: In 1960, seven pre-teen outcasts fight an evil demon who poses as a child-killing clown. Thirty years later, they reunite to stop the demon once and for all when it returns to their hometown.

title: Ju Dou
text: A woman married to the brutal and infertile owner of a dye mill in rural China conceives a boy with her husband's nephew but is forced to raise her son as her husband's heir without revealing his parentage in this circular tragedy.

title: Krays, The
text: This fact-based movie follows the life of the twin crime-lords in London's '60s underworld.

title: Lionheart
text: An Ex-French Soldier begins participating in underground street fights in order to make money for his brother's family.

title: Nuns on the Run
text: 2 criminals want out but their boss kills those leaving. When the men are ordered to rob the triad, they keep the money and hide from the boss, triad and police at a convent, dressed as nuns.

title: Patlabor: The Movie
text: The screwball cops of Special Vehicles Section 2 Division 2 must investigate and stop a spree of rampaging construction robots.

title: State of Grace
text: A New York cop is recruited to return to his hometown and infiltrate the mob ran by his best friend's brother.

title: 35 Up
text: Director Michael Apted interviews the same group of British-born adults after a 7 year wait as to the changes that have occurred in their lives during the last seven years.

title: Days of Being Wild
text: A man tries to find out who his real mother is after the woman who raised him tells him the truth.

title: Begotten
text: Presented in a surreal, gory and entirely visual manner, Begotten tells of the death of religion, the abuse of nature by Man and a nihilistic outlook on what life ultimately is.

title: Dutch
text: To get to know his girlfriend's son, a working-class good guy volunteers to pick him up from his prep school, only to learn that he isn't the nicest young man.

title: Hearts of Darkness: A Filmmakers Apocalypse
text: Documentary that chronicles how Francis Ford Coppola's Apocalypse Now  was plagued by extraordinary script, shooting, budget, and casting problems--nearly destroying the life and career of the celebrated director.

title: Johnny Stecchino
text: A kindhearted but bumbling idiot who likes to steal bananas, is passed off for a snitch hiding from the mob.

title: Riki-Oh: The Story of Ricky
text: Riki-Oh, a young man who has superhuman strength, is incarcerated at a private prison, where inmates are treated like slaves, and is forced to use his unstoppable form of martial arts to destroy the corrupt officials and their lackeys.

title: Mannequin 2: On the Move
text: A young department store intern falls in love with a female store mannequin who is really a peasant girl fallen under a thousand year spell. She comes to life whenever he removes the cursed necklace from her.

title: Only Yesterday
text: A twenty-seven-year-old office worker travels to the countryside while reminiscing about her childhood in Tokyo.

title: Other People's Money
text: A corporate raider buys up shares in an undervalued company and falls in love with the founder's son's lawyer/step daughter. Let the battle begin.

title: Quigley Down Under
text: Sharpshooter Matt Quigley is hired from Wyoming by an Australian rancher paying a very high price. But when Quigley arrives Down Under, all is not as it seems.

title: Prime Suspect 2
text: Detective Chief Inspector Jane Tennison's  investigation of a murder is complicated with the unexpected participation of her secret lover in her detective unit.

title: Captain America
text: Frozen in the ice for decades, Captain America is freed to battle against archcriminal The Red Skull.

title: City Hunter
text: A self-indulgent private investigator winds up on a cruise ship full of rich patrons, gorgeous women, murderous terrorists, and scarce food.

title: Porco Rosso
text: In 1930s Italy, a veteran World War I pilot is cursed to look like an anthropomorphic pig.

title: Stolen Children
text: Antonio, a policeman , has an order to take two children  from Milan to Sicily to an orphanage. Their mother has been arrested for forcing Rosetta  to work as a prostitute. First the relation between Antonio and the children is tough, but it relaxes so they become temporary friends.

title: Ladybugs
text: To climb the corporate ladder to success, a guy agrees to coach the company's all-girls soccer team with the help of his secret weapon: his fiancee's son.

title: Mambo Kings, The
text: Two Cuban brothers bring a new music to the 1950s USA. They are as different as the problems that await them.

title: Shining Through
text: An American woman of Irish, Jewish-German parentage goes undercover in Nazi Germany.

title: Sidekicks
text: A bullied teen who fantasizes about being Chuck Norris' sidekick trains in martial arts to fulfill his dreams.

title: Heart in Winter, A
text: Beautiful violin virtuoso Camille has two obsessions: the music of Ravel, and a friend of her husband's who crafts violins. But his heart seems to be as cold as her playing is passionate.

title: Visions of Light: The Art of Cinematography
text: Cameramen and women discuss the craft and art of cinematography, illustrating their points with clips from 100 films, from Birth of a Nation to Do the Right Thing.

title: Bad Boy Bubby
text: Bubby has spent thirty years trapped in the same small room, tricked by his mother. One day, he manages to escape, and, deranged and naive in equal measures, his adventure into the modern and nihilistic life begins.

title: Barbarians at the Gate
text: The president of a major tobacco company decides to buy the company himself, but a bidding war ensues as other companies make their own offers.

title: Fortress
text: In a future, private underground prison/Fortress, the inmates are computer controlled with CCTV, dream readers and devices that can cause pain or death. John and his illegally pregnant wife are inside but want to escape before birth.

title: Mr. Nanny
text: A former professional wrestler is hired to be the bodyguard/nanny for a couple of bratty kids whose inventor father is being stalked by a rival.

title: Sonatine
text: Several yakuza from Tokyo are sent to Okinawa to help end a gang war. The war then escalates and the Tokyo drifters decide to lay low at the beach.

title: Stand, The
text: After a deadly plague kills most of the world's population, the remaining survivors split into two groups - one led by a benevolent elder and the other by a malevolent being - to face each other in a final battle between good and evil.

title: Darkman II: Return of Durant, The
text: Darkman and Durant return and they hate each other as much as ever. This time, Durant has plans to take over the city's drug trade using high-tech weaponry. Darkman must step in and try to stop Durant once and for all.

title: Freaked
text: A vain actor, his best friend, and an activist end up at a mutant freak farm run by a weirdo scientist.

title: Fist of Legend
text: In 1937, a Chinese martial artist returns to Shanghai to find his teacher dead and his school harassed by the Japanese.

title: Major League II
text: The Indians are now a World Series contender. But last year's hunger is now replaced with complacency, and bad decisions by the new owner threaten to tear the team apart.

title: My Father the Hero
text: A teenage girl on vacation in the Bahamas with her divorced father tries to impress a potential boyfriend by saying that her father is actually her lover.

title: Pure Formality, A
text: Onoff is a famous writer who hasn't published any new books for quite some time and has become a recluse. When he is picked up by the police one stormy night, without any identification, out of breath and running madly, without clear memory of recent events, the Inspector is suspicious. Through interrogatory dialectic, the head of this lonely, isolated, broken-down police station tries to establish what has happened, by delving into the mind of his writer-hero, and clearing up a mysterious killing.

title: Langoliers, The
text: Most of the passengers on an airplane disappear, and the remainder land the plane in a mysteriously barren airport.

title: Last Wedding, The
text: Pekka returns to his native village to attend a wedding. The village has lost its younger generations, and the movie tells the story of the last wedding in the village.

title: Last of the Dogmen
text: A Montana bounty hunter and an anthropologist discover a tribe of Native Americans living in a settlement isolated from the rest of the world.

title: Whisper of the Heart
text: A love story between a girl who loves reading books, and a boy who has previously checked out all of the library books she chooses.

title: Street Fighter II: The Animated Movie
text: Based on the legendary video game series. This anime classic follows Ryu, a talented fighter who may be the greatest in all of the world, and Bison, the evil mastermind searching for Ryu's talents.

title: Summer's Tale, A
text: A shy maths graduate takes a holiday in Dinard before starting his first job. He hopes his sort-of girlfriend will join him, but soon strikes up a friendship with another girl working in town. She in turn introduces him to a further young lady who fancies him. Thus the quiet young lad finds he is having to do some tricky juggling in territory new to him.

title: Late Shift, The
text: A dramatization of the rivalry between David Letterman and Jay Leno to over which of them would succeed Johnny Carson as the host of "The Tonight Show".

title: Pusher
text: A drug pusher grows increasingly desperate after a botched deal leaves him with a large debt to a ruthless drug lord.

title: Emma
text: Faithful, enchanting adaptation of Jane Austen's nineteenth-century tale of Emma Woodhouse--a clever young woman whose mischievous matchmaking schemes nearly end up jeopardizing her own shot at romance.

title: Boxer, The
text: Young Danny Flynn is released from prison 14 years after "taking the rap" for the IRA and tries to rebuild his life in his old Belfast neighborhood.

title: Gummo
text: Lonely residents of a tornado-stricken Ohio town wander the deserted landscape trying to fulfill their boring, nihilistic lives.

title: Nirvana
text: The main character Solo in Nirvana, a computer game developed by Jimi for release in 3 days, has gained self-awareness after a virus attack. Solo wants to be deleted. Jimi wants to find his ex.

title: Lion King II: Simba's Pride, The
text: Simba's daughter is the key to a resolution of a bitter feud between Simba's pride and the outcast pride led by the mate of Scar.

title: From the Earth to the Moon
text: Dramatized portrayal of the Apollo manned space program.

title: Beowulf
text: In a besieged land, Beowulf must battle against the hideous creature Grendel and his vengeance seeking mother.

title: RKO 281
text: Orson Welles produces his greatest film, Citizen Kane , despite the opposition of the film's de facto subject, William Randolph Hearst.

title: From Dusk Till Dawn 2: Texas Blood Money
text: Five career criminals gather in Mexico to pull off a bank heist. They soon realize that they are up against far more frightening creatures than the police pursuing them.

title: Gia
text: The story of the life of Gia Carangi, a top fashion model from the late 1970s, from her meteoric rise to the forefront of the modeling industry, to her untimely death.

title: Thursday
text: A former L.A. drug dealer has moved to Houston to make a new life for himself as a married architect. Everything falls apart when he is suddenly visited by one of his former cohorts who comes carrying heroin.

title: Who Am I?
text: A Secret Agent loses his memory after falling from a crashing helicopter. He is then chased by several other agency operatives, but he has no idea why.

title: Merlin
text: Legendary wizard Merlin tells his story of his war against Queen Mab of the Sidhe and his creation of Camelot.

title: Brave New World
text: In a futuristic totalitarian utopian society, babies are created through genetic engineering, everyone has a predestined place in society and their minds are conditioned to follow the rules. A tragic outsider jeopardizes the status quo.

title: Addams Family Reunion
text: The Addams Family goes on a search for their relatives.

title: Purgatory
text: An outlaw band rides into a town that is actually Purgatory, between Heaven and Hell.

title: Bleeder
text: Two stories for the price of one: Lenny works in a video shop and tries to get aquainted with the waitress Lea. Leo beats his pregnant wife, Louise, which is a VERY bad idea, as her brother, Louis, is a violent racist.

title: Dark Portals: The Chronicles of Vidocq
text: Paris, 1830: Vidocq is killed by a mirror masked man. A thief turned investigator, he was working on a case of men killed by lightning. His biographer tries to solve the case.

title: Candyman 3: Day of the Dead
text: The Candyman is back, trying to convince his descendent, an artist, to join him.

title: Batman/Superman Movie, The
text: Joker goes to Metropolis with an offer and plan to kill Superman for Lex Luthor while Batman pursues the clown to Superman's turf.

title: Neon Genesis Evangelion: The End of Evangelion
text: Concurrent theatrical ending of the TV series Shin seiki evangerion .

title: Style Wars
text: A documentary that exposes the rich growing subculture of hip-hop that was developing in New York City in the late '70s and early '80s, specifically focusing on graffiti art and breakdancing.

title: In July
text: A young, insecure teacher embarks on a journey through Europe to Turkey, where he wants to see a woman again whom he believes to be his fate.

title: Kirikou and the Sorceress
text: In a troubled African village, an unusual baby is born.

title: Taxi 2
text: Police inspector Emilien and his taxi-driver pal Daniel are back, this time on the tail of a group of Japanese yakuza.

title: If These Walls Could Talk 2
text: Trio of stories about lesbian couples in three different decades.

title: 10th Kingdom, The
text: A father and daughter are caught in a parallel universe where the great Queens Snow White, Cinderella and Riding Hood III have had their kingdoms fragmented by warring trolls, giants and goblins.

title: Wind Will Carry Us, The
text: Irreverent city engineer Behzad comes to a rural village in Iran to keep vigil for a dying relative. In the meanwhile the film follows his efforts to fit in with the local community and how he changes his own attitudes as a result.
Several women enter a science fiction author's life over the course of a few years, after the author has lost the woman he considers his one true love.

title: Bartleby
text: A clueless boss has no idea what to do with his mundane office worker whose refusal of duties only gets worse each passing minute.

title: Batman Beyond: Return of the Joker
text: The Joker is back with a vengeance, and Gotham's newest Dark Knight needs answers as he stands alone to face Gotham's most infamous Clown Prince of Crime.

title: Audition
text: A widower takes an offer to screen girls at a special audition, arranged for him by a friend to find him a new wife. The one he fancies is not who she appears to be after all.

title: Nine Lives of Tomas Katz, The
text: A man comes to London, uses a strange force to take over different men's identities and creates chaos.

title: Monday
text: A simple funeral turns a man's world topsy turvy.

title: Paradise Lost 2: Revelations
text: The case of the West Memphis Three, its questionable circumstances and the parties involved are followed up years later.

title: Asterix & Obelix: Mission Cleopatra
text: Astérix and Obélix go to Egypt to help architect Numérobis who is building a palace for Cleopatra.

title: Daria: Is It Fall Yet?
text: This animated made-for-TV movie, based on MTV's hit "Daria," explores the summer vacation of Daria and her classmates at Lawndale High.

title: Late Night Shopping
text: An upbeat, oddball, after-hours comedy about the ups and downs of sex and shelf-stacking in the 21st century.
Roger Maris and Mickey Mantle race to break Babe Ruth's single-season home run record.

title: Joint Security Area
text: After a shooting incident at the North/South Korean border/DMZ leaves 2 North Korean soldiers dead, a neutral Swiss/Swedish team investigates, what actually happened.

title: Ripley's Game
text: A dying family man in need of money is persuaded to assassinate a European crime boss.

title: Jalla! Jalla!
text: Roro, a foreign worker in Swedish parks, loves his girlfriend but is about to marry another girl to prevent her from being sent back to Lebanon. Roros best friend, Måns, has his own problems: He has serious problems getting an erection...

title: Teknolust
text: Academy-AwardÂ winner Tilda Swinton plays four roles in this award-winning Sci-Fi about Rosetta Stone and her three Self-Replicating Automatons,  which she cloned from her own DNA.

title: Accidental Spy, The
text: At a Hong Kong shopping center, Buck Yuen's  intuition warns him. He saves a robbery's loot and gets on television, ends up in Istanbul via South Korea, and accidentally becomes a spy. Fortunately, he knows Kung Fu.

title: Darkness
text: A teenage girl moves into a remote country house with her family, only to discover that their gloomy new home has a horrifying past that threatens to destroy the family.

title: Blood: The Last Vampire
text: Saya is a Japanese vampire slayer whose next mission is in a high school on a US military base in 1960s Japan, where she poses as a student. She uses a katana/samurai sword to kill vampires.

title: Blueberry
text: In 1870, after a brutal run-in with an outlaw in a brothel, Mike Blueberry becomes marshal in Arizona where he keeps the peace between whites and Apaches, but an influx of gold-hunters threatens to lead to violence.

title: American Psycho II: All American Girl
text: A girl named Rachael Newman has developed a taste for murder and will stop at nothing to become a college professor's assistant.

title: Ali G Indahouse
text: Ali G unwittingly becomes a pawn in the Chancellor's plot to overthrow the Prime Minister of Great Britain. However, Ali is embraced by the nation as a voice of the youth, making the PM and his government more popular than ever.

title: Dead or Alive 2: Tôbôsha
text: Two contract killers cross paths in the middle of the same job and realize they are childhood friends.

title: Cube 2: Hypercube
text: Eight strangers awaken with no memory, in a puzzling cube-shaped room where the laws of physics do not always apply.

title: Pulse
text: Two groups of people discover evidence that suggests spirits may be trying to invade the human world through the Internet.

title: Dog Days
text: In the tomb-like quiet of their ranch-style purgatory, a divorced husband and wife fight a wordless war while mourning an unspeakable mutual loss. A sadistic lover's ritual humiliation spawns both tenderness and revenge.

title: My Sassy Girl
text: A young man sees a drunk, cute woman standing too close to the tracks at a metro station in Seoul and pulls her back. She ends up getting him into trouble repeatedly after that, starting on the train.

title: Nothing
text: After a terrible day, two good friends and housemates find the outside world converted into a featureless and empty white void.

title: Undertaking Betty
text: A woman, whose husband is cheating on her, and an undertaker, who has been in love with her since their childhood, decide to fake her death so they can be together.

title: Dead or Alive: Final
text: The ace cop of a totalitarian police force and a drifting android play their parts in a post-apocalyptic society. They are destined to fight. Their encounter will change them forever.

title: Fubar
text: Headbangers Terry and Dean explore the depths of friendship, and the art and science of drinking beer like a man.

title: Happiness of the Katakuris, The
text: A family moves to the country to run a rustic mountain inn when, to their horror, the customers begin befalling sudden and unlikely fates.

title: Dead End
text: Christmas Eve. On his way to his in-laws with his family, Frank Harrington decides to try a shortcut, for the first time in 20 years. It turns out to be the biggest mistake of his life.

title: Sympathy for Mr. Vengeance
text: A recently laid off factory worker kidnaps his former boss' friend's daughter, hoping to use the ransom money to pay for his sister's kidney transplant.

title: Jesus Christ Vampire Hunter
text: Kung-Fu Action / Comedy / Horror / Musical about the second coming.

title: Suicide Club
text: A detective is trying to find the cause of a string of suicides.

title: Battlestar Galactica
text: Following the destruction of the Twelve Colonies of Kobol by the Cylons, a rag-tag fugitive fleet of the last remnants of mankind flees the pursuing Cylons while simultaneously searching for their true home: Earth.

title: Sound of Thunder, A
text: A single mistake in the past, by a time travel company in the future, has devastating and unforeseen consequences.

title: Lion King 1½, The
text: Timon the meerkat and Pumbaa the warthog retell the story of The Lion King  from their own perspective.

title: Oasis
text: An irresponsible and childish ex-con befriends a girl with cerebral palsy and develops a progressively stronger bond with her.

title: Remember Me
text: In the dysfunctional Italian middle-class family Ristuccia, the middle-aged executive Carlo has a stalled life without passion, bored in his work and having a monotonous life with his wife Giulia. Giulia is a frustrated and hysterical woman because she gave up of being an actress in her youth to dedicate to the family. Their needy son Paolo feels lost and rejected, trying to find who he is and flirting with a schoolmate. Their seventeen years old daughter Valentina is decided to work in a television show, and is fighting to have an audition. When Carlo meets his former sweetheart Alessia in a class reunion, they confess to each other that their marriages are in crisis and both feel passion arising again. Meanwhile Giulia is invited to an audition in a stage production and to participate of a play. Paolo tries to make friends using marijuana in his birthday party, and Valentina has sex with different guys trying to be a dancer of the famous TV show 'Ali Babbi'. Their relationships change when Carlo has an accident.

title: Animatrix, The
text: A collection of nine short films featuring stories related to The Matrix .

title: Brown Bunny, The
text: Professional motorcycle racer Bud Clay heads from New Hampshire to California to race again. Along the way he meets various needy women who provide him with the cure to his own loneliness, but only a certain woman from his past will truly satisfy him.

title: Ju-on: The Curse
text: A teacher visits the house of one of his students after the boy goes missing, only to have a horrifying excuse for his absence from school.
The events leading up to an 11:14 p.m. car crash, from five very different perspectives.

title: Tremors 4: The Legend Begins
text: A prequel to Tremors , this movie tells us about how the town of Perfection, Nevada became founded and how they defended it against the Graboids with the help of Burt Gummer's ancestor, Hiram.

title: Bring It On Again
text: When new students can't get onto their college cheerleading team, they form their own squad and prepare for a cheer off.

title: Crimson Rivers 2: Angels of the Apocalypse
text: Pierre Niemans faces the threat of the apocalypse while investigating a series of ritual murders.

title: And Starring Pancho Villa as Himself
text: Hollywood makes a deal with Mexican revolutionary Pancho Villa to film his war and recreate his life.

title: Nicotina
text: A real-time dark comedy about a science geek who tangles with a clutch of Russian gangsters after he delivers them the wrong computer disk.

title: Battle Royale 2: Requiem
text: Three years after the failure of the last BR program, a second act is forged and a class of students are sent to an island with one objective: kill international terrorist Shuya Nanahara.

title: In Hell
text: A man must survive a prison where hardened criminals battle to the death for the wardens' entertainment.

title: Lemony Snicket's A Series of Unfortunate Events
text: When a massive fire kills their parents, three children are delivered to the custody of cousin and stage actor Count Olaf, who is secretly plotting to steal their parents' vast fortune.

title: Helen of Troy
text: The abduction of beautiful Helen, wife of Spartan King Menelaus, by Paris of Troy triggers a long war.

title: Green Butchers, The
text: 2 Danish friends are tired of their employer and open their own butcher shop. An electrician accidentally dies in the freezer and he's sold as marinated chicken and business picks up. What happens when they run out of "chicken"?

title: Very Long Engagement, A
text: Tells the story of a young woman's relentless search for her fiancé, who has disappeared from the trenches of the Somme during World War One.

title: Last Life in the Universe
text: A suicidal, obsessively compulsive Japanese librarian is forced to lie low in Thailand with a pot-smoking woman coping with the recent loss of her sister.

title: Ghost in the Shell 2: Innocence
text: In the year 2032, Batô, a cyborg detective for the anti-terrorist unit Public Security Section 9, investigates the case of a female robot--one created solely for sexual pleasure--who slaughtered her owner.

title: Cat Returns, The
text: After helping a cat, a seventeen-year-old girl finds herself involuntarily engaged to a cat Prince in a magical world where her only hope of freedom lies with a dapper cat statuette come to life.

title: Twilight Samurai, The
text: As the feudal Japan era draws to a close, a widower samurai experiences difficulty balancing clan loyalties, 2 young daughters, an aged mother, and the sudden reappearance of his childhood sweetheart.

title: Facing Windows
text: Overburdened and stuck in a greying marriage, Giovanna takes to caring for the Jewish Holocaust survivor her husband brings home. As she begins to reflect on her life, she turns to the man who lives across from her ...

title: Ginger Snaps: Unleashed
text: Ginger's sister Brigitte, now a werewolf herself, must try to find a cure for her blood lust before the next full moon while hiding out in a rehab clinic from a relentless werewolf.

title: Salem's Lot
text: Writer Ben Mears  returns to his childhood home of Jerusalem's Lot and discovers that it is being terrorized by vampires.

title: Comic Book: The Movie
text: The relationship between Hollywood and comic book culture is lambasted in this mockumentary as a beloved heroic character is rung through the studio system.

title: Intimate Strangers
text: A Frenchwoman tells her marital troubles to a man she mistakes for a psychiatrist, and soon they form an unusual relationship.

title: Down to the Bone
text: A woman stuck in a stale marriage struggles to raise her children and manage her secret drug habit. But when winter comes to her small town, her balancing act begins to come crashing down.

title: Ju-on: The Grudge
text: A mysterious and vengeful spirit marks and pursues anybody who dares enter the house in which it resides.

title: Old Boy
text: After being kidnapped and imprisoned for fifteen years, Oh Dae-Su is released, only to find that he must find his captor in five days.

title: Red Lights
text: Antoine and Helene drive to South France to return their kids from a holiday camp. The traffic is dense and the atmosphere growingly tense
column9: he is an alcoholic and becomes increasingly drunk the more often they stop. After a fierce discussion they split and both have to face great danger during the night.

title: Ginger Snaps Back: The Beginning
text: Set in 19th Century Canada, Brigette and her sister Ginger take refuge in a Traders' Fort which later becomes under siege by some savage werewolves.

title: One Missed Call
text: People mysteriously start receiving voicemail messages from their future selves, foretelling their deaths.

title: Jacket, The
text: A Gulf war veteran is wrongly sent to a mental institution for insane criminals, where he becomes the object of a doctor's experiments, and his life is completely affected by them.

title: Millions
text: Ethics, being human and the soul come to the fore when a 7-year old finds a bag of Pounds just days before the currency is switched to Euros and learns what we are really made of.

title: Starship Troopers 2: Hero of the Federation
text: In the sequel to Paul Verhoeven's loved/reviled sci-fi film, a group of troopers taking refuge in an abandoned outpost after fighting alien bugs, failing to realize that more danger lays in wait.

title: Ong-Bak: The Thai Warrior
text: When the head of a statue sacred to a village is stolen, a young martial artist goes to the big city and finds himself taking on the underworld to retrieve it.

title: Infernal Affairs 2
text: In this prequel to Mou gaan dou , Chan Wing Yan has just become an undercover cop in the triads while Lau Kin Ming joins the police force. Both the triads and the police find an enemy in a rival crime boss.

title: Sea Inside, The
text: The factual story of Spaniard Ramon Sampedro, who fought a 28 year campaign in favour of euthanasia and his own right to die.

title: Spanglish
text: A woman and her daughter emigrate from Mexico for a better life in America, where they start working for a family where the patriarch is a newly celebrated chef with an insecure wife.

title: Chorus, The
text: The new teacher at a severely administered boys' boarding school works to positively affect the students' lives through music.

title: Saints and Soldiers
text: Four American soldiers and one Brit fighting in Europe during World War II struggle to return to Allied territory after being separated from U.S. forces during the historic Malmedy Massacre.

title: Story of the Weeping Camel, The
text: When a Mongolian nomadic family's newest camel colt is rejected by its mother, a musician is needed for a ritual to change her mind.

title: Interpreter, The
text: Political intrigue and deception unfold inside the United Nations, where a U.S. Secret Service agent is assigned to investigate an interpreter who overhears an assassination plot.

title: Open Water
text: Based on the true story of two scuba divers accidentally stranded in shark infested waters after their tour boat has left.

title: Touch of Pink
text: A gay Canadian living in London has his perfectly crafted life upset when his devoutly Muslim mother comes to visit.

title: Slasher
text: A documentary on a stereotypically shady used car salesman, one who convinces customers to buy vehicles that others have deemed unfit for sale.

title: Bobby Jones, Stroke of Genius
text: Jim Caviezel stars as golf legend Bobby Jones, the icon who retired from competition at the tender age of 28.

title: Layer Cake
text: A successful cocaine dealer gets two tough assignments from his boss on the eve of his planned early retirement.

title: Return, The
text: In the Russian wilderness, two brothers face a range of new, conflicting emotions when their father - a man they know only through a single photograph - resurfaces.

title: Flight of the Phoenix
text: Survivors of a plane crash in the Mongolian desert work together to build a new plane.

title: Mean Creek
text: When a teen is bullied, his brother and friends lure the bully into the woods to seek revenge.

title: Ring Two, The
text: 6 months after the incidents involving the lethal videotape, new clues prove that there is a new evil lurking in the darkness.

title: Corporation, The
text: Documentary that looks at the concept of the corporation throughout recent history up to its present-day dominance.

title: Yes Men, The
text: Anti-corporate activists travel from conference to conference, impersonating member of the World Trade Organization.

title: Azumi
text: Raised to deal in cold blooded death, the teenage assassin girl Azumi must defeat three evil warlords while also battling her own heart.

title: In My Father's Den
text: A disillusioned war journalist's return home is blighted when he becomes implicated in the mysterious disappearance of a teenage girl he has befriended.

title: Tae Guk Gi: The Brotherhood of War
text: When two brothers are forced to fight in the Korean War, the elder decides to take the riskiest missions if it will help shield the younger from battle.

title: Metallica: Some Kind of Monster
text: The iconic metal band struggles for two years to create their album St. Anger, dealing with alcoholism, the loss of their bass player, and the challenge of working with a psychotherapist.

title: Born into Brothels
text: Two documentary filmmakers chronicle their time in Sonagchi, Calcutta and the relationships they developed with children of prostitutes who work the city's notorious red light district.

title: DiG!
text: A documentary on the once-promising American rock bands The Brian Jonestown Massacre and The Dandy Warhols, and the friendship/rivalry between their respective founders, Anton Newcombe and Courtney Taylor.

title: Riding Giants
text: Documentary detailing the origins and history of surf culture.

title: What the #$*! Do We Know!?
text: A fictional photographer's quest to spiritually rediscover herself is interspersed with documentary footage of scientists and theologians discussing the philosophical aspects of quantum physics.

title: Scanner Darkly, A
text: An undercover cop in a not-too-distant future becomes involved with a dangerous new drug and begins to lose his own identity as a result.

title: Casshern
text: Live-action sci-fi movie based on a 1973 Japanese animé of the same name . Theme song by Utada Hikaru.

title: Outfoxed: Rupert Murdoch's War on Journalism
text: Documentary on reported Conservative bias of the Rupert Murdoch-owned Fox News Channel , which promotes itself as "Fair and Balanced". Material includes interviews with former FNC employees and the inter-office memos they provided.

title: Million Dollar Baby
text: A determined woman works with a hardened boxing trainer to become a professional.

title: Gozu
text: A yakuza enforcer is ordered to secretly drive his beloved colleague to be assassinated. But when the colleague unceremoniously disappears en route, the trip that follows is a twisted, surreal and horrifying experience.

title: Hotel Rwanda
text: Paul Rusesabagina, a hotel manager, houses over a thousand Tutsi refugees during their struggle against the Hutu militia in Rwanda, Africa.

title: Charlie and the Chocolate Factory
text: A young boy wins a tour through the most magnificent chocolate factory in the world, led by the world's most unusual candy maker.

title: 3-Iron
text: A transient young man breaks into empty homes to partake of the vacationing residents' lives for a few days.

title: Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou, The
text: With a plan to exact revenge on a mythical shark that killed his partner, Oceanographer Steve Zissou  rallies a crew that includes his estranged wife, a journalist, and a man who may or may not be his son.

title: Aviator, The
text: A biopic depicting the early years of legendary Director and aviator Howard Hughes' career from the late 1920s to the mid 1940s.

title: Phantom of the Opera, The
text: A young soprano becomes the obsession of a disfigured and murderous musical genius who lives beneath the Paris Opéra House.

title: Beyond the Sea
text: A swooning study of "Mack the Knife" singer Bobby Darin and specifically his relationship with wife Sandra Dee.

title: Woodsman, The
text: A child molester returns to his hometown after 12 years in prison and attempts to start a new life.

title: In Good Company
text: A middle-aged ad exec is faced with a new boss who's nearly half his age... and who also happens to be sleeping with his daughter.

title: Meet the Fockers
text: All hell breaks loose when the Byrnes family meets the Focker family for the first time.

title: Assassination of Richard Nixon, The
text: Based on real life events, Assassination is set in 1974 and centers on a businessman who decides to take extreme measures to achieve his American dream.

title: Love Song for Bobby Long, A
text: A headstrong young woman returns to New Orleans after the death of her estranged mother.

title: Merchant of Venice, The
text: In 16th century Venice, when a merchant must default on a large loan from an abused Jewish moneylender for a friend with romantic ambitions, the bitterly vengeful creditor demands a gruesome payment instead.

title: Fat Albert
text: Fat Albert and the Cosby Kids come to life and step out of their animated, inner-city Philadelphia world.

title: Keys to the House, The
text: Meeting his handicapped son for the first time, a young father attempts to forge a relationship with the teenager.

title: In the Realms of the Unreal
text: A documentary on Henry Darger, visionary artist, janitor, and novelist.

title: White Noise
text: An architect's desire to speak with his wife from beyond the grave becomes an obsession with supernatural repercussions.

title: Upside of Anger, The
text: When her husband unexpectedly disappears, a sharp-witted suburban wife and her daughters juggle their mom's romantic dilemmas and family dynamics.

title: Little Miss Marker
text: A gruff bookie's life is turned upside-down when he gets a 6-year-old kid as collateral for a bet.

title: Sweet Liberty
text: After selling the rights of his book to a movie production company, a writer finds himself fighting the many egos and varying views around him.

title: I Remember Mama
text: A young writer recalls her ups and downs of growing up as one of four children to Norwegian immigrant parents in 1910s San Francisco.

title: Smooth Talk
text: A free-spirited 15-year-old girl flirts with a dangerous stranger in the Northern California suburbs and must prepare herself for the frightening and traumatic consequences.

title: Out Cold
text: Sunny is married to Ernie and their marriage is on the rocks. One evening drunken Ernie and Dave have a fight which results in Ernie getting knocked out in the fridge where he dies during the night.

title: Man Trouble
text: A sleazy but affable guard dog trainer is blackmailed to steal a manuscript for a tell-all book from one of his clients.

title: Battles Without Honor & Humanity
text: During the violent chaos of post-War Japanese black market, a young gangster called Shozo Hirono has to keep up with the rapid shifts of power between unscrupulous bosses.

title: Stander
text: The life and career of Andre Stander, a South African police officer turned bank robber.

title: Imaginary Heroes
text: Members of a dysfunctional family react differently to the suicide of the eldest son.

title: Sergeant York
text: A marksman is drafted in World War I and ends up becoming one of the most celebrated war heroes.

title: Ruby & Quentin
text: A tough criminal is arrested after hiding the loot from a Paris armored truck robbery. A talkative dimwit befriends him in prison and escapes with him - chased by police and his evil crime boss.

title: Wizards
text: On a post-apocalyptic Earth, a wizard and his faire folk comrades fight an evil wizard who's using technology in his bid for conquest.

title: Life and Death of Peter Sellers, The
text: The feature adaptation of Roger Lewis' book about the actor best remembered as Inspector Clouseau in the Pink Panther movies.

title: Appleseed
text: In a utopian society created at the end of the third world war, a female warrior who has been plucked from the badlands begins to see cracks in this new facade. And what does this community have planned for the rest of humankind?

title: Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh, The
text: In this collection of animated shorts based on the stories and characters by A.A. Milne, Winnie the Pooh, a honey-loving teddy bear, embarks on some eccentric adventures.

title: Elektra
text: Elektra the warrior survives a near-death experience, becomes an assassin-for-hire, and tries to protect her two latest targets, a single father and his young daughter, from a group of supernatural assassins.

title: Racing Stripes
text: An abandoned zebra grows up believing he is a racehorse, and, with the help of his barnyard friends and a teenage girl, sets out to achieve his dream of racing with thoroughbreds.

title: Coach Carter
text: Controversy surrounds high school basketball coach Ken Carter after he benches his entire team for breaking their academic contract with him.

title: Boys Town
text: When a death row prisoner tells him he wouldn't have led a life of crime if only he had had one friend as a child, Father Edward Flanagan decides to start a home for young boys.

title: Gold Diggers of 1935
text: Romantic antics abound among the guests at a luxury hotel, including a stage director, an eccentric millionaire, and the daughter of a financial backer.

title: Rocco and His Brothers
text: Having recently been uprooted to Milan, Rocco and his four brothers each look for a new way in life when a prostitute comes between Rocco and his brother Simone.

title: Memories of Murder
text: In a small Korean province in 1986, two detectives struggle with the case of multiple young women being found raped and murdered by an unknown culprit.

title: Chase, The
text: Escaped convict Jack Hammond takes a woman hostage and sets off for the Mexican border with the police hot on his tail.

title: Downfall
text: Traudl Junge, the final secretary for Adolf Hitler, tells of the Nazi dictator's final days in his Berlin bunker at the end of WWII.

title: Assault on Precinct 13
text: A police sergeant must rally the cops and prisoners together to protect themselves on New Year's Eve, just as corrupt policeman surround the station with the intent of killing all to keep their deception in the ranks.

title: Are We There Yet?
text: To impress a foxy divorcee, ladies' man Nick offers to take her kids on an extended road trip, unaware of the torture he's in for.

title: Alone in the Dark
text: A detective of the paranormal slowly unravels mysterious events with deadly results.

title: Hide and Seek
text: As a widower tries to piece together his life in the wake of his wife's suicide, his daughter finds solace, at first, in her imaginary friend.

title: Boogeyman
text: A young man tries to deal with the childhood terror that has never stopped haunting him.

title: Wedding Date, The
text: Single-girl anxiety causes Kat Ellis to hire a male escort to pose as her boyfriend at her sister's wedding. Her plan, an attempt to dupe her ex-fiancé, who dumped her a couple years prior, proves to be her undoing.

title: Rory O'Shea Was Here
text: When the kinetic Rory moves into his room in the Carrigmore Residential Home for the Disabled, his effect on the home is immediate. Most telling is his friendship with Michael, a young man with cerebral palsy and nearly unintelligible speech. Somehow, Rory understands Michael, and encourages him to experience life outside the confines of home.

title: Nobody Knows
text: In a small Tokyo apartment, twelve-year-old Akira must care for his younger siblings after their mother leaves them and shows no sign of returning.

title: Employee of the Month
text: It just isn't David's day. First he gets fired at the bank, then his fiancee breaks up and throws him out of the house. The bank gets robbed and he gets shot. Twists follow.

title: Marriage of Maria Braun, The
text: Maria marries Hermann Braun in the last days of World War II, only for him to go missing in the war. Alone, Maria puts to use her beauty and ambition in order to find prosperity during Germany's "economic miracle" of the 1950s.

title: Trou, Le
text: Distrust and uncertainty arise when four long-term inmates cautiously induct a new prisoner into their elaborate prison-break scheme.

title: Double Dragon
text: Two brothers have half of a powerful ancient Chinese talisman. An evil gang leader has the other half, and determines to get the brothers' half and have a complete medallion so he can gain absolute power.

title: Hands Off the Loot
text: An aging, world-weary gangster is double-crossed and forced out of retirement when his best friend is kidnapped and their stash of eight stolen gold bars demanded as ransom.

title: Purple Butterfly
text: Cynthia is a young Chinese woman in love with Itami, a Japanese man about to be sent home for military service.

title: El Cid
text: The fabled Spanish hero Rodrigo Diaz de Vivar  overcomes a family vendetta and court intrigue to defend Christian Spain against the Moors.

title: Howl's Moving Castle
text: When an unconfident young woman is cursed with an old body by a spiteful witch, her only chance of breaking the spell lies with a self-indulgent yet insecure young wizard and his companions in his legged, walking castle.

title: Steamboy
text: In 1860s Britain, a boy inventor finds himself caught in the middle of a deadly conflict over a revolutionary advance in steam power.

title: Gorgeous
text: A romantic girl travels to Hong Kong in search of certain love but instead meets a kind-hearted professional fighter for whom she begins to fall instead.

title: Hitch
text: A smooth-talking man falls for a hardened columnist while helping a shy accountant woo a beautiful heiress.

title: Uncle Nino
text: A distant, slightly dysfunctional family is brought closer together when the father's long-estranged Uncle Nino comes from Italy to Chicago for a surprise visit.

title: Bride & Prejudice
text: A modern adaptation of Jane Austen's classic novel, Pride and Prejudice, that features the lives of four unmarried daughters in an Indian family.

title: Constantine
text: Supernatural exorcist and demonologist John Constantine helps a policewoman prove her sister's death was not a suicide, but something more.

title: Son of the Mask
text: Tim Avery, an aspiring cartoonist, finds himself in a predicament when his dog stumbles upon the mask of Loki. Then after conceiving an infant son "born of the mask", he discovers just how looney child raising can be.

title: Because of Winn-Dixie
text: A mischievous dog befriends a lonely young girl in a new town and helps her make new friends.

title: Turtles Can Fly
text: Near the Iraqi-Turkish border on the eve of an American invasion, refugee children like 13-year-old Kak , gauge and await their fate.

title: Bunny Lake Is Missing
text: A woman reports that her young daughter is missing, but there seems to be no evidence that she ever existed.

title: Night Watch
text: A fantasy-thriller set in present-day Moscow where the respective forces that control daytime and nighttime do battle.

title: Sons of the Desert
text: When Stan and Ollie trick their wives into thinking that they are taking a medicinal cruise while they're actually going to a convention, the wives find out the truth the hard way.

title: Man of the House
text: A Texas Ranger must protect a group of cheerleaders who have witnessed a murder.

title: Kung Fu Hustle
text: In Shanghai, China in the 1940s, a wannabe gangster aspires to join the notorious "Axe Gang" while residents of a housing complex exhibit extraordinary powers in defending their turf.

title: Zelary
text: A nurse is part of the resistance in 1940s Czechoslovakia. She is discovered and must find a place to hide. A patient whose life she saved, from a remote mountain village where time stopped 150 years ago, agrees to hide her as his wife.

title: Dr. Giggles
text: A madman who believes he's a doctor comes to the town where his crazy father was killed, and soon begins murdering people and becoming infatuated with a teenage girl who has a heart condition.

title: Seven-Per-Cent Solution, The
text: To treat his friend's cocaine induced delusions, Watson lures Sherlock Holmes to Sigmund Freud.

title: Three Musketeers, The
text: A young swordsman comes to Paris and faces villains, romance, adventure and intrigue with three Musketeer friends.

title: Royal Flash
text: Ne'er-do-well Captain Harry Flashman  is coerced by Otto Von Bismarck  into impersonating a Prince.

title: Control
text: A tale about a strange young man, Bulcsú, the fellow inspectors on his team, all without exception likable characters, a rival ticket inspection team and racing along the tracks - and a tale about love.

title: Germany Year Zero
text: A young German boy faces the problems of the tough life in the immediate post-WWII Berlin.

title: Tyler Perry's Diary of a Mad Black Woman
text: A couple's seemingly solid marriage begins to crumble when the wife discovers that her husband intends to divorce her.

title: Cursed
text: A werewolf loose in Los Angeles changes the lives of three young adults who, after being mauled by the beast, learn they must kill it in order to avoid becoming werewolves themselves.

title: Pacifier, The
text: Having recovered from wounds received in a failed rescue operation, Navy SEAL Shane Wolfe is handed a new assignment: Protect the five Plummer kids from enemies of their recently deceased father -- a government scientist whose top-secret experiment remains in the kids' house.

title: Be Cool
text: Disenchanted with the movie industry, Chili Palmer tries the music industry, meeting and romancing a widow of a music executive on the way.

title: Gunner Palace
text: American soldiers of the 2/3 Field Artillery, a group known as the "Gunners," tell of their experiences in Baghdad during the Iraq War. Holed up in a bombed out pleasure palace built by Sadaam Hussein, the soldiers endured hostile situations some four months after President George W. Bush declared the end of major combat operations in the country.

title: Hostage
text: When a family is held hostage, former hostage negotiator Jeff Talley arrives at the scene. Talley's own family is kidnapped and Talley must decide which is more important: saving a family he doesn't even know or saving his own family.

title: Robots
text: In a robot world, a young idealistic inventor travels to the big city to join his inspiration's company, only to find himself opposing its sinister new management.

title: Class Action
text: An attorney representing a traumatized accident victim finds that his opponent is a very familiar defense attorney - his own daughter.

title: Cat and the Canary, The
text: Relatives of an eccentric millionaire gather in his spooky mansion on the 20th anniversary of his death for the reading of his will.

title: Oh, God! You Devil
text: George Burns returns as God, and as Satan. They battle over the soul of a young rock star who is willing to sell his soul to the devil.

title: Agony and the Ecstasy, The
text: The biographical story of Michelangelo's troubles while painting the Sistine Chapel at the urging of Pope Julius II.

title: Twentieth Century
text: A flamboyant Broadway impresario who has fallen on hard times tries to get his former lover, now a Hollywood diva, to return and resurrect his failing career.

title: Elevator to the Gallows
text: A self-assured businessman murders his employer, the husband of his mistress, which unintentionally provokes an ill-fated chain of events.

title: Cube Zero
text: A young programmer whose job is to watch over the reality-warping Cube defies orders to rescue an innocent mother trapped in one of its rooms.

title: Julia
text: At the behest of an old and dear friend, playwright Lillian Hellman undertakes a dangerous mission to smuggle funds into Nazi Germany.

title: Stealing Rembrandt
text: Mick and Tom are an unlikely father-son team of petty thieves. They've been hired to steal a painting from a museum. By accident, they steal the wrong painting: Denmark's only original Rembrandt masterpiece, worth millions.

title: Ice Princess
text: With the help of her coach, her mom, and the boy who drives the Zamboni machine, nothing can stop Casey  from realizing her dream to be a champion figure skater.

title: Melinda and Melinda
text: Two alternating stories, one comedy and the other tragedy, about Melinda's attempts to straighten out her life.

title: Milk and Honey
text: Over one night in New York City, lives of disparate strangers intersect by fate and circumstance.

title: Miss Congeniality 2: Armed and Fabulous
text: After Heather Burns  and Stan Fields  are kidnapped, Gracie Hart  goes undercover in Las Vegas, Nevada to find them.

title: Guess Who
text: A young woman, Theresa, brings her boyfriend, Simon, home to meet her parents and surprise them with the news of their engagement. Another surprise: Simon is white.

title: D.E.B.S.
text: Plaid-skirted schoolgirls are groomed by a secret government agency to become the newest members of the elite national-defense group, D.E.B.S.

title: League of Ordinary Gentlemen, A
text: Filmmaker Christopher Browne documents the mission of a group of middle-aged bowlers as they attempt to revitalize the sport and get the television-watching public interested in it again.

title: Incident at Loch Ness
text: A documentary exploring the myth of the Loch Ness monster.

title: Call Northside 777
text: Chicago reporter P.J. McNeal re-opens a decade-old murder case.

title: Sword of Doom, The
text: Through his unconscionable actions against others, a sociopath samurai builds a trail of vendettas that follow him closely.

title: 800 Bullets
text: Julián Torralba is a former movie stuntman in Almeria, Spain. He and several of his colleagues, who once made a living in American Westerns shot in Spain, now are reduced to doing stunt shows for minuscule audiences on the decaying set built for those old Westerns. Julián wrestles with dark memories of the death of his son, also a stuntman, and with estrangement from his daughter-in-law Laura and her son Carlos. Carlos, a young boy, becomes intrigued with his late father's life and runs away to join Julián and his band of has-beens. There Carlos is initiated into the rambunctious life of these hard-drinking faux cowboys. But when Laura, a powerful executive looking for a new site for a tourist resort, learns that Carlos has joined the hated Julián, she moves to destroy even this remnant of Julián's once-proud career. Julián and the cowboys decide to fight back the only way they know how.

title: If Looks Could Kill
text: Michael has to take summer class in French, a class trip to France, to graduate high school. He is, however, mistaken for an agent and people try to kill him. There are 007 style cars, cuties, crooks etc.

title: Greedy
text: Rich, old uncle Joe is surrounded by relatives waiting/hoping for him to die while trying to look good and backstabbing the competition. What should he do?

title: Pom Poko
text: A community of magical shape-shifting raccoon dogs struggle to prevent their forest home from being destroyed by urban development.

title: Knockin' on Heaven's Door
text: Two terminally ill patients escape from a hospital, steal a car and rush towards the sea.

title: We're No Angels
text: Three Devil's Island escapees hide out in the house of a kindly merchant and repay his kindness by helping him and his family out of several crises.

title: Touch of Zen, A
text: A lady fugitive on the run from corrupt government officials is joined in her endeavors by an unambitious painter and skilled Buddhist monks.

title: Walker
text: An unconventional retelling of the life of William Walker, a 19th century American mercenary leader who became the president of Nicaragua.

title: Memories
text: An animated science fiction anthology from the visionary anime director, Katsuhiro Otomo.

title: Wild Parrots of Telegraph Hill, The
text: A homeless musician finds meaning to his life when he starts a friendship with dozens of parrots.

title: Ballad of Jack and Rose, The
text: A father and daughter isolated on an island off the East Coast and living on a once-thriving commune grapple with the limits of family and sexuality.

title: Sin City
text: An exploration of the dark and miserable Basin City and three of its residents, all of whom are caught up in violent corruption.

title: Beauty Shop
text: A determined hairstylist  competes with her former boss  after opening her own business in Atlanta.

title: Sahara
text: Master explorer Dirk Pitt goes on the adventure of a lifetime of seeking out a lost Civil War battleship known as the "Ship of Death" in the deserts of West Africa while helping a WHO doctor being hounded by a ruthless dictator.

title: Fever Pitch
text: Lindsay is stuck in the middle of her relationship with Ben and his passion for the Boston Red Sox.

title: Not on the Lips
text: A romantic musical story having the vibes both France and USA.

title: Electra Glide in Blue
text: Bored with his highway traffic duties, Arizona motorcycle patrolman John Wintergreen is assigned to Homicide where his polite investigative style irks his macho boss.

title: Special Day, A
text: Two neighbors, a persecuted journalist and a resigned housewife, meet during Hitler's visit to Italy in May 1938.

title: Man Who Planted Trees, The
text: The story of a shepherd's single handed quest to re-forest a barren valley.

title: Tanguy
text: Tanguy is 28 years old and still living with his parents. They think it's time he moves out. He doesn't, so they hatch a plan...

title: National Lampoon's Lady Killers
text: A pair of losers marry two elderly sisters, thinking they'll inherit their fortune and Beverly Hills estate.

title: Little Girl Who Lives Down the Lane, The
text: 13-year-old Rynn Jacobs lives alone in a high-class Quebec small town, but unknown to the neighbors, she is leading a secret and dangerous life.

title: Ringu 0: Bâsudei
text: In this prequel to Ring, a young Sadako becomes an actress in hopes of escaping her troubled past. But strange visions and terrifying powers begin to manifest...

title: Brothers
text: Two brothers must negotiate changing roles and shifting family dynamics when one is sent to war in Afghanistan.

title: Maidens in Uniform
text: At an all-girls boarding school, Manuela falls in love with a teacher, to terrific consequences.

title: With Six You Get Eggroll
text: Two widowed people fall in love and marry, unprepared for the hostile reactions of their children.

title: Holiday
text: A village postman with no sense of humour delivers his mail via bicycle on the day the travelling fair comes to town. He is disrupted by a short film about US speed and efficiency and the playful teasing of the village folk.

title: Ivan's Childhood
text: During WWII, Soviet orphan Ivan Bondarev strikes up a friendship with three sympathetic Soviet officers while working as a scout behind the German lines.

title: Trip to the Moon, A
text: A group of astronomers go on an expedition to the Moon.

title: Ascent, The
text: Two Soviet partisans on a mission to gather food contend with the winter cold, the occupying Germans, and their own psyches.

title: Carrie
text: Carrie White is a lonely and painfully shy teenage girl with telekinetic powers who is slowly pushed to the edge of insanity by frequent bullying from both her classmates and her domineering, religious mother.

title: Boccaccio '70
text: Inspired by Boccaccio's novellas, each episode focuses on sex, love and seduction in Italy in the 1960s, an era of economic growth and major cultural changes.

title: Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy, The
text: Mere seconds before the Earth is to be demolished by an alien construction crew, journeyman Arthur Dent is swept off the planet by his friend Ford Prefect, a researcher penning a new edition of "The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy."

title: Amityville Horror, The
text: Newlyweds are terrorized by demonic forces after moving into a large house that was the site of a grisly mass murder a year before.

title: Mutant Aliens
text: Marooned by design in a strange asteroid inhabited by bizarre creatures, a left-for-dead astronaut miraculously heads back to Earth with a band of abominable mutant aliens to tie up some loose ends, after twenty long years in oblivion.

title: Before the Fall
text: Friedrich's boxing skills gets him in an elite Nazi high school in a castle in 1942. He enrolls against his dad's wish as it promises a brighter future. It's not what he expected.

title: Frisco Kid, The
text: A Polish rabbi wanders through the Old West on his way to lead a synagogue in San Francisco. On the way, he is nearly burned at the stake by Native Americans and almost killed by outlaws.

title: State Property 2
text: Three Philadelphia-based gangstas -- Beans, Dame and Loco -- are on a collision course with one another for turf. Alliances are forged and broken and lifelong friendships end in violence as each crime lord schemes to get the upper hand.

title: Palindromes
text: Aviva is thirteen, awkward and sensitive. Her mother Joyce is warm and loving, as is her father, Steve, a regular guy who does have a fierce temper from time to time. The film revolves around her family, friends and neighbors.

title: Lot Like Love, A
text: Unacquainted Emily and Oliver join the mile-high club together on the way from LAX to NYC--end of story. Except that they keep meeting constantly over the next seven years..

title: King's Ransom
text: Hoping to foil his own gold-digging wife's plan, a loathsome businessman arranges his own kidnapping, only to realize that there are plenty of other people interested in his wealth as well.

title: Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room
xXx: State of the Union
text: Darius Stone, a new agent in the xXx program, is sent to Washington, D.C. to stop a coup attempt against the President of the United States.

title: Kingdom of Heaven
text: Balian of Ibelin travels to Jerusalem during the Crusades of the 12th century, and there he finds himself as the defender of the city and its people.

title: House of Wax
text: A group of teens are unwittingly stranded near a strange wax museum and soon must fight to survive and keep from becoming the next exhibit.

title: Crash
text: Los Angeles citizens with vastly separate lives collide in interweaving stories of race, loss and redemption.

title: Mysterious Skin
text: A teenage hustler and a young man obsessed with alien abductions cross paths, together discovering a horrible, liberating truth.

title: Mischief
text: Obsessed with the hottest girl in class, a gawky high-school student of 1956 takes a crash course in teenage coolness from his motorcycle-rebel neighbor.

title: Between Your Legs
text: Javier's life gets complicated when a something unexpected turns up in his car's trunk.

title: San Francisco
text: A Barbary Coast saloonkeeper and a Nob Hill impresario are rivals for the affections of a beautiful singer, both personally and professionally in 1906 San Francisco.

title: Vampire Hunter D
text: When Doris Lang is chosen as the next bride for the vampire Count Magnus Lee, she will hire a mysterious vampire hunter known only as D in an attempt to escape her ill-gotten fate.

title: Common Thread, A
text: Claire , an unmarried pregnant teenager, finds an odd relation in Madame Mélikian , an older woman grieving over the death of her son.

title: Cocoanuts, The
text: During the Florida land boom, The Marx Brothers run a hotel, auction off some land, thwart a jewel robbery, and generally act like themselves.

title: Dear Wendy
text: A young boy in a nameless, timeless American town establishes a gang of youthful misfits united in their love of guns and their code of honor.

title: Los Angeles Plays Itself
text: A documentary on how Los Angeles has been used and depicted in the movies.

title: Unleashed
text: A man enslaved by the mob since childhood and raised into behaving like a human attack dog escapes his captors and attempts to start a new life.

title: Star Wars: Episode III - Revenge of the Sith
text: Three years into the Clone Wars, the Jedi rescue Palpatine from Count Dooku. As Obi-Wan pursues a new threat, Anakin acts as a double agent between the Jedi Council and Palpatine and is lured into a sinister plan to rule the galaxy.

title: Kicking & Screaming
text: Family man Phil Weston, a lifelong victim of his father's competitive nature, takes on the coaching duties of a kids' soccer team, and soon finds that he's also taking on his father's dysfunctional way of relating.

title: Monster-in-Law
text: The love life of Charlotte is reduced to an endless string of disastrous blind dates, until she meets the perfect man, Kevin. Unfortunately, his merciless mother will do anything to destroy their relationship.

title: Snow Walker, The
text: A pilot and his passenger struggle for survival after crashing in the Arctic tundra.

title: Divorce - Italian Style
text: A married Sicilian baron falls in love with his cousin and vows to wed her, but with divorce illegal he must concoct a crime of passion to do away with his wife.

title: Madagascar
text: A group of animals who have spent all their life in a New York zoo end up in the jungles of Madagascar, and must adjust to living in the wild.

title: Airborne
text: Mitchell Goosen is a California teenager who loves to surf and rollerblade. When his zoologist parents are given a grant to work in Australia, they can't take Mitchell so they send him to Cincinnati, Ohio to stay with his aunt, uncle, and cousin Wiley--who will be his roommate for the next six months. At his new school Mitchell gets on the bad side of the high-school hockey players, so he and Wiley endure weeks of torture from them. Until they all must learn to get along and team up to beat the Central High School rivals in a competition down the Devil's Backbone.

title: Mad Hot Ballroom
text: The students of several New York City elementary schools learn ballroom dancing and compete in a city wide dance competition.

title: Dominion: Prequel to the Exorcist
text: Years before Father Lankester Merrin helped save Regan MacNeil's soul, he first encounters the demon Pazuzu in East Africa. Merrin's initial battle with Pazuzu leads to the rediscovery of his faith.

title: Longest Yard, The
text: Prison inmates form a football team to challenge the prison guards.

title: Saving Face
text: A Chinese-American lesbian and her traditionalist mother are reluctant to go public with secret loves that clash against cultural expectations.

title: Cinderella Man
text: The story of James J. Braddock, a supposedly washed-up boxer who came back to challenge for the heavyweight championship of the world.

title: Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants, The
text: Four best girlfriends hatch a plan to stay connected with one another as their lives start off in different directions: they pass around a pair of secondhand jeans that fits each of their bodies perfectly.

title: Lords of Dogtown
text: The film follows the surf and skateboarding trends that originated in Venice, California during the 1970's.

title: Rock School
text: At the real life School of Rock a group of misfit kids get in touch with their inner rock star.

title: Mr. & Mrs. Smith
text: A bored married couple is surprised to learn that they are both assassins hired by competing agencies to kill each other.

title: Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl 3-D, The
text: A young boy is recruited by his imaginary friends Sharkboy and Lavagirl to help save their planet.

title: High Tension
text: Best friends Marie and Alexia decide to spend a quiet weekend at Alexia's parents' secluded farmhouse. But on the night of their arrival, the girls' idyllic getaway turns into an endless night of horror.

title: It's All Gone Pete Tong
text: A famous DJ in the Ibiza club scene finds the alcohol and drug-fueled party that is his life threatened by the progressive loss of his hearing.

title: Eddie Izzard: Dress to Kill
text: Executive transvestite Eddie Izzard takes his show to San Francisco to give a brief history of pagan and Christian religions, the building of Stonehenge, the birth of the Church of England and of Western empires, and the need for a European dream. Along the way, he dramatizes Dr. Heimlich's search for a maneuver, the naming of Engelbert Humperdinck, Scooby and Shaggy as archetypes, Neil Armstrong on the moon, society's tolerance of mass murderers, how we sing anthems and carols, Hollywood adapting British films, JFK's trip to Berlin, thoughts on puberty, and how to work schoolbook-French phrases into Parisian conversation. Closeups catch the glint in his eye and his carefully-applied make-up.

title: Quo Vadis
text: After fierce Roman commander Marcus Vinicius becomes infatuated with beautiful Christian hostage Lygia, he begins to question the tyrannical leadership of the despotic emperor Nero.

title: Batman Begins
text: After training with his mentor, Batman begins his fight to free crime-ridden Gotham City from corruption.

title: Godzilla: Final Wars
text: Godzilla's fiftieth Anniversary project, in which Godzilla travels around the world to fight his old foes and his allies plus a new, mysterious monster named Monster X.

title: Perfect Man, The
text: A lonely mother begins receiving romantic e-mails from a secret admirer, unaware that this perfect man is really a creation of her daughter who is trying to cheer her up.

title: Saint Ralph
text: Saint Ralph is the unlikely story of Ralph Walker, a ninth grader who outran everyone's expectations except his own in his bold quest of trying to win the 1954 Boston Marathon.

title: Herbie: Fully Loaded
text: Maggie Peyton, the new owner of Herbie, Number 53, the free-wheelin' Volkswagen bug with a mind of its own, puts the car through its paces on the road to becoming a NASCAR competitor.

title: Land of the Dead
text: The living dead have taken over the world, and the last humans live in a walled city to protect themselves as they come to grips with the situation.

title: Bewitched
text: Thinking he can overshadow an unknown actress in the part, an egocentric actor unknowingly gets a witch cast in an upcoming television remake of the classic sitcom Bewitched .

title: Rize
text: Rize chronicles a dance movement that rises out of South Central Los Angeles with roots in clowning and street youth culture.

title: Me and You and Everyone We Know
text: A lonely shoe salesman and an eccentric performance artist struggle to connect in this unique take on contemporary life.

title: Perfect Crime, The
text: An ambitious salesman will do anything for that big promotion he's been chasing, but inevitably, he will learn that there is no such thing as the perfect crime.

title: 3 Extremes
text: An Asian cross-cultural trilogy of horror films from accomplished indie directors.

title: Edukators, The
text: Three activists cobble together a kidnapping plot after they encounter a businessman in his home.

title: Cop and ½
text: After witnessing a murder, a young boy named Devon refuses to testify unless he is given the chance to be a policeman.

title: At the Circus
text: The Marx Brothers try to help the owner of a circus recover some stolen funds before he finds himself out of a job.

title: War of the Worlds
text: Sci-fi action film about an alien invasion threatening the future of humanity. The catastrophic nightmare is depicted through the eyes of one American family fighting for survival.

title: March of the Penguins
text: In the Antarctic, every March since the beginning of time, the quest begins to find the perfect mate and start a family.

title: Rebound
text: An acclaimed college basketball coach is demoted to a junior varsity team after a public meltdown.

title: Dark Water
text: A mother and daughter, still wounded from a bitter custody dispute, hole up in a run-down apartment building, where they are targeted by the ghost of a former resident.

title: Beat That My Heart Skipped, The
text: Will Thomas still lead a life of crime and cruelty, just like his thuggish father, or will he pursue his dream of becoming a pianist?

title: Fantastic Four
text: A group of astronauts gain superpowers after a cosmic radiation exposure and must use them to oppose the plans of their enemy, Doctor Victor Von Doom.

title: Murderball
text: Quadriplegics, who play full-contact rugby in wheelchairs, overcome unimaginable obstacles to compete in the Paralympic Games in Athens, Greece.

title: Wedding Crashers
text: John Beckwith and Jeremy Grey, a pair of committed womanizers who sneak into weddings to take advantage of the romantic tinge in the air, find themselves at odds with one another when John meets and falls for Claire Cleary.

title: Happy Endings
text: Happy Endings weaves multiple stories to create a witty look at love, family and the sheer unpredictability of life itself.

title: Hustle & Flow
text: With help from his friends, a Memphis pimp in a mid-life crisis attempts to become a successful hip-hop emcee.

title: Hardware
text: The head of a cyborg reactivates, rebuilds itself, and goes on a violent rampage in a space marine's girlfriend's apartment.

title: Calcium Kid, The
text: Following a bizarre series of events, Jimmy, a local amateur boxer, finds himself pitted in a match against the world champion.

title: Island, The
text: A man living in a futuristic sterile colony begins to question his circumscribed existence when his friend is chosen to go to the Island, the last uncontaminated place on earth.

title: Bad News Bears
text: A grizzled little league coach tries to turn his team of misfits into champs.

title: Devil's Rejects, The
text: The murderous, backwoods Firefly family take to the road to escape the vengeful Sheriff Wydell, who is not afraid of being as ruthless as his target.

title: Last Days
text: A Seattle musician's life and career are reminiscent to those of Kurt Cobain.

title: November
text: Sophie Jacobs is going through the most difficult time of her life. Now, she just has to find out if it's real.

title: Sky High
text: Set in an era where superheroes are commonly known and accepted, young William Stronghold, the son of the Commander and Jetstream, tries to find a balance between being a normal teenager and an extraordinary being.

title: Stealth
text: Deeply ensconced in a top-secret military program, three pilots struggle to bring an artificial intelligence program under control before it initiates the next world war.

title: Must Love Dogs
text: A thirty-something preschool teacher looks to the personals for a change of pace and a relationship, with hilarious results.

title: Aristocrats, The
text: One hundred superstar comedians tell the same very, VERY dirty, filthy joke--one shared privately by comics since Vaudeville.

title: Georgy Girl
text: A traditional girl  resists the advances of a swinger  who wants her as his mistress in 1960s London.

title: Order, The
text: A playboy criminal contacts his dad after stealing a Faberge egg. Later it seems his dad has gone missing in Israel so he heads there. His disappearance is linked to the religious sect: The Order. Lots of fight and chase scenes.

title: Serenity
text: The crew of the ship Serenity try to evade an assassin sent to recapture telepath River.

title: Broken Flowers
text: As the extremely withdrawn Don Johnston is dumped by his latest woman, he receives an anonymous letter from a former lover informing him that he has a son who may be looking for him. A freelance sleuth neighbor moves Don to embark on a cross-country search for his old flames in search of answers.

title: Miracles - Mr. Canton and Lady Rose
text: A country boy becomes the head of a gang through the purchase of some lucky roses from an old lady. He and a singer at the gang's nightclub try to do a good deed for the old lady when her daughter comes to visit.

title: Browning Version, The
