text: A veteran high school teacher befriends a younger art teacher, who is having an affair with one of her fifteen-year-old students. However, her intentions with this new "friend" also go well beyond a platonic friendship.

title: DOA: Dead or Alive
text: The world's best fighters are invited to DOA, an invitational martial arts contest. There, four female rival fighters will have to work together to uncover the secret that the organizer of the tournament is trying to hide.

title: Curse of the Golden Flower
text: During China's Tang dynasty the emperor has taken the princess of a neighboring province as wife. She has borne him two sons and raised his eldest. Now his control over his dominion is complete, including the royal family itself.

title: Good German, The
text: While in post-war Berlin to cover the Potsdam Conference, an American military journalist is drawn into a murder investigation which involves his former mistress and his driver.

title: Letters from Iwo Jima
text: The story of the battle of Iwo Jima between the United States and Imperial Japan during World War II, as told from the perspective of the Japanese who fought it.

title: Black Christmas
text: On Christmas Eve, an escaped maniac returns to his childhood home, which is now a sorority house, and begins to murder the sorority sisters one by one.

title: Stomp the Yard
text: When his brother is murdered, a street dancer moves to Georgia to work his way through college. He joins a fraternity's step dancing team for a competition. Will he also get an education and the girl?

title: Miss Potter
text: The story of Beatrix Potter, the author of the beloved and best-selling children's book, "The Tale of Peter Rabbit", and her struggle for love, happiness, and success.

title: American Pie Presents The Naked Mile
text: When Erik Stifler gets a free pass to do whatever he wants from his girlfriend, he and his two best friends head to see his cousin Dwight for the Naked Mile and a weekend they will never forget.

title: Venus
text: Life for a pair of veteran actors gets turned upside down after they meet a brash teenager.

title: The Return of Don Camillo
text: Energetic priest Don Camillo returns to the town of Brescello for more political and personal duels with Communist mayor Peppone.

title: The Little World of Don Camillo
text: A determined priest and a Communist mayor develop a grudging friendship in spite of their official rivalry.

title: Primeval
text: A news team is sent to Burundi to capture and bring home a legendary 25-foot crocodile. Their difficult task turns potentially deadly when a warlord targets them for death.

title: Alpha Dog
text: Johnny and a couple pals kidnap Jake's 15-year-old brother, Zach, then assigns his buddy Frankie to be Zach's minder. They develop a brotherly friendship. Zach parties with his captors as things begin to spin out of control.

title: Hitcher, The
text: A serial killer pins his crimes on two college students who gave him a ride.

title: After the Wedding
text: A manager of an orphanage in India is sent to Copenhagen, Denmark, where he discovers a life-altering family secret.

title: Bridge to Terabithia
text: A preteen's life turns upside down when he befriends the new girl in school and they imagine a whole new fantasy world to escape reality.

title: Beer League
text: An unemployed slacker inspires his softball teammates to improve their game so they won't get kicked out of the local league.

title: Dead Meat
text: An infection spreads from slaughtered animals to humans, which causes the dead to rise and feed on the living.

title: 49 Up
text: Director Michael Apted revisits the same group of British-born adults after a 7 year wait. The subjects are interviewed as to the changes that have occurred in their lives during the last seven years.

title: Waitress
text: Jenna is a pregnant, unhappily married waitress in the deep south. She meets a newcomer to her town and falls into an unlikely relationship as a last attempt at happiness.

title: Seven Up!
text: A group of British children aged 7 from widely ranging backgrounds are interviewed about a range of subjects.

title: Catch and Release
text: A woman struggles to accept the death of her fiancé and the secrets he kept from her as she rebuilds her life.

title: Smokin' Aces
text: When a Las Vegas performer-turned-snitch named Buddy Israel decides to turn state's evidence and testify against the mob, it seems that a whole lot of people would like to make sure he's no longer breathing.

title: Blood and Chocolate
text: A teenage werewolf is torn between honoring her family's secret and her love for a man.

title: Epic Movie
text: A spoof on previous years' epic movies , The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe  + 20 more), TV series, music videos and celebs. 4 orphans are on an epic adventure.

title: Messengers, The
text: An ominous darkness invades a seemingly serene sunflower farm in North Dakota, and the Solomon family is torn apart by suspicion, mayhem and murder.

title: Because I Said So
text: A meddling mother tries to set her daughter up with the right man so her kid won't follow in her footsteps.

title: Hannibal Rising
text: After the death of his parents during World War II, young Hannibal Lecter moves in with his beautiful aunt and begins plotting revenge on the barbarians responsible for his sister's death.

title: Norbit
text: A mild-mannered guy, who is married to a monstrous woman, meets the woman of his dreams, and schemes to find a way to be with her.

title: Boss of It All, The
text: An IT company hires an actor to serve as the company's president in order to help the business get sold to a cranky Icelander.

title: Cocaine Cowboys
text: The story of how Miami became the cocaine capital of the United States in the early 1980's and the police officers who turned the tide on crime.

title: Ratatouille
text: A rat who can cook makes an unusual alliance with a young kitchen worker at a famous restaurant.

title: Paris, I Love You
text: Through the neighborhoods of Paris, love is veiled, revealed, imitated, sucked dry, reinvented and awakened.

title: Astronaut Farmer, The
text: A NASA astronaut, forced to retire years earlier so he could save his family farm, has never given up his dream of space travel and looks to build his own rocket, despite the government's threats to stop him.

title: Wake Up, Ron Burgundy
text: While Ron Burgundy's rivalry with Veronica Corningstone persists, a group of unprofessional thieves endeavor to make the truth known.

title: It's a Boy Girl Thing
text: Sworn enemies find themselves in each other's bodies, and use this to ruin each other's lives.

title: Ugly Duckling and Me!, The
text: This modern version of Hans Christian Andersen's fairytale is charming. Ratso is a streetwise chancer of a rat whose theatre show is struggling. Then he finds an egg that hatches a mutant swan. Ratso soon sees the potential of showing Ugly as a freak. But things go awry when rodent heavies appear...

title: The Odyssey
text: The warrior King Odysseus leaves his idyllic life in the kingdom of Ithaca to fight in the Trojan War. After winning the war, he now must endure a lengthy, ten-year journey to return, and with all his wits, Odysseus must overcome deadly monsters, powerful forces of nature, seductive enchantresses, and even journey into the bowels of the Underworld.

title: Unknown
text: Five men wake up in a locked-down warehouse with no memory of who they are. They are forced to figure out who is good and who is bad to stay alive.

title: Ghost Rider
text: When motorcycle rider Johnny Blaze sells his soul to the Devil to save his father's life, he is transformed into the Ghost Rider, the Devil's own bounty hunter, and is sent to hunt down sinners.

title: Breach
text: FBI upstart Eric O'Neill enters into a power game with his boss, Robert Hanssen, an agent who was put on trial for selling secrets to the Soviet Union.

title: Tyler Perry's Daddy's Little Girls
text: A mechanic falls in love with his attorney.

title: Music and Lyrics
text: A washed up singer is given a couple days to compose a chart-topping hit for an aspiring teen sensation. Though he's never written a decent lyric in his life, he sparks with an offbeat younger woman with a flair for words.

title: Number 23, The
text: Walter Sparrow becomes obsessed with a novel that he believes was written about him, as more and more similarities between himself and his literary alter ego seem to arise.

title: Reno 911!: Miami
text: A rag-tag team of Reno cops are called in to save the day after a terrorist attack disrupts a national police convention in Miami Beach during spring break. Based on the Comedy Central series.

title: Black Snake Moan
text: A God-fearing bluesman takes to a wild young woman who, as a victim of childhood sexual abuse, looks everywhere for love, never quite finding it.

title: My Father and My Son
text: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

title: Factory Girl
text: Based on the rise and fall of socialite Edie Sedgwick, concentrating on her relationships with Andy Warhol and a folk singer.

title: Hot Fuzz
text: A skilled London police officer, after irritating superiors with his embarrassing effectiveness, is transferred to a village where the easygoing officers object to his fervor for regulations, as a string of grisly murders strikes the town.

title: Golden Door
text: A Sicilian peasant begins the journey to the promised land and meets a beautiful Englishwoman. But neither is prepared for the harsh realities of Ellis Island. Can they make it through the golden door to the America of their dreams?

title: Citizen X
text: During the 1980s, Soviet authorities hunt for a serial killer who picks his victims in railway stations and commuter trains and lures them into the woods.

title: Next
text: A Las Vegas magician who can see into the future is pursued by FBI agents seeking to use his abilities to prevent a nuclear terrorist attack.

title: Amazing Grace
text: The idealist William Wilberforce  maneuvers his way through Parliament, endeavoring to end the British transatlantic slave trade.

title: 2001 Maniacs
text: Eight college students travelling to Florida for Spring Break stumble into a remote town in Georgia, where they are set upon by the residents.

title: Zodiac
text: Between 1968 and 1983, a San Francisco cartoonist becomes an amateur detective obsessed with tracking down the Zodiac Killer, an unidentified individual who terrorizes Northern California with a killing spree.

title: Pusher III: I'm the Angel of Death
text: Milo tries to be a family man and run his criminal organization, but a wrong drug shipment endangers everything.

title: Meshes of the Afternoon
text: A woman returning home falls asleep and has vivid dreams that may or may not be happening in reality. Through repetitive images and complete mismatching of the objective view of time and space, her dark inner desires play out on-screen.

title: Wild Hogs
text: A group of suburban biker wannabes looking for adventure hit the open road, but get more than they bargained for when they encounter a New Mexico gang called the Del Fuegos.
King Leonidas of Sparta and a force of 300 men fight the Persians at Thermopylae in 480 B.C.

title: Abandoned, The
text: An adopted woman returns to her home country and the family home that she never knew and must face the mystery that lies there.

title: Starter for 10
text: Set in 1985, working-class student Brian Jackson  navigates his first year at Bristol University.

title: Last Mimzy, The
text: Two siblings begin to develop special talents after they find a mysterious box of toys. Soon the kids, their parents, and even their teacher are drawn into a strange new world and find a task ahead of them that is far more important than any of them could imagine!

title: Priceless
text: Through a set of wacky circumstances, a young gold digger mistakenly woos a mild-mannered bartender, thinking he's a wealthy suitor.

title: Host, The
text: A monster emerges from Seoul's Han River and begins attacking people. One victim's loving family does what it can to rescue her from its clutches.

title: Becoming Jane
text: A biographical portrait of a pre-fame Jane Austen and her romance with a young Irishman.

title: Namesake, The
text: American-born Gogol, the son of Indian immigrants, wants to fit in among his fellow New Yorkers, despite his family's unwillingness to let go of their traditional ways.

title: I Think I Love My Wife
text: A married man who daydreams about being with other women finds his will and morals tested after he's visited by the ex-mistress of his old friend.

title: Premonition
text: A depressed woman learns that her husband was killed in a car accident the previous day, then awakens the next morning to find him alive and well at home; then awakens the day after that to find that he's dead.

title: Dead Silence
text: A young widower returns to his hometown to search for answers to his wife's murder, which may be linked to the ghost of a deceased ventriloquist.

title: Reign Over Me
text: A man who lost his family in the September 11 attack on New York City runs into his old college roommate. Rekindling the friendship is the one thing that appears able to help the man recover from his grief.

title: Pride
text: The determined Jim Ellis starts a swim team for troubled teens at the Philadelphia Department of Recreation.

title: Shooter
text: A marksman living in exile is coaxed back into action after learning of a plot to kill the President. After being double crossed for the attempt and on the run, he sets out for the real killer and the truth.

title: Hills Have Eyes II, The
text: A group of National Guard trainees find themselves battling against a vicious group of mutants on their last day of training in the desert.

title: TMNT
text: When the world is threatened by an ancient evil, the four adolescent turtles must reunite and overcome their faults in order to stand against it.

title: Black Book
text: In the Nazi-occupied Netherlands during World War II, a Jewish singer infiltrates the regional Gestapo headquarters for the Dutch resistance.

title: Lookout, The
text: Chris is a once promising high school athlete whose life is turned upside down following a tragic accident. As he tries to maintain a normal life, he takes a job as a janitor at a bank, where he ultimately finds himself caught up in a planned heist.

title: Blades of Glory
text: In 2002, two rival Olympic ice skaters were stripped of their gold medals and permanently banned from men's single competition. Presently, however, they've found a loophole that will allow them to qualify as a pairs team.

title: Are We Done Yet?
text: Newlyweds Nick and Suzanne decide to move to the suburbs to provide a better life for their two kids. But their idea of a dream home is disturbed by a contractor with a bizarre approach to business.

title: Grindhouse
text: Quentin Tarantino and Robert Rodriguez's homage to exploitation double features in the '60s and '70s with two back-to-back cult films that include previews of coming attractions between them.

title: Reaping, The
text: A former Christian missionary, who specializes in debunking religious phenomena, investigates a small town which seems to be suffering from the 10 biblical plagues.

title: Meet the Robinsons
text: Lewis is a brilliant inventor who meets mysterious stranger named Wilbur Robinson, whisking Lewis away in a time machine and together they team up to track down Bowler Hat Guy in a showdown that ends with an unexpected twist of fate.

title: American Hardcore
text: The History of American Punk Rock 1980-1986

title: Inglorious Bastards
text: In 1944 France, a group of escaped American military prisoners en route to Switzerland volunteers to steal a Nazi V2 rocket warhead for the Allies.

title: Sunshine
text: A team of international astronauts are sent on a dangerous mission to reignite the dying Sun with a nuclear fission bomb in 2057.

title: Hoax, The
text: In what would cause a fantastic media frenzy, Clifford Irving sells his bogus biography of Howard Hughes to a premiere publishing house in the early 1970s.

title: How the Grinch Stole Christmas!
text: A grumpy hermit hatches a plan to steal Christmas from the Whos of Whoville.

title: Disturbia
text: A teen living under house arrest becomes convinced his neighbor is a serial killer.

title: Aqua Teen Hunger Force Colon Movie Film for Theaters
text: An action epic that explores the origins of Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, better known as the Aqua Teen Hunger Force, who somehow become pitted in a battle over an immortal piece of exercise equipment.

title: Vie en Rose, La
text: Biopic of the iconic French singer Édith Piaf. Raised by her grandmother in a brothel, she was discovered while singing on a street corner at the age of 19. Despite her success, Piaf's life was filled with tragedy.

title: Fracture
text: An attorney intending on climbing the career ladder toward success finds an unlikely opponent in a manipulative criminal he is trying to prosecute.

title: Vacancy
text: A married couple becomes stranded at an isolated motel and finds hidden video cameras in their room. They soon realize that unless they escape, they'll be the next victims of a snuff film.

title: In the Land of Women
text: A sleazy writer has a chance to redeem himself when he goes to stay with his grandmother and befriends the neighbors.

title: Mr. Bean's Holiday
text: Mr. Bean wins a trip to Cannes where he unwittingly separates a young boy from his father and must help the two reunite. On the way he discovers France, bicycling, and true love.

title: Invisible, The
text: A teenager is left invisible to the living after an attack.

title: Kickin It Old Skool
text: A young breakdancer hits his head during a talent show and slips into a coma for twenty years. Waking up in 2006, he looks to revive his and his team's career with the help of his girlfriend and his parents.

title: Spider-Man 3
text: A strange black entity from another world bonds with Peter Parker and causes inner turmoil as he contends with new villains, temptations, and revenge.

title: Lucky You
text: A hotshot poker player tries to win a tournament in Vegas, but is fighting a losing battle with his personal problems.

title: It's a Very Merry Muppet Christmas Movie
text: 'Twas the night before Christmas and the Muppet Theatre is in danger of being torn down, but with hilarious send-ups of just about every holiday movie ever made, the Muppets discover that what matters most is their love for each other.

title: 21 Up
text: Director Michael Apted interviews the same group of British-born adults after a 7 year wait as to the changes that have occurred in their lives during the last seven years.

title: Sharkwater
text: An investigation of sharks' importance to ecosystems and humankind's mass destruction of shark species worldwide.

title: Maniac Cop
text: A killer dressed in a police uniform begins murdering innocent people on the streets of New York City.

title: Ex, The
text: A slacker is forced to work for his father-in-law after his pregnant wife steps away from her high-paying job.

title: Paprika
text: When a machine that allows therapists to enter their patients' dreams is stolen, all hell breaks loose. Only a young female therapist, Paprika, can stop it.

title: Day Watch
text: A man who serves in the war between the forces of Light and Dark comes into possession of a device that can restore life to Moscow, which was nearly destroyed by an apocalyptic event.

title: This Is England
text: A young boy becomes friends with a gang of skinheads. Friends soon become like family, and relationships will be pushed to the very limit.

title: Away from Her
text: A man coping with the institutionalization of his wife because of Alzheimer's disease faces an epiphany when she transfers her affections to another man, Aubrey, a wheelchair-bound mute who also is a patient at the nursing home.

title: Knocked Up
text: For fun-loving party animal Ben Stone, the last thing he ever expected was for his one-night stand to show up on his doorstep eight weeks later to tell him she's pregnant with his child.

title: Hairspray
text: Pleasantly plump teenager Tracy Turnblad teaches 1962 Baltimore a thing or two about integration after landing a spot on a local TV dance show.

title: 28 Weeks Later
text: Six months after the rage virus was inflicted on the population of Great Britain, the US Army helps to secure a small area of London for the survivors to repopulate and start again. But not everything goes according to plan.

title: Wheels on Meals
text: Two Chinese friends, who operate a food truck in Barcelona, Spain, use their martial arts expertise to help their private investigator friend protect the pickpocket Sylvia, who's been targeted by a ruthless gang.

title: Jonestown: The Life and Death of Peoples Temple
text: Featuring never-before-seen footage, this documentary delivers a startling new look at the Peoples Temple, headed by preacher Jim Jones who, in 1978, led more than 900 members to Guyana, where he orchestrated a mass suicide via tainted punch.

title: Shrek the Third
text: Reluctantly designated as the heir to the land of Far, Far Away, Shrek hatches a plan to install the rebellious Artie as the new king while Princess Fiona tries to fend off a coup d'état by the jilted Prince Charming.

title: Once
text: A modern-day musical about a busker and an immigrant and their eventful week in Dublin, as they write, rehearse and record songs that tell their love story.

title: Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End
text: Captain Barbossa, Will Turner and Elizabeth Swann must sail off the edge of the map, navigate treachery and betrayal, find Jack Sparrow, and make their final alliances for one last decisive battle.

title: Bug
text: An unhinged war veteran holes up with a lonely woman in a spooky Oklahoma motel room. The line between reality and delusion is blurred as they discover a bug infestation.

title: Mr. Brooks
text: A well-respected businessman is sometimes controlled by his murder and mayhem-loving alter ego.

title: Librarian: Return to King Solomon's Mines, The
text: Librarian-turned-adventurer Flynn Carsen endeavors to find King Solomon's mines.

title: Librarian: Quest for the Spear, The
text: A bookworm becomes the librarian. Same night a magical spear gets stolen and he's off to get some real life experience around the globe on his quest for the spear - starting with being thrown off a plane over Amazonas by his cute helper.

title: Fay Grim
text: A ten-years-later continuation of Hal Hartley's "Henry Fool", where Fay Grim  is coerced by a CIA agent  to try and locate notebooks that belonged to her fugitive ex-husband . Published in them is information that could compromises the security of the U.S., causing Fay to first head to Paris to fetch them ...

title: I'm a Cyborg, But That's OK
text: A girl who thinks she is a combat cyborg checks into a mental hospital, where she encounters other psychotics. Eventually, she falls for a man who thinks he can steal people's souls.

title: Breed, The
text: A group of five college kids are forced to match wits with unwelcoming residents when they fly to a "deserted" island for a party weekend.

title: Cashback
text: After a painful breakup, Ben develops insomnia. To kill time, he starts working the late night shift at the local supermarket, where his artistic imagination runs wild.

title: Ocean's Thirteen
text: Danny Ocean rounds up the boys for a third heist after casino owner Willy Bank double-crosses one of the original eleven, Reuben Tishkoff.

title: Them
text: Lucas and Clementine live peacefully in their isolated country house, but one night they wake up to strange noise... they're not alone... and a group of hooded assailants begin to terrorize them throughout the night.

title: Sun Alley
text: A group of kids grow up on the short, wrong  side of the Sonnenallee in Berlin, right next to one of the few border crossings between East and West reserved for German citizens. The antics of these kids, their families, of the "West German" friends and relatives who come to visit, and of the East German border guards, all serve to illustrate the absurdity of everyday life on the Sonnenallee, and therefore throughout the former East Germany.

title: Hostel: Part II
text: Three American college students studying abroad are lured to a Slovakian hostel, and discover the grim reality behind it.

title: Paranoid Park
text: A teenage skateboarder's life begins to fray after he is involved in the accidental death of a security guard.

title: Legend of Sleepy Hollow, The
text: Angered that Katrina has grown fond of schoolmaster Crane, Brom Bones determines to scare off the interloper by filling his head with spooky tales of a Headless Horseman. Crane disparages the legends, until one fateful ride home in the dark of night.

title: Starcrash
text: An outlaw smuggler and her alien companion are recruited by the Emperor of the Galaxy to rescue his son and destroy a secret weapon by the evil Count Zarth Arn.

title: Surf's Up
text: A behind-the-scenes look at the annual Penguin World Surfing Championship, and its newest participant, up-and-comer Cody Maverick.

title: Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer
text: The Fantastic Four learn that they aren't the only super-powered beings in the universe when they square off against the powerful Silver Surfer and the planet-eating Galactus.

title: Nancy Drew
text: Teen detective Nancy Drew accompanies her father on a business trip to Los Angeles, where she happens upon clues to a murder mystery involving a movie star.

title: Fido
text: Space radiation turns the dead into Zombies. Zomcon fights zombies and finds ways to pacify and use them. On pre-teen Timmy's  1950s suburban street, they all have a zombie doing menial chores. Timmy's zombie becomes his pet and friend, and is named Fido .

title: Death Proof
text: Two separate sets of voluptuous women are stalked at different times by a scarred stuntman who uses his "death proof" cars to execute his murderous plans.

title: Rescue Dawn
text: A U.S. fighter pilot's epic struggle of survival after being shot down on a mission over Laos during the Vietnam War.

title: TV Set, The
text: The story of a TV pilot as it goes through the Network TV process of casting, production and finally airing.

title: Valet, The
text: A porter and a top-model have to pretend to be a couple in order to salvage a CEO's marriage.

title: Bring It On: All or Nothing
text: A transfer student to a rough high school tries joining the cheer-leading squad and she not only faces off against the head cheerleader, but against her former school in preparation for a cheer-off competition.

title: Power of Nightmares, The: The Rise of the Politics of Fear
text: A series of three documentaries about the use of fear for political gain.

title: Sicko
text: A documentary comparing the highly profitable American health care industry to other nations, and HMO horror stories including shotgun deaths.

title: Mighty Heart, A
text: Mariane Pearl embarks on a frantic search to locate her journalist husband, Daniel, when he goes missing in Pakistan.
A man who specialises in debunking paranormal occurrences checks into the fabled room 1408 in the Dolphin Hotel. Soon after settling in, he confronts genuine terror.

title: Death at a Funeral
text: Chaos ensues when a man tries to expose a dark secret regarding a recently deceased patriarch of a dysfunctional British family.

title: Live Free or Die Hard
text: John McClane and a young hacker join forces to take down master cyber-terrorist Thomas Gabriel in Washington D.C.

title: License to Wed
text: A reverend puts an engaged couple through a grueling marriage preparation course to see if they are meant to be married in his church.

title: Evan Almighty
text: God contacts Congressman Evan Baxter and tells him to build an ark in preparation for a great flood.

title: Transformers
text: An ancient struggle between two Cybertronian races, the heroic Autobots and the evil Decepticons, comes to Earth, with a clue to the ultimate power held by a teenager.

title: Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix
text: With their warning about Lord Voldemort's return scoffed at, Harry and Dumbledore are targeted by the Wizard authorities as an authoritarian bureaucrat slowly seizes power at Hogwarts.

title: I Now Pronounce You Chuck and Larry
text: Two straight, single Brooklyn firefighters pretend to be a gay couple in order to receive domestic partner benefits.

title: First Snow
text: A psychic's ominous reading sends a man into a tailspin.

title: Broken Arrow
text: Tom Jeffords tries to make peace between settlers and Apaches in Arizona territory.

title: Manufactured Landscapes
text: Photographer Edward Burtynsky travels the world observing changes in landscapes due to industrial work and manufacturing.

title: Across the Universe
text: The music of The Beatles and the Vietnam War form the backdrop for the romance between an upper-class American girl and a poor Liverpudlian artist.

title: Hot Rod
text: Self-proclaimed stuntman Rod Kimble is preparing for the jump of his life - to clear fifteen buses to raise money for his abusive stepfather Frank's life-saving heart operation.

title: Stardust
text: In a countryside town bordering on a magical land, a young man makes a promise to his beloved that he'll retrieve a fallen star by venturing into the magical realm.

title: Simpsons Movie, The
text: After Homer pollutes the town's water supply, Springfield is encased in a gigantic dome by the EPA and the Simpsons are declared fugitives.

title: I Know Who Killed Me
text: A young woman who was missing reappears, but she claims to be someone else entirely.

title: No Reservations
text: The life of a top chef changes when she becomes the guardian of her young niece.

title: Charlie Bartlett
text: A rich kid becomes the self-appointed psychiatrist to the student body of his new high school.

title: Bourne Ultimatum, The
text: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless C.I.A. official and his Agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

title: China Blue
text: The sweatshop conditions and the growing importance of China as an exporting country on a global scale are followed through by the life of a young seventeen-year-old worker in a Chinese jeans' factory.

title: Tell No One
text: An accidental discovery near a doctor's estate stirs up some painful memories eight years after his wife's hideous murder, and now, things are bound to take a turn for the unexpected. Does the good doctor know more than he's letting on?

title: Superbad
text: Two co-dependent high school seniors are forced to deal with separation anxiety after their plan to stage a booze-soaked party goes awry.

title: Brice Man, The
text: A wannabe surfer parties on the French Riviera while awaiting the perfect wave.

title: Rush Hour 3
text: After an attempted assassination on Ambassador Han, Lee and Carter head to Paris to protect a French woman with knowledge of the Triads' secret leaders.

title: Last Legion, The
text: As the Roman empire crumbles, young Romulus Augustus flees the city and embarks on a perilous voyage to Britain to track down a legion of supporters.

title: Balls of Fury
text: Down-and-out former professional ping-pong phenom, Randy Daytona, is sucked into a maelstrom when FBI Agent Ernie Rodriguez recruits him for a secret mission. Randy is determined to bounce back and win, and to smoke out his father's killer -- arch-fiend Feng.

title: Sydney White
text: A modern retelling of Snow White set against students in their freshman year of college in the greek system.

title: Kingdom, The
text: A team of U.S. government agents are sent to investigate the bombing of an American facility in the Middle East.

title: Rocket Science
text: Looking for answers to life's big questions, a stuttering boy joins his high school debate team.

title: Daddy Day Camp
text: Seeking to offer his son the satisfying summer camp experience that eluded him as a child, the operator of a neighborhood daycare center opens his own camp, only to face financial hardship and stiff competition from a rival camp.

title: Invasion, The
text: As a Washington, D.C. psychiatrist unearths the origin of an alien epidemic, she also discovers her son might be the only way it can be stopped.

title: Nanny Diaries, The
text: A college graduate goes to work as a nanny for a rich New York family. Ensconced in their home, she has to juggle their dysfunction, a new romance, and the spoiled brat in her charge.

title: Halloween
text: After being committed for 17 years, Michael Myers, now a grown man and still very dangerous, escapes from the mental institution and immediately returns to Haddonfield to find his baby sister, Laurie.

title: Death Sentence
text: Nick Hume is a mild-mannered executive with a perfect life, until one gruesome night he witnesses something that changes him forever. Transformed by grief, Hume eventually comes to the disturbing conclusion that no length is too great when protecting his family.

title: 2 Days in Paris
text: Marion and Jack try to rekindle their relationship with a visit to Paris, home of Marion's parents -- and several of her ex-boyfriends.

title: King of Kong, The
text: Die-hard gamers compete to break world records on classic arcade games.

title: Taxi 4
text: Daniel, the driver of a very special taxi in Marseille, gets a famous soccer player to the stadium in time and later helps his clumsy police friend Émilien catch the dangerous Belgian after he escaped on Émilien's guard.

title: Behind the Mask: The Rise of Leslie Vernon
text: The next great psycho horror slasher has given a documentary crew exclusive access to his life as he plans his reign of terror over the sleepy town of Glen Echo.

title: Brothers Solomon, The
text: A pair of well-meaning, but socially inept brothers try to find their perfect mates in order to provide their dying father with a grandchild.

title: Nines, The
text: A troubled actor, a television show runner, and an acclaimed videogame designer find their lives intertwining in mysterious and unsettling ways.

title: Planet Terror
text: After an experimental bio-weapon is released, turning thousands into zombie-like creatures, it's up to a rag-tag group of survivors to stop the infected and those behind its release.

title: 3:10 to Yuma
text: A small-time rancher agrees to hold a captured outlaw who's awaiting a train to go to court in Yuma. A battle of wills ensues as the outlaw tries to psych out the rancher.

title: Shoot 'Em Up
text: A man named Mr. Smith delivers a woman's baby during a shootout, and is then called upon to protect the newborn from the army of gunmen.

title: Ten, The
text: Ten stories, each inspired by one of the ten commandments.

title: Gotti
text: John Gotti rises to head the powerful Gambino crime family before being convicted in 1992 of racketeering and murder.

title: Atonement
text: Thirteen-year-old fledgling writer Briony Tallis irrevocably changes the course of several lives when she accuses her older sister's lover of a crime he did not commit.

title: Electroma
text: The journey of two robots on their quest to become human.

title: Requiem
text: An epileptic girl suffers a breakdown during her first year at university, then decides to seek help from a priest in battling the troubles associated with her strict upbringing.

title: 4 Months, 3 Weeks and 2 Days
text: A woman assists her friend in arranging an illegal abortion in 1980s Romania.

title: No End in Sight
text: A comprehensive look at the Bush Administration's conduct of the Iraq war and its occupation of the country.

title: Brave One, The
text: Struggling to recover emotionally from a brutal assault that killed her fiancé and left her in a coma, a radio personality begins a quest for vengeance against the perpetrators that leaves a bloody trail across New York City.

title: In the Valley of Elah
text: A retired military investigator works with a police detective to uncover the truth behind his son's disappearance following his return from a tour of duty in Iraq.

title: December Boys
text: One summer, four orphans boys who have grown to be the closest of friends find themselves competing for the attention of the same family.

title: Shanghai Kiss
text: An Asian-American actor, living in Los Angeles, is forced to reconsider his roots as well as the possibilities afforded him by his present situation after suddenly inheriting his grandmother's home in Shanghai.

title: Hunting Party, The
text: A young journalist, a seasoned cameraman and a discredited war correspondent embark on an unauthorized mission to find the No.1 war criminal in Bosnia. However, their extremely dangerous target decides to come after them.

title: Eastern Promises
text: A teenager who dies during childbirth leaves clues in her journal that could tie her child to a rape involving a violent Russian mob family.

title: Unreasonable Man, An
text: A look at the career of consumer advocate Ralph Nader.

title: Tekkonkinkreet
text: 2 boys defend Treasure Town. Yakuza try to take over and clear it for new development.

title: Love and Other Disasters
text: An American intern at U.K. Vogue helps her friends find love.

title: Interview
text: After falling out with his editor, a fading political journalist is forced to interview America's most popular soap actress.

title: Cashback
text: Ben is an art college student in London, whose imagination runs wild as he works the late-night shift at the local supermarket. What do he and his colleagues do to pass the long, endless hours of the night?

title: Resident Evil: Extinction
text: Survivors of the Raccoon City catastrophe travel across the Nevada desert, hoping to make it to Alaska. Alice joins the caravan and their fight against the evil Umbrella Corp.

title: Mr. Woodcock
text: Taken aback by his mother's wedding announcement, a young man returns home in an effort to stop her from marrying his old high school gym teacher, a man who made middle school hell for generations of students.

title: Good Luck Chuck
text: In order to keep the woman of his dreams from falling for another guy, Charlie Logan has to break the curse that has made him wildly popular with single women: Sleep with Charlie once, and the next man you meet will be your true love.

title: Into the Wild
text: After graduating from Emory University, top student and athlete Christopher McCandless abandons his possessions, gives his entire $24,000 savings account to charity and hitchhikes to Alaska to live in the wilderness. Along the way, Christopher encounters a series of characters that shape his life.

title: Game Plan, The
text: An NFL quarterback living the bachelor lifestyle discovers that he has an 8-year-old daughter from a previous relationship.

title: Lust, Caution
text: During World War II era, a young woman, Wang Jiazhi, gets swept up in a dangerous game of emotional intrigue with a powerful political figure, Mr. Yee.

title: Seeker: The Dark Is Rising, The
text: A boy's life is turned upside down when he learns that he is the last of a group of immortal warriors who have dedicated their lives to fighting the forces of the dark.

title: Heartbreak Kid, The
text: A newly wed man who believes he's just gotten hitched to the perfect woman encounters another lady on his honeymoon.

title: Dan in Real Life
text: A widower finds out the woman he fell in love with is his brother's girlfriend.

title: Darjeeling Limited, The
text: A year after their father's funeral, three brothers travel across India by train in an attempt to bond with each other.

title: We Own the Night
text: A New York City nightclub manager tries to save his brother and father from Russian Mafia hitmen.

title: Elizabeth: The Golden Age
text: A mature Queen Elizabeth endures multiple crises late in her reign including court intrigues, an assassination plot, the Spanish Armada, and romantic disappointments.

title: Michael Clayton
text: A law firm brings in its "fixer" to remedy the situation after a lawyer has a breakdown while representing a chemical company that he knows is guilty in a multibillion-dollar class action suit.

title: Sleuth
text: On his sprawling country estate, an aging writer matches wits with the struggling actor who has stolen his wife's heart.

title: Lars and the Real Girl
text: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet.

title: 30 Days of Night
text: After an Alaskan town is plunged into darkness for a month, it is attacked by a bloodthirsty gang of vampires.

title: Gone Baby Gone
text: Two Boston area detectives investigate a little girl's kidnapping, which ultimately turns into a crisis both professionally and personally.

title: Comebacks, The
text: A comedy that spoofs inspirational sports movies, this movie is about an out-of-luck coach who drives a rag-tag bunch of college misfits towards the football championship.

title: Weirdsville
text: A pair of slackers get in way over their heads when they try to dump the body of a dead girlfriend in the basement of a drive-in movie theater where a satanic cult performs ritual sacrifices.

title: Assassination of Jesse James by the Coward Robert Ford, The
text: Robert Ford, who's idolized Jesse James since childhood, tries hard to join the reforming gang of the Missouri outlaw, but gradually becomes resentful of the bandit leader.

title: 10th & Wolf
text: A former street tough returns to his Philadelphia home after a stint in the military. Back on his home turf, he once again finds himself tangling with the mob boss who was instrumental in his going off to be a soldier.

title: Persepolis
text: A precocious and outspoken Iranian girl grows up during the Islamic Revolution.

title: Control
text: A profile of Ian Curtis, the enigmatic singer of Joy Division whose personal, professional, and romantic troubles led him to commit suicide at the age of 23.

title: The Jane Austen Book Club
text: Six Californians start a club to discuss the works of Jane Austen, only to find their relationships -- both old and new -- begin to resemble 21st century versions of her novels.

title: Last Winter, The
text: Sent to evaluate the environmental impact of oil drilling in the Arctic, James Hoffman clashes with the drilling crew's chief, who wants to get the job done.

title: Black Sheep
text: An experiment in genetic engineering turns harmless sheep into bloodthirsty killers that terrorize a sprawling New Zealand farm.

title: Edge of Heaven, The
text: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Saw IV
text: Despite Jigsaw's death, and in order to save the lives of two of his colleagues, Lieutenant Rigg is forced to take part in a new game, which promises to test him to the limit.

title: For the Bible Tells Me So
text: An exploration of the intersection between religion and homosexuality in the U.S. and how the religious right has used its interpretation of the Bible to stigmatize the gay community.

title: My Kid Could Paint That
text: A look at the work and surprising success of a four-year-old girl whose paintings have been compared to the likes of Picasso and has raked in hundreds of thousands of dollars.

title: Elite Squad
text: In 1997 Rio de Janeiro, Captain Nascimento has to find a substitute for his position while trying to take down drug dealers and criminals before the Pope visits.

title: King of California
text: An unstable dad who after getting out of a mental institution tries to convince his daughter that there's Spanish gold buried somewhere under suburbia.

title: American Gangster
text: An outcast New York City cop is charged with bringing down Harlem drug lord Frank Lucas, whose real life inspired this partly biographical film.

title: Bee Movie
text: Barry B. Benson, a bee just graduated from college, is disillusioned at his lone career choice: making honey. On a special trip outside the hive, Barry's life is saved by Vanessa, a florist in New York City. As their relationship blossoms, he discovers humans actually eat honey, and subsequently decides to sue them.

title: Before the Devil Knows You're Dead
text: When two brothers organize the robbery of their parents' jewelry store the job goes horribly wrong, triggering a series of events that sends them, their father and one brother's wife hurtling towards a shattering climax.

title: Diving Bell and the Butterfly, The
text: The true story of Elle editor Jean-Dominique Bauby who suffers a stroke and has to live with an almost totally paralyzed body
column9: only his left eye isn't paralyzed.

title: No Country for Old Men
text: Violence and mayhem ensue after a hunter stumbles upon a drug deal gone wrong and more than two million dollars in cash near the Rio Grande.

title: Be Kind Rewind
text: Two bumbling store clerks inadvertently erase the footage from all of the tapes in their video rental store. In order to keep the business running, they re-shoot every film in the store with their own camera, with a budget of zero dollars.

title: Itty Bitty Titty Committee
text: High School grad and all American gal, Anna, finds her purpose and herself after she hooks up with the radical feminists in The Itty Bitty Titty Committee.

title: Fugitive, The
text: Anti-Catholic and anti-cleric policies in the Mexican state of Tabasco lead the revolutionary government to persecute the state's last remaining priest.

title: August Rush
text: An orphaned musical prodigy uses his gift to try to find his birth parents.

title: Man from Earth, The
text: An impromptu goodbye party for Professor John Oldman becomes a mysterious interrogation after the retiring scholar reveals to his colleagues he has a longer and stranger past than they can imagine.

title: Lions For Lambs
text: Injuries sustained by two Army rangers behind enemy lines in Afghanistan set off a sequence of events involving a congressman, a journalist and a professor.

title: Beowulf
text: The warrior Beowulf must fight and defeat the monster Grendel, who is terrorizing Denmark, then Grendel's Mother, who begins killing out of revenge.

title: Southland Tales
text: During a three-day heat wave just before a huge 4th of July celebration, an action star stricken with amnesia meets up with a porn star who is developing her own reality TV project, and a policeman who holds the key to a vast conspiracy.

title: Evening with Kevin Smith 2: Evening Harder, An
text: In this second Q&A with Kevin Smith he now enters the homes of some of his fans in Toronto and London.

title: Harrison Bergeron
text: In a distant future, egalitarianism has created a truly equal state. The cost? The sacrifice of everything great about humankind. The question: is peace worth the price?

title: I Served the King of England
text: A look at the glamorous life at an old-world Prague hotel.

title: Mist, The
text: A freak storm unleashes a species of bloodthirsty creatures on a small town, where a small band of citizens hole up in a supermarket and fight for their lives.

title: Enchanted
text: A young maiden in a land called Andalasia, who is prepared to be wed, is sent away to New York City by an evil Queen, where she falls in love with a lawyer.

title: Hitman
text: A gun-for-hire known only as Agent 47 hired by a group known only as 'The Organization' is ensnared in a political conspiracy, which finds him pursued by both Interpol and the Russian military as he treks across Russia and Eastern Europe.

title: Awake
text: A wealthy young man undergoing heart transplant surgery discovers that the surgical team intend to murder him.

title: Golden Compass, The
text: In a parallel universe, young Lyra Belacqua journeys to the far North to save her best friend and other kidnapped children from terrible experiments by a mysterious organization.

title: I Am Legend
text: Years after a plague kills most of humanity and transforms the rest into monsters, the sole survivor in New York City struggles valiantly to find a cure.

title: Alvin and the Chipmunks
text: Three musical chipmunks are discovered by an aspiring songwriter who wants to use their amazing singing abilities to become famous.

title: Futurama: Bender's Big Score
text: Planet Express sees a hostile takeover and Bender falls into the hands of criminals where he is used to fulfill their schemes.

title: Margot at the Wedding
text: Margot and her son Claude decide to visit her sister Pauline after she announces that she is marrying less-than-impressive Malcolm. In short order, the storm the sisters create leaves behind a mess of thrashed relationships and exposed family secrets.

title: I'm Not There
text: Ruminations on the life of Bob Dylan, where six characters embody a different aspect of the musician's life and work.

title: Savages, The
text: A sister and brother face the realities of familial responsibility as they begin to care for their ailing father.

title: Wrong Turn 2: Dead End
text: A group of reality show contestants find themselves fighting for their survival against a family of hideously deformed inbred cannibals who plan to ruthlessly butcher them all.

title: Orphanage, The
text: A woman brings her family back to her childhood home, which used to be an orphanage for handicapped children. Before long, her son starts to communicate with an invisible new friend.

title: Juno
text: Faced with an unplanned pregnancy, an offbeat young woman makes an unusual decision regarding the unborn child.

title: Maxed Out: Hard Times, Easy Credit and the Era of Predatory Lenders
text: When Hurricane Katrina ravaged America's Gulf Coast, it laid bare an uncomfortable reality-America is not only far from the world's wealthiest nation; it is crumbling beneath a staggering burden of individual and government debt. Maxed Out takes us on a journey deep inside the American debt-style, where everything seems okay as long as the minimum monthly payment arrives on time. Sure, most of us may have that sinking feeling that something isn't quite right, but we're told not to worry. After all, there's always more credit! Maxed Out shows how the modern financial industry really works, explains the true definition of "preferred customer" and tells us why the poor are getting poorer and the rich getting richer. By turns hilarious and profoundly disturbing, Maxed Out paints a picture of a national nightmare which is all too real for most of us.

title: My Blueberry Nights
text: A young lonely woman takes a soul-searching journey across America to resolve her questions about love while encountering a series of offbeat characters along the way.

title: Helvetica
text: A documentary about typography, graphic design, and global visual culture.

title: Bucket List, The
text: Two terminally ill men escape from a cancer ward and head off on a road trip with a wish list of to-dos before they die.

title: Kite Runner, The
text: After spending years in California, Amir returns to his homeland in Afghanistan to help his old friend Hassan, whose son is in trouble.

title: Deaths of Ian Stone, The
text: An all-American guy is murdered each day by horrifying pursuers, only to wake up in slightly different lives to experience the terror of being murdered again.

title: Wristcutters: A Love Story
text: A film set in a strange afterlife way station that has been reserved for people who have committed suicide.

title: Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street
text: The infamous story of Benjamin Barker, aka Sweeney Todd, who sets up a barber shop in London which is the basis for a sinister partnership with his fellow tenant, Mrs. Lovett.

title: National Treasure: Book of Secrets
text: Benjamin Gates must follow a clue left in John Wilkes Booth's diary to prove his ancestor's innocence in the assassination of Abraham Lincoln.

title: There Will Be Blood
text: A story of family, religion, hatred, oil and madness, focusing on a turn-of-the-century prospector in the early days of the business.

title: Charlie Wilson's War
text: A drama based on a Texas congressman Charlie Wilson's covert dealings in Afghanistan, where his efforts to assist rebels in their war with the Soviets have some unforeseen and long-reaching effects.

title: AVPR: Aliens vs. Predator - Requiem
text: Warring Alien and Predator races descend on a rural Colorado town, where unsuspecting residents must band together for any chance of survival.

title: Walk Hard: The Dewey Cox Story
text: Singer Dewey Cox overcomes adversity to become a musical legend.

title: As You Like It
text: A daughter of the powerful Duke must show her courage and inventiveness to be with the man she loves.

title: Drained
text: A pawn shop proprietor buys used goods from desperate locals--as much to play perverse power games as for his own livelihood, but when the perfect rump and a backed-up toilet enter his life, he loses all control.

title: Dedication
text: The romantic comedy follows a misogynistic children's book author who is forced to work closely with a female illustrator instead of his long-time collaborator and only friend.

title: Water Horse: Legend of the Deep, The
text: A lonely boy discovers a mysterious egg that hatches a sea creature of Scottish legend.

title: Battlestar Galactica: Razor
text: A two-hour Battlestar Galactica special that tells the story of the Battlestar Pegasus several months prior to it finding the Galactica.

title: P.S. I Love You
text: A young widow discovers that her late husband has left her 10 messages intended to help ease her pain and start a new life.

title: 27 Dresses
text: After serving as a bridesmaid 27 times, a young woman wrestles with the idea of standing by her sister's side as her sibling marries the man she's secretly in love with.

title: Cassandra's Dream
text: The tale of two brothers with serious financial woes. When a third party proposes they turn to crime, things go badly and the two become enemies.

title: Like Stars on Earth
text: An eight-year-old boy is thought to be a lazy trouble-maker, until the new art teacher has the patience and compassion to discover the real problem behind his struggles in school.

title: Band's Visit, The
text: A band comprised of members of the Egyptian police force head to Israel to play at the inaugural ceremony of an Arab arts center, only to find themselves lost in the wrong town.

title: [REC]
text: A television reporter and cameraman follow emergency workers into a dark apartment building and are quickly locked inside with something terrifying.

title: In the Name of the King: A Dungeon Siege Tale
text: A man named Farmer sets out to rescue his kidnapped wife and avenge the death of his son, two acts committed by the Krugs, a race of animal-warriors who are controlled by the evil Gallian.

title: Cloverfield
text: A group of friends venture deep into the streets of New York on a rescue mission during a rampaging monster attack.

title: Hatchet
text: When a group of tourists in a New Orleans haunted swamp tour find themselves stranded in the wilderness, their evening of fun and spooks turns into a horrific nightmare.

title: Heaven and Earth
text: In 16th century Japan, two samurai engage in massive battles across the countryside; one attempting to conquer and the other attempting to defend his land while repressing his love for a woman after taking a vow of celibacy.

title: Cat Soup
text: A young anthropomorphic cat goes on a psychedelic journey with his sister in order to save her soul.

title: Girl Who Leapt Through Time, The
text: A high-school girl named Makoto acquires the power to travel back in time, and decides to use it for her own personal benefits. Little does she know that she is affecting the lives of others just as much as she is her own.

title: First Sunday
text: 2 bungling, petty criminal BFFs try to rob a church, but someone from staff beat them to it. They spend the night with the church staff to get the money.

title: Untraceable
text: FBI agent Jennifer Marsh is tasked with hunting down a seemingly untraceable serial killer who posts live videos of his victims on the Internet. As time runs out, the cat and mouse chase becomes more personal.

title: Rambo
text: In Thailand, John Rambo joins a group of mercenaries to venture into war-torn Burma, and rescue a group of Christian aid workers who were kidnapped by the ruthless local infantry unit.

title: Meet the Spartans
text: A spoof of 300  and many other movies, TV series/shows/commercials, video games and celebrities. King Leonidas of Sparta and his army of 12 go to war against Xerxes of Persia to fight to the death for Sparta's freedom.

title: Strange Wilderness
text: With the ratings dropping for a wilderness-themed television show, two animal fans go to the Andes Mountains in search of Bigfoot.

title: Signal, The
text: A horror film told in three parts, from three perspectives, in which a mysterious transmission that turns people into killers invades every cell phone, radio, and television.

title: Hellboy II: The Golden Army
text: A prince of the mythical world starts a rebellion against humanity in order to rule the Earth, and Hellboy his team must fight to stop him from locating the all-powerful Golden Army.

title: In Bruges
text: Guilt-stricken after a job gone wrong, hitman Ray and his partner await orders from their ruthless boss in Bruges, Belgium, the last place in the world Ray wants to be.

title: World on a Wire
text: Somewhere in the future there is a computer project called Simulacron one of which is able to simulate a full featured reality, when suddenly project leader Henry Vollmer dies. His successor Dr. Fred Stiller experiences odd phenomena. A good friend, Guenther Lause, disappears in the middle of a conversation and a week later nobody has ever heard of him. And those fits of dizzyness - Stiller cannot believe himself to be fool. There has to be an explanation for all this. Could Simulacron have something to do with it?

title: Rise of the Footsoldier
text: The life of career criminal Carlton Leach.

title: Teeth
text: Still a stranger to her own body, a high school student discovers she has a physical advantage when she becomes the object of male violence.

title: Fool's Gold
text: A new clue to the whereabouts of a lost treasure rekindles a married couple's sense of adventure -- and their estranged romance.

title: Jumper
text: A teenager with teleportation abilities suddenly finds himself in the middle of an ancient war between those like him and their sworn annihilators.

title: Definitely, Maybe
text: A political consultant tries to explain his impending divorce and past relationships to his 11-year-old daughter.

title: Air I Breathe, The
text: A drama based on an ancient Chinese proverb that breaks life down into four emotional cornerstones: happiness, pleasure, sorrow and love. A businessman bets his life on a horse race; a gangster sees the future; a pop star falls prey to a crime boss; a doctor must save the love of his life.

title: Vantage Point
text: The attempted assassination of the American President is told and re-told from several different perspectives.

title: Spiderwick Chronicles, The
text: Upon moving into the run-down Spiderwick Estate with their mother, twin brothers Jared and Simon Grace, along with their sister Mallory, find themselves pulled into an alternate world full of faeries and other creatures.

title: Step Up 2 the Streets
text: Romantic sparks occur between two dance students from different backgrounds at the Maryland School of the Arts.

title: Other Boleyn Girl, The
text: Two sisters contend for the affection of King Henry VIII.

title: Semi-Pro
text: Jackie Moon, the owner-coach-player of the American Basketball Association's Flint Michigan Tropics, rallies his teammates to make their NBA dreams come true.

title: Run Fatboy Run
text: Five years after jilting his pregnant fiancée on their wedding day, out-of-shape Dennis decides to run a marathon to win her back.

title: Taxi to the Dark Side
text: Alex Gibney exposes the haunting details of the USA's torture and interrogation practices during the War in Afghanistan.

title: Descent
text: A college co-ed is brutally raped and struggles alone to rebuild her life.

title: College Road Trip
text: When an overachieving high school student decides to travel around the country to choose the perfect college, her overprotective cop father decides to accompany her to keep her on the straight and narrow.

title: 10,000 BC
text: In the prehistoric past, D'Leh is a mammoth hunter who bonds with the beautiful Evolet. When warriors on horseback capture Evolet and the tribesmen, D'Leh must embark on an odyssey to save his true love.

title: Bank Job, The
text: Martine offers Terry a lead on a foolproof bank hit on London's Baker Street. She targets a roomful of safe deposit boxes worth millions in cash and jewelry along with a treasure trove of dirty secrets.

title: Doomsday
text: A futuristic action thriller where a team of people work to prevent a disaster threatening the future of the human race.

title: Horton Hears a Who!
text: Horton the Elephant struggles to protect a microscopic community from his neighbors who refuse to believe it exists.

title: Funny Games U.S.
text: Two psychopathic young men take a family hostage in their cabin.

title: Counterfeiters, The
text: The story of the Operation Bernhard, the largest counterfeiting operation in history, carried out by Germany during WWII.

title: Mongol
text: The story recounts the early life of Genghis Khan who was a slave before going on to conquer half the world in 1206.

title: War Dance
text: Three children living in a displacement camp in northern Uganda compete in their country's national music and dance festival.

title: Love Guru, The
text: Pitka, an American raised outside of his country by gurus, returns to the States in order to break into the self-help business. His first challenge is to settle the romantic troubles and subsequent professional skid of a star hockey player whose wife left him for a rival athlete.

title: Diary of the Dead
text: A group of young film students run into real-life zombies while filming a horror movie of their own.

title: Penelope
text: A modern romantic tale about a young aristocratic heiress born under a curse that can only be broken when she finds true love with "one who will accept her as one of their own."

title: City of Men
text: Best buddies Acerola and Laranjinha, about to turn 18, discover things about their missing fathers' pasts which will shatter their solid friendship, in the middle of a war between rival drug gangs from Rio's favelas.

title: Zeitgeist: The Movie
text: Mythology and belief in society today, presenting uncommon perspectives of common cultural issues.

title: Justice League: The New Frontier
text: In the 1950s, a new generation of superheroes must join forces with the community's active veterans and a hostile US government to fight a menace to Earth.

title: Heima
text: In the summer of 2006, Sigur Rós returned home to play a series of free, unannounced concerts for the people of Iceland.

title: Snow Angels
text: A drama that interweaves the life of a teenager, with his old baby sitter, her estranged husband, and their daughter.

title: Class, The
text: An average guy of an Estonian high-school decides to defend his bullied classmate. This starts war between him and the informal leader of the class. As teenagers' honour is a touchy thing, everything ends in bloodshed.

title: Dark Knight, The
text: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

title: Never Back Down
text: A frustrated and conflicted teenager arrives at a new high school to discover an underground fight club and meet a classmate who begins to coerce him into fighting.

title: Drillbit Taylor
text: Three kids hire a low-budget bodyguard to protect them from the playground bully.

title: Youth Without Youth
text: A love story wrapped in a mystery. Set in World War II Europe, a professor is changed by a cataclysmic event and explores the mysteries of life.
"21" is the fact-based story about six MIT students who were trained to become experts in card counting and subsequently took Vegas casinos for millions in winnings.

title: Smart People
text: Into the life of a widowed professor comes a new love and an unexpected visit from his adopted brother.

title: Shepherd: Border Patrol, The
text: A former New Orleans cop battles drug cartels and ex-Army Special Forces who are smuggling drugs from Mexico into U.S. through a Texas border town.

title: Leatherheads
text: In 1925, an enterprising pro football player convinces America's too-good-to-be-true college football hero to play for his team and keep the league from going under.

title: Assembly
text: A soldier fights to gain recognition for comrades who died during the Chinese Civil War.

title: Zebraman
text: A down-and-out school teacher receives the calling to become the real life personification of an old television superhero, Zebraman.

title: Stop-Loss
text: A veteran soldier returns from his completed tour of duty in Iraq, only to find his life turned upside down when he is arbitrarily ordered to return to field duty by the Army.

title: Shine a Light
text: A career-spanning documentary on The Rolling Stones, with concert footage from their "A Bigger Bang" tour.

title: Inside
text: Four months after the death of her husband, a woman on the brink of motherhood is tormented in her home by a strange woman who wants her unborn baby.

title: Nim's Island
text: A young girl inhabits an isolated island with her scientist father and communicates with a reclusive author of the novel she's reading.

title: Ruins, The
text: A leisurely Mexican holiday takes a turn for the worse when a group of friends and a fellow tourist embark on a remote archaeological dig in the jungle, where something evil lives among the ruins.

title: Forgetting Sarah Marshall
text: Devastated Peter takes a Hawaiian vacation in order to deal with the recent break-up with his TV star girlfriend, Sarah. Little does he know, Sarah's traveling to the same resort as her ex - and she's bringing along her new boyfriend.

title: Superhero Movie
text: Orphaned high school student Rick Riker is bitten by a radioactive dragonfly, develops super powers , and becomes a hero.

title: Street Kings
text: An undercover cop, disillusioned by the death of his wife, is implicated in the murder of an officer and must struggle to clear himself.

title: Visitor, The
text: A college professor travels to New York City to attend a conference and finds a young couple living in his apartment.

title: Harold & Kumar Escape from Guantanamo Bay
text: After being mistaken for terrorists and thrown into Guantánamo Bay, stoners Harold and Kumar escape and return to the U.S., where they proceed to flee across the country with federal agents in hot pursuit.

title: 99 francs
text: The life of Octave Parango, a flamboyant ad designer, filled with success, satire, misery and love.

title: Speed Racer
text: Young driver Speed Racer aspires to be champion of the racing world with the help of his family and his high-tech Mach 5 automobile.

title: Forbidden Kingdom, The
text: A discovery made by a kung fu obsessed American teen sends him on an adventure to China, where he joins up with a band of martial arts warriors in order to free the imprisoned Monkey King.

title: Happy-Go-Lucky
text: A look at a few chapters in the life of Poppy, a cheery, colorful, North London schoolteacher whose optimism tends to exasperate those around her.

title: Religulous
text: Bill Maher's take on the current state of world religion.

title: Outpost
text: In war-torn Eastern Europe, a mysterious businessman hires a group of mercenaries on a routine mission to protect him not knowing of the long-hidden secret that lies there.

title: Are You Scared?
text: Six kidnapped teens awake in an abandoned factory to discover they're being filmed for a twisted and terrifying reality show.

title: Son of Rambow
text: During a long English summer in the early 1980s, two schoolboys from differing backgrounds set out to make a film inspired by First Blood .

title: Super High Me
text: Stand up comedian and marijuana user Doug Benson documents thirty days of pot free living and thirty days of non-stop use to compare the effects of both.

title: Outsourced
text: After his entire department is outsourced, an American novelty products salesman  heads to India to train his replacement.

title: Baby Mama
text: A successful, single businesswoman who dreams of having a baby discovers she is infertile and hires a working class woman to be her unlikely surrogate.

title: Expelled: No Intelligence Allowed
text: Ben Stein examines the issue of academic freedom and decides that there is none when it comes to the debate over intelligent design.

title: Prom Night
text: Donna's senior prom is supposed to be the best night of her life, though a sadistic killer from her past has different plans for her and her friends.

title: Iron Man
text: After being held captive in an Afghan cave, billionaire engineer Tony Stark creates a unique weaponized suit of armor to fight evil.

title: Made of Honor
text: A guy in love with an engaged woman tries to win her over after she asks him to be her maid of honor.

title: Redbelt
text: A fateful event leads to a job in the film business for top mixed-martial arts instructor Mike Terry. Though he refuses to participate in prize bouts, circumstances conspire to force him to consider entering such a competition.

title: Taken
text: A retired CIA agent travels across Europe and relies on his old skills to save his estranged daughter, who has been kidnapped while on a trip to Paris.

title: Fall, The
text: In a hospital on the outskirts of 1920s Los Angeles, an injured stuntman begins to tell a fellow patient, a little girl with a broken arm, a fantastic story of five mythical heroes. Thanks to his fractured state of mind and her vivid imagination, the line between fiction and reality blurs as the tale advances.

title: What Happens in Vegas...
text: A man and a woman are compelled, for legal reasons, to live life as a couple for a limited period of time. At stake is a large amount of money.

title: American Pie Presents Beta House
text: Erik and Cooze start college and pledge the Beta House fraternity, presided over by none other than legendary Dwight Stifler.

title: Bella
text: A chef with a mysterious past spends the day with a waitress who needs a friend.

title: Chronicles of Narnia: Prince Caspian, The
text: The Pevensie siblings return to Narnia, where they are enlisted to once again help ward off an evil king and restore the rightful heir to the land's throne, Prince Caspian.

title: Shelter
text: When his college dreams are sidelined by family obligations, a young man finds comfort in surfing with his best friend's brother.

title: Girl Next Door, The
text: Follows the unspeakable torture and abuses committed on a teenage girl in the care of her aunt and the boys who witness and fail to report the crime.

title: Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull
text: In 1957, archaeologist and adventurer Dr. Henry "Indiana" Jones, Jr. is called back into action and becomes entangled in a Soviet plot to uncover the secret behind mysterious artifacts known as the Crystal Skulls.

title: Nina's Heavenly Delights
text: A feisty young woman returns to Glasgow to run her deceased father's curry house.

title: Sex and the City
text: A New York City writer on sex and love is finally getting married to her Mr. Big. But her three best girlfriends must console her after one of them inadvertently leads Mr. Big to jilt her.

title: Strangers, The
text: A young couple staying in an isolated vacation home are terrorized by three unknown assailants.

title: Bigger, Stronger, Faster*
text: An examination of America's win-at-all-cost culture from the perspective of bodybuilding and performance enhancing drugs, as it focuses on a pair of siblings chasing their dream.

title: All the Boys Love Mandy Lane
text: A group of high-schoolers invite Mandy Lane, an innocent, desirable girl, to a weekend party on a secluded ranch. While the festivities rage on, the number of revelers begins to drop mysteriously.

title: Kung Fu Panda
text: To everyone's surprise, including his own, Po, an overweight, clumsy panda, is chosen as protector of the Valley of Peace. His suitability will soon be tested as the valley's arch-enemy is on his way.

title: Recount
text: A chronicle of the weeks after the 2000 U.S. Presidential election, and the subsequent recounts in Florida.

title: Ex Drummer
text: Three handicapped losers who form a band ask famous writer Dries to be their drummer. He joins the band and starts manipulating them.

title: You Don't Mess with the Zohan
text: An Israeli Special Forces Soldier fakes his death so he can re-emerge in New York City as a hair stylist.

title: Stuck
text: A young woman commits a hit-and-run, then finds her fate tied to her victim.

title: Protector, The
text: Two New York City cops, Billy Wong and Danny Garoni, head to Hong Kong after the daughter of a rich businessman is kidnapped by the drug lord, Mr. Ko.

title: Chaos Theory
text: The story of an obsessively organized efficiency expert whose life unravels in unexpected ways when fate forces him to explore the serendipitous nature of love and forgiveness.

title: Boy A
text: The story of a young Jack, newly released from serving a prison sentence for a violent crime he committed as a child.

title: Spiral
text: A recluse telemarkets at an office, where his boss is his only friend. As he befriends a new, social colleague and sketches/paints her, his dark mind surfaces.

title: Happening, The
text: A science teacher, his wife, and a young girl struggle to survive a plague that causes those infected to commit suicide.

title: Incredible Hulk, The
text: Bruce Banner, a scientist on the run from the U.S. Government, must find a cure for the monster he turns into whenever he loses his temper.

title: Children of Huang Shi, The
text: About young British journalist, George Hogg, who with the assistance of a courageous Australian nurse, saves a group of orphaned children during the Japanese occupation of China in 1937.

title: WALL·E
text: In the distant future, a small waste-collecting robot inadvertently embarks on a space journey that will ultimately decide the fate of mankind.

title: Wanted
text: A frustrated office worker discovers that he is the son of a professional assassin, and that he shares his father's superhuman killing abilities.

title: Hancock
text: Hancock is a superhero whose ill-considered behavior regularly causes damage in the millions. He changes when the person he saves helps him improve his public image.

title: Get Smart
text: Maxwell Smart, a highly intellectual but bumbling spy working for the CONTROL agency, is tasked with preventing a terrorist attack from rival spy agency KAOS.

title: Young People Fucking
text: On a Tuesday night, five couples have separate sexual adventures.

title: St. Trinian's
text: In order to save their bankrupt school, a group of troublesome girls stage a robbery with a group of geniuses on their backs

title: Futurama: The Beast with a Billion Backs
text: The Planet Express crew discovers a tentacle-covered, planet-sized alien that wishes to copulate with it all the inhabitants of Earth.

title: Kit Kittredge: An American Girl
text: Set in Cincinnati at the height of the Great Depression, Kit Kittredge, a resourceful young girl, helps her mother run a boardinghouse after her father loses his job.

title: Gonzo: The Life and Work of Dr. Hunter S. Thompson
text: A portrait of the late gonzo journalist Hunter S. Thompson.

title: Wackness, The
text: It's the summer of 1994, and the streets of New York are pulsing with hip-hop. Set against this backdrop, a lonely teenager named Luke Shapiro spends his last summer before university selling marijuana throughout New York City, trading it with his unorthodox psychotherapist for treatment, while having a crush on his stepdaughter.

title: Strange Circus
text: The erotic novelist Taeko is writing a morbid story of a family destroyed by incest, murder and abuse. Her assistant, Yuji, sets on a mission to uncover the reality of this story, but the reality might be too much to bear.

title: Encounters at the End of the World
text: Film-maker Werner Herzog travels to the McMurdo Station in Antarctica, looking to capture the continent's beauty and investigate the characters living there.

title: Zombie Strippers!
text: A zombie epidemic spreads throughout a strip club in Nebraska.

title: Frosty the Snowman
text: A living snowman and a little girl struggle to elude a greedy magician who is after the snowman's magic hat.

title: Battle for Haditha
text: An investigation of the massacre of 24 men, women and children in Haditha, Iraq allegedly shot by 4 U.S. Marines in retaliation for the death of a U.S. Marine killed by a roadside bomb. The movie follows the story of the Marines of Kilo Company, an Iraqi family, and the insurgents who plant the roadside bomb.

title: Mamma Mia!
text: The story of a bride-to-be trying to find her real father told using hit songs by the popular 1970s group ABBA.

title: Welcome to the Sticks
text: A French public servant from Provence is banished to the far North. Strongly prejudiced against this cold and inhospitable place, he leaves his family behind to relocate temporarily there, with the firm intent to quickly come back.

title: Rogue
text: An American journalist on assignment in the Australian outback encounters a man-eating crocodile while trapped on a rapidly flooding mud island.

title: It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown
text: The Peanuts gang celebrates Halloween while Linus waits for the Great Pumpkin.

title: Journey to the Center of the Earth
text: On a quest to find out what happened to his missing brother, a scientist, his nephew and their mountain guide discover a fantastic and dangerous lost world in the center of the earth.

title: Meet Dave
text: A crew of miniature aliens operate a spaceship that has a human form. While trying to save their planet, the aliens encounter a new problem, as their ship becomes smitten with an Earth woman.

title: Machine Girl, The
text: Maimed while seeking revenge, a girl becomes stronger than ever.

title: Shrooms
text: A group of friends are stalked and murdered whilst looking for psilocybin mushrooms in the Irish woods.

title: Transsiberian
text: A Transsiberian train journey from China to Moscow becomes a thrilling chase of deception and murder when an American couple encounters a mysterious pair of fellow travelers.

title: Stargate: Continuum
text: Ba'al travels back in time and prevents the Stargate program from being started. SG-1 must somehow restore history.

title: Watchmen
text: In 1985 where former superheroes exist, the murder of a colleague sends active vigilante Rorschach into his own sprawling investigation, uncovering something that could completely change the course of history as we know it.

title: Shotgun Stories
