title: Single Man, A
text: An English professor, one year after the sudden death of his boyfriend, is unable to cope with his typical days in 1960s Los Angeles.

title: Lovely Bones, The
text: Centers on a young girl who has been murdered and watches over her family - and her killer - from purgatory. She must weigh her desire for vengeance against her desire for her family to heal.

title: Invictus
text: Nelson Mandela, in his first term as President of South Africa, initiates a unique venture to unite the Apartheid-torn land: enlist the national rugby team on a mission to win the 1995 Rugby World Cup.

title: Princess and the Frog, The
text: A waitress, desperate to fulfill her dreams as a restaurant owner, is set on a journey to turn a frog prince back into a human being, but she has to face the same problem after she kisses him.

title: Peacekeeper, The
text: When a terrorist group steals the US President's personal communications computer for launching the US arsenal in case of war, only a heroic Major has the key to prevent a Presidential assassination or a nuclear holocaust.

title: Did You Hear About the Morgans?
text: In New York City, an estranged couple who witness a murder are relocated to small town Wyoming as part of the Witness Protection Program.

title: Snow White
text: Snow White is a motherless princess, who arouses the jealousy and hatred of Mary Jane, her mother's former lady-in-waiting, who is the ugliest woman in the kingdom, but aspires to the throne. She gives her heart to the witch, Hex, in return for which she becomes beautiful and wins the love of the king. While hunting, the king falls from his horse and is killed, leaving Mary Jane, who has been rechristened Brangomar, upon the throne. Brangomar forces Snow White to work in the kitchen and takes her lovely clothes away from her. When Snow White accidentally meets a young hunter she becomes interested in him and he is fascinated, though neither has any idea who the other is. So they are dumbfounded when he comes to Snow White's castle and presents a letter to the queen, asking for the hand of Snow White, for he is the Prince Florimund, who has been sent to ask for the hard of the little princess, whom he has never seen. Brangomar, who believed that the prince was coming to sue for her hand, is furious. She decides to kill the little girl and forces old Berthold, a hunter, and Snow White's devoted slave, to promise to kill the child. He is to bring her the heart of Snow White as proof of his act. Berthold takes Snow White into the woods and tells her what he has been forced to promise and she tells him to kill a pig and take its heart back to the queen. While he is doing this, a bird leads Snow White to the cabin of the seven little dwarfs, where she wins their undying gratitude. When the queen discovers that Snow White has escaped her, she tries to kill her with a magic comb and then inveigles her into biting a poisoned apple. Snow White falls prostrate and is discovered by the dwarfs, who carry her body in state to the palace, where the queen rejoices until the furious Prince Florimund threatens to kill her. In the excitement the dwarfs drop the casket, in which there lies the body of Snow White, and she awakens. The apple had stuck in her throat and she had not swallowed it. The witch turns Brangomar into a peacock and all ends happily.

title: Alice
text: Everything you know about Alice's Adventures in Wonderland is about to be turned upside down in this modern-day mini-series. The cast includes Kathy Bates, Caterina Scorsone, Matt Frewer, Harry Dean Stanton, and Tim Curry.

title: Avatar
text: A paraplegic Marine dispatched to the moon Pandora on a unique mission becomes torn between following his orders and protecting the world he feels is his home.

title: It's Complicated
text: When attending their son's college graduation, a couple reignite the spark in their relationship. But the complicated fact is they're divorced and he's remarried.

title: Sherlock Holmes
text: Detective Sherlock Holmes and his stalwart partner Watson engage in a battle of wits and brawn with a nemesis whose plot is a threat to all of England.

title: Crazy Heart
text: A faded country music musician is forced to reassess his dysfunctional life during a doomed romance that also inspires him.

title: Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel
text: The world-famous singing preteen chipmunk trio return to contend with the pressures of school, celebrity, and a rival female music group known as The Chipettes.

title: American Pie Presents: The Book of Love
text: Ten years after the first American Pie movie, three new hapless virgins discover the Bible hidden in the school library at East Great Falls High.

title: Sorority Babes in the Slimeball Bowl-O-Rama
text: As part of a sorority ritual, pledges and their male companions steal a trophy from a bowling alley; unbeknownst to them, it contains a devilish imp who makes their lives a living Hell.

title: Pontypool
text: A radio host interprets the possible outbreak of a deadly virus which infects the small Ontario town he is stationed in.

title: Youth in Revolt
text: While his trailer trash parents teeter on the edge of divorce, Nick Twisp sets his sights on dream girl Sheeni Saunders, hoping that she'll be the one to take away his virginity.

title: Daybreakers
text: In the year 2019, a plague has transformed almost every human into vampires. Faced with a dwindling blood supply, the fractured dominant race plots their survival; meanwhile, a researcher works with a covert band of vamps on a way to save humankind.

title: Hachiko: A Dog's Story
text: A college professor bonds with an abandoned dog he takes into his home.

title: Leap Year
text: Anna Brady plans to travel to Dublin, Ireland to propose to her boyfriend Jeremy on February 29, leap day, because, according to Irish tradition, a man who receives a marriage proposal on a leap day must accept it.

title: Book of Eli, The
text: A post-apocalyptic tale, in which a lone man fights his way across America in order to protect a sacred book that holds the secrets to saving humankind.

title: Girl Who Kicked the Hornet's Nest, The
text: Lisbeth is recovering in a hospital and awaiting trial for three murders when she is released. Mikael must prove her innocence, but Lisbeth must be willing to share the details of her sordid experiences with the court.

title: Prophet, A
text: A young Algerian man is sent to a French prison.

title: Staten Island
text: The lives of three residents of New York's Staten Island intersect as they struggle to get ahead.

title: Maiden Heist, The
text: A comedy centered on three museum security guards who devise a plan to steal back the artworks to which they have become attached after they are transferred to another museum.

title: Blood: The Last Vampire
text: A vampire named Saya, who is part of covert government agency that hunts and destroys demons in a post-WWII Japan, is inserted in a military school to discover which one of her classmates is a demon in disguise.

title: MacGyver: Lost Treasure of Atlantis
text: MacGyver and his former college professor are first hunting some artifacts attributed to Zenon, an ancient scientist from Atlantis, and later the lost city of Atlantis itself.

title: Bart Got a Room
text: While Danny's father and mother independently search for love, Danny is on his own desperate quest to find a prom date. Danny's search becomes progressively more pathetic once he and his family learn that Bart, the school's biggest dweeb, not only secured a date for the prom, but got a hotel room as well.

title: Project A 2
text: Dragon is now transferred to be the police head of Sai Wan district, and has to contend with a gangster kingpin, anti-Manchu revolutionaries, some runaway pirates, Manchu Loyalists and a corrupt Police Superintendent.

title: Robin-B-Hood
text: Thongs and Octopus accept a job from their landlord: kidnap a baby. Soon, the baby awakens strong paternal feelings in the two crooks, leading to complications when it comes to handing him over to his possibly crazy gang boss grandfather.

title: Concert, Le
text: Thirty years ago Bolshoi Orchestra conductor Andreï Filipov was fired for hiring Jewish musicians. Now a lowly janitor, an opportunity arises to gather his old musicians to go and pose as the official Buolshoi orchestra in Paris.

title: Ninja
text: A westerner named Casey, studying Ninjutsu in Japan, is asked by the Sensei to return to New York to protect the legendary Yoroi Bitsu, an armored chest that contains the weapons of the last Koga Ninja.

title: Asterix at the Olympic Games
text: Astérix and Obélix compete at the Olympics in order to help their friend Lovesix marry Princess Irina. Brutus also tries to win the game with his own team and get rid of his father Julius Caesar.

title: Chaser, The
text: A disgraced ex-policeman who runs a small ring of prostitutes finds himself in a race against time when one of his women goes missing.

title: Meantime
text: When one brother gets a job from their wealthy aunt, the other becomes increasingly jealous.

title: Rudolph, the Red-Nosed Reindeer
text: A misfit reindeer and his friends look for a place that will accept them.

title: Dennis the Menace Christmas, A
text: To make sure that his beloved neighbour, Mr Wilson, has the perfect Christmas, the neighbourhood's lively six-year-old boy, Dennis Mitchell, makes a long list of things one needs to make it work. However, is Mr Wilson willing to change?

title: Undisputed II: Last Man Standing
text: Sequel to the 2002 film. This time, Heavyweight Champ George "Iceman" Chambers is sent to a Russian Jail on trumped-up drug charges.

title: 3 Idiots
text: Two friends are searching for their long lost companion. They revisit their college days and recall the memories of their friend who inspired them to think differently, even as the rest of the world called them "idiots".

title: Legion
text: When a group of strangers at a dusty roadside diner come under attack by demonic forces, their only chance for survival lies with an archangel named Michael, who informs a pregnant waitress that her unborn child is humanity's last hope.

title: Stan Helsing
text: A spoof on many horror movie series. Ending his shift at the video rental, Stan's picked up by his BFF and 2 cute girls, all going to a Halloween party. Will they even get there?

title: Peter Pan
text: In this magical tale about the boy who refuses to grow up, Peter Pan and his mischievous fairy sidekick Tinkerbell visit the nursery of Wendy, Michael, and John Darling.

title: Wicked City
text: Two agents, a lady-killer human and a voluptuous demon, attempt to protect a signatory to a peace treaty between the human world and the demon world from radicalized demons.

title: When in Rome
text: Beth is a young, ambitious New Yorker who is completely unlucky in love. However, on a whirlwind trip to Rome, she impulsively steals some coins from a reputed fountain of love, and is then aggressively pursued by a band of suitors.

title: Dream of Light
text: The artist Antonio López tries to capture the sunlight hitting his quince tree all autumn, but the struggle seems futile.

title: Triangle
text: Yacht passengers encounter mysterious weather conditions that force them to jump onto another ship, only to have the odd havoc increase.

title: I Love You Phillip Morris
text: A cop turns con man once he comes out of the closet. Once imprisoned, he meets the second love of his life, whom he'll stop at nothing to be with.

title: Anne of Green Gables: The Sequel
text: Anne Shirley accepts a teaching position at a girls boarding school in a town dominated by a rich and belligerant family determined to make her life miserable.

title: Temple Grandin
text: A biopic of Temple Grandin, an autistic woman who has become one of the top scientists in the humane livestock handling industry.

title: Captain Newman, M.D.
text: In 1944, an Army doctor is in charge of a neuropsychiatric ward at an Army Air Corps hospital in Arizona, and he must deal with a variety of tough cases.

title: House of the Devil, The
text: In 1983, financially struggling college student Samantha Hughes takes a strange babysitting job that coincides with a full lunar eclipse. She slowly realizes her clients harbor a terrifying secret, putting her life in mortal danger.

title: Valentine's Day
text: Intertwining couples and singles in Los Angeles break-up and make-up based on the pressures and expectations of Valentine's Day.

title: Wolfman, The
text: Upon his return to his ancestral homeland, an American man is bitten, and subsequently cursed by, a werewolf.

title: Shutter Island
text: In 1954, a U.S. Marshal investigates the disappearance of a murderer who escaped from a hospital for the criminally insane.

title: Persuasion
text: Anne was in love with Frederick, who was rejected by her snobby parents 8 years ago. They've now hit hard times and rent out their mansion to his brother-in-law. He returns a Royal Navy captain. Will he remember Anne?

title: Girl Who Played with Fire, The
text: As computer hacker Lisbeth and journalist Mikael investigate a sex-trafficking ring, Lisbeth is accused of three murders, causing her to go on the run while Mikael works to clear her name.

title: Percy Jackson & the Olympians: The Lightning Thief
text: A teenager discovers he's the descendant of a Greek god and sets out on an adventure to settle an on-going battle between the gods.

title: Cop Out
text: Jimmy's rare baseball card is robbed. Since it's his only hope to pay for his daughter's upcoming wedding, he recruits his cop partner Paul to track down the robber, a memorabilia-obsessed gangster.

title: Ghost Writer, The
text: A ghost writer, hired to complete the memoirs of a former British Prime Minister, uncovers secrets that put his own life in jeopardy.

title: Secret of Kells, The
text: A young boy in a remote medieval outpost under siege from barbarian raids is beckoned to adventure when a celebrated master illuminator arrives with an ancient book, brimming with secret wisdom and powers.

title: Spy Next Door, The
text: Former C.I.A. spy Bob Ho takes on his toughest assignment to date: looking after his girlfriend's three kids, who haven't exactly warmed to their mom's beau.

title: Agora
text: A historical drama set in Roman Egypt, concerning a slave who turns to the rising tide of Christianity in the hope of pursuing freedom while falling in love with his mistress, the philosophy and mathematics professor Hypatia of Alexandria.

title: Motherhood
text: In Manhattan, a mother of two preparing for her daughter's sixth birthday party has no idea of the challenges she's about to face in order to pull off the event.

title: District 13: Ultimatum
text: Damien and Leito return to District 13 on a mission to bring peace to the troubled sector that is controlled by five different gang bosses, before the city's secret services take drastic measures to solve the problem.

title: Yes Men Fix the World, The
text: Troublemaking duo Andy Bichlbaum and Mike Bonanno, posing as their industrious alter-egos, expose the people profiting from Hurricane Katrina, the faces behind the environmental disaster in Bhopal, and other shocking events.

title: Mike Bassett: England Manager
text: After England's football  manager has a heart attack, Mike Bassett is hired as the new manager and promptly announces the team will win the World Cup.

title: Crazies, The
text: After a strange and insecure plane crash, an unusual toxic virus enters a quaint farming town. A young couple are quarantined, but they fight for survival along with help from a couple of people.

title: Dear John
text: A romantic drama about a soldier who falls for a conservative college student while he's home on leave.

title: Last Train Home
text: A couple embarks on a journey home for Chinese new year along with 130 million other migrant workers, to reunite with their children and struggle for a future. Their unseen story plays out as China soars towards being a world superpower.

title: Tooth Fairy
text: A bad deed on the part of a tough minor-league hockey player results in an unusual sentence: He must serve one week as a real-life tooth fairy.

title: Gentlemen of Fortune
text: It so happens that peaceful kindergarten teacher is incredibly similar to the terrible villain who stole the helmet of Alexander the Great. And villain's accomplices are unexpectedly similar to children - they also need love and care.

title: [REC]²
text: In order to ascertain the current situation inside, a supposed medical officer and a GEO team step into the quarantined and ill-fated apartment building.

title: Room, The
text: Johnny is a successful bank executive who lives quietly in a San Francisco townhouse with his fiancée, Lisa. One day, putting aside any scruple, she seduces Johnny's best friend, Mark. From there, nothing will be the same again.

title: Alice in Wonderland
text: Nineteen-year-old Alice returns to the magical world from her childhood adventure, where she reunites with her old friends and learns of her true destiny: to end the Red Queen's reign of terror.

title: Town Called Panic, A
text: Cowboy and Indian's only wish was to come up with a brilliant idea for Mr Horse's birthday, but when their plan ends up in utter disaster, they'll need to travel the world and back to make things right again.

title: Green Zone
text: Discovering covert and faulty intelligence causes a U.S. Army officer to go rogue as he hunts for Weapons of Mass Destruction in an unstable region.

title: From Paris with Love
text: In Paris, a young employee in the office of the US Ambassador hooks up with an American spy looking to stop a terrorist attack in the city.

title: Dorian Gray
text: A corrupt young man somehow keeps his youthful beauty eternally, but a special painting gradually reveals his inner ugliness to all.

title: Greenberg
text: A man from Los Angeles, who moved to New York years ago, returns to L.A. to figure out his life while he house-sits for his brother. He soon sparks with his brother's assistant.

title: She's Out of My League
text: An average Joe meets the perfect woman, but his lack of confidence and the influence of his friends and family begin to pick away at the relationship.

title: Harry Brown
text: An elderly ex-serviceman and widower looks to avenge his best friend's murder by doling out his own form of justice.

title: Remember Me
text: A romantic drama centered on two new lovers: Tyler, whose parents have split in the wake of his brother's suicide, and Ally, who lives each day to the fullest since witnessing her mother's murder.

title: Burrowers, The
text: In the Wild West a rescue party sets out to find a family of settlers that has vanished from their home under mysterious circumstances.

title: Frozen
text: Three skiers stranded on a chairlift are forced to make life-or-death choices, which prove more perilous than staying put and freezing to death.

title: Generation X
text: A group of young mutants--humans with a genetic variation that gives them superpowers and makes them feared by the population at large--begin training at a school for heroes. Their studies are interrupted when they must rescue one of their number from a mad scientist who can enter others' dreams.

title: Little Ashes
text: About the young life and loves of artist Salvador Dalí, filmmaker Luis Buñuel and writer Federico García Lorca.

title: Our Family Wedding
text: The weeks leading up to a young couple's wedding are comic and stressful, especially as their respective fathers try to lay their long standing feud to rest.

title: Bounty Hunter, The
text: A bounty hunter learns that his next target is his ex-wife, a reporter working on a murder cover-up. Soon after their reunion, the always-at-odds duo find themselves on a run-for-their-lives adventure.

title: Leaves of Grass
text: An Ivy League professor is lured back to his Oklahoma hometown, where his twin brother, a small-time pot grower, has concocted a scheme to take down a local drug lord.

title: Women in Trouble
text: A serpentine day in the life of ten seemingly desperate women: a porn star, a flight attendant, a psychiatrist, a masseuse, a bartender, a pair of call girls, an actress, a masseuse. All of them with one crucial thing in common. Trouble.

title: Mondo Cane
text: A "shockumentary" consisting of a collection of mostly real archive footage displaying mankind at its most depraved and perverse, displaying bizarre rites, cruel behavior and bestial violence.

title: Repo Men
text: Set in the near future when artificial organs can be bought on credit, it revolves around a man who struggles to make the payments on a heart he has purchased. He must therefore go on the run before said ticker is repossessed.

title: Case 39
text: A social worker fights to save a girl from her abusive parents, only to discover that the situation is more dangerous than she ever expected.

title: Oceans
text: An ecological drama/documentary, filmed throughout the globe. Part thriller, part meditation on the vanishing wonders of the sub-aquatic world.

title: Slammin' Salmon, The
text: The owner of a Miami restaurant indebted to the mob institutes a contest to see what waiter can earn the most money in one night.

title: Hot Tub Time Machine
text: A malfunctioning time machine at a ski resort takes a man back to 1986 with his two friends and nephew, where they must relive a fateful night and not change anything to make sure the nephew is born.

title: Mother
text: A mother desperately searches for the killer who framed her son for a girl's horrific murder.

title: How to Train Your Dragon
text: A hapless young Viking who aspires to hunt dragons becomes the unlikely friend of a young dragon himself, and learns there may be more to the creatures than he assumed.

title: Bone Man, The
text: Private Investigator Brenner is handling a case at the grill-station "Löschenkohl". There he finds - besides some chicken - also other meat...that doesn't belong in a good meal.

title: Micmacs
text: A man and his friends come up with an intricate and original plan to destroy two big weapons manufacturers.

title: Clash of the Titans
text: Perseus, demigod, son of Zeus, battles the minions of the underworld to stop them from conquering heaven and earth.

title: Kick-Ass
text: Dave Lizewski is an unnoticed high school student and comic book fan who one day decides to become a superhero, even though he has no powers, training or meaningful reason to do so.

title: Date Night
text: In New York City, a case of mistaken identity turns a bored married couple's attempt at a glamorous and romantic evening into something more thrilling and dangerous.

title: Emperor's New Groove 2: Kronk's New Groove, The
text: Kronk desperately tries to find ways to impress his dad, whom he can never please. But when things go wrong, Kronk kicks into comical gear and discovers the true riches in life are his friends and being "true to your groove".

title: Steam of Life
text: Finnish men in sauna, speaking straight from the heart.

title: Mortadelo & Filemon: The Big Adventure
text: The DDT, the professor Bacterio's dangerous invention has just been stolen by the dictator of Tirania. The Súper wants to recover it but he knows that it should not call Mortadelo and Filemón, so it sends the case to a boaster detective called Freddy Mazas so that recover the invention, but Freddy is bribed by the dictator Tirano. The mission seems that it will fail although Mortadelo and Filemón investigate the case for their own means.

title: American Drug War: The Last White Hope
text: With commentary from soldiers on both sides of the conflict, filmmaker Kevin Booth's incisive documentary wades into the murky waters of the American war on drugs, the longest and costliest war in U.S. history.

title: Runaways, The
text: A coming-of-age biographical film about the 1970s teenage all-girl rock band The Runaways. The relationship between band members Cherie Currie and Joan Jett is also explored.

title: Wild China
text: An in-depth look at some of China's most impressive natural sites such as the ancient Han kingdom, the Mongol steppes, the Silk Road and the Tibetan Plateau.

title: Death at a Funeral
text: A funeral ceremony turns into a debacle of exposed family secrets and misplaced bodies.

title: Valhalla Rising
text: Forced for some time to be a fighting slave, a pagan warrior escapes his captors with a boy and joins a group of Crusaders on their quest to the Holy Land.

title: Diary of a Wimpy Kid
text: The adventures of a 12 year old who is fresh out of elementary and transitions to middle school, where he has to learn the consequences and responsibility to survive the year.

title: Union: The Business Behind Getting High, The
text: BC's illegal marijuana trade industry has evolved into a business giant, dubbed by some involved as 'The Union', Commanding upwards of $7 billion Canadian annually. With up to 85% of 'BC Bud' being exported to the United States, the trade has become an international issue. Follow filmmaker Adam Scorgie as he demystifies the underground market and brings to light how an industry can function while remaining illegal. Through growers, police officers, criminologists, economists, doctors, politicians and pop culture icons, Scorgie examines the cause and effect nature of the business - an industry that may be profiting more by being illegal.

title: Disgrace
text: After having an affair with a student, a Cape Town professor moves to the Eastern Cape, where he gets caught up in a mess of post-apartheid politics.

title: Losers, The
text: A CIA special forces team is betrayed and left for dead by their superiors, galvanizing them to mount an offensive on the CIA.

title: Last Song, The
text: A rebellious girl is sent to a Southern beach town for the summer to stay with her father. Through their mutual love of music, the estranged duo learn to reconnect.

title: Cyrus
text: John and Molly, a divorced middle aged man and a single mother meet at a friends party and start up a small relationship, all John has to do now is meet Molly's son... Cyrus

title: Human Centipede, The
text: A mad scientist kidnaps and mutilates a trio of tourists in order to reassemble them into a human centipede, created by stitching their mouths to each others' rectums.

title: Exit Through the Gift Shop
text: Following the style of some of the world's most prolific street artists, an amateur filmmaker makes a foray into the art world.

title: Iron Man 2
text: With the world now aware of his identity as Iron Man, Tony Stark must contend with both his declining health and a vengeful mad man with ties to his father's legacy.

title: MacGruber
text: Former special operative MacGruber is called back into action to take down his arch-enemy, Dieter Von Cunth, who's in possession of a nuclear warhead and bent on destroying Washington, D.C.

title: Three Men and a Cradle
text: Jacques, Pierre, and Michel are three adult friends who enjoy single life until they find themselves stuck with a baby.

title: Sky Crawlers, The
text: The Kildren, a group of eternally young fighter pilots, experience the sudden loss of innocence as they battle the enemy in astonishing dogfights above the clouds.

title: Cargo
text: Dr. Laura P. takes a job on a cargo spaceship for 4 years plus 4 years back. She'll join her sister on Rhea. 44 months later, in Laura's shift, strange things happen in cargo. The crew is reanimated and the captain dies mysteriously.

title: Nightmare on Elm Street, A
text: The spectre of a disfigured man haunts the children of the parents who murdered him, stalking and killing them in their dreams.

title: Four Lions
text: Four incompetent British terrorists set out to train for and commit an act of terror.

title: St Trinian's 2: The Legend of Fritton's Gold
text: The girls of St. Trinians are on the hunt for buried treasure after discovering headmistress Miss Fritton is related to a famous pirate.

title: 12 Angry Men
text: Twelve men must decide the fate of one when one juror objects to the jury's decision.

title: Robin Hood
text: In twelfth-century England, Robin Longstride and his band of marauders confront corruption in a local village and lead an uprising against the crown that will forever alter the balance of world power.

title: Lovers & Leavers
text: This movie is about Iiris Vaara. She turns 30 and meets young director Marko. All dreams come true but does Marko share her dreams?

title: Merantau
text: A young man from the countryside uses his skills in silat martial arts to survive the slave trade.

title: Stingray Sam
text: A dangerous mission reunites STINGRAY SAM with his long lost accomplice, The Quasar Kid. Follow these two space convicts as they earn their freedom in exchange for the rescue of a young girl who is being held captive by the genetically designed figurehead of a very wealthy planet.

title: Cemetery Junction
text: A 1970s-set comedy centered on three young working class friends in a dreary suburb of Reading.

title: Blue Valentine
text: The relationship of a contemporary married couple, charting their evolution over a span of years by cross-cutting between time periods.

title: Killers
text: A vacationing woman meets her ideal man, leading to a swift marriage. Back at home, however, their idyllic life is upset when they discover their neighbors could be assassins who have been contracted to kill the couple.

title: Buried
text: Paul is a U.S. truck driver working in Iraq. After an attack by a group of Iraqis he wakes to find he is buried alive inside a coffin. With only a lighter and a cell phone it's a race against time to escape this claustrophobic death trap.

title: Shake Hands with the Devil
text: The story of General Romeo Dallaire's frustrated efforts to stop the madness of the Rwandan Genocide, despite the complete indifference of his superiors.

title: Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time
text: A young fugitive prince and princess must stop a villain who unknowingly threatens to destroy the world with a special dagger that enables the magic sand inside to reverse time.

title: Please Give
text: In New York City, a husband and wife butt heads with the granddaughters of the elderly woman who lives in the apartment the couple owns.

title: Baarìa
text: Baaria is Sicilian slang for Bagheria where Tornatore was born and this is an autobiographic epic of three generations in the Sicilian village where he was born.

title: Ricky Gervais Live: Animals
text: Ricky Gervais entertains a live audience in his first stand-up routine.

title: Sex and the City 2
text: While wrestling with the pressures of life, love, and work in Manhattan, Carrie, Miranda, and Charlotte join Samantha for a trip to Abu Dhabi , where Samantha's ex is filming a new movie.

title: Get Him to the Greek
text: A record company intern is hired to accompany out-of-control British rock star Aldous Snow to a concert at L.A.'s Greek Theater.

title: Unthinkable
text: A psychological thriller centered around a black-ops interrogator and an F.B.I. Agent who press a suspect terrorist into divulging the location of three nuclear weapons set to detonate in the U.S.

title: Back-up Plan, The
text: A woman conceives twins through artificial insemination, then meets the man of her dreams on the very same day.

title: Splice
text: Genetic engineers Clive Nicoli and Elsa Kast hope to achieve fame by successfully splicing together the DNA of different animals to create new hybrid animals for medical use.

title: Letters to Juliet
text: Sophie dreams of becoming a writer and travels to Verona, Italy where she meets the "Secretaries of Juliet".

title: Exam
text: Eight candidates for a highly desirable corporate job are locked together in an exam room and given a final test with just one seemingly simple question. However, it doesn't take long for confusion to ensue and tensions to unravel.

title: Jonah Hex
text: The U.S. military makes a scarred bounty hunter with warrants on his own head an offer he cannot refuse: in exchange for his freedom, he must stop a terrorist who is ready to unleash Hell on Earth.

title: A-Team, The
text: A group of Iraq War veterans look to clear their name with the U.S. Military, who suspect the four men of committing a crime for which they were framed.

title: Toy Story 3
text: The toys are mistakenly delivered to a day-care center instead of the attic right before Andy leaves for college, and it's up to Woody to convince the other toys that they weren't abandoned and to return home.

title: Ricky Gervais Live 3: Fame
text: The third part of Ricky's themed live stand-up shows.

title: Winter's Bone
text: An unflinching Ozark Mountain girl hacks through dangerous social terrain as she hunts down her drug-dealing father while trying to keep her family intact.

title: Scalphunters, The
text: Forced to trade his valuable furs for a well-educated escaped slave, a rugged trapper vows to recover the pelts from the Indians and later the renegades that killed them.

title: Barking Dogs Never Bite
text: An idle part-time college lecturer is annoyed by the yapping sound of a nearby dog. He decides to take drastic action.

title: Shrek Forever After
text: Rumpelstiltskin tricks a mid-life crisis burdened Shrek into allowing himself to be erased from existence and cast in a dark alternate timeline where Rumpelstiltskin rules supreme.

title: TiMER
text: If a clock could count down to the moment you meet your soul mate, would you want to know?

title: Best Worst Movie
text: A look at the making of the film Troll 2  and its journey from being crowned the "worst film of all time" to a cherished cult classic.

title: Twilight Saga: Eclipse, The
text: As a string of mysterious killings grips Seattle, Bella, whose high school graduation is fast approaching, is forced to choose between her love for vampire Edward and her friendship with werewolf Jacob.

title: Enter the Void
text: An American drug dealer living in Tokyo is betrayed by his best friend and killed in a drug deal. His soul, observing the repercussions of his death, seeks resurrection.

title: Last Airbender, The
text: Follows the adventures of Aang, a young successor to a long line of Avatars, who must master all four elements and stop the Fire Nation from enslaving the Water Tribes and the Earth Kingdom.

title: Endgame
text: A story based on the covert discussions that brought down the Apartheid regime in South Africa.

title: Empire of Dreams: The Story of the 'Star Wars' Trilogy
text: An in-depth making of documentary about the original Star Wars trilogy, covering the productions of the three films and their impact on popular culture.

title: South Park: Imaginationland
text: In this never-before-seen Director's Cut, the doors of the world's imagination are thrown wide open and the boys of South Park are transported to a magical realm in their greatest odyssey ever.

title: Predators
text: A group of elite warriors parachute into an unfamiliar jungle and are hunted by members of a merciless alien race.

title: When You're Strange
text: A look at the late '60s and early '70s rock band The Doors, including rare exclusive footage.

title: Despicable Me
text: When a criminal mastermind uses a trio of orphan girls as pawns for a grand scheme, he finds their love is profoundly changing him for the better.

title: Inception
text: A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O., but his tragic past may doom the project and his team to disaster.

title: Grown Ups
text: After their high school basketball coach passes away, five good friends and former teammates reunite for a Fourth of July holiday weekend.

title: Sorcerer's Apprentice, The
text: Balthazar Blake, an apprentice of the legendary magician Merlin, must train his old teacher's successor - an introverted but resourceful physics prodigy - in the art of sorcery to prevent the return of Morgana le Fay.

title: Knight and Day
text: A young woman gets mixed up with a disgraced spy who is trying to clear his name.

title: Karate Kid, The
text: Work causes a single mother to move to China with her young son; in his new home, the boy embraces kung fu, taught to him by a master.

title: Kids Are All Right, The
text: Two children conceived by artificial insemination bring their biological father into their non-traditional family life.

title: Serbian Film, A
text: An aging porn star agrees to participate in an "art film" in order to make a clean break from the business, only to discover that he has been drafted into making a pedophilia and necrophilia themed snuff film.

title: Cherrybomb
text: Three teenagers go on a wild weekend of drink, drugs, shop-lifting and stealing cars that quickly spins beyond their control.

title: Batman: Under the Red Hood
text: There's a mystery afoot in Gotham City, and Batman must go toe-to-toe with a mysterious vigilante, who goes by the name of Red Hood. Subsequently, old wounds reopen and old, once buried memories come into the light.

title: Salt
text: A CIA agent goes on the run after a defector accuses her of being a Russian spy.

title: Watch Out for the Automobile
text: A very good cop tries to catch a very insidious and extremely clever serial car thief. The bitter irony is that the thief is not very clever, absolutely not insidious, and moreover - a virtuous person and his friend.

title: Mr. Nobody
text: A boy stands on a station platform as a train is about to leave. Should he go with his mother or stay with his father? Infinite possibilities arise from this decision. As long as he doesn't choose, anything is possible.

title: Dinner for Schmucks
text: When he finds out that his work superiors host a dinner celebrating the idiocy of their guests, a rising executive questions it when he's invited, just as he befriends a man who would be the perfect guest.

title: Deadly Outlaw: Rekka
text: When his beloved boss is killed, a dangerous young gangster cuts a path of vengeance through the Japanese mafia.

title: Hellsinki
text: Professional criminals in Finland from 1966 to 1979.

title: Ip Man 2
text: Centering on Ip Man's migration to Hong Kong in 1949 as he attempts to propagate his discipline of Wing Chun martial arts.

title: Ramona and Beezus
text: An adventurous young girl uses her imagination to escape her reality, that is quickly spinning out of reach.

title: Rebound, The
text: In New York City, a single mom captivates her new neighbor, a much younger man.

title: Other Guys, The
text: Two mismatched New York City detectives seize an opportunity to step up like the city's top cops, whom they idolize, only things don't quite go as planned.

title: Paper Man
text: A washed-up writer forms an unlikely friendship with a teenager from Long Island.

title: Expendables, The
text: A CIA operative hires a team of mercenaries to eliminate a Latin dictator and a renegade CIA agent.

title: Scott Pilgrim vs. the World
text: In a magically realistic version of Toronto, a young man must defeat his new girlfriend's seven evil exes one by one in order to win her heart.

title: I Killed My Mother
text: A semi-autobiographical story about Hubert as a young homosexual at odds with his mother.

title: Heartless
text: Jamie Morgan, a young man with a large heart-shaped birthmark on his face, discovers that there are demons on the streets of East London.

title: Piranha
text: After a sudden underwater tremor sets free scores of the prehistoric man-eating fish, an unlikely group of strangers must band together to stop themselves from becoming fish food for the area's new razor-toothed residents.

title: Extraordinary Adventures of Adèle Blanc-Sec, The
text: An adventure set in the early part of the 20th century and focused on a popular novelist and her dealings with would-be suitors, the cops, monsters, and other distractions.

title: Get Low
text: A movie spun out of equal parts folk tale, fable and real-life legend about the mysterious, 1930s Tennessee hermit who famously threw his own rollicking funeral party... while he was still alive.

title: Joneses, The
text: A seemingly perfect family moves into a suburban neighborhood, but when it comes to the truth as to why they're living there, they don't exactly come clean with their neighbors.

title: Dragon Ball Z: Dead Zone
text: In order to wish for immortality and avenge his father, Garlic Jr. collects the dragon balls, kidnapping Goku's son Gohan in the process. Goku, Kami, Piccolo, and Krillin unite to rescue Gohan and save the world from being sucked into a dead zone.

title: Last Exorcism, The
text: A troubled evangelical minister agrees to let his last exorcism be filmed by a documentary crew.

title: Sisters
text: Two young girls, Sveta and Dina, go on the run to avoid being kidnapped by the former associates of Dina's recently released gangster father.

title: American, The
text: An assassin hides out in Italy for one last assignment.

title: Jackass 2.5
text: The Jackass crew reunite to discuss their experiences with Jackass Number Two and show off some unused content and ideas.

title: Horde, The
text: An end of the world battle between gangsters, cops and zombies.

title: Switch, The
text: Seven years after the fact, a man comes to the realization that he was the sperm donor for his best friend's boy.

title: Machete
text: After being set-up and betrayed by the man who hired him to assassinate a Texas Senator, an ex-Federale launches a brutal rampage of revenge against his former boss.

title: Going the Distance
text: A romantic comedy centered on a guy and a gal who try to keep their love alive as they shuttle back and forth between New York and San Francisco to see one another.

title: Resident Evil: Afterlife
text: While still out to destroy the evil Umbrella Corporation, Alice joins a group of survivors living in a prison surrounded by the infected who also want to relocate to the mysterious but supposedly unharmed safe haven known only as Arcadia.

title: Princess
text: Princess tells the true story of former cabaret dancer Anna Lappalainen's redemptive struggle with insanity, who checked in to Finland's Kellokoski Psychiatric Hospital in 1945.

title: Social Network, The
text: As Harvard student Mark Zuckerberg creates the social networking site that would become known as Facebook, he is sued by the twins who claimed he stole their idea, and by the co-founder who was later squeezed out of the business.

title: Man Vanishes, A
text: Plastics salesman Oshima disappeared without a word to anyone, and has been missing for two years. Shohei Imamura and his crew follow Oshima's fiancé Yoshie and actor Shigeru Tsuyuguchi as they investigate the disappearance.

title: Town, The
text: A proficient group of thieves rob a bank and hold Claire, the assistant manager, hostage. Things begin to get complicated when one of the crew members falls in love with Claire.

title: Easy A
text: A clean-cut high school student relies on the school's rumor mill to advance her social and financial standing.

title: Eat Pray Love
text: A married woman realizes how unhappy her marriage really is, and that her life needs to go in a different direction. After a painful divorce, she takes off on a round-the-world journey to "find herself".

title: Howl
text: As Allen Ginsberg talks about his life and art, his most famous poem is illustrated in animation while the obscenity trial of the work is dramatized.

title: I'm Still Here
text: Documents Joaquin Phoenix's transition from the acting world to a career as an aspiring rapper.

title: Patrik Age 1.5
text: A Swedish gay couple adopt what they think is an 18-month-old orphan, only to meet their new son, a 15-year-old homophobic delinquent.

title: Flipped
text: Two eighth-graders start to have feelings for each other despite being total opposites.

title: Wall Street: Money Never Sleeps
text: Now out of prison but still disgraced by his peers, Gordon Gekko works his future son-in-law, an idealistic stock broker, when he sees an opportunity to take down a Wall Street enemy and rebuild his empire.

title: Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole
text: When a young owl is abducted by an evil Owl army, he must escape with new-found friends and seek the legendary Guardians to stop the menace.

title: It's Kind of a Funny Story
text: A clinically depressed teenager gets a new start after he checks himself into an adult psychiatric ward.

title: Middle Men
text: Chronicles Jack Harris, one of the pioneers of internet commerce, as he wrestles with his morals, and struggles not to drown in a sea of con men, mobsters, drug addicts, and porn stars.

title: Alice in Wonderland
text: In Victorian England a bored young girl dreams that she has entered a fantasy world called Wonderland populated by even more fantastic characters.

title: Let Me In
text: A bullied young boy befriends a young female vampire who lives in secrecy with her guardian.

title: Sintel
text: The film follows a girl named Sintel who is searching for a baby dragon she calls Scales.

title: Secretariat
text: Penny Chenery Tweedy and colleagues guide her long-shot but precocious stallion to set, in 1973, the unbeaten record for winning the Triple Crown.

title: Devil
text: A group of people are trapped in an elevator and the Devil is mysteriously amongst them.

title: You Again
text: When a young woman realizes her brother is about to marry the girl who bullied her in high school, she sets out to expose the fiancée's true colors.

title: Life as We Know It
text: Two single adults become caregivers to an orphaned girl when their mutual best friends die in an accident.

title: Catfish
text: Young filmmakers document their colleague's budding online friendship with a young woman and her family which leads to an unexpected series of discoveries.

title: You Will Meet a Tall Dark Stranger
text: Sally's parents' marriage breaks up when her father undergoes a mid-life crisis and impulsively weds a prostitute. Meanwhile, Sally's own marriage also begins to disintegrate.

title: Stone
text: A convicted arsonist looks to manipulate a parole officer into a plan to secure his parole by placing his beautiful wife in the lawman's path.

title: Inside Job
text: Takes a closer look at what brought about the 2008 financial meltdown.

title: Monsters
text: Six years after Earth has suffered an alien invasion, a cynical journalist agrees to escort a shaken American tourist through an infected zone in Mexico to the safety of the U.S. border.

title: Never Let Me Go
text: The lives of three friends, from their early school days into young adulthood, when the reality of the world they live in comes knocking.

title: Illusionist, The
text: A French illusionist finds himself out of work and travels to Scotland, where he meets a young woman. Their ensuing adventure changes both their lives forever.

title: Luck by Chance
text: When Vikram gets tapped to play the male lead in a Bollywood film, he can't believe his luck. But it may ruin his relationship with his girlfriend.

title: Rubber
text: A homicidal car tire, discovering it has destructive psionic power, sets its sights on a desert town once a mysterious woman becomes its obsession.

title: Jackass 3D
text: Johnny Knoxville and company return for the third installment of their TV show spin-off, where dangerous stunts and explicit public displays rule.

title: Restrepo
text: A year with one platoon in the deadliest valley in Afghanistan.

title: Waiting for 'Superman'
text: An examination of the current state of education in America today.

title: Red
text: When his peaceful life is threatened by a high-tech assassin, former black-ops agent Frank Moses reassembles his old team in a last-ditch effort to survive and uncover his assailants.

title: In a Better World
text: The lives of two Danish families cross each other, and an extraordinary but risky friendship comes into bud. But loneliness, frailty and sorrow lie in wait.

title: Heartbreaker
text: Alex and his sister run a business designed to break up relationships. They are hired by a rich man to break up the wedding of his daughter. The only problem is that they only have one week to do so.

title: Paranormal Activity 2
text: After experiencing what they think are a series of "break-ins", a family sets up security cameras around their home, only to realize that the events unfolding before them are more sinister than they seem.

title: Heartbeats
text: The story of three close friends who are involved in a love-triangle.

title: Hereafter
text: A drama centered on three people - a blue-collar American, a French journalist and a London school boy - who are touched by death in different ways.

title: Undisputed III: Redemption
text: Boyka is back. This time he is fighting in the first ever inter-prison tournament with one knee.

title: Saw VII 3D - The Final Chapter
text: As a deadly battle rages over Jigsaw's brutal legacy, a group of Jigsaw survivors gathers to seek the support of self-help guru and fellow survivor Bobby Dagen, a man whose own dark secrets unleash a new wave of terror.

title: Due Date
text: High-strung father-to-be Peter Highman is forced to hitch a ride with aspiring actor Ethan Tremblay on a road trip in order to make it to his child's birth on time.

title: 127 Hours
text: A mountain climber becomes trapped under a boulder while canyoneering alone near Moab, Utah and resorts to desperate measures in order to survive.

title: Megamind
text: Evil genius Megamind finally defeats his do-gooder nemesis, Metro Man, but is left without a purpose in a superhero-free world.

title: Black Swan
text: A committed dancer struggles to maintain her sanity after winning the lead role in a production of Tchaikovsky's "Swan Lake".

title: I Shot Jesse James
text: Bob Ford murders his best friend Jesse James in order to obtain a pardon that will free him to marry his girlfriend but is plagued by guilt and self-disgust.

title: Unstoppable
text: With an unmanned, half-mile-long freight train barreling toward a city, a veteran engineer and a young conductor race against the clock to prevent a catastrophe.

title: Morning Glory
text: An upstart television producer accepts the challenge of reviving a struggling morning show program with warring co-hosts.

title: Certified Copy
text: In Tuscany to promote his latest book, a middle-aged British writer meets a French woman who leads him to the village of Lucignano. While there, a chance question reveals something deeper.

title: Next Three Days, The
text: A married couple's life is turned upside down when the wife is accused of a murder.

title: Somewhere
text: After withdrawing to the Chateau Marmont, a passionless Hollywood actor reexamines his life when his eleven-year-old daughter surprises him with a visit.

title: Biutiful
text: A man dying of cancer tries his best to leave the world on his own terms.

title: First Beautiful Thing, The
text: A misanthropic professor returns to his hometown to assist his dying mother.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1
text: As Harry, Ron, and Hermione race against time and evil to destroy the Horcruxes, they uncover the existence of the three most powerful objects in the wizarding world: the Deathly Hallows.

title: King's Speech, The
text: The story of King George VI, his impromptu ascension to the throne of the British Empire in 1936, and the speech therapist who helped the unsure monarch overcome his stammer.

title: Tangled
text: The magically long-haired Rapunzel has spent her entire life in a tower, but now that a runaway thief has stumbled upon her, she is about to discover the world for the first time, and who she really is.

title: Art of the Steal, The
text: Documentary that follows the struggle for control of Dr. Albert C. Barnes' 25 billion dollar collection of modern and post-impressionist art.

title: Fighter, The
text: Based on the story of Micky Ward, a fledgling boxer who tries to escape the shadow of his more famous but troubled older boxing brother and get his own shot at greatness.

title: Romantics, The
text: Seven close friends reunite for the wedding of two of their friends. Problems arise because the bride and the maid of honor have had a long rivalry over the groom.

title: Loved Ones, The
text: When Brent turns down his classmate Lola's invitation to the prom, she concocts a wildly violent plan for revenge.

title: Casino Jack
text: A hot shot Washington DC lobbyist and his protégé go down hard as their schemes to peddle influence lead to corruption and murder.

title: Vincent Wants to Sea
text: A young man suffering from Tourette's syndrome absconds from an institution with two other inhabitants to travel to Italy to fulfill his mother's last wish.

title: London Boulevard
text: An ex-con with a reputation tries to go straight by working as a handy man for a reclusive actress but this is unfortunately not the wish of London's underground crime lord.

title: Skyline
text: Strange lights descend on the city of Los Angeles, drawing people outside like moths to a flame where an extraterrestrial force threatens to swallow the entire human population off the face of the Earth.

title: Beastly
text: A modern-day take on the "Beauty and the Beast" tale where a New York teen is transformed into a hideous monster in order to find true love.

title: Love and Other Drugs
text: In 1990s Pittsburgh, a medicine peddler starts a relationship with a young woman suffering from Parkinson's disease.

title: Chronicles of Narnia: The Voyage of the Dawn Treader, The
text: Lucy and Edmund Pevensie return to Narnia with their cousin Eustace where they meet up with Prince Caspian for a trip across the sea aboard the royal ship The Dawn Treader. Along the way they encounter dragons, dwarves, merfolk, and a band of lost warriors before reaching the edge of the world.

title: Tourist, The
text: Revolves around Frank, an American tourist visiting Italy to mend a broken heart. Elise is an extraordinary woman who deliberately crosses his path.

title: Rare Exports: A Christmas Tale
text: In the depths of the Korvatunturi mountains, 486 meters deep, lies the closest ever guarded secret of Christmas. The time has come to dig it up. This Christmas everyone will believe in Santa Claus.

title: Hatchet II
text: Marybeth escapes the clutches of the bayou-butcher Victor Crowley and returns to the swamp with an army of hunters and gunmen, determined to end Crowley's reign of horror once and for all.

title: All Good Things
text: Mr. David Marks was suspected but never tried for killing his wife Katie who disappeared in 1982, but the truth is eventually revealed.

title: True Grit
text: A stubborn teenager enlists the help of a tough U.S. Marshal to track down her father's murderer.

title: Tron: Legacy
text: The son of a virtual world designer goes looking for his father and ends up inside the digital world that his father designed. He meets his father's corrupted creation and a unique ally who was born inside the digital world.

title: How Do You Know
text: After being cut from the U.S.A. softball team and feeling a bit past her prime, Lisa finds herself evaluating her life and in the middle of a love triangle, as a corporate guy in crisis competes with her current, baseball-playing beau.

title: Barney's Version
text: The picaresque and touching story of the politically incorrect, fully lived life of the impulsive, irascible and fearlessly blunt Barney Panofsky.

title: Company Men, The
text: The story centers on a year in the life of three men trying to survive a round of corporate downsizing at a major company - and how that affects them, their families, and their communities.

title: One-Armed Swordsman, The
text: A noble swordsman, whose arm had been chopped off, returns to his former teacher to defend him from a villainous gang of rival swordsmen.

title: I Saw the Devil
text: A secret agent exacts revenge on a serial killer through a series of captures and releases.

title: Trash Humpers
text: Follows the lives of a small group of sociopathic elderly people in Nashville, Tennessee.

title: Faster
text: An ex-con gets on a series of apparently unrelated killings. He gets tracked by a veteran cop with secrets of his own and an egocentric hit man.

title: Little Big Soldier
text: An old soldier kidnaps a young General of an enemy state and takes him on a long journey to collect the reward.

title: Rabbit Hole
text: Life for a happy couple is turned upside down after their young son dies in an accident.

title: One Week
text: A newly wedded couple attempts to build a house with a prefabricated kit, unaware that a rival sabotaged the kit's component numbering.

title: Little Fockers
text: Family-patriarch Jack Byrnes wants to appoint a successor. Does his son-in-law, the male nurse Greg Focker, have what it takes?

title: Gulliver's Travels
text: Travel writer Lemuel Gulliver takes an assignment in Bermuda but ends up on the island of Lilliput, where he towers over its tiny citizens.

title: Sweetgrass
text: In the summer of 2003, a group of shepherds took a herd of sheep one final time through the Beartooth Mountains of Montana, in the extreme north-west of the United States. It was a journey of almost three hundred kilometres through expansive green valleys, by fields of snow, and across hazardous, narrow ridges - a journey brimming with challenges. The aging shepherds do their very best to keep the hundreds of sheep together; the panoramic high mountains are teeming with hungry wolves and grizzly bears.

title: Burlesque
text: A small-town girl ventures to Los Angeles and finds her place in a neo-burlesque club run by a former dancer.

title: Secret World of Arrietty, The
text: The Clock family are four-inch-tall people who live anonymously in another family's residence, borrowing simple items to make their home. Life changes for the Clocks when their teenage daughter, Arrietty, is discovered.

title: Tucker & Dale vs Evil
text: Affable hillbillies Tucker and Dale are on vacation at their dilapidated mountain cabin when they are mistaken for murderers by a group of preppy college students.

title: Yogi Bear
text: A documentary filmmaker travels to Jellystone Park to shoot a project and soon crosses paths with Yogi Bear, his sidekick Boo-Boo and Ranger Smith.

title: Made in Dagenham
text: A dramatization of the 1968 strike at the Ford Dagenham car plant, where female workers walked out in protest against sexual discrimination.

title: Green Hornet, The
text: Following the death of his father, Britt Reid, heir to his father's large company, teams up with his late dad's assistant Kato to become a masked crime fighting team.

title: Way Back, The
text: Siberian gulag escapees travel four thousand miles by foot to freedom in India.

title: Warrior's Way, The
text: A warrior-assassin is forced to hide in a small town in the American Badlands after refusing a mission.

title: Season of the Witch
text: Fourteenth century knights transport a suspected witch to a monastery, where monks deduce her powers could be the source of the Black Plague.

title: Amer
text: As a young girl Ana was a rebellious child. She was also tormented by images of death and a shadowy, ominous figure in black. Now an adult, she is once again tormented by shadowy, other-worldly forms.

title: Cowboys & Aliens
text: A spaceship arrives in Arizona, 1873, to take over the Earth, starting with the Wild West region. A posse of cowboys and natives are all that stand in their way.

title: Anything for Her
text: With no legal means left to him, a high school teacher devises a daring plan to rescue his wrongfully imprisoned wife from jail.

title: Day & Night
text: Day encounters Night, a stranger of distinctly darker moods. But their suspicions soon turn to curiosity, and they are delighted to find the joys of their budding friendship.

title: Marwencol
text: After a vicious attack leaves him brain-damaged and broke, Mark Hogancamp seeks recovery in "Marwencol", a 1/6th scale World War II-era town he creates in his backyard.

title: Dilemma, The
text: A man discovers that his best friend's wife is having an affair.

title: Down Argentine Way
text: An American girl on vacation in Argentina falls for a wealthy racehorse owner.

title: Trip, The
text: Steve Coogan has been asked by The Observer to tour the country's finest restaurants, but after his girlfriend backs out on him he must take his best friend and source of eternal aggravation, Rob Brydon.

title: Limitless
text: With the help of a mysterious pill that enables the user to access 100% of his brain's abilities, a struggling writer becomes a financial wizard, but it also puts him in a new world with many dangers.

title: Happy People: A Year in the Taiga
text: A documentary depicting the life and work of the trappers of Bakhtia, a village in the heart of the Siberian Taiga, where daily life has changed little in over a century.

title: Evangelion: 2.0 You Can  Advance
text: Under constant attack by Angels, NERV introduces two new pilots: the mysterious Makinami Mari Illustrous and the intense Asuka Langley Shikinami. Parallel to the incursion, Gendo Ikari and SEELE proceed the secret project that involves both Rei and Shinji.

title: I Spit on Your Grave
text: A writer who is brutalized during her cabin retreat seeks revenge on her attackers, who left her for dead.

title: Even the Rain
text: As a director and his crew shoot a controversial film about Christopher Columbus in Cochabamba, Bolivia, local people rise up against plans to privatize the water supply.

title: It Happened on Fifth Avenue
text: Two homeless men move into a mansion while its owners are wintering in the South.

title: Zeitgeist: Moving Forward
text: A feature length documentary work which presents a case for a needed transition out of the current socioeconomic monetary paradigm which governs the entire world society.

title: No Strings Attached
text: A guy and girl try to keep their relationship strictly physical, but it's not long before they learn that they want something more.

title: Lincoln Lawyer, The
text: A lawyer defending a wealthy man begins to believe his client is guilty of more than just one crime.

title: All-Star Superman
text: After being poisoned by sun radiation, a dying Superman decides to fulfill his lifelong dreams while Lex Luthor has his own agenda.

title: Girls About Town
text: Two gold diggers prey on old rich men, but one of them falls in love with a young, rich man.

title: Kill!
text: Two ronin - an ex-samurai and an ex-farmer - get caught up in a local official's complex game of murder and betrayal.

title: Pekka ja Pätkä salapoliiseina
text: Pekka and Pätkä start a detective agency. Two businessmen give them a mission they think is impossible.

title: Unknown
text: When a man awakens from a coma only to discover that someone has taken on his identity, he teams up with a young woman to prove who he is.

title: Cedar Rapids
text: Tim Lippe has no idea what he's in for when he's sent to Cedar Rapids, Iowa to represent his company at an annual insurance convention, where he soon finds himself under the "guidance" of three convention veterans.

title: Gnomeo & Juliet
text: Separated by a garden fence and a feud, are blue gnomes on one side and red gnomes on the other. This doesn't stop blue Gnomeo and red Juliet from falling in love with each other. Do they have a future together?

title: Burke and Hare
text: A black comedy about two nineteenth century grave robbers, who find a lucrative business providing cadavers for an Edinburgh medical school.

title: Castaway on the Moon
text: A failed suicide attempt leads a heartbroken man to live a life in the wilderness.

title: Paul
text: Two English comic book geeks traveling across the U.S. encounter an alien outside Area 51.

title: Asphyx, The
text: English country squire Sir Hugo Cunningham searches for immortality by literally 'bottling up' the Spirit of the Dead, or Asphyx.

title: Brother 2
text: Arriving in Moscow, Danila discovers Konstantin dead and he sets out to avenge his death; a journey that leads him to Chicago and a whole new experience.

title: Emma
text: Emma Woodhouse seems to be perfectly content, to have a loving father for whom she cares, friends, and a home. But Emma has a terrible habit: matchmaking. She cannot resist finding suitors for her friends, most of all Harriet Smith. Emma is desperate for Harriet to find happiness, but every suitor she finds for her friend ends up attracted to Emma. But is Emma so focused on Harriet's happiness that she is not considering her own happiness in love?

title: Drive Angry
text: A vengeful father escapes from hell and chases after the men who killed his daughter and kidnapped his granddaughter.

title: Rango
text: Rango is an ordinary chameleon who accidentally winds up in the town of Dirt, a lawless outpost in the Wild West in desperate need of a new sheriff.

title: Take Me Home Tonight
text: Four years after graduation, an awkward high school genius uses his sister's boyfriend's Labor Day party as the perfect opportunity to make his move on his high school crush.

title: Confessions
text: A psychological thriller of a grieving mother turned cold-blooded avenger with a twisty master plan to pay back those who were responsible for her daughter's death.

title: Adjustment Bureau, The
text: The affair between a politician and a contemporary dancer is affected by mysterious forces keeping the lovers apart.

title: Mechanic, The
text: An elite hitman teaches his trade to an apprentice who has a connection to one of his previous victims.

title: Hall Pass
text: Rick and Fred, two husbands who are having difficulty in their marriages, are given a Hall Pass by their wives: for one week, they can do whatever they want.

title: Eagle, The
text: In Roman-ruled Britain, a young Roman soldier endeavors to honor his father's memory by finding his lost legion's golden emblem.

title: I Am Number Four
text: Aliens and their Guardians are hiding on Earth from intergalactic bounty hunters. They can only be killed in numerical order, and Number Four is next on the list. This is his story.

title: Battle: Los Angeles
text: A squad of U.S. Marines becomes the last line of defense against a global invasion.

title: Summer Wars
text: A student tries to fix a problem he accidentally caused in OZ, a digital world, while pretending to be the fiancé of his friend at her grandmother's 90th birthday.

title: Sunset Limited, The
text: Through a chance encounter, two men of opposing ideologies deliberate spiritual, philosophical, and profound matters in a New York City apartment.

title: Winnie the Pooh and the Honey Tree
text: Christopher Robin's bear attempts to raid a beehive in a tall tree.

title: Mars Needs Moms
text: A young boy named Milo gains a deeper appreciation for his mom after Martians come to Earth to take her away.

title: Scooby-Doo! Curse of the Lake Monster
text: School is out and the familiar Scooby gang are looking to enjoy a long vacation. However, sightings of a Lake Monster cause them to band together once again to solve yet another mystery.

title: Winnie the Pooh and Tigger Too
text: Rabbit is tired of Tigger always bouncing him, so he gets Pooh and Piglet together to come up with an idea to get the bounce out of Tigger. Rabbit suggests they take him into the middle of nowhere and leave him overnight. The idea backfires and Rabbit, Piglet and Pooh find themselves lost, but Pooh's tummy guides them home. Then, Tigger and Roo go out for a bounce and get caught in a tree, which Tigger is too afraid to get out of, and Rabbit makes Tigger promise that if they help get Tigger down, that Tigger can never bounce again. So Tigger is rescued and feels sad that he can no longer bounce, but everyone, including Rabbit, agrees they liked the old bouncy Tigger better.

title: Hard Ticket to Hawaii
text: In Hawaii, an undercover DEA agent and her civilian friend stumble upon a drug trafficking operation, and have to enlist the help of all their colleagues/friends to go after the vicious drug kingpin.

title: Elite Squad: The Enemy Within
text: After a prison riot, former-Captain Nascimento, now a high ranking security officer in Rio de Janeiro, is swept into a bloody political dispute that involves government officials and paramilitary groups.

title: Mesrine: Public Enemy #1
text: The story of the notorious French gangster Jacques Mesrine, with the focus on his life and death as France's Public Enemy No. 1 in the 1970s.

title: Just Go with It
text: On a weekend trip to Hawaii, a plastic surgeon convinces his loyal assistant to pose as his soon-to-be-divorced wife in order to cover up a careless lie he told to his much-younger girlfriend.

title: Cave of Forgotten Dreams
text: Werner Herzog gains exclusive access to film inside the Chauvet caves of Southern France and captures the oldest known pictorial creations of humanity.

title: Red Riding Hood
text: Set in a medieval village that is haunted by a werewolf, a young girl falls for an orphaned woodcutter, much to her family's displeasure.

title: Big Mommas: Like Father, Like Son
text: Malcolm Turner and his stepson Trent go undercover at an all-girls school to flush out a killer.

title: Super
text: After his wife falls under the influence of a drug dealer, an everyday guy transforms himself into Crimson Bolt, a superhero with the best intentions, but lacking in heroic skills.

title: Troll Hunter, The
text: A group of students investigates a series of mysterious bear killings, but learns that there are much more dangerous things going on. They start to follow a mysterious hunter, learning that he is actually a troll hunter.

title: Source Code
text: A soldier wakes up in someone else's body and discovers he's part of an experimental government program to find the bomber of a commuter train within 8 minutes.

title: Jane Eyre
text: A mousy governess who softens the heart of her employer soon discovers that he's hiding a terrible secret.

title: Sucker Punch
text: A young girl institutionalized by her abusive stepfather retreats to an alternative reality as a coping strategy and envisions a plan to help her escape.

title: Chalet Girl
text: Former skateboard champion Kim wants to make more money after her mother's tragic death. She joins the elite posh servicing company, which sends her off to Austria.

title: BURN-E
text: If BURN-E  had known how much trouble he'd be caused by WALL-E's pursuit of EVE, then he'd have taken the day off.

title: Senna
text: A documentary on Brazilian Formula One racing driver Ayrton Senna, who won the F1 world championship three times before his death at age 34.

title: Family Guy Presents: It's a Trap
Insidious
text: A family looks to prevent evil spirits from trapping their comatose child in a realm called The Further.

title: Hobo with a Shotgun
text: A homeless vigilante blows away crooked cops, pedophile Santas, and other scumbags with his trusty pump-action shotgun.

title: Win Win
text: A struggling lawyer and volunteer wrestling coach's chicanery comes back to haunt him when the teenage grandson of the client he has double-crossed comes into his life.

title: Room in Rome
text: A hotel room in the center of Rome serves as the setting for two young and recently acquainted women to have a physical adventure that touches their very souls.

title: Boy
text: Set on the east coast of New Zealand in 1984, Boy, an 11-year-old child and devout Michael Jackson fan, gets a chance to know his absentee criminal father, who has returned to find a bag of money he buried years ago.

title: Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules
text: Back in middle school after summer vacation, Greg Heffley and his older brother Rodrick must deal with their parents' misguided attempts to have them bond.

title: Henry's Crime
text: Released from prison for a crime he didn't commit, an ex-con targets the same bank he was sent away for robbing.

title: Hop
text: E.B., the Easter Bunny's teenage son, heads to Hollywood, determined to become a drummer in a rock 'n' roll band. In LA, he's taken in by Fred after the out-of-work slacker hits E.B. with his car.

title: Playing the Victim
text: A young man drops out of university and goes to the police. He's done nothing wrong he just wants a job. A particular job. Playing the victim in murder reconstructions. Maybe by getting close to death he can manage to cheat on his own.

title: Films to Keep You Awake: The Christmas Tale
text: In 1985, in a coastal town, the friends Koldo, Peti, Tito, Eugenio and Moni stumble with a woman dressed like Santa Claus trapped in a hole in the woods. While the boys go to the police station to ask for help, the others find a rope to take the woman out of the hole. However, the boys find in the police station that the woman is the dangerous thief Rebeca Expósito, who has just stolen two million pesetas from a bank and is wanted. The group decides to leave the woman in the hole without any food to force her to give the robbed money to them. Meanwhile, Peti and Eugenio that are fans of the movie "Zombie Invasion", decide to make a voodoo ceremony with Rebecca to transform her into a zombie. When Rebecca escapes from her imprisonment, she uses an axe to chase the evil boys.

title: 13 Assassins
text: A group of assassins come together for a suicide mission to kill an evil lord.

title: Hanna
text: A sixteen-year-old girl who was raised by her father to be the perfect assassin is dispatched on a mission across Europe, tracked by a ruthless intelligence agent and her operatives.

title: Connections
text: Follow James Burke through the history of science and technology in this collection of 10 1-hour episodes, starting with "The Trigger Effect."

title: Into Eternity
text: A documentary on the safety of nuclear storage.

title: Daffy Duck's Quackbusters
text: Daffy Duck opens a detective agency for the supernatural along side his Looney Toon buddies.

title: American: The Bill Hicks Story
text: Photo-animated feature documentary, uniquely narrated by the 10 people who knew Bill best.

title: Arthur
text: A drunken playboy stands to lose a wealthy inheritance when he falls for a woman his family doesn't like.

title: Scream 4
text: Ten years have passed, and Sidney Prescott, who has put herself back together thanks in part to her writing, is visited by the Ghostface Killer.

title: Rio
text: When Blu, a domesticated macaw from small-town Minnesota, meets the fiercely independent Jewel, he takes off on an adventure to Rio de Janeiro with the bird of his dreams.

title: Melancholia
text: Two sisters find their already strained relationship challenged as a mysterious new planet threatens to collide with Earth.

title: Thor
text: The powerful but arrogant god Thor is cast out of Asgard to live amongst humans in Midgard , where he soon becomes one of their finest defenders.

title: Louis C.K.: Hilarious
text: In this unique and dynamic live concert experience, Louis C.K.'s exploration of life after 40 destroys politically correct images of modern life with thoughts we have all had...but would rarely admit to.

title: Louis C.K.: Chewed Up
text: Louis C.K.'s second one-hour special filmed at the Berklee Performance Center in Boston, MA.

title: Atlas Shrugged: Part 1
text: Railroad executive Dagny Taggart and steel mogul Henry Rearden form an alliance to fight the increasingly authoritarian government of the United States.

title: Louis C.K.: Shameless
text: Comedy and television star Louis C.K. returns to HBO for an hour of no-holds-barred, adults-only stand-up comedy taped before a live audience at the Henry Fonda Theater in Los Angeles.

title: Mildred Pierce
text: Divorced single mom Mildred Pierce decides to open a restaurant business, which tears at the already-strained relationship with her ambitious elder daughter, Veda.

title: Voices from the List
text: Documentary film produced for the 10th anniversary release of the film Schindler's List  and the establishment of the "Survivors of the Shoah Visual History Foundation"

title: Water for Elephants
text: Set in the 1930s, a former veterinary student takes a job in a travelling circus and falls in love with the ringmaster's wife.

title: African Cats
text: Meet Mara, an endearing lion cub striving to be like her mother; Sita, a cheetah and single mother of five; and Fang, a proud leader of the pride who must defend his family from a rival lion.

title: Kill the Irishman
text: The true story of Danny Greene, a tough Irish thug working for mobsters in Cleveland during the 1970's.

title: Fast Five
text: Dominic Toretto and his crew of street racers plan a massive heist to buy their freedom while in the sights of a powerful Brazilian drug lord and a dangerous federal agent.

title: Idiots and Angels
text: Much to his surprise, an utter misanthrope is transformed into a reluctant do-gooder, when a glorious pair of angelic snow-white wings sprouts up from his back. Now, everyone in town wants a piece of his feathered appendages.

title: Incendies
text: Twins journey to the Middle East to discover their family history and fulfill their mother's last wishes.

title: Soul Surfer
text: Teenage surfer Bethany Hamilton overcomes the odds and her own fears of returning to the water after losing her left arm in a shark attack.

title: Something Borrowed
text: Friendships are tested and secrets come to the surface when terminally single Rachel falls for Dex, her best friend Darcy's fiancé.

title: Bridesmaids
text: Competition between the maid of honor and a bridesmaid, over who is the bride's best friend, threatens to upend the life of an out-of-work pastry chef.

title: Priest
text: A priest disobeys church law to track down the vampires who kidnapped his niece.

title: Mothra
text: An expedition to Infant Island discovers a native population and tiny twin fairy priestesses of the island's mythical deity. Named Mothra, she sets out to rescue her fairies after they are kidnapped by an exploitative businessman.

title: Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides
text: Jack Sparrow and Barbossa embark on a quest to find the elusive fountain of youth, only to discover that Blackbeard and his daughter are after it too.

title: Midnight in Paris
text: While on a trip to Paris with his fiancée's family, a nostalgic screenwriter finds himself mysteriously going back to the 1920s every day at midnight.

title: The Man from Nowhere
text: A quiet pawnshop keeper with a violent past takes on a drug-and-organ trafficking ring in hope of saving the child who is his only friend.

title: Tree of Life, The
text: The story of a family in Waco, Texas in 1956. The eldest son witnesses the loss of innocence and struggles with his parents' conflicting teachings.

title: Hangover Part II, The
text: Two years after the bachelor party in Las Vegas, Phil, Stu, Alan, and Doug jet to Thailand for Stu's wedding. Stu's plan for a subdued pre-wedding brunch, however, goes seriously awry.

title: Nothing to Declare
text: A Belge-Francophobe customs officer is forced to team up with a Frenchman during the elimination of the Franco-Belge borders in the 90s.

title: Across the Hall
text: A thriller about a standoff between a young man, his fiancée and his best friend who comes to his aide.

title: Roommate, The
text: When college freshman Sara arrives on campus for the first time, she befriends her roommate, Rebecca, unaware that the girl is becoming dangerously obsessed with her.

title: Attack the Block
