text: A teen gang in South London defend their block from an alien invasion.

title: The Way
text: A father heads overseas to recover the body of his estranged son who died while traveling the "El camino de Santiago," and decides to take the pilgrimage himself.

title: Let the Bullets Fly
text: In 1920s China, a bandit arrives in a remote provincial town posing as its new mayor, where he faces off against a tyrannical local nobleman.

title: Kung Fu Panda 2
text: Po and his friends fight to stop a peacock villain from conquering China with a deadly new weapon, but first the Dragon Warrior must come to terms with his past.

title: X-Men: First Class
text: In the 1960s, superpowered humans Charles Xavier and Erik Lensherr work together to find others like them, but Erik's vengeful pursuit of an ambitious mutant who ruined his life causes a schism to divide them.

title: Submarine
text: 15-year-old Oliver Tate has two objectives: To lose his virginity before his next birthday, and to extinguish the flame between his mother and an ex-lover who has resurfaced in her life.

title: American Grindhouse
text: A documentary about the history of exploitation movies, from the silent movie era to the 1970s.

title: Everything Must Go
text: When an alcoholic relapses, causing him to lose his wife and his job, he holds a yard sale on his front lawn in an attempt to start over. A new neighbor might be the key to his return to form.

title: Beginners
text: A young man is rocked by two announcements from his elderly father: that he has terminal cancer and that he has a young male lover.

title: Super 8
text: During the summer of 1979, a group of friends witness a train crash and investigate subsequent unexplained events in their small town.

title: Bernie
text: A 30 year old orphan finds his life's official version hard to swallow. His parents couldn't possibly have abandoned him in a trash can as a baby. No, they were victims of a mafia plot and today, if they're still alive, they need his help.

title: Green Lantern
text: Reckless test pilot Hal Jordan is granted an alien ring that bestows him with otherworldly powers that inducts him into an intergalactic police force, the Green Lantern Corps.

title: Elektra Luxx
text: Life for porn actress Elektra Luxx gets turned upside down when she finds out she's pregnant.

title: Mr. Popper's Penguins
text: The life of a businessman begins to change after he inherits six penguins, and as he transforms his apartment into a winter wonderland, his professional side starts to unravel.

title: Bad Teacher
text: A lazy, incompetent middle school teacher who hates her job, her students, and her co-workers is forced to return to teaching to make enough money for breast implants after her wealthy fiancé dumps her.

title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon
text: The Autobots learn of a Cybertronian spacecraft hidden on the moon, and race against the Decepticons to reach it and to learn its secrets.

title: Larry Crowne
text: After losing his job, a middle-aged man reinvents himself by going back to college.

title: Your Highness
text: When Prince Fabious's bride is kidnapped, he goes on a quest to rescue her... accompanied by his lazy useless brother Thadeous.

title: Too Big to Fail
text: Chronicles the financial meltdown of 2008 and centers on Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson.

title: Takers
text: A group of bank robbers find their multi-million dollar plan interrupted by a hard-boiled detective.

title: My Life as McDull
text: McDull is not the brightest kid on the block, but he continuously tries to do his best to please his mother. Still it seems he may not be destined for great things like she wishes, but McDull strives to try anyway.

title: Zookeeper
text: A group of zoo animals decide to break their code of silence in order to help their lovable zookeeper find love, without opting to leave his current job for something more illustrious.

title: Horrible Bosses
text: Three friends conspire to murder their awful bosses when they realize they are standing in the way of their happiness.

title: Cars 2
text: Star race car Lightning McQueen and his pal Mater head overseas to compete in the World Grand Prix race. But the road to the championship becomes rocky as Mater gets caught up in an intriguing adventure of his own: international espionage.

title: Between the Folds
text: Depicts a cast of fine artists and eccentric scientists  who have devoted their lives to the unlikely medium of modern origami. Through their determination to reinterpret the world in paper, they arouse a fascinating mix of sensibilities towards art, form, expressiveness, creativity and meaning.

title: Delhi Belly
text: Three struggling room-mates unknowingly become potential prey of a ruthless gangster.

title: Upside Down: The Creation Records Story
text: The definitive film about Creation Records, one of the world's most successful and colorful independent labels.

title: Monte Carlo
text: Three young women vacationing in Paris find themselves whisked away to Monte Carlo after one of the girls is mistaken for a British heiress.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
text: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

title: Drive
text: An action drama about a mysterious Hollywood stuntman and mechanic moonlighting as a getaway driver finding himself in trouble when he helps out his neighbor.

title: Captain America: The First Avenger
text: Steve Rogers, a rejected military soldier, transforms into Captain America after taking a dose of a "Super-Soldier serum". But being Captain America comes at a price as he attempts to take down a war monger and a terrorist organization.

title: Crazy, Stupid, Love.
text: A middle-aged husband's life changes dramatically when his wife asks him for a divorce. He seeks to rediscover his manhood with the help of a newfound friend, Jacob, learning to pick up girls at bars.

title: One Day
text: After spending the night together on the night of their college graduation Dexter and Emma are shown each year on the same date to see where they are in their lives. They are sometimes together, sometimes not, on that day.

title: Guard, The
text: An unorthodox Irish policeman with a confrontational personality is partnered with an up-tight F.B.I. agent to investigate an international drug-smuggling ring.

title: Winnie the Pooh
text: While searching for honey, Pooh and his friends embark on an adventure to find Eeyore's missing tail and rescue Christopher Robin from an unknown monster called The Backson.

title: Woman, The
text: When a successful country lawyer captures and attempts to "civilize" the last remaining member of a violent clan that has roamed the Northeast coast for decades, he puts the lives of his family in jeopardy.

title: New One-Armed Swordsman, The
text: Lei Li lost his right-arm in a sword duel with the master of a martial arts school, long ago. Now, he is able to defend himself well with just his left arm, and kung fu techniques. That he proves with just the help of his friend Chung-Chieng, when he crosses his path with a beautiful girl in need, Pao Chiao. Even against impossible odds, he will prove a great warrior.

title: Mike's New Car
text: Mike's bought a new 6-wheel-drive car, and he can't wait to show it off to Sulley. Only problem is, Mike hasn't exactly mastered the controls yet, and they're pretty complicated.

title: Smurfs, The
text: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into New York City.

title: Friends with Benefits
text: A young man and woman decide to take their friendship to the next level without becoming a couple, but soon discover that adding sex only leads to complications.

title: Paper Birds
text: The lives of a comics and artists group in the hard times after of Spanish Civil War.

title: Blitz
text: A tough cop is dispatched to take down a serial killer who has been targeting police officers.

title: Yellow Sea, The
text: When the attempt to kill a professor goes wrong, a series of violent events are triggered which force a taxi driver to run for his life.

title: Our Idiot Brother
text: A comedy centered on an idealist who barges into the lives of his three sisters.

title: SUBWAYStories: Tales from the Underground
text: The actual experiences of New York City subway riders are dramatized in a collection of 10 intriguing and very different vignettes. The tales showcase an ensemble of familiar faces, and range from stories of compassion and love to reflections on violence and loss. Among them: a disabled beggar quarrels with a woman and ruins her shoes with his wheelchair, provoking onlookers to wrath and pity; a skittish tourist proves to be her own worst enemy; a newlywed trysts with a mysterious sexpot; a commuter helplessly witnesses a suicide attempt; and, in the most affecting segment, a young woman grieves over her mother's imminent death.

title: Death Race 2
text: Explores the origins of the first "Frankenstein" car driver, Carl "Luke" Lucas, who died in a race at the beginning of the first film.

title: Rise of the Planet of the Apes
text: A substance designed to help the brain repair itself gives advanced intelligence to a chimpanzee who leads an ape uprising.

title: Terri
text: The story of a bullied fifteen-year-old boy in a small town as he struggles to adjust to his difficult life.

title: Change-Up, The
text: Dave is a married man with three kids and a loving wife, and Mitch is a single man who is at the prime of his sexual life. One fateful night while Mitch and Dave are peeing in a fountain, lightning strikes and they switch bodies.

title: Help, The
text: An aspiring author during the civil rights movement of the 1960s decides to write a book detailing the African American maids' point of view on the white families for which they work, and the hardships they go through on a daily basis.

title: 30 Minutes or Less
text: Two fledgling criminals kidnap a pizza delivery guy, strap a bomb to his chest, and inform him that he has mere hours to rob a bank or else...

title: My Afternoons with Margueritte
text: A semi-literate and lonely odd-job man bonds with a much older and well-read woman.

title: Final Destination 5
text: Death returns to claim the lucky survivors of a deadly bridge collapse in this fifth frightening installment in the series.

title: Very Harold & Kumar 3D Christmas, A
text: Six years after their Guantanamo Bay adventure, stoner buds Harold Lee and Kumar Patel cause a holiday fracas by inadvertently burning down Harold's father-in-law's prize Christmas tree.

title: Don't Be Afraid of the Dark
text: A young girl sent to live with her father and his new girlfriend believes that she has released creatures from a sealed ash pit in the basement of her new home.

title: Fright Night
text: When a nice new neighbor moves in next door, Charley discovers that he is an ancient vampire who preys on the community. Can he save his neighborhood from the creature with the help of the famous "vampire killer", Peter Vincent?

title: Another Earth
text: On the night of the discovery of a duplicate Earth in the Solar system, an ambitious young student and an accomplished composer cross paths in a tragic accident.

title: Hesher
text: A young boy has lost his mother and is losing touch with his father and the world around him. Then he meets Hesher who manages to make his life even more chaotic.

title: Stake Land
text: In a world of vampires, an expert vampire hunter and his young protégé travel toward sanctuary.

title: Debt, The
text: In 1965, three Mossad Agents cross into East Berlin to apprehend a notorious Nazi war criminal. Thirty years later, the secrets the Agents share come back to haunt them.

title: Colombiana
text: A young girl in Bogotá witnesses her parents' murder and grows up to be a stone-cold assassin.

title: Bill Cunningham New York
text: A profile of the noted and extraordinarily cheerful veteran New York City fashion photographer.

title: Skin I Live In, The
text: A brilliant plastic surgeon, haunted by past tragedies, creates a type of synthetic skin that withstands any kind of damage. His guinea pig: a mysterious and volatile woman who holds the key to his obsession.

title: Conan the Barbarian
text: A vengeful barbarian warrior sets off to get his revenge on the evil warlord who attacked his village and murdered his father when he was a boy.

title: Walled In
text: Supervising the razing of a mysterious building, a young demolition engineer discovers past inhabitants entombed within its walls by a vicious murderer. Now she must turn the tables before she becomes the killer's latest victim.

title: Birdemic: Shock and Terror
text: A horde of mutated birds descends upon the quiet town of Half Moon Bay, California. With the death toll rising, Two citizens manage to fight back, but will they survive Birdemic?

title: Inbetweeners Movie, The
text: Four socially troubled 18-year-olds from the south of England go on holiday to Malia.

title: Red State
text: Set in Middle America, a group of teens receive an online invitation for sex, though they soon encounter fundamentalists with a much more sinister agenda.

title: Pearl Jam Twenty
text: A documentary on the band Pearl Jam that marks their 20th anniversary in the year 2011.

title: I Don't Know How She Does It
text: A comedy centered on the life of Kate Reddy, a finance executive who is the breadwinner for her husband and two kids.

title: Shark Night 3D
text: A weekend at a lake house in the Louisiana Gulf turns into a nightmare for seven vacationers as they are subjected to shark attacks.

title: Contagion
text: Healthcare professionals, government officials and everyday people find themselves in the midst of a pandemic as the CDC works to find a cure.

title: Moneyball
text: Oakland A's general manager Billy Beane's successful attempt to assemble a baseball team on a lean budget by employing computer-generated analysis to acquire new players.

title: Neds
text: Encompassed by violent street gangs, neglectful parents, bullying teachers and a dearth of positive role models, a studious but emotionally abandoned kid turns thug.

title: Cold Fish
text: The lives of a bored suburban couple are changed forever when a seemingly nice old man gives their daughter a job at his fish store, and soon his gruesome hobbies are brought to light.

title: Phineas and Ferb the Movie: Across the 2nd Dimension
text: Phineas and Ferb discover that Perry is a secret agent, and they all get stuck in an alternate dimension where Doofenschmirtz is the ruler of the tri-state area.

title: Northanger Abbey
text: A young woman's penchant for sensational Gothic novels leads to misunderstandings in the matters of the heart.

title: Avengers, The
text: Earth's mightiest heroes must come together and learn to fight as a team if they are going to stop the mischievous Loki and his alien army from enslaving humanity.

title: Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy
text: In the bleak days of the Cold War, espionage veteran George Smiley is forced from semi-retirement to uncover a Soviet Agent within MI6.

title: Separation, A
text: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Dangerous Method, A
text: A look at how the intense relationship between Carl Jung and Sigmund Freud gives birth to psychoanalysis.

title: Warrior
text: The youngest son of an alcoholic former boxer returns home, where he's trained by his father for competition in a mixed martial arts tournament - a path that puts the fighter on a collision course with his estranged, older brother.

title: Ides of March, The
text: An idealistic staffer for a new presidential candidate gets a crash course on dirty politics during his stint on the campaign trail.

title: Kill List
text: Nearly a year after a botched job, a hitman takes a new assignment with the promise of a big payoff for three killings. What starts off as an easy task soon unravels, sending the killer into the heart of darkness.

title: Killer Elite
text: When his mentor is taken captive by a disgraced Arab sheik, a killer-for-hire is forced into action. His mission: kill three members of Britain's elite Special Air Service responsible for the death of his sons.

title: Bellflower
text: Two friends spend all their free time building flame-throwers and weapons of mass destruction in hopes that a global apocalypse will occur and clear the runway for their imaginary gang "Mother Medusa".
Inspired by a true story, a comedy centered on a 27-year-old guy who learns of his cancer diagnosis and his subsequent struggle to beat the disease.

title: Generation P
text: A chronicle of the rise of the advertising industry in Post-Soviet Russia.

title: The Artist
text: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: Gigi
text: Gilberte is a sixteen year old girl raised by her aunt and grandmother to be a demimondaine. But she's not ready for that yet, and spends her days in lessons and in teasing Mamita's old friend, the rich playboy Gaston LaChaille, and following his affairs from afar. But when Gaston throws off his latest mistress, it looks as if Gigi just might be ready to begin her destined career.

title: BlinkyTM
text: A young boy living in the near future looks for an escape from a home with arguing parents. As a way to cope with the recent arguments from his parents he receives a robot companion that he ends up abusing.

title: Take Shelter
text: Plagued by a series of apocalyptic visions, a young husband and father questions whether to shelter his family from a coming storm, or from himself.

title: Three Outlaw Samurai
text: When poor peasants kidnap a magistrate's daughter to coerce him into reducing their unfair taxes, a wandering ronin decides to give them some help.

title: Antonio Gaudí
text: The work of Catalan architect Antonio Gaudí, as seen by Japanese New Wave director Hiroshi Teshigahara.

title: Real Steel
text: In the near future, robot boxing is a top sport. A struggling ex-boxer feels he's found a champion in a discarded robot.

title: Footloose
text: City teenager Ren MacCormack moves to a small town where rock music and dancing have been banned, and his rebellious spirit shakes up the populace.

title: Thing, The
text: At an Antarctica research site, the discovery of an alien craft leads to a confrontation between graduate student Kate Lloyd and scientist Dr. Sander Halvorson.

title: Beautiful Boy
text: A married couple on the verge of separation are leveled by the news their 18-year-old son committed a mass shooting at his college, then took his own life.

title: Tyrannosaur
text: Joseph, a man plagued by violence and a rage that is driving him to self-destruction, earns a chance of redemption that appears in the form of Hannah, a Christian charity shop worker.

title: Martha Marcy May Marlene
text: Haunted by painful memories and increasing paranoia, a damaged woman struggles to re-assimilate with her family after fleeing an abusive cult.

title: We Need to Talk About Kevin
text: Kevin's mother struggles to love her strange child, despite the increasingly dangerous things he says and does as he grows up. But Kevin is just getting started, and his final act will be beyond anything anyone imagined.

title: Behind Enemy Lines II: Axis of Evil
text: Navy SEALS, headed by Lt. Bobby James, are dispatched to North Korea on a covert mission, all in an effort to take out a missile site...

title: Three Musketeers, The
text: The hot-headed young D'Artagnan along with three former legendary but now down on their luck Musketeers must unite and defeat a beautiful double agent and her villainous employer from seizing the French throne and engulfing Europe in war.

title: In Time
text: In a future where people stop aging at 25, but are engineered to live only one more year, having the means to buy your way out of the situation is a shot at immortal youth. Here, Will Salas finds himself accused of murder and on the run with a hostage - a connection that becomes an important part of the way against the system.

title: Margaret
text: A young woman witnesses a bus accident, and is caught up in the aftermath, where the question of whether or not it was intentional affects many people's lives.

title: Carnage
text: Two pairs of parents hold a cordial meeting after their sons are involved in a fight, though as their time together progresses, increasingly childish behavior throws the discussion into chaos.

title: Margin Call
text: Follows the key people at an investment bank, over a 24-hour period, during the early stages of the 2008 financial crisis.

title: Paranormal Activity 3
text: In 1988, young sisters Katie and Kristi befriend an invisible entity who resides in their home.

title: Puncture
text: A David and Goliath law drama about a drug-addicted lawyer who takes on a health supply corporation while battling his own personal demons.

title: Johnny English Reborn
text: Johnny English goes up against international assassins hunting down Chinese Premier Xiang Ping.

title: Abduction
text: A young man sets out to uncover the truth about his life after finding his baby photo on a missing persons website.

title: This Must Be the Place
text: Cheyenne, a retired rock star living off his royalties in Dublin, returns to New York City to find the man responsible for a humiliation suffered by his recently deceased father during W.W.II.

title: Shame
text: A sex addict's carefully cultivated private life falls apart after his sister arrives for an indefinite stay.

title: What's Your Number?
text: A woman looks back at the past nineteen men she's had relationships with in her life and wonders if one of them might be her one true love.

title: Headhunters
text: An accomplished headhunter risks everything to obtain a valuable painting owned by a former mercenary.

title: Batman: Year One
text: A wealthy playboy and a Chicago cop both return to Gotham City where their lives will intersect in unexpected ways.

title: Miss Representation
text: Explores the under-representation of women in positions of power and influence in America, and challenges the media's limited portrayal of what it means to be a powerful woman.

title: Puss in Boots
text: An outlaw cat, his childhood egg-friend and a seductive thief kitty set out in search for the eggs of the fabled Golden Goose to clear his name, restore his lost honor and regain the trust of his mother and town.

title: Tower Heist
text: When a group of hard-working guys find out they've fallen victim to their wealthy employer's Ponzi scheme, they conspire to rob his high-rise residence.

title: J. Edgar
text: J. Edgar Hoover, powerful head of the F.B.I. for nearly fifty years, looks back on his professional and personal life.

title: Double, The
text: A retired CIA operative is paired with a young FBI agent to unravel the mystery of a senator's murder, with all signs pointing to a Soviet assassin.

title: Adventures of Tintin, The
text: Intrepid reporter Tintin and Captain Haddock set off on a treasure hunt for a sunken ship commanded by Haddock's ancestor.

title: Starsuckers
text: Documentary that explores mankind's desire to be famous and its effect on society.

title: Tomboy
text: A family moves into a new neighborhood, and a 10-year-old named Laure deliberately presents as a boy named Mikhael to the neighborhood children.

title: George Harrison: Living in the Material World
text: Filmmaker Martin Scorsese examines the life of musician George Harrison, weaving together interviews, concert footage, home movies and photographs.

title: Hugo
text: In 1931 Paris, an orphan living in the walls of a train station gets wrapped up in a mystery involving his late father and an automaton.

title: Immortals
text: Theseus is a mortal man chosen by Zeus to lead the fight against the ruthless King Hyperion, who is on a rampage across Greece to obtain a weapon that can destroy humanity.

title: Jack and Jill
text: Family guy Jack Sadelstein prepares for the annual event he dreads: the Thanksgiving visit of his fraternal twin sister, the needy and passive-aggressive Jill, who then refuses to leave.

title: Into the Abyss
text: Conversations with death row inmate Michael Perry and those affected by his crime serve as an examination of why people - and the state - kill.

title: Sign of Four, The
text: The disappearance of a young woman's father and a mysterious note years later after the strange regular annual delivery of valuable pearls to her puts Sherlock Holmes on the case.

title: Descendants, The
text: A land baron tries to reconnect with his two daughters after his wife is seriously injured in a boating accident.

title: Like Crazy
text: A British college student falls for an American student, only to be separated from him when she's banned from the U.S. after overstaying her visa.

title: Muppets, The
text: A Muppet fanatic with some help from his 2 human compatriots must regroup the Muppet gang to stop an avaricious oil mogul from taking down one of their precious life-longing treasures.

title: Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn - Part 1, The
text: The Quileutes close in on expecting parents Edward and Bella, whose unborn child poses a threat to the Wolf Pack and the towns people of Forks.

title: War Horse
text: Young Albert enlists to serve in World War I after his beloved horse is sold to the cavalry. Albert's hopeful journey takes him out of England and to the front lines as the war rages on.

title: Rum Diary, The
text: American journalist Paul Kemp takes on a freelance job in Puerto Rico for a local newspaper during the 1960s and struggles to find a balance between island culture and the expatriates who live there.

title: Lifted
text: A teenage alien is trying to abduct a sleeping human, but doesn't know which switch to use.

title: Hipsters
text: Young people struggle to do things their way in the 1950s.

title: Another Cinderella Story
text: Mary lives with her evil stepmom/sisters and slaves for them. At the high school masquerade ball, she gets to dance with her pop idol, Joey. Running home before midnight, she drops her Zune. Joey tries to find the girl who fits the Zune.

title: Bunraku
text: The story of a a young man who has spent his life searching for revenge only to find himself up against a bigger challenge than he originally bargained for.

title: Sitter, The
text: A college student on suspension is coaxed into babysitting the kids next door, though he is fully unprepared for the wild night ahead of him.

title: Extremely Loud and Incredibly Close
text: A nine-year-old amateur inventor, Francophile, and pacifist searches New York City for the lock that matches a mysterious key left behind by his father, who died in the World Trade Center on September 11, 2001.

title: Play the Game
text: A young ladies' man teaches his dating tricks to his lonely, widowed grandfather, and plays his best mind games to meet the woman of his dreams.

title: Asterix in America
text: Caesar has had enough when another legion is hacked to pieces by the damned single indomitable village in Gaul because of the druid's magic potion, so he decides to tackle the problem at the root before conspiratorial senators exploit his humiliation: sycophant Lucullus is ordered to capture the druid  and push him over the edge of the earth . By pure luck, Lucullus' first net traps both druid and Obelix's pet dog, so the giant and Asterix follow them by ship on the Atlantic, and crash after a storm on the North America coast in pursuit of the druid who was catapulted off the Roman galley before Lucullus triumphantly sets sails back for Europe. They find the druid and meet a tribe of Indians , literally a whole New World for the equally primitive Celts. At the home front, Caesar sees his chance to overrun the village, but has to wait till the last magic potion has run out, hoping the heroes won't return. In America, the medicine man has a bad eye in the foreigners, especially when the druid proves a dangerous rival...

title: Asterix and the Vikings
text: The vikings come to Gaul and kidnap the chief's nephew. The chief sends Asterix and Obelix up north to get him back but the nephew has fallen in love with the viking chief's daughter v.v. What to do?

title: Happy Feet Two
text: Mumble's son, Erik, is struggling to realize his talents in the Emperor Penguin world. Meanwhile, Mumble and his family and friends discover a new threat their home -- one that will take everyone working together to save them.

title: Arthur Christmas
text: Santa's clumsy son Arthur sets out on a mission with Grandsanta to give out a present they misplaced to a young girl in less than two hours.

title: Violet & Daisy
text: Two teenage assassins accept what they think will be a quick-and-easy job, until an unexpected target throws them off their plan.

title: Bullet to the Head
text: After watching their respective partners die, a New Orleans hitman and a Washington, D.C. detective form an alliance in order to bring down their common enemy.

title: Expendables 2, The
text: Mr. Church reunites the Expendables for what should be an easy paycheck, but when one of their men is murdered on the job, their quest for revenge puts them deep in enemy territory and up against an unexpected threat.

title: Snowman, The
text: On Christmas Eve, a young boy builds a snowman that comes to life and takes him to the North Pole to meet Father Christmas.

title: The Hunger Games
text: Katniss Everdeen voluntarily takes her younger sister's place in the Hunger Games: a televised competition in which two teenagers from each of the twelve Districts of Panem are chosen at random to fight to the death.

title: Dark Knight Rises, The
text: Eight years after the Joker's reign of anarchy, Batman, with the help of the enigmatic Catwoman, is forced from his exile to save Gotham City from the brutal guerrilla terrorist Bane.

title: Bourne Legacy, The
text: An expansion of the universe from Robert Ludlum's novels, centered on a new hero whose stakes have been triggered by the events of the previous three films.

title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows
text: Detective Sherlock Holmes is on the trail of criminal mastermind Professor Moriarty, who is carrying out a string of random crimes across Europe.

title: Coriolanus
text: A banished hero of Rome allies with a sworn enemy to take his revenge on the city.

title: Young Adult
text: Soon after her divorce, a fiction writer returns to her home in small-town Minnesota, looking to rekindle a romance with her ex-boyfriend, who is now happily married and has a newborn daughter.

title: New Year's Eve
text: The lives of several couples and singles in New York City intertwine over the course of New Year's Eve.

title: Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol
text: The IMF is shut down when it's implicated in the bombing of the Kremlin, causing Ethan Hunt and his new team to go rogue to clear their organization's name.

title: We Bought a Zoo
text: Set in Southern California, a father moves his young family to the countryside to renovate and re-open a struggling zoo.

title: Girl with the Dragon Tattoo, The
text: Journalist Mikael Blomkvist is aided in his search for a woman who has been missing for forty years by Lisbeth Salander, a young computer hacker.

title: Darkest Hour, The
text: In Moscow, five young people lead the charge against an alien race who have attacked Earth via our power supply.

title: Last Holiday
text: After a lonely, unappreciated farm equipment salesman discovers he has only a few weeks to live, he withdraws his savings for a final holiday at a "posh" resort.

title: Alvin and the Chipmunks: Chipwrecked
text: Playing around while aboard a cruise ship, the Chipmunks and Chipettes accidentally go overboard and end up marooned in a tropical paradise. They discover their new turf is not as deserted as it seems.

title: Salvation Boulevard
text: Set in the world of mega-churches in which a former Deadhead-turned-born again-Christian finds himself on the run from fundamentalist members of his mega-church who will do anything to protect their larger-than-life pastor.

title: Friends with Kids
text: Two best friends decide to have a child together while keeping their relationship platonic, so they can avoid the toll kids can take on romantic relationships.

title: Girl Walks Into a Bar
text: A sharp-witted comedy that follows a group of apparent strangers in interlocking stories taking place in ten different bars during the course of one evening throughout Los Angeles.

title: Contraband
text: To protect his brother-in-law from a drug lord, a former smuggler heads to Panama to score millions of dollars in counterfeit bills.

title: Way South, The
text: Johan van der Keuken went against the grain in 1980: from Amsterdam  via Paris, southern France and Italy to Egypt. He made his personal travelogue in three parts for VPRO television. Later, he fused the three parts into one long movie.

title: Being Elmo: A Puppeteer's Journey
text: The Muppet Elmo is one of the most beloved characters among children across the globe. Meet the unlikely man behind the puppet - the heart and soul of Elmo - Kevin Clash.

title: Joyful Noise
text: G.G. Sparrow faces off with her choir's newly appointed director, Vi Rose Hill, over the group's direction as they head into a national competition.

title: Iron Lady, The
text: An elderly Margaret Thatcher talks to the imagined presence of her recently deceased husband as she struggles to come to terms with his death while scenes from her past life, from girlhood to British prime minister, intervene.

title: Albatross
text: Beth, a bookish teenager, befriends Emilia, an aspiring novelist who has just arrived in town. Emilia soon begins an affair with Beth's father that threatens to have devastating consequences.

title: Revenant, The
text: In Los Angeles, a fallen soldier who has joined the ranks of the living dead reunites with his best friend in order to deal with the city's drug dealers and killers - a perfect way to collect the blood that one of them so desperately needs.

title: Underworld: Awakening
text: When human forces discover the existence of the Vampire and Lycan clans, a war to eradicate both species commences. The vampire warrior Selene leads the battle against humankind.

title: Grey, The
text: After their plane crashes in Alaska, six oil workers are led by a skilled huntsman to survival, but a pack of merciless wolves haunts their every step.

title: Man on a Ledge
text: As a police psychologist works to talk down an ex-con who is threatening to jump from a Manhattan hotel rooftop, the biggest diamond heist ever committed is in motion.

title: Sacrifice
text: To save the only child of the Zhao Family, whose entire clan was massacred at the hands of a nefarious minister, a doctor sacrifices his own son; after the Zhao child grows up, the doctor becomes intent on seeking his vengeance.

title: Haywire
text: A black ops super soldier seeks payback after she is betrayed and set up during a mission.

title: Contact High
text: An episodic comedy that follows the lives of four men living in Vienna.

title: Whistleblower, The
text: A drama based on the experiences of Kathryn Bolkovac, a Nebraska cop who served as a peacekeeper in post-war Bosnia and outed the U.N. for covering up a sex trafficking scandal.

title: Einstein and Eddington
text: Drama about the development of Albert Einstein's theory of general relativity, and Einstein's relationship with British scientist Sir Arthur Eddington, the first physicist to experimentally prove his ideas.

title: Apollo 18
text: Decades-old found footage from NASA's abandoned Apollo 18 mission, where three American astronauts were sent on a secret expedition, reveals the reason the U.S. has never returned to the moon.

title: Seeking Justice
text: After his wife is assaulted, a husband enlists the services of a vigilante group to help him settle the score. Then he discovers they want a 'favor' from him in return.

title: Red Tails
text: A crew of African American pilots in the Tuskegee training program, having faced segregation while kept mostly on the ground during World War II, are called into duty under the guidance of Col. A.J. Bullard.

title: Flowers of War, The
text: An American finds refuge during the 1937 Japanese invasion of Nanking in a church with a group of women. Posing as a priest, he attempts to lead the women to safety.

title: Intouchables
text: After he becomes a quadriplegic from a paragliding accident, an aristocrat hires a young man from the projects to be his caregiver.

title: One for the Money
text: Unemployed and newly-divorced Stephanie Plum lands a job at her cousin's bail-bond business, where her first assignment puts her on the trail of a wanted local cop from her romantic past.

title: Innkeepers, The
text: During the final days at the Yankee Pedlar Inn, two employees determined to reveal the hotel's haunted past begin to experience disturbing events as old guests check in for a stay.

title: Puss in Boots
text: While being on the run for saving a mouse, the famous Puss in Boots, Pero, helps a young peasant boy win the heart of a lovely princess, while trying to rescue her from an evil wizard.

title: Grave Encounters
text: For their ghost hunting reality show, a production crew locks themselves inside an abandoned mental hospital that's supposedly haunted - and it might prove to be all too true.

title: Chronicle
text: Three high school friends gain superpowers after making an incredible discovery underground. Soon they find their lives spinning out of control and their bond tested as they embrace their darker sides.

title: Woman in Black, The
text: A young solicitor travels to a remote village where he discovers that the vengeful ghost of a scorned woman is terrorizing the locals.

title: Woman in Love
text: An actor's career takes a "Tootsie"-like turn when he lets himself be cast as a woman in a movie.

title: Art of Getting By, The
text: George, a lonely and fatalistic teen who has made it all the way to his senior year without ever having done a real day of work, is befriended by Sally, a popular but complicated girl who recognizes in him a kindred spirit.

title: All Watched Over by Machines of Loving Grace
text: A series of films about how humans have been colonized by the machines we have built. Although we don't realize it, the way we see everything in the world today is through the eyes of the computers.

title: Dylan Moran: Monster
text: Irish comedian Dylan Moran live at Vicar Street, Dublin.

title: Safe House
text: A young CIA agent is tasked with looking after a fugitive in a safe house. But when the safe house is attacked, he finds himself on the run with his charge.

title: Vow, The
text: A car accident puts Paige in a coma, and when she wakes up with severe memory loss, her husband Leo works to win her heart again.

title: Louis C.K.: Live at the Beacon Theater
text: Louis jokes about fatherhood, success, and flying first class at the Beacon Theatre in New York.

title: Pitfall
text: A man wanders into a seemingly deserted town with his young son in search of work. But after a bit of bad luck, he joins the town's population of lost souls.

title: Monsieur Lazhar
text: At a Montréal public grade school, an Algerian immigrant is hired to replace a popular teacher who committed suicide in her classroom. While helping his students deal with their grief, his own recent loss is revealed.

title: For a Good Time, Call...
text: Former college frenemies Lauren and Katie move into a fabulous Gramercy Park apartment, and in order to make ends meet, the unlikely pair start a phone sex line together.

title: Janie Jones
text: A young girl who has been abandoned by her former-groupie mother informs a fading rock star that she is his daughter.

title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
text: Sean Anderson partners with his mom's husband on a mission to find his grandfather, who is thought to be missing on a mythical island.

title: Perfect Sense
text: A chef and a scientist fall in love as an epidemic begins to rob people of their sensory perceptions.

title: Rollo and the Woods Sprite
text: Troll-like rolleys find a village of goblins of the forest and take it as their own. The oldest of the rolley tribe leaves the community as it has came the time of him to rest and the tribe to choose a new lead. One rolley named Rölli follows the old leader and sees him changing into a turkey by a weird huge scale on top of a hill. New social order of the tribe does not come without conflicts in the community and between the rolleys and the goblins. One brave goblin called Milli tries to make a peace between rolleys and goblins, but rolleys can not be friends with kind creatures. Yet Milli and Rölli become partners in trying to return the balance between the good and the bad in the forest.

title: Atomic Brain, The
text: A rich but unscrupulous old woman plots with a scientist to have her brain implanted in the skull of a sexy young woman.

title: Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance
text: Johnny Blaze, tortured by the Ghost Rider's curse, gets a chance of redemption through protecting the Devil's son, whose father is pursuing him.

title: Prayers for Bobby
text: True story of Mary Griffith, gay rights crusader, whose teenage son committed suicide due to her religious intolerance. Based on the book of the same title by Leroy Aarons.

title: Very Potter Musical, A
text: Harry and his pals are in for adventure when the Dark Lord returns from the dead to take revenge on The Boy Who Lived! So take a ride on Voldemort's flying machine and get ready to go back to Hogwarts!

title: Very Potter Sequel, A
text: Harry and his pals are back for more adventures when they face off against dark wizards, demented monsters, and the most horrible woman in the world, Dolores Umbridge! So strap on your diapers because it's time to go back to Hogwarts.

title: Miss Nobody
text: A mild-mannered secretary discovers that she has a talent for murder as she ascends the corporate ladder.

title: Civil War, The
text: A comprehensive survey of the American Civil War.

title: Ro.Go.Pa.G.
text: Four short films by four different directors dealing with the principles of modern life.

title: Women on the 6th Floor, The
text: In 1960s Paris, a conservative couple's lives are turned upside down by a group of Spanish maids that live in the same building.

title: Mega Shark vs. Crocosaurus
text: A megalodon battles with a crocosaurus causing massive destruction. The US Army has to try and destroy the havoc creating monsters.

title: Red Hill
text: A young police officer must survive his first day's duty in a small country town.

title: Mickey's The Prince and the Pauper
text: A poor boy and a prince exchange identities and lives while the villainous Captain of the Guard plots to take advantage of this.

title: Gone
text: A woman is convinced her kidnapper has returned when her sister goes missing.

title: Project X
text: 3 high school seniors throw a birthday party to make a name for themselves. As the night progresses, things spiral out of control as word of the party spreads.

title: Dr. Seuss' The Lorax
text: A 12-year-old boy searches for the one thing that will enable him to win the affection of the girl of his dreams. To find it he must discover the story of the Lorax, the grumpy yet charming creature who fights to protect his world.

title: Big Year, The
text: Two bird enthusiasts try to defeat the cocky, cutthroat world record holder in a year-long bird-spotting competition.

title: Act of Valor
text: An elite team of Navy SEALs embark on a covert mission to recover a kidnapped CIA agent.

title: Trailer Park Boys
text: Two petty felons have a documentary made about their life in a trailer park.

title: This Means War
text: C.I.A. operatives wage an epic battle on each other when they discover they are dating the same woman.

title: John Carter
text: Transported to Barsoom, a Civil War vet discovers a barren planet seemingly inhabited by 12-foot tall barbarians. Finding himself prisoner of these creatures, he escapes, only to encounter Woola and a princess in desperate need of a savior.

title: Goon
text: Labeled an outcast by his brainy family, a bouncer overcomes long odds to lead a team of under performing misfits to semi-pro hockey glory, beating the crap out of everything that stands in his way.

title: Ledge, The
text: A police officer looks to talk down a young man lured by his lover's husband to the ledge of a high rise, where he has one hour to contemplate a fateful decision.

title: 21 Jump Street
text: A pair of underachieving cops are sent back to a local high school to blend in and bring down a synthetic drug ring.

title: Jeff, Who Lives at Home
text: Dispatched from his basement room on an errand for his widowed mother, slacker Jeff might discover his destiny  when he spends the day with his unhappily married brother as he tracks his possibly adulterous wife.

title: Lockout
text: A man wrongly convicted of conspiracy to commit espionage against the U.S. is offered his freedom if he can rescue the president's daughter from an outer space prison taken over by violent inmates.

title: Snowtown
text: Based on true events, 16 year-old Jamie falls in with his mother's new boyfriend and his crowd of self-appointed neighborhood watchmen, a relationship that leads to a spree of torture and murder.

title: Space Battleship Yamato
text: In 2199, the crew of the space battleship Yamato embark on a dangerous journey to the planet Iskandar to acquire a device that will rejuvenate the war-ravaged Earth.

title: Jiro Dreams of Sushi
text: A documentary on 85-year-old sushi master Jiro Ono, his renowned Tokyo restaurant, and his relationship with his son and eventual heir, Yoshikazu.

title: Damsels in Distress
text: A trio of girls set out to change the male-dominated environment of the Seven Oaks college campus, and to rescue their fellow students from depression, grunge and low standards of every kind.

title: Salmon Fishing in the Yemen
text: A fisheries expert is approached by a consultant to help realize a sheik's vision of bringing the sport of fly-fishing to the desert and embarks on an upstream journey of faith and fish to prove the impossible possible.

title: Wrath of the Titans
text: Perseus braves the treacherous underworld to rescue his father, Zeus, captured by his son, Ares, and brother Hades who unleash the ancient Titans upon the world.

title: Detachment
text: A substitute teacher who drifts from classroom to classroom finds a connection to the students and teachers during his latest assignment.

title: Iron Sky
text: The Nazis set up a secret base on the dark side of the moon in 1945 where they hide out and plan to return to power in 2018.

title: Absentia
text: A woman and her sister begin to link a mysterious tunnel to a series of disappearances, including that of her own husband.

title: American Reunion
text: Jim, Michelle, Stifler, and their friends reunite in East Great Falls, Michigan for their high school reunion.

title: The Raid: Redemption
text: A S.W.A.T. team becomes trapped in a tenement run by a ruthless mobster and his army of killers and thugs.

title: Cabin in the Woods, The
text: Five friends go for a break at a remote cabin, where they get more than they bargained for, discovering the truth behind the cabin in the woods.

title: God Bless America
text: On a mission to rid society of its most repellent citizens, terminally ill Frank makes an unlikely accomplice in 16-year-old Roxy.

title: Three Stooges, The
text: While trying to save their childhood orphanage, Moe, Larry and Curly inadvertently stumble into a murder plot and wind up starring in a reality television show.

title: Raven, The
text: When a madman begins committing horrific murders inspired by Edgar Allan Poe's works, a young Baltimore detective joins forces with Poe to stop him from making his stories a reality.

title: North & South
text: North and South is a four part adaptation of Elizabeth Gaskell's love story of Margaret Hale, a middle class southerner who is forced to move to the northern town of Milton.

title: Big Bang, The
text: A private detective is hired to find a missing stripper. A simple job turns complicated when everyone he questions ends up dead.

title: Mirror Mirror
text: An evil queen steals control of a kingdom and an exiled princess enlists the help of seven resourceful rebels to win back her birthright.

title: Battleship
text: A fleet of ships is forced to do battle with an armada of unknown origins in order to discover and thwart their destructive goals.

title: Best Exotic Marigold Hotel, The
text: British retirees travel to India to take up residence in what they believe is a newly restored hotel. Less luxurious than advertised, the Marigold Hotel nevertheless slowly begins to charm in unexpected ways.

title: Comic-Con Episode IV: A Fan's Hope
text: A behind-the-scenes look at the fans who gather by the thousands each year in San Diego, California to attend Comic-Con, the world's largest comic book convention.

title: Bully
text: A documentary on peer-to-peer bullying in schools across America.

title: Hysteria
text: The truth of how Mortimer Granville devised the invention of the first vibrator in the name of medical science.

title: Dante's Inferno: An Animated Epic
text: Dante journeys through the nine circles of Hell -- limbo, lust, gluttony, greed, anger, heresy, violence, fraud and treachery -- in search of his true love, Beatrice.

title: Atomic Submarine, The
text: Ships mysteriously disappear on route across the Arctic Sea, and a specially-equipped submarine is sent to investigate.

title: Five-Year Engagement, The
text: One year after meeting, Tom proposes to his girlfriend, Violet, but unexpected events keep tripping them up as they look to walk down the aisle together.

title: Think Like a Man
text: Four friends conspire to turn the tables on their women when they discover the ladies have been using Steve Harvey's relationship advice against them.

title: Lucky One, The
text: A Marine travels to Louisiana after serving three tours in Iraq and searches for the unknown woman he believes was his good luck charm during the war.

title: Safe
text: Mei, a young girl whose memory holds a priceless numerical code, finds herself pursued by the Triads, the Russian mob, and corrupt NYC cops. Coming to her aid is an ex-cage fighter whose life was destroyed by the gangsters on Mei's trail.

title: Dark Shadows
text: An imprisoned vampire, Barnabas Collins, is set free and returns to his ancestral home, where his dysfunctional descendants are in need of his protection.

title: 96 Minutes
text: The story of 4 lives slammed together in a shocking moment. Intercutting between a carjacking and the separate stories of the 4 kids in Atlanta, we watch as they hurtle toward a life-changing end.

title: Decoy Bride, The
text: When the world's media descend on the remote Scottish island where a Hollywood actress is attempting to get married, a local girl is hired as a decoy bride to put the paparazzi off the scent.

title: Rocket Singh: Salesman of the Year
text: A story of a fresh graduate trying to find a balance between the maddening demands of the 'professional' way, and the way of his heart.

title: Dictator, The
text: The heroic story of a dictator who risked his life to ensure that democracy would never come to the country he so lovingly oppressed.

title: Walking with Monsters
text: The final installment in the "Walking with" series is a 90-minute documentary about the evolution of life before the dinosaurs.

title: Men in Black III
text: Agent J travels in time to M.I.B.'s early days in 1969 to stop an alien from assassinating his friend Agent K and changing history.

title: Snow White and the Huntsman
text: In a twist to the fairy tale, the Huntsman ordered to take Snow White into the woods to be killed winds up becoming her protector and mentor in a quest to vanquish the Evil Queen.

title: Sound of My Voice
text: Two documentary filmmakers attempt to penetrate a cult who worships a woman who claims to be from the future.

title: Eva
text: A shy genius is employed by his former university to design robot software.

title: Pirates! Band of Misfits, The
text: Pirate Captain sets out on a mission to defeat his rivals Black Bellamy and Cutlass Liz for the Pirate of the year Award. The quest takes Captain and his crew from the shores of Blood Island to the foggy streets of Victorian London.

title: Prometheus
text: Following clues to the origin of mankind, a team finds a structure on a distant moon, but they soon realize they are not alone.

title: Pact, The
text: As a woman struggles to come to grips with her past in the wake of her mother's death and the disappearance of her sister, an unsettling presence emerges in her childhood home.

title: Bernie
text: In small-town Texas, an affable mortician strikes up a friendship with a wealthy widow, though when she starts to become controlling, he goes to great lengths to separate himself from her grasp.

title: Inhale
text: A couple goes to dangerous lengths to find a lung donor for their daughter.

title: Take This Waltz
text: A happily married woman falls for the artist who lives across the street.

title: Wanderlust
text: Rattled by sudden unemployment, a Manhattan couple surveys alternative living options, ultimately deciding to experiment with living on a rural commune where free love rules.

title: Moonrise Kingdom
text: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: Get the Gringo
text: A career criminal nabbed by Mexican authorities is placed in a tough prison where he learns to survive with the help of a young boy.

title: Superman/Doomsday
text: When LexCorps accidentally unleash a murderous creature, Doomsday, Superman meets his greatest challenge as a champion. Based on the "The Death of Superman" storyline that appeared in DC Comics' publications in the 1990s.

title: Thousand Words, A
text: After stretching the truth on a deal with a spiritual guru, literary agent Jack McCall finds a Bodhi tree on his property. Its appearance holds a valuable lesson on the consequences of every word he speaks.

title: Safety Not Guaranteed
text: Three magazine employees head out on an assignment to interview a guy who placed a classified advertisement seeking a companion for time travel.

title: Madagascar 3: Europe's Most Wanted
text: The Madagascar animals join a struggling European circus to get back to New York, but find themselves being pursued by a psychotic animal control officer.

title: Your Sister's Sister
text: Iris invites her friend Jack to stay at her family's island getaway after his brother's death. Jack's drunken encounter with Iris' sister Hannah at their remote cabin kicks off a revealing stretch of days.

title: Dragon Ball: The Curse Of The Blood Rubies
text: Goku and his friends must stop King Gurumes from destroying the city for blood rubies and gathering the seven Dragon Balls.

title: Dragon Ball: Sleeping Princess in Devil's Castle
text: Goku and Krillin want to be trained in the martial arts by the great Master Roshi. The only way he will agree to train them is if they go to Devil's Castle to find the Sleeping Princess, who is being held prisoner by Count Lucifer, and bring her back to his island.

title: Superman/Batman: Public Enemies
text: When Lex Luthor gets elected US President, he uses the threat of an oncoming kryptonite meteor striking Earth as a rationale to frame Superman.

title: Dragon Ball: Mystical Adventure
text: Emperor Chiaotzu's wife has gone missing, and he is told by Master Shen that if he collects the seven dragon balls he can call upon the eternal dragon and wish for her return. Meanwhile, Goku and Krillin attend the World Martial Arts Tournament, which is hosted by the Emperor; Bora and his son Upa attempt to hide the dragon ball they found from the emperor's forces, which are under the control of the evil Shen and General Tao; and Bulma conducts her own search for the dragon balls with the help of Yamcha, Puar, and Oolong.

title: Dragon Ball Z the Movie: The World's Strongest
text: The Z-Fighters must stop a mad scientist out to take over the world.

title: Brave
text: Determined to make her own path in life, Princess Merida  defies a custom that brings chaos to her kingdom. Granted one wish, Merida must rely on her bravery and her archery skills to undo a beastly curse.

title: Beauty and the Beast: The Enchanted Christmas
text: Astonished to find the Beast  has a deep-seeded hatred for the Christmas season, Belle  endeavors to change his mind on the matter.

title: Front of the Class
text: Brad Cohen who, despite being challenged by Tourette's Syndrome at a very young age, defies all odds to become a gifted teacher.

title: Dragon Ball Z the Movie: The Tree of Might
text: A group of aliens visit Earth to plant the Tree of Might, a plant that grants cosmic power by draining the Earth's life force.

title: Pocahontas II: Journey to a New World
text: Pocahontas sets off on a journey to England with Meeko, Flit, and Percy. Hearing rumors of John Smith's death, Pocahontas tries to prevent war and battle.

title: What to Expect When You're Expecting
text: Follows the lives of five interconnected couples as they experience the thrills and surprises of having a baby and realize that no matter what you plan for, life does not always deliver what is expected.

title: To Rome with Love
text: The lives of some visitors and residents of Rome and the romances, adventures and predicaments they get into.

title: Abraham Lincoln: Vampire Hunter
text: Abraham Lincoln, the 16th President of the United States, discovers vampires are planning to take over the United States. He makes it his mission to eliminate them.

title: First Position
text: A documentary that follows six young dancers from around the world as they prepare for the Youth America Grand Prix, one of the most prestigious ballet competitions in the world.

title: Rock of Ages
text: A small-town girl and a city boy meet on the Sunset Strip while pursuing their Hollywood dreams.

title: Seeking a Friend for the End of the World
text: As an asteroid nears Earth, a man finds himself alone after his wife leaves in a panic. He decides to take a road trip to reunite with his high school sweetheart. Accompanying him is a neighbor who inadvertently puts a wrench in his plan.

title: Presto
text: A stage magician's rabbit gets into a magical onstage brawl against his neglectful guardian with two magic hats.

title: Jack-Jack Attack
text: The Parrs' baby Jack-Jack is thought to be normal, not having any super-powers like his parents or siblings. But when an outsider is hired to watch him, Jack-Jack shows his true potential.

title: One Man Band
text: Two buskers engage in a petty feud over a child's donation.

title: Ted
text: John Bennett, a man whose childhood wish of bringing his teddy bear to life came true, now must decide between keeping the relationship with the bear, Ted or his girlfriend, Lori.

title: Magic Mike
text: A male stripper teaches a younger performer how to party, pick up women, and make easy money.

title: Dragon Ball Z: The Return of Cooler
text: Cooler has resurrected himself as a robot and is enslaving the people of New Namek. Goku and the gang must help.

title: Dragon Ball Z: Cooler's Revenge
text: Frieza's older brother Cooler travels to Earth to take revenge against Goku for Frieza's defeat on planet Namek.

title: Dragon Ball Z: Super Android 13!
text: The death of Dr. Gero at the hands of Androids 17 and 18 prompts the activation of Androids 13, 14, and 15. They try to kill Goku, who fights them with the help of Trunks, Piccolo, Vegeta, Krillin, and Gohan.

title: Dragon Ball Z: Broly - The Legendary Super Saiyan
text: Vegeta is lured to the planet New Vegeta by a group of Saiyan survivors in hopes that he will be the king of their new planet. But when he finds that they have ulterior motives of universal domination, he and the Z Warriors must fight Broly, the legendary Super Saiyan.

title: Cleanskin
text: A British secret service agent is faced with the task of pursuing and eliminating a British-born suicide bomber and his terrorist cell.

title: Amazing Spider-Man, The
text: After Peter Parker is bitten by a genetically altered spider, he gains newfound, spider-like powers and ventures out to save the city from the machinations of a mysterious reptilian foe.

title: Dragon Ball Z: Bojack Unbound
text: Bojack is a demon who was freed from prison when King Kai's planet was destroyed. Now, without his father Goku by his side, can Gohan save the Earth?

title: Ice Age 4: Continental Drift
text: Manny, Diego, and Sid embark upon another adventure after their continent is set adrift. Using an iceberg as a ship, they encounter sea creatures and battle pirates as they explore a new world.

title: Beasts of the Southern Wild
text: Faced with both her hot-tempered father's fading health and melting ice-caps that flood her ramshackle bayou community and unleash ancient aurochs, six-year-old Hushpuppy must learn the ways of courage and love.

title: Savages
text: Pot growers Ben and Chon face off against the Mexican drug cartel who kidnapped their shared girlfriend.

title: Firm, The
text: Football hooligans organize themselves into firms that represent their favorite team.

title: Spirit Camp
text: When a street smart "goth girl"  is forced to attend cheerleader camp as part of her rehabilitation from a juvenile correction facility, she clashes with the "popular girls," and finds herself embroiled in a bitter rivalry with the bitchy ringleader Rachel . But when members of the spirit squad start turning up dead, the girls must put aside their differences and struggle to survive the murderous rage of a crazed psycho-killer lurking among them!

title: Geri's Game
text: Geri sets up a chess game to play his greatest opponent - himself.

title: Some Guy Who Kills People
text: Ken Boyd, a lonely man fresh out of the loony bin, who sets out to kill those he deems responsible for his miserable life.

title: Treasure Island
text: In 1765, young English boy Jim Hawkins gets involved with buccaneers during his quest to find pirate Captain Flint's treasure buried on a secret island.

title: Watch, The
text: Four men who form a neighborhood watch group as a way to get out of their day-to-day family routines find themselves defending the Earth from an alien invasion.

title: Adventures of Mary-Kate and Ashley, The: The Case of the Christmas Caper
text: In this episode, the sly sleuths are busy wrapping holiday gifts and learning carols when a call from the Three Wise Men sends them in search of The Spirit of Christmas! Now, it's up to the dynamic duo to use all their computer smarts and solve this holiday crime by Christmas time!

title: 2 Days in New York
text: Manhattan couple Marion and Mingus, who each have children from prior relationships, find their comfortable family dynamic jostled by a visit from Marion's relatives.

title: Killer Joe
text: When a debt puts a young man's life in danger, he turns to putting a hit out on his evil mother in order to collect the insurance.

title: Anaconda: The Offspring
text: A mercenary-for-hire accepts a mission from a billionaire to capture a dangerous snake that could possibly help cure a terminal illness.

title: Christmas Carol, A
text: An old bitter miser who makes excuses for his uncaring nature learns real compassion when three ghosts visit him on Christmas Eve.

title: Goodbye Charlie
text: Womanizing Charlie is shot by an angry husband and falls in the sea. He arrives home after his memorial as a cute, amnesic woman. His old friend helps her/him.

title: For the Birds
text: A group of snooty birds roosting on a telephone wire get their just deserts when a goofy bird drops in.

title: Ruby Sparks
text: A novelist struggling with writer's block finds romance in a most unusual way: by creating a female character he thinks will love him, then willing her into existence.

title: Total Recall
text: A factory worker, Douglas Quaid, begins to suspect that he is a spy after visiting Rekall - a company that provides its clients with implanted fake memories of a life they would like to have led - goes wrong and he finds himself on the run.

title: Angels' Share, The
text: Narrowly avoiding jail, new dad Robbie vows to turn over a new leaf. A visit to a whisky distillery inspires him and his mates to seek a way out of their hopeless lives.

title: Immature, The
text: Twenty years ago, while they were 12th grade students, Giorgio, Lorenzo, Piero, Luisa, Virgilio and Francesca were a high-spirited band. Then they graduated, integrated themselves into society and lost track of one another. One day they receive a letter from the Ministry of Education: because of a formal error, they must retake the exam. With the initial shock now past, they grasp the opportunity to meet again, to share laughters and to cram together like they used to. On the other hand, they are not the same persons they were two decades before...

title: Dragon Ball Z: Bardock - The Father of Goku
text: The tale of Bardock, the father of Goku, and his rebellion against his master the mighty Frieza.

title: Dragon Ball Z: The History of Trunks
text: In a dark future where the Androids have taken over Earth, Gohan and his student Trunks are the last defense against these deadly killing machines.

title: Dragon Ball GT: A Hero's Legacy
text: Goku Jr. is the great-great-grandson of the legendary warrior Goku, but unlike his predecessor he's not a brave fighter. He's constantly picked on by school bullies--his grandmother Pan sees this and is worried, but even though Goku Jr. is not a strong and powerful saiyan, he has a kind heart, and Pan loves him. When Pan gets sick, Goku Jr. realizes that he must do something if he doesn't want to lose her. Then he remembers about the legends of the Dragon Balls. It was told that they grant a wish to the bearer, and Goku Jr. needs a magical wish more than ever, so he sets out to find the dragon ball that his grandmother told him about.

title: Sidewalls
text: Martín and Mariana are slightly damaged people who live in buildings just opposite one another. While they often don't notice each other, separation might be the very thing that brings them together.

title: Skyfall
text: James Bond's loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. When MI6 comes under attack, 007 must track down and destroy the threat, no matter how personal the cost.

title: Hands Over the City
text: Prior to a city council election, the collapse of a building leaves a land developer and his political backers defending themselves against a scandal.

title: Campaign, The
text: An incumbent Representative embroiled in personal scandal faces a no-holds-barred challenge from a naive newcomer funded by two unscrupulous billionaire lobbyist brothers.

title: Brake
text: A Secret Service Agent is held captive in the trunk of a car and endures mental and physical torture as terrorists attempt to extract information for their plot against the President of the United States.

title: Hope Springs
text: After thirty years of marriage, a middle-aged couple attends an intense, week-long counseling session to work on their relationship.

title: Queen of Versailles, The
text: A documentary that follows a billionaire couple as they begin construction on a mansion inspired by Versailles. During the next two years, their empire, fueled by the real estate bubble and cheap money, falters due to the economic crisis.

title: ParaNorman
text: A misunderstood boy takes on ghosts, zombies and grown-ups to save his town from a centuries-old curse.

title: Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days
text: School's out. Summer vacation is on. However, Greg may not have the best summer vacation ever. What could go wrong?

title: Broken
text: Three suburban English families' lives intertwine with tragic consequences.

title: 6 Days to Air: The Making of South Park
text: A look at the making of HUMANCENTiPAD .

title: Premium Rush
text: In Manhattan, a bike messenger picks up an envelope that attracts the interest of a dirty cop, who pursues the cyclist throughout the city.

title: Odd Life of Timothy Green, The
text: A childless couple bury a box in their backyard, containing all of their wishes for an infant. Soon, a child is born, though Timothy Green is not all that he appears.

title: Lawless
text: Set in Depression-era Franklin County, Virginia, a trio of bootlegging brothers are threatened by a new special deputy and other authorities angling for a cut of their profits.

title: Piranha 3DD
text: After the events at Lake Victoria, the pre-historic school of blood-thirsty piranhas make their way into a newly opened waterpark.

title: Prime Suspect 3
text: Assigned to a Vice squad, Detective Chief Inspector Jane Tennison  investigates a child murder and discovers a sinister link to the police.

title: Searching for Sugar Man
text: Two South Africans set out to discover what happened to their unlikely musical hero, the mysterious 1970s rock n roller, Rodriguez.

title: Prime Suspect 6: The Last Witness
text: Detective Superintendent Jane Tennison's  investigation of the murder of a Bosnian refugee leads her to one, or possibly two, Serbian war criminals determined to silence the last witness to a massacre a decade before.

title: Prime Suspect: The Lost Child
text: Superintendent Jane Tennison  orchestrates a search for an abducted baby, but events take a turn for the worse when personal emotions cause complications.

title: Conception
text: A comedy that follows nine very different couples on the night they conceive, showing that sex can sometimes be more neurotic than erotic.

title: Paradise Lost 3: Purgatory
text: A further followup of the case of the West Memphis Three and the decades long fight to exonerate them that finally gained traction with new DNA evidence.

title: Words, The
text: A writer at the peak of his literary success discovers the steep price he must pay for stealing another man's work.

title: Pitch Perfect
text: Beca, a freshman at Barden University, is cajoled into joining The Bellas, her school's all-girls singing group. Injecting some much needed energy into their repertoire, The Bellas take on their male rivals in a campus competition.

title: Samsara
text: Filmed over nearly five years in twenty-five countries on five continents, and shot on seventy-millimetre film, Samsara transports us to the varied worlds of sacred grounds, disaster zones, industrial complexes, and natural wonders.

title: Runaway Brain
text: In an attempt to convince Minnie that he hasn't forgotten to buy her an anniversary present, Mickey Mouse ends up promising to take her to Hawaii. Funds being short, he applies for a job as lab assistant to the sinister Dr. Frankenollie, who happens to be searching for a donor to provide his monstrous creation with a brain...

title: Looper
text: In 2074, when the mob wants to get rid of someone, the target is sent into the past, where a hired gun awaits - someone like Joe - who one day learns the mob wants to 'close the loop' by sending back Joe's future self for assassination.

title: That's My Boy
text: While in his teens, Donny fathered a son, Todd, and raised him as a single parent until Todd's 18th birthday. Now Donny resurfaces just before Todd's wedding after years apart, sending the groom-to-be's world crashing down.

title: Robot & Frank
text: In the near future, an ex-jewel thief receives a gift from his son: a robot butler programmed to look after him. But soon the two companions try their luck as a heist team.

title: Resident Evil: Retribution
text: Alice fights alongside a resistance movement to regain her freedom from an Umbrella Corporation testing facility.

title: Lola Versus
text: Dumped by her boyfriend just three weeks before their wedding, Lola enlists her close friends for a series of adventures she hopes will help her come to terms with approaching 30 as a single woman.

title: Master, The
text: A Naval veteran arrives home from war unsettled and uncertain of his future - until he is tantalized by the Cause and its charismatic leader.

title: Dredd
text: In a violent, futuristic city where the police have the authority to act as judge, jury and executioner, a cop teams with a trainee to take down a gang that deals the reality-altering drug, SLO-MO.

title: End of Watch
text: Shot documentary-style, this film follows the daily grind of two young police officers in LA who are partners and friends, and what happens when they meet criminal forces greater than themselves.

title: V/H/S
text: When a group of misfits are hired by an unknown third party to burglarize a desolate house and acquire a rare VHS tape, they discover more found footage than they bargained for.

title: Perks of Being a Wallflower, The
text: An introvert freshman is taken under the wings of two seniors who welcome him to the real world.

title: Hunt, The
text: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son's custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.

title: Holy Motors
text: From dawn to dusk, a few hours in the shadowy life of a mystic man named Monsieur Oscar.

title: Taken 2
text: In Istanbul, retired CIA operative Bryan Mills and his wife are taken hostage by the father of a kidnapper Mills killed while rescuing his daughter.

title: House at the End of the Street
text: After moving with her mother to a small town, a teenager finds that an accident happened in the house at the end of the street. Things get more complicated when she befriends a boy. A double murder is not an accident.

title: My Left Eye Sees Ghosts
text: A car accident gives a spoiled, troubled young woman the ability to see ghosts, including one of a former classmate.

title: Love Lasts Three Years
text: A look at the dissolution of a marriage.

title: Tall Man, The
text: When her child goes missing, a mother looks to unravel the legend of the Tall Man, an entity who allegedly abducts children.

title: LOL
text: As a new year at school begins, Lola's heart is broken by her boyfriend, though soon she's surprised by her best friend, promising musician Kyle, who reveals his feelings for her.

title: Rust and Bone
text: Put in charge of his young son, Alain leaves Belgium for Antibes to live with his sister and her husband as a family. Alain's bond with Stephanie, a killer whale trainer, grows deeper after Stephanie suffers a horrible accident.

title: Marley
text: A documentary on the life, music, and legacy of Bob Marley.

title: Frankenweenie
text: When a boy's beloved dog passes away suddenly, he attempts to bring the animal back to life through a powerful science experiment.

title: Sinister
text: Washed-up true crime writer Ellison Oswalt finds a box of super 8 home movies in his new home that suggest the murder that he is currently researching is the work of a serial killer whose legacy dates back to the 1960s.

title: Thing: Terror Takes Shape, The
text: A revealing and insightful look into the making of this underrated horror film.

title: Hotel Transylvania
text: Dracula, who operates a high-end resort away from the human world, goes into overprotective mode when a boy discovers the resort and falls for the count's teenaged daughter.

title: Side by Side
text: The documentary investigates the history, process and workflow of both digital and photochemical film creation.

title: Take Aim at the Police Van
text: A prison truck is assaulted and the two convicts inside are murdered. The prison guard on duty gets suspended for negligence and takes it upon himself to track down the killers.

title: Argo
text: Acting under the cover of a Hollywood producer scouting a location for a science fiction film, a CIA agent launches a dangerous operation to rescue six Americans in Tehran during the U.S. hostage crisis in Iran in 1979.

title: Seven Psychopaths
text: A struggling screenwriter inadvertently becomes entangled in the Los Angeles criminal underworld after his oddball friends kidnap a gangster's beloved Shih Tzu.

title: Liberal Arts
text: When 30-something Jesse returns to his alma mater for a professor's retirement party, he falls for Zibby, a college student, and is faced with a powerful attraction that springs up between them.

title: Catch .44
text: 3 women are sent to intercept a major drug deal at a diner at 3 AM and get the money. Simple - save for Murphy's law: Anything that can go wrong will go wrong.

title: [REC]³ 3 Génesis
text: A couple's wedding day turns horrific as some of the guests start showing signs of a strange illness.

title: Asterix & Obelix: God Save Britannia
text: Asterix crosses the channel to help second-cousin Anticlimax face down Julius Caesar and invading Romans.

title: Paranormal Activity 4
text: It has been five years since the disappearance of Katie and Hunter, and a suburban family witness strange events in their neighborhood when a woman and a mysterious child move in.

title: Alex Cross
text: A homicide detective is pushed to the brink of his moral and physical limits as he tangles with a ferociously skilled hired killer who specializes in torture and pain.

title: Cloud Atlas
text: An exploration of how the actions of individual lives impact one another in the past, present and future, as one soul is shaped from a killer into a hero, and an act of kindness ripples across centuries to inspire a revolution.

title: Hellboy': The Seeds of Creation
text: In-depth documentary about the history of the Hellboy comic book, the history of the character and the making of the 2004 movie adaptation of the same name.

title: Silent Hill: Revelation 3D
text: When her adoptive father disappears, Sharon Da Silva is drawn into a strange and terrifying alternate reality that holds answers to the horrific nightmares that have plagued her since childhood.

title: Here Comes the Boom
text: A high-school biology teacher looks to become a successful mixed martial arts fighter in an effort to raise money to prevent extracurricular activities from being axed at his cash-strapped school.

title: Mental
text: A charismatic, crazy hothead transforms a family's life when she becomes the nanny of five girls whose mother has cracked from her husband's political ambitions and his infidelity.

title: Killing Them Softly
text: Jackie Cogan is an enforcer hired to restore order after three dumb guys rob a Mob protected card game, causing the local criminal economy to collapse.

title: Imposter, The
text: A documentary centered on a young man in Spain who claims to a grieving Texas family that he is their 16-year-old son who has been missing for 3 years.

title: Sessions, The
text: A man in an iron lung who wishes to lose his virginity contacts a professional sex surrogate with the help of his therapist and priest.

title: Smashed
text: A married couple whose bond is built on a mutual love of alcohol gets their relationship put to the test when the wife decides to get sober.

title: Wreck-It Ralph
