title: Haunted House 2, A
text: Having exorcised the demons of his ex, Malcolm is starting fresh with his new girlfriend and her two children. After moving into their dream home, however, Malcolm is once again plagued by bizarre paranormal events.

title: Mulan II
text: While preparing for their wedding, Shang and Mulan are suddenly sent off on a secret mission. Mushu starts to meddle, and a surprise attack by Mongolians doesn't help either.

title: Brick Mansions
text: An undercover Detroit cop navigates a dangerous neighborhood that's surrounded by a containment wall with the help of an ex-con in order to bring down a crime lord and his plot to devastate the entire city.

title: Locke
text: Ivan Locke, a dedicated family man and successful construction manager, receives a phone call on the eve of the biggest challenge of his career that sets in motion a series of events that threaten his carefully cultivated existence.

title: Neighbors
text: After they are forced to live next to a fraternity house, a couple with a newborn baby do whatever they can to take them down.

title: Alpha and Omega 3: The Great Wolf Games
text: After receiving word about The Great Games, Stinky, Claudette, and Runt decide to form a team to compete as well. However, Kate is out of town, so Humphrey becomes their coach. Will the Western team succeed, or fail?

title: Mom's Night Out
text: Hardworking mom Allyson has a crazy night out with her friends, while their husbands watch their children.

title: Lucy
text: A woman, accidentally caught in a dark deal, turns the tables on her captors and transforms into a merciless warrior evolved beyond human logic.

title: X-Men: Days of Future Past
text: The X-Men send Wolverine to the past in a desperate effort to change history and prevent an event that results in doom for both humans and mutants.

title: Godzilla
text: The world is beset by the appearance of monstrous creatures, but one of them may be the only one who can save humanity.

title: Walk of Shame
text: A reporter's dream of becoming a news anchor is compromised after a one-night stand leaves her stranded in downtown L.A. without a phone, car, ID or money - and only 8 hours to make it to the most important job interview of her life.

title: Blue Ruin
text: A mysterious outsider's quiet life is turned upside down when he returns to his childhood home to carry out an act of vengeance. Proving himself an amateur assassin, he winds up in a brutal fight to protect his estranged family.

title: Chef
text: A head chef quits his restaurant job and buys a food truck in an effort to reclaim his creative promise, while piecing back together his estranged family.

title: Afflicted
text: Two best friends see their trip of a lifetime take a dark turn when one of them is struck by a mysterious affliction. Now, in a foreign land, they race to uncover the source before it consumes him completely.

title: Blended
text: After a bad blind date, a man and woman find themselves stuck together at a resort for families, where their attraction grows as their respective kids benefit from the burgeoning relationship.

title: Begin Again
text: A chance encounter between a down-and-out music-business executive and a young singer-songwriter, new to Manhattan, turns into a promising collaboration between the two talents.

title: Maleficent
text: A vengeful fairy is driven to curse an infant princess, only to discover that the child may be the one person who can restore peace to their troubled land.

title: Zombeavers
text: A fun weekend turns into madness and horror for a bunch of groupies looking for fun in a beaver infested swamp.

title: At Middleton
text: Two parents fall in love over the course of a single day while playing hooky from their children's college tour.

title: Dance of Reality, The
text: In a Chilean little town, the son of an uprooted couple, formed by a rigorous communist father and a loving but weak mother, tries to pave his own path in a society that does not understand their Jewish-Ukrainian origins.

title: A Million Ways to Die in the West
text: As a cowardly farmer begins to fall for the mysterious new woman in town, he must put his newly found courage to the test when her husband, a notorious gun-slinger, announces his arrival.

title: Edge of Tomorrow
text: A soldier fighting aliens gets to relive the same day over and over again, the day restarting every time he dies.

title: Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation
text: Ethan and his team take on their most impossible mission yet when they have to eradicate an international rogue organization as highly skilled as they are and committed to destroying the IMF.

title: Midnight Chronicles
text: In the world of MIDNIGHT, it is a time of overwhelming darkness. After three ages of scheming and war, the dark god Izrador has finally defeated the heroes and armies of the free races. Now, he rules the world of Aryth with an iron fist. Enslaved under the Shadow, the race of men leads an oppressed existence, and the elves and dwarves have retreated to distant forests and mountains, where their desperate resistance is slowly succumbing to the unyielding might of the Shadow. Investigating the disappearance of a legate priest, the infamous Mag Kiln has been ordered by the church to travel to the small Erenlander town of Blackweir. There, he soon becomes entangled in an old mystery and begins to uncover not only the forbidden legacy of the town, but the malevolent, prophetic force that grows within him. MIDNIGHT CHRONICLES is the epic narrative that tells the tale of two legendary characters -- one for the cause of good, the other for the cause of evil. This is the story of their rise, their struggle, and ultimately their fate, as their destinies become intertwined with that of the world and the dark god that occupies it.

title: Million Dollar Arm
text: A sports agent stages an unconventional recruitment strategy to get talented Indian cricket players to play Major League Baseball.

title: G.B.F.
text: What happens after Tanner is outed by his classmates and becomes the title "gay best friend" for three high school queen bees?

title: Jimi: All Is by My Side
text: A drama based on Jimi Hendrix's life as he left New York City for London, where his career took off.

title: Bad Asses
text: Frank Vega teams up with grumpy old agoraphobic Bernie Pope to kick ass and clean up the streets of L.A.

title: Lilting
text: A young man of Chinese-Cambodian descent dies, leaving behind his isolated mother and his 4-year male lover, who grieve but don't speak a lick of each other's language.

title: The Fault in Our Stars
text: Two teenage cancer patients begin a life-affirming journey to visit a reclusive author in Amsterdam.

title: Tangled Ever After
text: Rapunzel and Flynn Rider have their wedding, but Pascal and Maximus must recover the rings they lose in mid-ceremony.

title: Maps to the Stars
text: A tour into the heart of a Hollywood family chasing celebrity, one another and the relentless ghosts of their pasts.

title: 22 Jump Street
text: After making their way through high school , big changes are in store for officers Schmidt and Jenko when they go deep undercover at a local college.

title: Equalizer, The
text: A man who believes he has put his mysterious past behind him cannot stand idly by when he meets a young girl under the control of ultra-violent Russian gangsters.

title: How to Train Your Dragon 2
text: When Hiccup and Toothless discover an ice cave that is home to hundreds of new wild dragons and the mysterious Dragon Rider, the two friends find themselves at the center of a battle to protect the peace.

title: Birdman: Or
text: A washed-up superhero actor attempts to revive his fading career by writing, directing, and starring in a Broadway production.

title: Boyhood
text: The life of Mason, from early childhood to his arrival at college.

title: Think Like a Man Too
text: All the couples are back for a wedding in Las Vegas, but plans for a romantic weekend go awry when their various misadventures get them into some compromising situations that threaten to derail the big event.

title: Jersey Boys
text: The story of four young men from the wrong side of the tracks in New Jersey who came together to form the iconic 1960s rock group The Four Seasons.

title: Nick Fury: Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.
text: Agent Nick Fury is asked to fight the menace of Hydra after exiling himself in the Yukon since the end of the Cold War.

title: Internet's Own Boy: The Story of Aaron Swartz, The
text: The story of programming prodigy and information activist Aaron Swartz, who took his own life at the age of 26.

title: Transformers: Age of Extinction
text: When humanity allies with a bounty hunter in pursuit of Optimus Prime, the Autobots turn to a mechanic and his family for help.

title: Frank
text: Jon, a young wanna-be musician, discovers he's bitten off more than he can chew when he joins an eccentric pop band led by the mysterious and enigmatic Frank.

title: They Came Together
text: Molly owns a quaint little sweet shop. Joel works for a gigantic candy company threatening to shut her down. How they meet, fall in love, break up and get back together is hilariously recounted in this rom-com spoof.

title: Honey
text: Irene, nicknamed 'Honey', has devoted herself to people looking for help, and tries to alleviate their suffering, even when they make extreme decisions. One day she has to cope with Grimaldi and his invisible malaise.

title: Planes: Fire & Rescue
text: When Dusty learns that his engine is damaged and he may never race again, he joins a forest fire and rescue unit to be trained as a firefighter, or else his air strip will be shut down.

title: Tammy
text: After getting fired and finding out her husband is cheating, Tammy hits the road with her profane, alcoholic grandmother.

title: Colourful
text: A sinful spirit is granted the opportunity to prove worthy for rebirth, inhabiting the body of a student who killed himself.

title: Babadook, The
text: A single mother and her child fall into a deep well of paranoia when an eerie children's book titled "Mister Babadook" manifests in their home.

title: Whiplash
text: A promising young drummer enrolls at a cut-throat music conservatory where his dreams of greatness are mentored by an instructor who will stop at nothing to realize a student's potential.

title: Gone Girl
text: With his wife's disappearance having become the focus of an intense media circus, a man sees the spotlight turned on him when it's suspected that he may not be innocent.

title: Angriest Man in Brooklyn, The
text: A perpetually angry man is informed he has 90 minutes to live and promptly sets out to reconcile with his family and friends in the short time he has left.

title: Dawn of the Planet of the Apes
text: A growing nation of genetically evolved apes led by Caesar is threatened by a band of human survivors of the devastating virus unleashed a decade earlier.

title: Deliver Us from Evil
text: New York police officer Ralph Sarchie investigates a series of crimes. He joins forces with an unconventional priest, schooled in the rites of exorcism, to combat the possessions that are terrorizing their city.

title: And So It Goes
text: A self-absorbed realtor enlists the help of his neighbor when he's suddenly left in charge of the granddaughter he never knew existed until his estranged son drops her off at his home.

title: Sex Tape
text: A married couple wake up to discover that the sex tape they made the evening before has gone missing, leading to a frantic search for its whereabouts.

title: I Origins
text: A molecular biologist and his laboratory partner uncover evidence that may fundamentally change society as we know it.

title: Purge: Anarchy, The
text: Three groups of people intertwine and are left stranded in the streets on Purge Night, trying to survive the chaos and violence that occurs.

title: Guardians of the Galaxy
text: A group of intergalactic criminals must pull together to stop a fanatical warrior with plans to purge the universe.

title: Signal, The
text: On a road trip, Nic and two friends are drawn to an isolated area by a computer genius. When everything suddenly goes dark, Nic regains consciousness - only to find himself in a waking nightmare.

title: The Expendables 3
text: Barney augments his team with new blood for a personal battle: to take down Conrad Stonebanks, the Expendables co-founder and notorious arms trader who is hell bent on wiping out Barney and every single one of his associates.

title: Hercules
text: Having endured his legendary twelve labors, Hercules, the Greek demigod, has his life as a sword-for-hire tested when the King of Thrace and his daughter seek his aid in defeating a tyrannical warlord.

title: A Most Wanted Man
text: A Chechen Muslim illegally immigrates to Hamburg, where he gets caught in the international war on terror.

title: Life After Beth
text: A young man's recently deceased girlfriend mysteriously returns from the dead, but he slowly realizes she is not the way he remembered her.

title: Felony
text: An accident involving a young child sets off a chain of events that brings an Australian police officer's world crashing down.

title: Get on Up
text: A chronicle of James Brown's rise from extreme poverty to become one of the most influential musicians in history.

title: Magic in the Moonlight
text: A romantic comedy about an Englishman brought in to help unmask a possible swindle. Personal and professional complications ensue.

title: Housebound
text: A young woman is forced to return to her childhood home after being placed under house arrest, where she suspects that something evil may be lurking.

title: The Hundred-Foot Journey
text: The Kadam family leaves India for France where they open a restaurant directly across the road from Madame Mallory's Michelin-starred eatery.

title: Batman: Assault on Arkham
text: Batman works desperately to find a bomb planted by the Joker while Amanda Waller hires her newly formed Suicide Squad to break into Arkham Asylum to recover vital information stolen by the Riddler.

title: White Frog
text: Twilight's Booboo Stewart plays a neglected teen trying to make it through each day after tragedy strikes.

title: Den, The
text: While studying the habits of web cam chat users from the apparent safety of her own home, a young woman's life begins to spiral out of control after witnessing a grisly murder online.

title: Jupiter Ascending
text: A young woman discovers her destiny as an heiress of intergalactic nobility and must fight to protect the inhabitants of Earth from an ancient and destructive industry.

title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
text: When a kingpin threatens New York City, a group of mutated turtle warriors must emerge from the shadows to protect their home.

title: I'll Follow You Down
text: After the disappearance of a young scientist on a business trip, his son and wife struggle to cope, only to make a bizarre discovery years later - one that may bring him home.

title: Old Lady and the Pigeons, The
text: In seductive central Paris, an undernourished gendarme willing to go to great lengths to feed himself hatches a desperate, yet utterly cunning plan.

title: Giver, The
text: In a seemingly perfect community, without war, pain, suffering, differences or choice, a young boy is chosen to learn from an elderly man about the true pain and pleasure of the "real" world.

title: Pretty One, The
text: A tragedy presents Laurel with the chance to reinvent herself as her idolized twin sister, Audrey. As she eases into the life she has always wanted, she must decide between continuing the lie or revealing herself as the perfect fraud.

title: Revenge of the Green Dragons
text: Two best friends rise through the ranks of New York's Chinese underworld in the 1980s.

title: Let's Be Cops
text: Two struggling pals dress as police officers for a costume party and become neighborhood sensations. But when these newly-minted "heroes" get tangled in a real life web of mobsters and dirty detectives, they must put their fake badges on the line.

title: Inbetweeners 2, The
text: Jay, Neil, Simon, and Will reunite in Australia for a holiday.

title: Sacrament, The
text: A news team trails a man as he travels into the world of Eden Parish to find his missing sister, where it becomes apparent that this paradise may not be as it seems.

title: Sin City: A Dame to Kill For
text: Some of Sin City's most hard-boiled citizens cross paths with a few of its more reviled inhabitants.

title: If I Stay
text: Life changes in an instant for young Mia Hall after a car accident puts her in a coma. During an out-of-body experience, she must decide whether to wake up and live a life far different than she had imagined. The choice is hers if she can go on.

title: Two Days, One Night
text: Liège, Belgium. Sandra is a factory worker who discovers that her workmates have opted for a EUR1,000 bonus in exchange for her dismissal. She has only a weekend to convince her colleagues to give up their bonuses in order to keep her job.

title: Coherence
text: Strange things begin to happen when a group of friends gather for a dinner party on an evening when a comet is passing overhead.

title: As Above, So Below
text: When a team of explorers ventures into the catacombs that lie beneath the streets of Paris, they uncover the dark secret that lies within this city of the dead.

title: One I Love, The
text: A troubled couple vacate to a beautiful getaway, but bizarre circumstances further complicate their situation.

title: Headshot
text: A cop who becomes a hitman for a group aimed at eliminating those who are above the law finds his world turned upside down by a single a devastating blow.

title: Guest, The
text: A soldier introduces himself to the Peterson family, claiming to be a friend of their son who died in action. After the young man is welcomed into their home, a series of accidental deaths seem to be connected to his presence.

title: Pride
text: U.K. gay activists work to help miners during their lengthy strike of the National Union of Mineworkers in the summer of 1984.

title: Honeymoon
text: A newlywed couple finds their lake-country honeymoon descend into chaos after Paul finds Bea wandering and disoriented in the middle of the night.

title: The Drop
text: Bob Saginowski finds himself at the center of a robbery gone awry and entwined in an investigation that digs deep into the neighborhood's past where friends, families, and foes all work together to make a living - no matter the cost.

title: 20,000 Days on Earth
text: Writer and musician Nick Cave marks his 20,000th day on the planet Earth.

title: The Skeleton Twins
text: Having both coincidentally cheated death on the same day, estranged twins reunite with the possibility of mending their relationship.

title: Beautiful Losers
text: This documentary follows the lives and careers of a collective group of Do-it-yourself artists and designers who inadvertently affected the art world.

title: Maze Runner, The
text: Thomas is deposited in a community of boys after his memory is erased, soon learning they're all trapped in a maze that will require him to join forces with fellow "runners" for a shot at escape.

title: Camp X-Ray
text: A soldier assigned to Guantanamo Bay befriends a man who has been imprisoned there.

title: Walk Among the Tombstones, A
text: Private investigator Matthew Scudder is hired by a drug kingpin to find out who kidnapped and murdered his wife.

title: Laggies
text: In the throes of a quarter-life crisis, Megan panics when her boyfriend proposes, then, taking an opportunity to escape for a week, hides out in the home of her new friend, 16-year-old Annika, who lives with her world-weary single dad.

title: La cravate
text: A short mime adaptation of a Thomas Mann story about a Parisian urchin who makes her living selling human heads.

title: Cesar Chavez
text: A biography of the civil-rights activist and labor organizer Cesar Chavez.

title: Who Am I
text: Benjamin, a young German computer whiz, is invited to join a subversive hacker group that wants to be noticed on the world's stage.

title: Tale of Princess Kaguya, The
text: Found inside a shining stalk of bamboo by an old bamboo cutter and his wife, a tiny girl grows rapidly into an exquisite young lady. The mysterious young princess enthralls all who encounter her, but ultimately she must confront her fate, the punishment for her crime.

title: This Is Where I Leave You
text: After their father passes away, four grown siblings are forced to return to their childhood home and live under the same roof for a week, along with their over-sharing mother and an assortment of spouses, exes and might-have-beens.

title: Angel's Egg
text: A mysterious young girl wanders a desolate, otherworldly landscape, carrying a large egg.

title: American Sniper
text: Navy S.E.A.L. sniper Chris Kyle's pinpoint accuracy saves countless lives on the battlefield and turns him into a legend. Back home with his family after four tours of duty, however, Chris finds that it is the war he can't leave behind.

title: Tusk
text: A brash and arrogant podcaster gets more than he bargained for when he travels to Canada to interview a mysterious recluse... who has a rather disturbing fondness for walruses.

title: Hector and the Search for Happiness
text: A psychiatrist searches the globe to find the secret of happiness.

title: Horns
text: In the aftermath of his girlfriend's mysterious death, a young man awakens to find strange horns sprouting from his forehead.

title: Annabelle
text: A couple begins to experience terrifying supernatural occurrences involving a vintage doll shortly after their home is invaded by satanic cultists.

title: Two Night Stand
text: A snowstorm forces two people who made an online connection to unwillingly extend their one-night stand as the blizzard goes through the night.

title: Dracula Untold
text: As his kingdom is being threatened by the Turks, young prince Vlad Tepes must become a monster feared by his own people in order to obtain the power needed to protect his own family, and the families of his kingdom.

title: Stretch
text: A hard-luck limo driver struggles to go straight and pay off a debt to his bookie. He takes on a job with a crazed passenger, whose sought-after ledger implicates some seriously dangerous criminals.

title: Autómata
text: Human race is at edge of the end. Robot race is at edge of the beginning.

title: Captive, The
text: Eight years after the disappearance of Cassandra, some disturbing incidents seem to indicate that she's still alive. Police, parents and Cassandra herself, will try to unravel the mystery of her disappearance.

title: Predestination
text: For his final assignment, a top temporal agent must pursue the one criminal that has eluded him throughout time. The chase turns into a unique, surprising and mind-bending exploration of love, fate, identity and time travel taboos.

title: Justin and the Knights of Valour
text: A young boy grows up as he embarks on a quest to become a knight.

title: Ward 13
text: Ben, our main character, wakes up in an unusual hospital after seemingly landing on an asphalt road due to a car collision. He later wakes up to the sound of dog barking and decides to explore the hospital. After he studies the hospital, noticing all the details from the plain white hallways from the surgical tools spread about the rooms, he realizes this isn't a normal hospital. He then hears footsteps and goes into the nearest room where he finds an experimental patient. The patient, lying on a bed moaning, comes to life in a horrific manner and leaves our main character, Ben, running for his life through the hospital while being chased by surgeons along the way. Ben realizes that the only chance of survival is leaving the Hospital with haste. Run Ben, Run.

title: What We Do in the Shadows
text: Viago, Deacon and Vladislav are vampires who are finding that modern life has them struggling with the mundane - like paying rent, keeping up with the chore wheel, trying to get into nightclubs and overcoming flatmate conflicts.

title: John Wick
text: An ex-hit-man comes out of retirement to track down the gangsters that killed his dog and took everything from him.

title: Plastic
text: Sam and Fordy run a credit card fraud scheme, but when they steal from the wrong man, they find themselves threatened by a sadistic gangster. They need to raise £2m and pull off a daring diamond heist to clear their debt.

title: Judge, The
text: Big-city lawyer Hank Palmer returns to his childhood home where his father, the town's judge, is suspected of murder. Hank sets out to discover the truth and, along the way, reconnects with his estranged family.

title: Culture High, The
text: Scours the deep-seated roots of this morally induced Marijuana campaign and reveal the fascinating path it has taken to get to where it is today.

title: Fury
text: A grizzled tank commander makes tough decisions as he and his crew fight their way across Germany in April, 1945.

title: Salvation, The
text: In 1870s America, the fury of a notorious gang leader is unleashed when a peaceful American settler avenges the death of his family. Then as his cowardly fellow townspeople betray him, he is forced to hunt down the outlaws alone.

title: St. Vincent
text: A young boy whose parents have just divorced finds an unlikely friend and mentor in the misanthropic, bawdy, hedonistic war veteran who lives next door.

title: Rewrite, The
text: An Oscar-winning writer in a slump leaves Hollywood to teach screenwriting at a college on the East Coast, where he falls for a single mom taking classes there.

title: Nightcrawler
text: When Louis Bloom, a con man desperate for work, muscles into the world of L.A. crime journalism, he blurs the line between observer and participant to become the star of his own story.

title: Big Hero 6
text: A special bond develops between plus-sized inflatable robot Baymax and prodigy Hiro Hamada, who together team up with a group of friends to form a band of high-tech heroes.

title: The Book of Life
text: Manolo, a young man who is torn between fulfilling the expectations of his family and following his heart, embarks on an adventure that spans three fantastic worlds where he must face his greatest fears.

title: Love, Rosie
text: Rosie and Alex have been best friends since they were 5, so they couldn't possibly be right for one another...or could they? When it comes to love, life and making the right choices, these two are their own worst enemies.

title: Time Lapse
text: Three friends discover a mysterious machine that takes pictures twenty-four hours into the future, and conspire to use it for personal gain, until disturbing and dangerous images begin to develop.

title: Ex Machina
text: A young programmer is selected to participate in a ground-breaking experiment in synthetic intelligence by evaluating the human qualities of a highly advanced humanoid A.I.

title: Crippled Avengers
text: Three men, crippled by an evil warlord, become friends and learn kung fu with the help of an old teacher and his idiot pupil.

title: Mr Hublot
text: Mr Hublot is a withdrawn, idiosyncratic character with OCD, scared of change and the outside world. Robot Pet's arrival turns his life upside down: he has to share his home with this very invasive companion.

title: Copenhagen
text: When the girl of your dreams is half your age, it's time to grow up.

title: Simpsons: The Longest Daycare, The
text: Maggie Simpson spends the day in the Ayn Rand School for Tots.

title: Generation War
text: Five friends go out to war and promise each other to be back for Christmas.

title: Christmas in Connecticut
text: Elizabeth, the star of a successful cooking show, is set to do a live show on Christmas, where she'll cook a Christmas dinner. But what no one knows is that she can't cook.

title: Leviathan
text: In a Russian coastal town, Kolya is forced to fight the corrupt mayor when he is told that his house will be demolished. He recruits a lawyer friend to help, but the man's arrival brings further misfortune for Kolya and his family.

title: Reign of Assassins
text: Drizzle/Zeng Jing tries to start a new life after she had betrayed her gang and hid the remains of monk.

title: Zulu
text: Policemen Ali Sokhela and Brian Epkeen investigate the brutal murder of a young white woman, apparently provoked by the availability of a new illegal drug and somehow connected to the disappearance of black street children.

title: Tangerines
text: In 1992, war rages in Abkhazia, a breakaway region of Georgia. An Estonian man Ivo has decided to stay behind and harvest his crops of tangerines. In a bloody conflict at his door, a wounded man is left behind, and Ivo takes him in.

title: Life Partners
text: Sasha and Paige's co-dependent friendship is tested as Paige gets serious with a guy for the first time.

title: Drive Hard
text: A former race car driver is abducted by a mysterious thief and forced to be the wheel-man for a crime that puts them both in the sights of the cops and the mob.

title: New Kids Nitro
text: Gerrie, Richard, Rikkert, Robbie and Barry from Maaskantje are in a big fight with the village of Schijndel. When a zombie kills someone from Brabant, things get out of hand.

title: Stalingrad
text: A group of Russian soldiers fight to hold a strategic building in their devastated city against a ruthless German army, and in the process become deeply connected to two Russian women who have been living there.

title: Dead Snow 2: Red vs. Dead
text: Still on the run from a group of Nazi zombies, a man seeks the aid of a group of American zombie enthusiasts, and discovers new techniques for fighting the zombies.

title: Volga - Volga
text: Widely claimed to be Joseph Stalin's favorite movie, this classic musical comedy is a must-see. The action takes place on a steamboat on the iconic Volga River, as two groups of performers travel to Moscow to perform in the Moscow Musical Olympiad.

title: You Are the Apple of My Eye
text: A group of close friends who attend a private school all have a debilitating crush on the sunny star pupil, Shen Jiayi. The only member of the group who claims not to is Ke Jingteng, but he ends up loving her as well.

title: DeadHeads
text: Two inexplicably coherent zombies awake amidst a zombie attack, and decide to take a road trip to find the one's lost love, unaware they are being chased by the agents of a ruthless company with its own agenda.

title: The Imitation Game
text: During World War II, the English mathematical genius Alan Turing tries to crack the German Enigma code with help from fellow mathematicians while attempting to come to terms with his troubled private life.

title: Inherent Vice
text: In 1970, drug-fueled Los Angeles private investigator Larry "Doc" Sportello investigates the disappearance of a former girlfriend.

title: Rudderless
text: A grieving father in a downward spiral stumbles across a box of his recently deceased son's demo tapes and lyrics. Shocked by the discovery of this unknown talent, he forms a band in the hope of finding some catharsis.

title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay - Part 1
text: Katniss Everdeen is in District 13 after she shatters the games forever. Under the leadership of President Coin and the advice of her trusted friends, Katniss spreads her wings as she fights to save Peeta and a nation moved by her courage.

title: Sex Ed
text: Eddie lands his first teaching gig at an inner city middle school and finds his highly pubescent pupils are receiving no form of sexual education. Eddie isn't really equipped to teach them...he's not exactly experienced romantically.

title: Exodus: Gods and Kings
text: The defiant leader Moses rises up against Egyptian Pharaoh Ramses II, setting six hundred thousand slaves on a monumental journey of escape from Egypt and its terrifying cycle of deadly plagues.

title: Wild Tales
text: Six short stories that explore the extremities of human behavior involving people in distress.

title: Jetsons: The Movie
text: George Jetson is forced to uproot his family when Mr. Spacely promotes him to take charge of a new factory on a distant planet.

title: Ski School
text: Rival groups in a skiing school do battle on and off the piste. One gang are rich and serious, the other group are party animals.

title: Dumb and Dumber To
text: 20 years since their first adventure, Lloyd and Harry go on a road trip to find Harry's newly discovered daughter, who was given up for adoption.

title: The Longest Week
text: Conrad  is helped by his old friend Dylan  and returns the favor by falling for Dylan's girlfriend Beatrice .

title: Miss Meadows
text: A story centered on a proper elementary school teacher who moonlights as a vigilante.

title: Too Many Cooks
text: A series of montages that parodies the introductory title sequences of generic 70s, 80s and 90s TV shows of various genres slowly turns into an absurdist meta slasher and then the parody becomes even weirder.

title: Painted Skin
text: An action-thriller centered on a vampire-like woman who eats the skins and hearts of her lovers.

title: The Theory of Everything
text: A look at the relationship between the famous physicist Stephen Hawking and his wife.

title: Doctor Who: The Time of the Doctor
Virunga
text: A team of brave individuals risk their lives to protect the last mountain gorillas.

title: The Madagascar Penguins in a Christmas Caper
text: The penguins of the Central Park Zoo have an adventure in the city on Christmas Eve.

title: Song of the Sea
text: Ben, a young Irish boy, and his little sister Saoirse, a girl who can turn into a seal, go on an adventure to free the fairies and save the spirit world.

title: In the Heart of the Sea
text: A recounting of a New England whaling ship's sinking by a giant whale in 1820, an experience that later inspired the great novel Moby-Dick.

title: Jurassic World
text: A new theme park, built on the original site of Jurassic Park, creates a genetically modified hybrid dinosaur, the Indominus Rex, which escapes containment and goes on a killing spree.

title: Watermark
text: A documentary on how water shapes humanity.

title: Citizenfour
text: A documentarian and a reporter travel to Hong Kong for the first of many meetings with Edward Snowden.

title: Asterix: The Land of the Gods
text: In order to wipe out the Gaulish village by any means necessary, Caesar plans to absorb the villagers into Roman culture by having an estate built next to the village to start a new Roman colony.

title: Hit by Lightning
text: Disappointed that all his friends are married and happy, Ricky goes on the dating site and soon starts dating Danita, who seems to be way out of his league. However, everything comes at a price, he soon realizes.

title: Horrible Bosses 2
text: Dale, Kurt and Nick decide to start their own business but things don't go as planned because of a slick investor, prompting the trio to pull off a harebrained and misguided kidnapping scheme.

title: Double Trouble
text: Muscle-bound twins try to smash a jewel smuggling ring.

title: Dragonheart 2: A New Beginning
text: An orphaned stable boy befriends with a young dragon named Drake and with the help of others help him learn how to fly and fight and protect himself from a ruthless knight.

title: La Belle Verte
text: On a distant planet, rural vegans master telepathy and mental power to travel interstellar etc. Mila is sent to Earth to report back. She lands in Paris - quite a cultural shock. Earthlings are strange.

title: Penguins of Madagascar
text: Skipper, Kowalski, Rico and Private join forces with undercover organization The North Wind to stop the villainous Dr. Octavius Brine from destroying the world as we know it.
In 1971, a young and disoriented British soldier is accidentally abandoned by his unit following a riot on the deadly streets of Belfast.

title: The Rabbi's Cat
text: Set in Algeria in the 1920s, a rabbi's cat who learns how to speak after swallowing the family parrot expresses his desire to convert to Judaism.

title: Still Alice
text: A linguistics professor and her family find their bonds tested when she is diagnosed with Alzheimer's Disease.

title: Paddington
text: A young Peruvian bear travels to London in search of a home. Finding himself lost and alone at Paddington Station, he meets the kindly Brown family, who offer him a temporary haven.

title: Maze Runner: Scorch Trials
text: After having escaped the Maze, the Gladers now face a new set of challenges on the open roads of a desolate landscape filled with unimaginable obstacles.

title: Ice Age: A Mammoth Christmas
text: Sid, Eddie and Crash get in trouble with Santa and have to get their names off of the naughty list.

title: The Voices
text: A likable guy pursues his office crush with the help of his evil talking pets, but things turn sinister when she stands him up for a date.

title: Courier
text: The story of a teenager boy in times of the comunism fall in the Soviet Union.

title: The Green Prince
text: The son of a founding leader in the Palestinian organization, Hamas, becomes a spy for the Israelis.

title: Dying of the Light
text: When a devastating illness threatens to end Evan Lake's career in the C.I.A., he goes rogue to hunt down a terrorist who tortured him during a mission gone awry years ago.

title: Hellbenders
text: The Augustine Interfaith Order of Hellbound Saints, a team of blasphemous ministers who live in a constant state of debauchery, work to drag the worst of demons back to Hell.

title: Omega Doom
text: After Earth is taken over by an army of robots, the small number of humans left are forced into hiding. In the nuclear winter, only droids walk the face of the Earth, in fear of the rumored human resurgence, and in search of a hidden cache of weapons. One robot, his evil circuits destroyed, enters a small town where a robot civil war is taking place. He tries to convince both sides to join forces in search of the weapons, all the while having a hidden agenda, and an affinity for one of the local droids.

title: By the Gun
text: Nick, a young Boston Italian, trying to find purpose in the ideology of the mafia and finding his world turned upside down.

title: Kill the Messenger
text: Journalist Gary Webb, California 1996, started investigating CIA's role in the 1980s in getting crack cocaine to the black part of LA to get money and weapons to the Contras/freedom fighters in Nicaragua.

title: Bring It On: In It To Win It
text: At Camp Spirit Thunder, high school cheer leaders compete. The red team/Sharks' cutie, Carson, and blue team/Jets' hunk, Penn, are in love. Does that make them archenemies like the Sharks and Jets?

title: Fans
text: Four different stories about italian football team's supporter.

title: The Mule
text: After a trip to Thailand, a first-time drug mule finds himself in police custody, with his stomach crammed with narcotics. Now, he has to endure seven sphincter-clenching days to convince them of his innocence. Will nature take its course?

title: The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies
text: Bilbo and company are forced to engage in a war against an array of combatants and keep the Lonely Mountain from falling into the hands of a rising darkness.

title: Selma
text: A chronicle of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.'s campaign to secure equal voting rights via an epic march from Selma to Montgomery, Alabama, in 1965.

title: Unbroken
text: After a near-fatal plane crash in WWII, Olympian Louis Zamperini spends a harrowing 47 days in a raft with two fellow crewmen before he's caught by the Japanese navy and sent to a prisoner-of-war camp.

title: Black Sea
text: In order to make good with his former employers, a submarine captain takes a job with a shadowy backer to search the depths of the Black Sea for a submarine rumored to be loaded with gold.

title: Playing It Cool
text: Unrequited love motivates a guy to write about his experiences.

title: National Lampoon's Bag Boy
text: A teenager enters the competitive world of grocery store bagging.

title: Closer to the Moon
text: A Romanian police officer teams up with a small crew of old friends from the World War II Jewish Resistance to pull off a heist by convincing everyone at the scene of the crime that they are only filming a movie.

title: Girl Walks Home Alone at Night, A
text: In the Iranian ghost-town Bad City, a place that reeks of death and loneliness, the townspeople are unaware they are being stalked by a lonesome vampire.

title: Dave Chappelle: For What it's Worth
text: Chappelle cuts loose in what he does best, Chappelle-style! And for what it's worth, no one is safe from Dave!

title: Scooby-Doo! Abracadabra-Doo
text: The gang goes on a trip to check on Velma's younger sister, Madelyn. She's been studying stage magic at the Whirlen Merlin Magic Academy, where apparently there have been sightings of a giant griffin. The gang decides to investigate.

title: Mommy
text: A widowed single mother, raising her violent son alone, finds new hope when a mysterious neighbor inserts herself into their household.

title: Wild
text: A chronicle of one woman's one thousand one hundred mile solo hike undertaken as a way to recover from a recent personal tragedy.

title: Top Five
text: A comedian tries to make it as a serious actor when his reality television star fiancée talks him into broadcasting their wedding on her television show.

title: Bill Burr: I'm Sorry You Feel That Way
text: Comedian Bill Burr's 2014 stand-up comedy special.

title: Big Eyes
text: A drama about the awakening of painter Margaret Keane, her phenomenal success in the 1950s, and the subsequent legal difficulties she had with her husband, who claimed credit for her works in the 1960s.

title: Into the Woods
text: A witch tasks a childless baker and his wife with procuring magical items from classic fairy tales to reverse the curse put on their family tree.

title: Men, Women & Children
text: A group of high school teenagers and their parents attempt to navigate the many ways the Internet has changed their relationships, their communications, their self-images, and their love lives.

title: The Interview
text: Dave Skylark and his producer Aaron Rapaport run the celebrity tabloid show "Skylark Tonight". When they land an interview with a surprise fan, North Korean dictator Jong-Un Kim, they are recruited by the CIA to assassinate him.

title: Kingsman: The Secret Service
text: A spy organisation recruits a promising street kid into the agency's training program, while a global threat emerges from a twisted tech genius.

title: Bill Burr: You People Are All the Same
text: Funnyman Bill Burr takes the stage to uncork a profanity-laced, incisive routine that pokes fun at plastic surgery, reality TV, gold diggers and more.

title: Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb
text: Larry spans the globe, uniting favorite and new characters while embarking on an epic quest to save the magic before it is gone forever.

title: Paradox
text: Homicide detective Sean Nault, a cop on a parallel Earth whose technology is powered exclusively by magic. Sean investigates a baffling series of murders committed by a means he's never seen before: science. With the aid of Lenoir, a member of the ridiculed subculture of "pragmatists" who believe science is more than the stuff of myths & children's stories, and the 130-year-old sorcerer Winston Churchill, Sean uncovers an ominous plot that will lead him to another dimension and the realization that, unless he prevents it, both earths could well be destroyed.

title: The Punisher: Dirty Laundry
text: Frank Castle is staying in a bad neighborhood, where he encounters a gang that terrorizes its residents.

title: Seventh Son
text: When Mother Malkin, the queen of evil witches, escapes the pit she was imprisoned in by professional monster hunter Spook decades ago and kills his apprentice, he recruits young Tom, the seventh son of the seventh son, to help him.

title: Corner Gas: The Movie
text: As the town of Dog River goes bankrupt the residents of the town must pack up and move out. However our favourite citizens make one last-ditch effort to save Dog River.

title: A Man Called Blade
text: A bounty hunter is hired by a mining town's crippled mayor to find his daughter, who has been kidnapped by the mayor's corrupt right-hand-man and his outlaw gang.

title: A Merry Friggin' Christmas
text: Boyd Mitchler and his family must spend Christmas with his estranged family of misfits. Upon realizing that he left all his son's gifts at home, he hits the road with his dad in an attempt to make the 8-hour round trip before sunrise.

title: Into the Forest of Fireflies' Light
text: Hotaru is rescued by a spirit when she gets lost in a forest as a child. The two become friends, despite the spirit revealing that he will disappear if he is ever touched by a human.

title: PK
text: An alien on Earth loses the only device he can use to communicate with his spaceship. His innocent nature and child-like questions force the country to evaluate the impact of religion on its people.

title: Chappie
text: In the near future, crime is patrolled by a mechanized police force. When one police droid, Chappie, is stolen and given new programming, he becomes the first robot with the ability to think and feel for himself.

title: The Salt of the Earth
text: The life and work of photographer Sebastião Salgado, who has spent forty years documenting societies in hidden corners of the world.

title: The Fool
text: Dima Nikitin is an ordinary honest plumber who suddenly decides to face the corrupt system of local politics in order to save the lives of 800 inhabitants of an old dormitory, which is about to collapse.

title: Taken 3
text: Accused of a ruthless murder he never committed or witnessed, Bryan Mills goes on the run and brings out his particular set of skills to find the true killer and clear his name.

title: Blackhat
text: A furloughed convict and his American and Chinese partners hunt a high-level cybercrime network from Chicago to Los Angeles to Hong Kong to Jakarta.

title: By the Law
text: A five-person team of gold prospectors in the Yukon has just begun to enjoy great success when one of the members snaps, and suddenly kills two of the others. The two survivors, a husband and wife, subdue the killer but are then faced with an agonizing dilemma. With no chance of turning him over to the authorities for many weeks, they must decide whether to exact justice themselves or to risk trying to keep him restrained until they can return to civilization.

title: Son of a Gun
text: JR busts out of prison with Brendan Lynch, Australia's most notorious criminal, and joins Lynch's gang for a gold heist that soon pits the two men against one another.

title: Terminator Genisys
text: When John Connor, leader of the human resistance, sends Sgt. Kyle Reese back to 1984 to protect Sarah Connor and safeguard the future, an unexpected turn of events creates a fractured timeline.

title: John Mulaney: New In Town
text: Comedian John Mulaney talks about his milk toast boyish looks, his childhood, his Jewish girlfriend, his gayish charm, his favorite TV shows, Ice-T, a homeless person he met in N.Y., and a prostate exam with Batman.

title: Patton Oswalt: My Weakness Is Strong
text: The critically-acclaimed comedian, actor, writer, and voice of Remy the Rat  takes time out from his many film and television outings to return to the comedy stage for his fourth stand-up special.

title: The Hound of the Baskervilles
text: When the latest heir to the Baskerville estate seems to be threatened by a family curse, only the master detective, Sherlock Holmes, can find out the truth.

title: Man on High Heels
text: From people's eyes he seems like a sadistic cop who give no mercy to his enemy. But, deep inside his heart Ji-wook hides his desire to become a woman.

title: Space Buddies
text: Disney's pups are back and take one small step for dog and one giant leap for dogkind.

title: Houdini
text: Follow the man behind the magic as he finds fame, engages in espionage, battles spiritualists and encounters the greatest names of the era, from U.S. presidents to Sir Arthur Conan Doyle and Grigori Rasputin.

title: To Grandmother's House We Go
text: When twins Sarah and Julie feel like their mom is tired of them, they take off on an exciting adventure to their great-grandmother's house and encounter a pair of villains along the way.

title: 101 Dalmatians II: Patch's London Adventure
text: Being one of 101 takes its toll on Patch, who doesn't feel unique. When he's accidentally left behind on moving day, he meets his idol, Thunderbolt, who enlists him on a publicity campaign.

title: The Hungover Games
text: A spoof on The Hangover , The Hunger Games  and other movies, TV series etc. 4 men, with hangovers after a bachelor party, find themselves in a future, dystopian, kill or be killed game.

title: The Duke of Burgundy
text: A woman who studies butterflies and moths tests the limits of her relationship with her lesbian lover.

title: Red Army
text: The story of the Soviet Union's famed Red Army hockey team through the eyes of its players.

title: It Follows
text: A young woman is followed by an unknown supernatural force after a sexual encounter.

title: The Town that Dreaded Sundown
text: 65 years after a masked serial killer terrorized the small town of Texarkana, the so-called "moonlight murders" begin again. Is it a copycat or something even more sinister? A lonely high school girl may be the key to catching him.

title: Carry on Cabby
text: Speedee Taxis is a great success, which means its workaholic owner Charlie starts neglecting Peggy, his wife. Suddenly a fleet of rival taxis appears from nowhere and start pinching all the fares. The rivals are Glamcabs, and they have a secret weapon. All their drivers are very attractive women! Who's behind Glamcabs? It's open warfare and only one fleet can survive!

title: Carry on Cruising
text: Captain Crowther's lot is not a happy one! Five of his crew have to be replaced and at such short notice before the voyage begins there isn't much to choose from. Not only does he get the five most incompetent shipmates ever to sail the seven seas, but the passengers turn out to be a rather strange bunch too. The SS Happy Wanderer will never be the same.

title: Bill Burr: Let It Go
text: Stand-up comedian Bill Burr's 2010 comedy special.

title: Bill Burr: Why Do I Do This?
text: In his first stand-up special, Comedian Bill Burr takes aim at the stuff that drives us crazy, political correctness gone haywire, and girlfriends; or as he calls them, "relentless psycho robots."

title: Killer Movie
text: A reality TV director copes with a spoiled celebutante and a show gone haywire when a masked killer starts bumping off the crew in this slasher-movie satire.

title: Sebastian Maniscalco: What's Wrong with People?
text: "What's Wrong with People?" asks Sebastian Maniscalco, as he hilariously tries to bridge the Italian-American Old World he grew up in with the contemporary frenetic world we all live in today.

title: Stuart Little 3: Call of the Wild
text: The Little family spend their vacation near Lake Garland. Meanwhile, in the forest, a beast is threatening the animals to give her food every night.

title: Guy X
text: A black comedy set in 1979, about a soldier mistakenly posted to an Arctic military base.

title: Tooth Fairy 2
text: When dreamer Larry Guthrie  loses his first love to the town hot shot, he decides to win her back by volunteering to help the local children at her after school program. But when Larry accidentally tells the kids that the tooth fairy is make believe, he is soon transformed into a tutu clad fairy with a sentence of collecting teeth.

title: The Diary of Anne Frank
text: During World War II, a teenage Jewish girl named Anne Frank and her family are forced into hiding in the Nazi-occupied Netherlands.

title: The Deadly Bees
text: Trouble strikes when an exhausted pop singer, sent on a vacation to a farm, realizes that the farm's owner grows deadly bees.

title: Wicked Blood
text: Hannah and Amber Baker are trapped in a dark Southern underworld of violence, drugs and bikers. Both live in fear of their "Uncle Frank" Stinson, the ruthless leader of a crime organization.

title: Oblivion 2: Backlash
text: On another planet, in the futuristic wild west town called Oblivion, the pacifist sheriff Stone, dandy alien bounty hunter Sweeney, and the lizard-like alien Jaggar are all after Lash, the sexy villainies from the previous movie.

title: Mad Max: Fury Road
text: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, a woman rebels against a tyrannical ruler in search for her homeland with the aid of a group of female prisoners, a psychotic worshiper, and a drifter named Max.

title: Insidious: Chapter 3
text: A prequel set before the haunting of the Lambert family that reveals how gifted psychic Elise Rainier reluctantly agrees to use her ability to contact the dead in order to help a teenage girl who has been targeted by a dangerous supernatural entity.

title: Star Wars: Episode VII - The Force Awakens
text: As a new threat to the galaxy rises, Rey, a desert scavenger, and Finn, an ex-stormtrooper, must join Han Solo and Chewbacca to search for the one hope of restoring peace.

title: Ben-hur
text: Judah Ben-Hur, a prince falsely accused of treason by his adopted brother, an officer in the Roman army, returns to his homeland after years at sea to seek revenge, but finds redemption.

title: Warcraft
text: As an Orc horde invades the planet Azeroth using a magic portal, a few human heroes and dissenting Orcs must attempt to stop the true evil behind this war.

title: Avengers: Age of Ultron
text: When Tony Stark and Bruce Banner try to jump-start a dormant peacekeeping program called Ultron, things go horribly wrong and it's up to Earth's mightiest heroes to stop the villainous Ultron from enacting his terrible plan.

title: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
text: Captain Jack Sparrow is pursued by old rival Captain Salazar and a crew of deadly ghosts who have escaped from the Devil's Triangle. They're determined to kill every pirate at sea...notably Jack.

title: Justice League
text: Fueled by his restored faith in humanity and inspired by Superman's selfless act, Bruce Wayne enlists the help of his new-found ally, Diana Prince, to face an even greater enemy.

title: Ant-Man
text: Armed with a super-suit with the astonishing ability to shrink in scale but increase in strength, cat burglar Scott Lang must embrace his inner hero and help his mentor, Dr. Hank Pym, pull off a plan that will save the world.

title: Fantastic Four
text: Four young outsiders teleport to an alternate and dangerous universe which alters their physical form in shocking ways. The four must learn to harness their new abilities and work together to save Earth from a former friend turned enemy.

title: Deadpool
text: A wisecracking mercenary gets experimented on and becomes immortal but ugly, and sets out to track down the man who ruined his looks.

title: Black Panther
text: T'Challa, heir to the hidden but advanced kingdom of Wakanda, must step forward to lead his people into a new future and must confront a challenger from his country's past.

title: Avengers: Infinity War - Part I
text: The Avengers and their allies must be willing to sacrifice all in an attempt to defeat the powerful Thanos before his blitz of devastation and ruin puts an end to the universe.

title: Thor: Ragnarok
text: Imprisoned on the planet Sakaar, Thor must race against time to return to Asgard and stop Ragnarök, the destruction of his world, at the hands of the powerful and ruthless villain Hela.

title: Guardians of the Galaxy 2
text: The Guardians struggle to keep together as a team while dealing with their personal family issues, notably Star-Lord's encounter with his father the ambitious celestial being Ego.

title: Captain America: Civil War
text: Political involvement in the Avengers' affairs causes a rift between Captain America and Iron Man.

title: Doctor Strange
text: While on a journey of physical and spiritual healing, a brilliant neurosurgeon is drawn into the world of the mystic arts.

title: X-Men: Apocalypse
text: In the 1980s the X-Men must defeat an ancient all-powerful mutant, En Sabah Nur, who intends to thrive through bringing destruction to the world.

title: Untitled Spider-Man Reboot
text: Peter Parker balances his life as an ordinary high school student in Queens with his superhero alter-ego Spider-Man, and finds himself on the trail of a new menace prowling the skies of New York City.

title: Elsa & Fred
text: A withdrawn senior experiences life in new ways when he begins spending time with the free-spirited woman who lives across the hall.

title: Jim Jefferies: I Swear to God
text: Politically incorrect Australian comedian Jim Jefferies performs.

title: Tornado!
text: An accountant sent to produce an evaluation of a tornado research project, and the scientist running the project pursue tornadoes and each other.

title: The Blue Lagoon
text: In the Victorian period, two children are shipwrecked on a tropical island in the South Pacific and fall in love while growing up together.

title: In the Name of the King III
text: A modern day assassin, wanting out, is hired for one final job: to kidnap the kids of a local businessman. Things go haywire when it turns out he's chosen to return to the Middle Ages and bring back order to a kingdom in chaos.

title: Cake
text: The acerbic, hilarious Claire Bennett becomes fascinated by the suicide of a woman in her chronic pain support group. As she uncovers the details of Nina's suicide and develops a poignant relationship with Nina's husband, she also grapples with her own, very raw personal tragedy.

title: Kevin Smith: Too Fat For 40
text: A no holds barred concert with award winning filmmaker and raconteur Kevin Smith. In this special celebrating his milestone 40th birthday, Kevin answers questions from his fans, revealing stories and hilarious truths. In HD.

title: Snowflake, the White Gorilla
text: In order to fit in with the rest of the gorillas, Snowflake embarks on an exciting adventure to find a magical potion to make her a "normal gorilla".

title: Kenny & Company
text: A coming-of-age story about the lives of a teenage boy and his friend as they traverse the highs and lows of boyhood in the run-up to Halloween.

title: Delirium
text: Set in a world where love is deemed illegal and can be eradicated with a special procedure. With 95 days to go until her scheduled treatment, Lena Holoway does the unthinkable: she falls in love.

title: Why Man Creates
text: Through several amusing live action and animated vignettes, Saul Bass illustrates a fundamental and essential particularity of human nature that keeps us alive and the world turning, evolving and reaching new designs and possibilities: the necessity of creation. And by creation, Bass means everything from art to mundane things, from words and numbers to unusual abstract works.

title: The Gambler
text: Literature professor and gambler Jim Bennett's debt causes him to borrow money from his mother and a loan shark. Further complicating his situation, is his relationship with one of his students. Will Bennett risk his life for a second chance?

title: The Beast of Hollow Mountain
text: An American cowboy living in Mexico discovers his cattle are being eaten by a giant prehistoric dinosaur.

title: Mortdecai
text: Juggling angry Russians, the British Mi5, and an international terrorist, debonair art dealer and part-time rogue Charlie Mortdecai races to recover a stolen painting rumored to contain a code that leads to lost gold.

title: Fifty Shades of Grey
text: Literature student Anastasia Steele's life changes forever when she meets handsome, yet tormented, billionaire Christian Grey.

title: Halloweentown
text: When a young girl living with her good-witch grandmother learns she too is a witch, she must help her grandmother save Halloweentown from evil forces.

title: Halloweentown High
text: A girl in a magical world bets her family's magic that nothing bad will happen when kids from Halloweentown attend high school in the mortal realm.

title: A Flintstones Christmas Carol
text: Fred is cast as Ebenezer Scrooge in a stage adaption of the story, but is acting a bit stingy in real-life.

title: Hedgehog in the Fog
text: A little hedgehog, on the way to visit his friend the bear, gets lost in thick fog, where horses, dogs and even falling leaves take on a terrifying new aspect.

title: The Cave of the Golden Rose
American Heist
text: James owes his life to his older brother, Frankie after taking the rap for a crime they committed together. While Frankie served time, James worked to turn his life around, got a steady job and began courting his former girlfriend Emily. Now, Frankie is released and back on the streets with no money and no place to go.

title: Solyaris
text: Kris Kelvin joins the space station orbiting the planet Solaris, only to find its two crew members plagued by "phantoms," creations of Solaris. Kelvin is soon confronted with his own phantom, taking the shape of his dead wife Hari.

title: The Pacific
text: The Pacific Theatre of World War II, as seen through the eyes of several young Marines.

title: Strange Magic
text: Goblins, elves, fairies and imps, and their misadventures sparked by the battle over a powerful potion.

title: The DUFF
text: A high school senior instigates a social pecking order revolution after finding out that she has been labeled the DUFF - Designated Ugly Fat Friend - by her prettier, more popular counterparts.

title: Daddy, I'm A Zombie
text: The misadventures of a teenager girl in her new life as zombie.

title: The Fox and the Hound 2
text: Tod and Copper still go together like an itch and a scratch, but when Copper gets a shot at the big time with a nutty group of hound dog howlers, their purebred friendship is put to the test.

title: Operation 'Y' & Other Shurik's Adventures
text: Three stories about Shurik - a young student. He fights against criminals, falls in love, confuses apartments, passes exams - he lives after all.

title: Project Almanac
text: A group of teens discover secret plans of a time machine, and construct one. However, things start to get out of control.

title: Louis C.K.: Live at The Comedy Store
text: Comedian Louis C.K. performs live at the Comedy store in LA.

title: Brooklyn
text: An Irish immigrant lands in 1950s Brooklyn, where she quickly falls into a romance with a local. When her past catches up with her, however, she must choose between two countries and the lives that exist within.

title: The End of the Tour
text: The story of the five-day interview between Rolling Stone reporter David Lipsky and acclaimed novelist David Foster Wallace, which took place right after the 1996 publication of Wallace's groundbreaking epic novel, 'Infinite Jest.'

title: Experimenter
text: In 1961, famed social psychologist Stanley Milgram conducted a series of radical behavior experiments that tested ordinary humans' willingness to obey authority.

title: Mistress America
text: A lonely college freshman's life is turned upside-down by her impetuous, adventurous stepsister-to-be.

title: Zipper
text: A successful family man with a blossoming political career loses all sense of morality when he becomes addicted to using an escort agency.

title: A Walk in the Woods
text: After spending two decades in England, Bill Bryson  returns to the U.S., where he decides the best way to connect with his homeland is to hike the Appalachian Trail with one of his oldest friends, Stephen Katz .

title: True Story
text: When disgraced New York Times reporter Michael Finkel meets accused killer Christian Longo - who has taken on Finkel's identity - his investigation morphs into a game of cat-and-mouse.

title: Kurt Cobain: Montage of Heck
text: An authorized documentary on the late musician Kurt Cobain, from his early days in Aberdeen, Washington to his success and downfall with the grunge band Nirvana.

title: Going Clear: Scientology and the Prison of Belief
text: A documentary looking at the inner-workings of the Church of Scientology.

title: What Happened, Miss Simone?
text: A documentary about the life and legend Nina Simone, an American singer, pianist, and civil rights activist labeled the "High Priestess of Soul."

title: A Story of Children and Film
text: A Story of Children and Film is the world's first movie about kids in global cinema. It's passionate, poetic, portrait of the adventure of childhood: its surrealism, loneliness, fun, destructiveness and stroppiness: as seen through 53 great films from 25 countries. A story of children and film is an eye opener, a landmark film and a celebration of both childhood and the movies.

title: Story of Film: An Odyssey, The
text: A comprehensive history of the medium and art of motion pictures.

title: Eden
text: Paul, a teenager in the underground scene of early-nineties Paris, forms a DJ collective with his friends and together they plunge into the nightlife of sex, drugs, and endless music.

title: Dope
text: Life changes for Malcolm, a geek who's surviving life in a tough neighborhood, after a chance invitation to an underground party leads him and his friends into a Los Angeles adventure.

title: Me and Earl and the Dying Girl
text: High schooler Greg, who spends most of his time making parodies of classic movies with his co-worker Earl, finds his outlook forever altered after befriending a classmate who has just been diagnosed with cancer.

title: The Overnight
text: Alex, Emily, and their son, RJ, are new to Los Angeles. A chance meeting at the park introduces them to the mysterious Kurt, Charlotte, and Max. A family "playdate" becomes increasingly interesting as the night goes on.

title: The Stanford Prison Experiment
text: In 1971, twenty-four male students are selected to take on randomly assigned roles of prisoners and guards in a mock prison situated in the basement of the Stanford psychology building.

title: A Pigeon Sat on a Branch Reflecting on Existence
text: Sam and Jonathan, a pair of hapless novelty salesmen, embark on a tour of the human condition in reality and fantasy that unfold in a series of absurdist episodes.

title: The Loft
text: Five married guys secretly share a penthouse loft in the city where they can carry out hidden affairs. But the fantasy becomes a nightmare, when they discover the dead body of a woman in the loft one of the group must be involved.

title: Vice
text: Bruce Willis stars in this Sci-Fi thriller about ultimate resort: VICE, where customers can play out their wildest fantasies with artificial inhabitants who look like humans.

title: Trinity and Sartana Are Coming
text: Trinity and Sartana

title: Kevin Hart: I'm a Grown Little Man
text: With his wisecracking one-of-a-kind style of comedy, Kevin Hart pokes fun at everyone - even his audience.

title: Jim Norton: American Degenerate
text: For his second EPIX comedy special, Jim Norton takes self-deprecation and outrageous humor to new extremes. Norton attacks a wide range of topics with the knowledge that some of his remarks will no doubt inspire complaints. In HD.

title: Jim Jefferies: BARE
text: Covers topics from gun control to family values.

title: Hard Promises
text: With only seventy-two hours to keep his future from being a bleak one, Brian pulls out all the stops to win back his ex-wife before she remarries.

title: The Hateful Eight
text: In the dead of a Wyoming winter, a bounty hunter and his prisoner find shelter in a cabin currently inhabited by a collection of nefarious characters.

title: Patton Oswalt: Tragedy Plus Comedy Equals Time
text: Recorded in Spreckels Theater in San Diego, California, comedian Patton Oswalt returns for his 5th feature-length stand-up comedy special.

title: Wild Card
text: When a Las Vegas bodyguard with lethal skills and a gambling problem gets in trouble with the mob, he has one last play...and it's all or nothing.

title: Paper Towns
text: After an all-night adventure, Quentin's lifelong crush, Margo, disappears, leaving behind clues that Quentin and his friends follow on the journey of a lifetime.

title: The Wedding Ringer
text: Two weeks shy of his wedding, a socially awkward guy enters into a charade by hiring the owner of a company that provides best men for grooms in need.

title: Wyrmwood
text: A talented mechanic prepares to battle his way through hordes of flesh-eating monsters after his sister is kidnapped on the eve of a zombie apocalypse.

title: The Boy Next Door
text: A woman, separated from her unfaithful husband, falls for a younger man who has moved in next door, but their torrid affair soon takes a dangerous turn.

title: Boy Meets Girl
text: Boy Meets Girl is a funny, tender, sex positive romantic comedy that explores what it means to be a real man or woman, and how important it is to live a courageous life not letting fear stand in the way of going after your dreams.

title: Victoria
text: A young Spanish woman who has recently moved to Berlin finds her flirtation with a local guy turn potentially deadly as their night out with his friends reveals a dangerous secret.

title: The Dark Valley
text: Through a hidden path a lone rider reaches a little town high up in the Alps. Nobody knows where the stranger comes from, nor what he wants there. But everyone knows that they don't want him to stay.

title: I'm Here
text: A young man faces the abrupt loss of his friend.

title: The Last Five Years
text: A struggling actress and her novelist lover each illustrate the struggle and deconstruction of their love affair.

title: Crimson Peak
text: In the aftermath of a family tragedy, an aspiring author is torn between love for her childhood friend and the temptation of a mysterious outsider. Trying to escape the ghosts of her past, she is swept away to a house that breathes, bleeds - and remembers.

title: Dragonheart 3: The Sorcerer's Curse
text: A young knight and a dragon named Drago, whose lives they now share with one heart, join forces to protect a nest filled with dragon eggs from an evil sorcerer, as well undo a curse placed on Drago.

title: Chris Rock: Bigger & Blacker
text: Chris Rock's third HBO comedy special shows him performing his stand-up routine at Apollo Theater in Harlem.

title: The Natural Love
text: A documentary on Brazil's relationship with the poetry of Carlos Drummond de Andrade, and to their own sexuality.

title: The Forgotten Space
text: Details the catastrophic effects globalization has wrought on the ship, truck and train industries. We visit displaced farmers and villagers in Holland and Belgium, underpaid truck drivers in Los Angeles, seafarers aboard mega-ships shuttling between Asia and Europe, and factory workers in China, whose low wages are the fragile key to the whole puzzle. At a moment when collective bargaining rights are under attack in the United States, and China continues to bow to foreign pressures to prevent such rights from being granted at all, this film asks: Is capitalism the Trojan horse that turns on its inventors?

title: Cloudburst
text: A lesbian couple escape from their nursing home and head up to Canada to get married. Along the way, they pick up a young, male hitchhiker.

title: Tom Segura: Completely Normal
text: Levelheaded stand-up Tom Segura shares offhand appraisals on hotels and opens up about his hobbies and digestive ailments in this comedy special.

title: Honey, We Shrunk Ourselves
text: Wayne Szalinzki, a wacky, absent-minded inventor, is back again but only this time he decides to use his infamous shrink machine just one more time. His wife Diane asks him to get rid of the "Tiki Man" a large tiki sculpture. Wayne refuses to get rid of it so he decides to restart the shrink ray and reduces the Tiki Man to pocket-size. However, after Wayne shrinks the Tiki Man the machine is accidentally activated and Wayne ends up shrinking himself and his brother Gordon. Meanwhile, when Gordon's wife Patty and Diane were going on a vacation they went back to the house when Patty suddenly realizes she forgot Mitch's medicine for his potassium deficiency. When they were about to leave, they decide to sneak into the attic and surprise the men, but the shrink ray is activated once again, and the ladies are shrunk as well. So the team must be very brave of disgusting household insects the size of dinosaurs and more in their biggest adventure to get their children's attention.

title: Stitch! The Movie
text: Stitch, an alien living on Earth disguised as a dog with his human family, continues his adventures when he discovers that the alien family he never knew he had is now in Hawaii, being hunted down by galactic forces.

title: Hot Tub Time Machine 2
text: When Lou's shot in the groin, Nick and Jacob drag him in the Hot Tub Time Machine to go back in time and save Lou. The three end up 10 years in the future, where they need to go to find the shooter.

title: Johnny Express
text: In the year 2150, Johnny, a lazy Space Delivery Man, must deliver a package on a planet he does not fully understand.

title: Eddie Izzard: Glorious
text: Eddie Izzard's routine has a loose trajectory from the beginning of the Old Testament and the creation of the world in seven days to Revelations; God, in the voice of James Mason, makes several appearances. Along the way, Izzard dramatizes or comments on the search for a career, bad giraffes, Prince Philip's gaffes, toilets in French campsites, the mysteries of hopscotch, becoming one's Dad, getting a computer to print, and his court victory after being the victim of tranny bashing. Izzard calls his bits "mimes," in part because his physical comedy is sans props. Filmed at Labatt's Apollo Theatre, Izzard is in a shimmering red pants suit and low heels.

title: Northmen - A Viking Saga
text: A band of Vikings cross enemy lines and a panicked race begins. The losers will pay with their lives.

title: Superfast!
text: A spoof on The Fast and the Furious  and the following F&F movies. An undercover cop joins a gang of criminal street racers to get close to the LA crime kingpin.

title: Reality
text: A wanna-be director is given 48 hours by a producer to find the best groan of pain, worthy of an Oscar, as the only condition to back his film.

title: Julia
text: A neo-noir revenge thriller centering on Julia Shames, who after suffering a brutal trauma, falls prey to an unorthodox form of therapy to restore herself.

title: Focus
text: In the midst of veteran con man Nicky's latest scheme, a woman from his past - now an accomplished femme fatale - shows up and throws his plans for a loop.

title: Marvel One-Shot: Item 47
text: SHIELD agent Sitwell is assigned to recover an abandoned Chitauri weapon being used by a young couple robbing a bank.

title: The Second Best Exotic Marigold Hotel
text: As the Best Exotic Marigold Hotel has only a single remaining vacancy, posing a rooming predicament for two fresh arrivals, Sonny Kapoor  pursues his expansionist dream of opening a second hotel.

title: George Carlin: It's Bad for Ya!
text: It's Bad For Ya, Carlin's Emmy-nominated 14th and final HBO special from March of 2008 features Carlin's noted irreverent and unapologetic observations on topics ranging from death, religion, bureaucracy, patriotism, overprotected children and big business to the pungent examinations of modern language and the decrepit state of the American culture. Carlin once again comes up with an hour of brand new material that not only makes you laugh, but makes you think. George Carlin will always remain part of the popular lexicon for his 'Seven Dirty Words' routine, and as a comedian who was never afraid to challenge his audience.

title: Tracers
text: Wanted by the Chinese mafia, a New York City bike messenger escapes into the world of parkour after meeting a beautiful stranger.

title: McFarland, USA
text: Jim White moves his family after losing his last job as a football coach, and at his new school he turns seven disappointing students into one of the best cross-country teams in the region.

title: Unfinished Business
text: A hard-working small business owner and his two associates travel to Europe to close the most important deal of their lives. But what began as a routine business trip goes off the rails in every way imaginable, and unimaginable.

title: Ghost in the Shell Arise - Border 1: Ghost Pain
text: In this prequel set one year after the fourth World War, cyborg and hacker extraordinaire Motoko Kusanagi from the military's 501st Secret Unit finds herself wrapped up in the investigation of a devastating bombing.

title: Run All Night
text: Mobster and hit man Jimmy Conlon has one night to figure out where his loyalties lie: with his estranged son, Mike, whose life is in danger, or his longtime best friend, mob boss Shawn Maguire, who wants Mike to pay for the death of his own son.

title: Digging Up the Marrow
text: A documentary exploring genre based monster art takes an odd turn when the filmmakers are contacted by a man who claims he can prove that monsters are indeed real.

title: Clown
text: A loving father finds a clown suit for his son's birthday party, only to realize that it's cursed.

title: Cinderella
text: When her father unexpectedly dies, young Ella finds herself at the mercy of her cruel stepmother and her scheming stepsisters. Never one to give up hope, Ella's fortunes begin to change after meeting a dashing stranger.

title: Kidnapping Mr. Heineken
text: The inside story of the planning, execution, rousing aftermath, and ultimate downfall of the kidnappers of beer tycoon Alfred "Freddy" Heineken in 1983, which resulted in the largest ransom ever paid for an individual.

title: The Cobbler
text: A cobbler, bored of his everyday life, stumbles upon a magical heirloom that allows him to become other people and see the world in a different way.

title: Ruby Red
text: On her 16th birthday, Gwendolyn Shepherd finds out that instead of her cousin, she has inherited a rare gene that allows her to travel through time.

title: Pan
text: Twelve-year-old orphan Peter is spirited away to the magical world of Neverland, where he finds both fun and danger, and ultimately discovers his destiny -- to become the hero who will be for ever known as Peter Pan.

title: While We're Young
text: A middle-aged couple's career and marriage are overturned when a disarming young couple enters their lives.

title: Too Late for Tears
text: Through a fluke circumstance, a ruthless woman stumbles across a suitcase filled with $60,000, and is determined to hold onto it even if it means murder.

title: Insurgent
text: Beatrice Prior must confront her inner demons and continue her fight against a powerful alliance which threatens to tear her society apart with the help from others on her side.

title: La vérité si je mens !
text: The sentimental and comedic adventures of Eddie, a non-Jew trying to pass as Jewish though totally ignorant of Jewish traditions, as he works in a Jewish community.

title: The Amazing Screw-On Head
text: A Civil War-era secret agent with an extraordinary special power serves under president Abraham Lincoln protecting America from supernatural foes. Unsold animated TV pilot adapted from a short comic book from the creator of Hellboy.

title: Home
text: An alien on the run from his own people makes friends with a girl. He tries to help her on her quest, but can be an interference.

title: Midnight Special
