text: A young man's political awakening and coming of age during the days and weeks leading up to the Stonewall Riots.

title: Frankenstein
text: A married couple of scientists create a modern-day monster.

title: Welcome to Happiness
text: There's a magical door in Woody's closet that allows those who go through it to erase mistakes from their past. When he finds out where it goes, his life will be changed forever.

title: Risen
text: In 33 AD, a Roman Tribune in Judea is tasked to find the missing body of Jesus Christ, who rose from the dead.

title: The Survivalist
text: In a time of starvation, a survivalist lives off a small plot of land hidden deep in forest. When two women seeking food and shelter discover his farm, he finds his existence threatened.

title: Dirty Grandpa
text: Right before his wedding, an uptight guy is tricked into driving his grandfather, a lecherous former Army Lieutenant Colonel, to Florida for Spring Break.

title: Reptilicus
text: After copper miners discover part of the frozen tail of a prehistoric monster in Lapland, scientists inadvertently bring it back to life.

title: Requiem for the American Dream
text: Renowned academic and author Noam Chomsky elucidates 10 principles of concentration of wealth and power that have led to unprecedented inequality and the hollowing out of the American middle class.

title: Death Note Rewrite: Genshisuru Kami
text: See the world of Death Note through Ryuk's point of view.

title: Three from Prostokvashino
text: Little Fedor brings a cat to home despite his mother's distaste for cats. He runs away with his talking cat, to make more friends on the way.

title: The Finest Hours
text: The Coast Guard makes a daring rescue attempt off the coast of Cape Cod after a pair of oil tankers are destroyed during a blizzard in 1952.

title: Ghost in the Shell: Solid State Society
text: A.D. 2034. It has been two years since Motoko Kusanagi left Section 9. Togusa is now the new leader of the team, that has considerably increased its appointed personnel. The expanded new Section 9 confronts a rash of complicated incidents, and investigations reveal that an ultra-wizard hacker nicknamed the "Puppet Master" is behind the entire series of events.

title: Grease Live
text: After enjoying a summer romance, high school students Danny and Sandy are unexpectedly reunited when she transfers to Rydell High. There Sandy must contend with cynical Rizzo and the Pink Ladies in attempt to win Danny's heart again.

title: Gods of Egypt
text: Mortal hero Bek teams with the god Horus in an alliance against Set, the merciless god of darkness, who has usurped Egypt's throne, plunging the once peaceful and prosperous empire into chaos and conflict.

title: Embrace of the Serpent
text: The story of the relationship between Karamakate, an Amazonian shaman and last survivor of his people, and two scientists who work together over the course of forty years to search the Amazon for a sacred healing plant.

title: Race
text: Jesse Owens' quest to become the greatest track and field athlete in history thrusts him onto the world stage of the 1936 Olympics, where he faces off against Adolf Hitler's vision of Aryan supremacy.

title: 10 Cloverfield Lane
text: A young woman is held in an underground bunker by a man who insists that a hostile event has left the surface of the Earth uninhabitable.

title: London Has Fallen
text: In London for the Prime Minister's funeral, Mike Banning is caught up in a plot to assassinate all the attending world leaders.

title: Zootopia
text: In a city of anthropomorphic animals, a rookie bunny cop and a cynical con artist fox must work together to uncover a conspiracy.

title: Whiskey Tango Foxtrot
text: A journalist recounts her wartime coverage in Afghanistan.

title: Desierto
text: A group of people trying to cross the border from Mexico into the United States encounter a racist man who has taken border patrol duties into his own hands.

title: The Brothers Grimsby
text: A new assignment forces a top spy to team up with his football hooligan brother.

title: Dad's Army
text: The misadventures of a ragtag group of elderly Home Guard local defense volunteers at the onset of WW2.

title: Michael Jackson's Thriller
text: A night at the movies turns into a nightmare when Michael and his date are attacked by a hoard of bloodthirsty zombies - only a "Thriller" can save them now.

title: The Wait
text: A mother unexpectedly meets her son's fiancée at a villa in Sicily and gets to know her as she waits for her son to arrive.

title: War and Peace
text: As the Russian conflict with Napoleon reaches its peak, five aristocratic families face the possibility of their lives being changed forever.

title: Southbound
text: Five interlocking tales of terror follow the fates of a group of weary travellers who confront their worst nightmares - and darkest secrets - over one long night on a desolate stretch of desert highway.

title: Ip Man 3
text: When a band of brutal gangsters led by a crooked property developer make a play to take over a local school, Master Ip is forced to take a stand.

title: Santa's Little Helper
text: After getting fired from his job, a slick, fast-talking businessman  is thrown into an elf competition to become Santa¹s next second-in-command. Put through a series of rigorous training exercises to prepare for the contest, The Miz and another aspiring elf go head-to-head in the hopes of becoming Santa¹s Little Helper.

title: Who Killed Chea Vichea?
text: After the assassination of a Cambodian union leader, filmmaker Bradley Cox tracks down witnesses and unravels the police plot that framed two men.

title: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
text: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

title: Rabbits
text: In a nameless city deluged by continuous rain, three rabbits live with a fearful mystery.

title: Genius Party
text: Several directors take part in an anthology dedicated to short anime films.

title: Long Live Ghosts!
text: Trespassing gang of boys encounter a ghost in the ruins of a castle. When they rescue the ghost who is caught in a trapset, they become allies in a fight to prevent ruins from being turned into mushroom farm by the city authorities.

title: Tears for Sale
text: Story of two sisters that grew up in a small Serbian village in the beginning of the 1930s. The village is torn up by wars and years long blood oath. There are no men left in the village. Our heroines, Ognjenka and Mala Boginja decide to go to the city, kidnap men and return life to their village. The lights of the metropolis dazzle them and there starts this little amusing and sentimental adventure.

title: Dad's Army
text: The Walmington-on-Sea Home Guard platoon deal with a visiting female journalist and a German spy as World War II draws to its conclusion.

title: The Barkley Marathons: The Race That Eats Its Young
text: A famous prison escape sparks the idea for a cult-like race that has seen only 10 finishers in its first 25 years. This award-winning, oddly inspiring, and wildly funny documentary reveals the sports world's most guarded secret.

title: Merci Patron !
text: A family fired by a company owned by LVMH  seeks reparation from their previous employer with the help of the movie director.

title: The Neon Demon
text: An aspiring model, Jesse, is new to Los Angeles. However, her beauty and youth, which generate intense fascination and jealousy within the fashion industry, may prove themselves sinister.

title: Fraktus
text: An inept music manager documents his attempt of bringing about a comeback of the 80s techno pioneers Fraktus, who in the past 30 years have disconnected both from each other and their music.

title: Eye in the Sky
text: Col. Katherine Powell, a military officer in command of an operation to capture terrorists in Kenya, sees her mission escalate when a girl enters the kill zone triggering an international dispute over the implications of modern warfare.

title: Camino
text: In the jungles of Colombia, a photojournalist captures the truth behind a group of missionaries who may not be what they seem.

title: Mr. Right
text: A girl falls for the "perfect" guy, who happens to have a very fatal flaw: he's a hitman on the run from the crime cartels who employ him.

title: Noin 7 veljestä
text: Medieval knight spoof about Sir Wilhelm who wants to court beautiful Helena, the daughter of evil von Wurstburg living in his large castle. People around the village also include Robin Hood, the hero of the local peasants, inventor Leonardo, and a troubadour explaining the plot to the viewer.

title: Florence Foster Jenkins
text: The story of Florence Foster Jenkins, a New York heiress who dreamed of becoming an opera singer, despite having a terrible singing voice.

title: My Big Fat Greek Wedding 2
text: A Portokalos family secret brings the beloved characters back together for an even bigger and Greeker wedding.

title: Neon Bull
text: Iremar works at the rodeo in North East of Brazil. From his home, the truck used to transport the animals, he dreams of a future in the region's booming clothing industry.

title: Get a Job
text: After college, Will is having problems getting a good, lasting job, as are his roomies, his girlfriend, and his just-fired dad.

title: Keanu
text: When the adorable kitten of an L.A. crime kingpin unexpectedly enters the life of two cousins, they will have to go through tough gangs, pitiless hit-men, and ruthless drug dealers who all claim him, to get him back. How hard can it be?

title: Me Him Her
text: Vicenarian drifter Cory arrives in Los Angeles to help his semi-famous T.V. star friend Brendan take his first steps out of the closet.

title: Ice Age: The Great Egg-Scapade
text: When Sid takes a job as an egg nanny, he's unaware an old enemy has plans of his own. The shenanigans lead to the first egg hunt and creation of popular Easter traditions.

title: Everybody Wants Some
text: In 1980, a group of college baseball players navigate their way through the freedoms and responsibilities of unsupervised adulthood.

title: Sing Street
text: A boy growing up in Dublin during the 1980s escapes his strained family life by starting a band to impress the mysterious girl he likes.

title: Zoom
text: A multi-dimensional interface between a comic book artist, a novelist, and a film director. Each lives in a separate reality but authors a story about one of the others.

title: Paterson
text: A quiet observation of the triumphs and defeats of daily life, along with the poetry evident in its smallest details.

title: The Huntsman Winter's War
text: Eric and fellow warrior Sara, raised as members of ice Queen Freya's army, try to conceal their forbidden love as they fight to survive the wicked intentions of both Freya and her sister Ravenna.

title: Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising
text: When their new next-door neighbors turn out to be a sorority even more debaucherous than the fraternity previously living there, Mac and Kelly team with their former enemy, Teddy, to bring the girls down.

title: Project X
text: A spy is brought back from cryogenic suspension after being almost killed in a plane crash returning from a mission to learn about a deadly new weapon being developed in the East. But the vital memories are being suppressed, so the authorities use ultra-advanced technologies to try to uncover the secret.

title: The Trust
text: A pair of cops investigating a drug invasion stumble upon a mysterious bank vault.

title: Hush
text: A deaf and mute writer who retreated into the woods to live a solitary life must fight for her life in silence when a masked killer appears at her window.

title: Jimmy Carr: Telling Jokes
text: Jimmy Carr delivers more of his cynical take on life's little absurdities in his trademark deadpan style in this live stand-up release.

title: Jimmy Carr: Making People Laugh
text: Jimmy Carr: Making People Laugh features over two hours of material that's too rude for TV.

title: Texas - Doc Snyder hält die Welt in Atem
text: A parody of a western filmed in the country of Karl May, a German writer famous for his adventure books which feature the Apache Winnetou.

title: 00 Schneider - Jagd auf Nihil Baxter
text: Detective 00 Schneider has to return from retirement to catch a mad art collector.

title: The Man Who Knew Infinity
text: The story of the life and academic career of the pioneer Indian mathematician, Srinivasa Ramanujan, and his friendship with his mentor, Professor G.H. Hardy.

title: Despite the Falling Snow
text: In Cold War Moscow, a female spy steals secrets from an idealistic politician - and falls in love with him.

title: Wizards of the Lost Kingdom II
text: Three kingdoms have been overtaken by three evil lords and only a teenage boy with magical powers can restore peace to the land.

title: Money Monster
text: Financial TV host Lee Gates and his producer Patty are put in an extreme situation when an irate investor takes them and their crew as hostage.

title: Barbershop: The Next Cut
text: As their surrounding community has taken a turn for the worse, the crew at Calvin's Barbershop come together to bring some much needed change to their neighborhood.

title: Finding Dory
text: Friendly but forgetful blue tang Dory begins a search for her long-lost parents, and everyone learns a few things about the real meaning of family along the way.

title: The Boss
text: A titan of industry is sent to prison after she's caught insider trading. When she emerges ready to rebrand herself as America's latest sweetheart, not everyone she screwed over is so quick to forgive and forget.

title: The Angry Birds Movie
text: When an island populated by happy, flightless birds is visited by mysterious green piggies, it's up to three unlikely outcasts - Red, Chuck and Bomb - to figure out what the pigs are up to.

title: Bakuman
text: Moritaka Mashiro, a junior high student, forgets his notebook in class. His classmate Akito Takagi, notes Mashiro's drawings in it and asks him to become a manga artist to his stories. Mashiro declines. Takagi incites Mashiro to meet with Miho Azuki, Mashiro's crush, and tells her the two plan to become mangakas . In response, Azuki reveals her plans to be a seiyuu . Mashiro proposes to her that they should both marry when Azuki becomes a voice actress for the anime adaptation of their manga. The two then start creating their manga, under the pen name Muto Ashirogi, in hopes of getting serialized in Weekly Shounen Jump.

title: I Am Wrath
text: Stanley Hill opens a can of brutal vengeance on the thugs who murdered his wife and the corrupt cops who are protecting them.

title: Precious Cargo
text: A crime boss tries to make off with loot that belongs to another thief.

title: Snowden
text: The NSA's illegal surveillance techniques are leaked to the public by one of the agency's employees, Edward Snowden, in the form of thousands of classified documents distributed to the press.

title: Tenchi Muyô! In Love
text: Tenchi and co. find their existence unsettled by a time-travelling entity called Kain. Desiring revenge upon the Juraian emperor, Tenchi, Kain travels back in time to kill Tenchi's mother. Trying to preserve the timestream, Tenchi and friends follow him back. Unfortunately, Tenchi must also deal with the pain that seeing his mother causes him. Since she died in the future, seeing her alive in the past reopens his old wounds.

title: Ratchet & Clank
text: When the galaxy comes under the threat of a nefarious space captain, a mechanic and his newfound robot ally join an elite squad of combatants to save the universe.

title: Kicking Off
text: After their football team is relegated, two fans kidnap the referee who they believe unfairly disallowed a winning goal.

title: SORI: Voice from the Heart
text: The plot revolves around a robotic satellite with artificial intelligence that crash lands in Korea and contains clues for a father who is desperately searching for his missing daughter.

title: Gintama: The Final Chapter - Be Forever Yorozuya
text: Gintoki travels into the future and discovers it to be a wasteland with his friends fallen apart. He reunites them to find out what went wrong and how to fix things.

title: The Nice Guys
text: In 1970s Los Angeles, a mismatched pair of private eyes investigate a missing girl and the mysterious death of a porn star.

title: Kindergarten Cop 2
text: Assigned to recover sensitive stolen data, a gruff FBI agent goes undercover as a kindergarten teacher, but the school's liberal, politically correct environment is more than he bargained for.

title: Buck Rogers in the 25th Century
text: A 20th century astronaut emerges out of 500 years of suspended animation into a future time where Earth is threatened by alien invaders.

title: World of Glory
text: After witnessing an act of unprecedented violence without even flinching, an emotionally numb real-estate agent visits his ailing mother at the hospital, and then, the graveyard. Is there a speck of happiness in this cruel and short life?

title: The Crew
text: Aircraft crew members must put off their differences when a natural disaster threatens to death hundreds of tourists.

title: The Shallows
text: A mere 200 yards from shore, surfer Nancy is attacked by a great white shark, with her short journey to safety becoming the ultimate contest of wills.

title: Gen-X Cops
text: A ridiculed HK cop hires 3 cadets, directly  out of police academy, to go undercover and get the criminals, who stole explosives and killed his partner.

title: The Handmaiden
text: A woman is hired as a handmaiden to a Japanese heiress, but secretly she is involved in a plot to defraud her.

title: Alice Through the Looking Glass
text: Alice returns to the whimsical world of Wonderland and travels back in time to help the Mad Hatter.

title: The BFG
text: An orphan little girl befriends a benevolent giant who takes her to Giant Country, where they attempt to stop the man-eating giants that are invading the human world.

title: My Scientology Movie
text: Louis Theroux documents his investigation into what goes on behind the scenes of the infamous Church of Scientology.

title: Sausage Party
text: A sausage strives to discover the truth about his existence.

title: Karate Bullfighter
text: This movie is based on the true life story of a Korean fighter named Choi Bae-dal , the founder of Kyokushin Karate in Japan.

title: All Yours
text: Cass, a widowed mother of two and driven attorney, is in need of a nanny. She hires Matt, a handsome single family friend. Matthew's more laid back style changes the demeanor of the family's intense schedule. Does Cass realize she's needs to adjust her life's focus?

title: Kill Command
text: Set in a near future, technology-reliant society that pits man against killing machines.

title: Captain Fantastic
text: In the forests of the Pacific Northwest, a father devoted to raising his six kids with a rigorous physical and intellectual education is forced to leave his paradise and enter the world, challenging his idea of what it means to be a parent.

title: Toni Erdmann
text: A practical joking father tries to reconnect with his hard working daughter by creating an outrageous alter ego and posing as her CEO's life coach.

title: The Wailing
text: Soon after a stranger arrives in a little village, a mysterious sickness starts spreading. A policeman, drawn into the incident, is forced to solve the mystery in order to save his daughter.

title: Comedy of the Strict Regime
text: The action is set in 1970 as the Soviet Union  are preparing to celebrate Lenin's centenary. Not to be outdone, the camp commander decides to have the prisoners put on a play about Lenin's life. However, the ensuing preparations turn everything upside down and seem to offer a God-given chance to plot an escape.

title: The Meddler
text: An aging widow from New York City follows her daughter to Los Angeles in hopes of starting a new life after her husband passes away.

title: Now You See Me 2
text: The Four Horsemen resurface, and are forcibly recruited by a tech genius to pull off their most impossible heist yet.

title: Ali Wong: Baby Cobra
text: Ali Wong's stand up special delves into her sexual adventures, hoarding, the rocky road to pregnancy, and why feminism is terrible.

title: Café Society
text: In the 1930s, a Bronx native moves to Hollywood and falls in love with a young woman who is seeing a married man.

title: Neo Tokyo
text: A trilogy of separate stories. In "Labyrinth labyrinthos", a girl and her cat enter a strange world. In "Running Man", a racer takes on the ultimate opponent. In "Construction Cancellation Order", a man must shut down worker robots.

title: Swiss Army Man
text: A hopeless man stranded on a deserted island befriends a dead body, and together they go on a surreal journey to get home.

title: The Do-Over
text: Two down-on-their-luck guys decide to fake their own deaths and start over with new identities, only to find the people they're pretending to be are in even deeper trouble.

title: Death Smiles on a Murderer
text: Greta, a mysterious woman with amnesia, is taken in by the wealthy Mr. and Mrs. von Ravensbruck. The three soon enter into a love triangle that turns deadly, as Greta's gruesome past is slowly revealed.

title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Out of the Shadows
text: The Turtles get into another battle with their enemy the Shredder, who has acquired new allies: the mutant thugs Bebop and Rocksteady and the alien being Krang.

title: The Fundamentals of Caring
text: A man suffering a family loss enrolls in a class about care-giving that changes his perspective on life.

title: Popstar: Never Stop Never Stopping
text: When it becomes clear that his solo album is a failure, a former boy band member does everything in his power to maintain his celebrity status.

title: A Midsummer Night's Dream
text: A modern re-telling of the classic fantasy drama by William Shakespeare, A Midsummer Night's Dream holds a star-studded cast with euphoric effects and melodramatic storytelling.

title: The Bremen Town Musicians
text: A story loosely based on the Brothers Grimm fairy tale 'Town Musicians of Bremen', about a donkey, a dog, a cat, a rooster and their master Troubadour.

title: Planet Earth
text: Emmy Award-winning, 11 episodes, five years in the making, the most expensive nature documentary series ever commissioned by the BBC, and the first to be filmed in high definition.

title: Bo Burnham: Make Happy
text: Bo Burnham tackles life, death, sexuality, hypocrisy, mental illness and Pringles cans in his dazzling new stand-up special.

title: The Conjuring 2
text: Ed and Lorraine Warren travel to North London to help a single mother raising four children alone in a house plagued by a supernatural spirit.

title: Pelé: Birth of a Legend
text: Pele's meteoric rise from the slums of Sao Paulo to leading Brazil to its first World Cup victory at the age of 17 is chronicled in this biographical drama.

title: Ghostbusters
text: Following a ghost invasion of Manhattan, paranormal enthusiasts Erin Gilbert and Abby Yates, nuclear engineer Jillian Holtzmann, and subway worker Patty Tolan band together to stop the otherworldly threat.

title: Central Intelligence
text: After he reconnects with an awkward pal from high school through Facebook, a mild-mannered accountant is lured into the world of international espionage.

title: O.J.: Made in America
text: A chronicle of the rise and fall of O.J. Simpson, whose high-profile murder trial exposed the extent of American racial tensions, revealing a fractured and divided nation.

title: Bloodmoon
text: Martial arts action film finds a retired detective returning to action to stop a martial arts master with steel fingers who is killing champions from all sports.

title: Genius
text: A chronicle of Max Perkins's time as the book editor at Scribner, where he oversaw works by Thomas Wolfe, Ernest Hemingway, F. Scott Fitzgerald and others.

title: The Wooden Horse
text: True story of three British POWs and their attempt to escape from Nazi Germany.

title: Jason Bourne
text: The CIA's most dangerous former operative is drawn out of hiding to uncover more explosive truths about his past.

title: The Maid's Room
text: THE MAID'S ROOM is a psychological thriller that explores the complex relationships between truth and justice, hubris and power, wealth and fear.

title: Sympathy for the Underdog
text: A yakuza gang gets driven out of Yokohama by a big gang from Tokyo. They relocate to Okinawa to violently start over.

title: The Legend of Tarzan
text: Tarzan, having acclimated to life in London, is called back to his former home in the jungle to investigate the activities at a mining encampment.

title: The Purge: Election Year
text: Former Police Sergeant Barnes becomes head of security for Senator Charlie Roan, a Presidential candidate targeted for death on Purge night due to her vow to eliminate the Purge.

title: Mike & Dave Need Wedding Dates
text: Two hard-partying brothers place an online ad to find the perfect dates for their sister's Hawaiian wedding. Hoping for a wild getaway, the boys instead find themselves out-hustled by an uncontrollable duo.

title: Ice Age: Collision Course
text: When Scrat's acorn sends an asteroid to Earth, the Herd must find a way to stop the asteroid from hitting Earth with the help of a returning friend.

title: Lights Out
text: Rebecca must unlock the terror behind her little brother's experiences that once tested her sanity, bringing her face to face with a supernatural spirit attached to their mother.

title: Pete's Dragon
text: The adventures of an orphaned boy named Pete and his best friend Elliott, who happens to be a dragon.

title: Indignation
text: In 1951, Marcus, a working-class Jewish student from New Jersey, attends a small Ohio college, where he struggles with sexual repression and cultural disaffection, amid the ongoing Korean War.

title: Goat
text: Reeling from a terrifying assault, a 19 year-old enrolls into college with his brother and pledges the same fraternity. What happens there in the name of "brotherhood" tests him and his loyalty to his brother in brutal ways.

title: Marauders
text: When a bank is hit by a brutal heist, all evidence points to the owner and his high-powered clients. But as a group of FBI agents dig deeper into the case - and the deadly heists continue - it becomes clear that a larger conspiracy is at play.

title: Piper
text: A hungry sandpiper hatchling ventures from her nest for the first time to dig for food by the shoreline. The problem is, the food is buried in the sand where scary waves roll up.

title: The Adderall Diaries
text: Elliot, a troubled former successful writer decides to write about a missing wife and the following murder trial of her husband.

title: Hazard
text: Faced by a society of criminals, these three youths avenge their rights.

title: The Red Turtle
text: A man is shipwrecked on a deserted island and encounters a red turtle, which changes his life.

title: Satanic
text: Four friends on their way to Coachella stop off in Los Angeles to tour true-crime occult sites, only to encounter a mysterious young runaway who puts them on a terrifying path to ultimate horror.

title: Nerve
text: A high school senior finds herself immersed in an online game of truth or dare, where her every move starts to become manipulated by an anonymous community of "watchers."

title: Hellevator
text: One elevator, one girl who can read minds and one floor where the elevator should have never stopped: the ideal ingredients for a classic piece of weird horror. In the claustrophobic space of the elevator, a bunch of screwed up psychos who board halfway through produce absolute madness and mayhem on every square inch.

title: Sully
text: The story of Chesley "Sully" Sullenberger , an American pilot who became a hero after landing his damaged plane on the Hudson River in order to save the flight's passengers and crew.

title: The Forbidden Dance
text: A Brazilian princess tries to save the rain forests by introducing the world to the electrifying exotic lambada.

title: Jim Jefferies: Freedumb
text: Jim Jefferies talks about family life and challenges the idea of American freedom live on stage in Nashville, Tennessee.

title: The Grandmother
text: A young boy plants some strange seeds and they grow into a grandmother.

title: Webmaster
text: JB is the city's best attacker, who lives a carefully organized life in and outside the network. After hacking into the most powerful of all domains the Stoiser domain, JB thought that the cruel Stoiser would kill him. But instead he gave him a job - as a webmaster.

title: The Infiltrator
text: A U.S. Customs official uncovers a money laundering scheme involving Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar.

title: War Dogs
text: Loosely based on the true story of two young men, David Packouz and Efraim Diveroli, who won a three hundred million dollar contract from the Pentagon to arm America's allies in Afghanistan.

title: Vigilante Diaries
text: After killing a lot of bad guys including Armenians, Vigilante is wanted by the Armenian mafia boss, who gets help - but so does Vigilante.

title: Batman: The Killing Joke
text: As Batman hunts for the escaped Joker, the Clown Prince of Crime attacks the Gordon family to prove a diabolical point mirroring his own fall into madness.

title: Bad Moms
text: When three overworked and under-appreciated moms are pushed beyond their limits, they ditch their conventional responsibilities for a jolt of long overdue freedom, fun and comedic self-indulgence.

title: Hell or High Water
text: A divorced father and his ex-con older brother resort to a desperate scheme in order to save their family's ranch in West Texas.

title: Kingsglaive: Final Fantasy XV
text: King Regis, who oversees the land of Lucis, commands his army of soldiers to protect the kingdom from the Niflheim empire's plans to steal the sacred crystal which gives Lucis its magic and power.

title: Don't Breathe
text: Hoping to walk away with a massive fortune, a trio of thieves break into the house of a blind man who isn't as helpless as he seems.

title: Body
text: A night out turns deadly when three girls break into a seemingly empty mansion.

title: Sharknado 4: The 4th Awakens
text: Fin, his family and the cosmos have been blissfully sharknado-free in the five years since the most recent attack, but now sharks and tornadoes are being whipped up in unexpected ways and places.

title: The Edge of Seventeen
text: High-school life gets even more unbearable for Nadine when her best friend, Krista, starts dating her older brother.

title: Elle
text: A successful businesswoman gets caught up in a game of cat and mouse as she tracks down the unknown man who raped her.

title: Train to Busan
text: While a zombie virus breaks out in South Korea, passengers struggle to survive on the train from Seoul to Busan.

title: Tom Segura: Mostly Stories
text: The bearded, bawdy and comically bitter Tom Segura gets real about body piercings, the "Area 51" of men's bodies, and the lie he told Mike Tyson.

title: The Magnificent Seven
text: Seven gunmen from a variety of backgrounds are brought together by a vengeful young widow to protect her town from the private army of a destructive industrialist.

title: Moonlight
text: A young African-American man grapples with his identity and sexuality while experiencing the everyday struggles of childhood, adolescence, and burgeoning adulthood.

title: Masterminds
text: A guard at an armored car company in the Southern U.S. organizes one of the biggest bank heists in American history. Based on the October 1997 Loomis Fargo robbery.

title: Kubo and the Two Strings
text: A young boy named Kubo must locate a magical suit of armour worn by his late father in order to defeat a vengeful spirit from the past.

title: Bridget Jones's Baby
text: Forty-something and single again, Bridget decides to focus on her job and surround herself with friends. In a twist, she finds herself pregnant, but with one hitch - she can only be fifty percent sure of the identity of her baby's father.

title: Deepwater Horizon
text: A dramatization of the disaster in April 2010, when the offshore drilling rig called the Deepwater Horizon exploded, resulting in the worst oil spill in American history.

title: Miss Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children
text: When Jacob  discovers clues to a mystery that stretches across time, he finds Miss Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children. But the danger deepens after he gets to know the residents and learns about their special powers.

title: The Girl on the Train
text: A divorcee becomes entangled in a missing persons investigation that promises to send shockwaves throughout her life.

title: The Accountant
text: As a math savant uncooks the books for a new client, the Treasury Department closes in on his activities, and the body count starts to rise.

title: Imperium
text: A young FBI agent, eager to prove himself in the field, goes undercover as a white supremacist.

title: Kizumonogatari Part 1: Tekketsu
text: Follows Araragi's encounter with the vampire Kiss-shot Acerola-orion Heart-under-blade and his journey back into humanity from being a vampire.

title: Shin Godzilla
text: Japan is plunged into chaos upon the appearance of a giant monster.

title: Winnie Pooh
text: A Soviet version of Winnie-the-Pooh. His first adventure is a desperate attempt to get to honey in a bee hollow. He is ready to take decisive action.

title: Winnie the Pooh Goes Visiting
text: Winnie the Pooh and Piglet visit their friend the rabbit. After a hearty breakfast of honey, Pooh finds it hard to leave.

title: Your Name.
text: Two strangers find themselves linked in a bizarre way. When a connection forms, will distance be the only thing to keep them apart?

title: Winnie the Pooh and the Day of Concern
text: Vinni-Pukh is trying to help his friend donkey with huge depression which happened to be on his birthday

title: Comedy Central Roast of David Hasselhoff
text: Time to hassle the Hoff at the rudest, raunchiest television event of the year--The Comedy Central Roast of David Hasselhoff. From running in slo-mo on the beach to inspiring Germany with the power of cheesy pop--it's almost too easy.

title: DC Super Hero Girls: Hero of the Year
text: It's up Wonder Woman, Supergirl, Batgirl and Bumblebee at Super Hero High to stop Dark Opal from stealing their valued possessions to form the ultimate weapon!

title: Hacksaw Ridge
text: World War II American Army Medic Desmond T. Doss, who served during the Battle of Okinawa, refuses to kill people and becomes the first man in American history to receive the Medal of Honor without firing a shot.

title: David Cross: Making America Great Again
text: Actor/comedian David Cross skewers Donald Trump, takes shots at religious taboos and American swagger in a hilarious yet provocative night of comedy at the Paramount Theatre in Austin, TX.

title: Over the Garden Wall
text: Two brothers find themselves lost in a mysterious land and try to find their way home.

title: Wings, Legs and Tails
text: An ostrich is trying to learn how to fly in a dessert.

title: Blair Witch
text: After discovering a video showing what he believes to be his vanished sister Heather, James and a group of friends head to the forest believed to be inhabited by the Blair Witch.

Five carnival workers are kidnapped and held hostage in an abandoned, hellish compound where they are forced to participate in a violent game, the goal of which is to survive twelve hours against a gang of sadistic clowns.

title: ARQ
text: Trapped in a lab and stuck in a time loop, a disoriented couple fends off masked raiders while harboring a new energy source that could save humanity.

title: Arrival
text: A linguist works with the military to communicate with alien lifeforms after twelve mysterious spacecraft appear around the world.

title: Storks
text: Storks have moved on from delivering babies to packages. But when an order for a baby appears, the best delivery stork must scramble to fix the error by delivering the baby.

title: Maximum Ride
text: A flock of winged children mount a rescue plan when wolf-boys abduct their youngest member and return her to the militarized institution that created them all.

title: Endless Poetry
text: Surrealist filmmaker Alejandro Jodorowsky tells the story of himself as a young man becoming a poet in Chile, befriending other artists, and freeing himself from the limits of his youth.

title: The Girl with All the Gifts
text: A scientist and a teacher living in a dystopian future embark on a journey of survival with a special young girl named Melanie.

title: All Roads Lead to Rome
text: Maggie is an uptight, single mother and college writing teacher from New York City. In an effort to reconnect with her troubled teen daughter Summer, she decides to embark on a journey to a Tuscan village that she frequented in her younger days. Upon arrival, Maggie runs into Luca, a handsome former lover who is still a bachelor and lives with his eighty-year-old mother, Carmen. Summer  and Carmen  impulsively steal Luca's car and race off to Rome. Maggie and Luca quickly pursue allowing the two mismatched couples to spend some time together and develop a new understanding of each other.

title: Amanda Knox
text: American exchange student Amanda Knox is convicted and eventually acquitted for the 2007 death of another student in Italy.

title: Dirty 30
text: When the party is on, it is off the hook! Kate has only a few days to turn her life around before she turns Dirty 30, but with three besties and zero rules, anything is possible!

title: Gimme Danger
text: An in-depth look at legendary punk band The Stooges.

title: Go Figure
text: A teenager dreams of becoming a champion ice-skater, and soon discovers a top Russian instructor is working at a nearby private school.

title: Anything for Love
text: A high-powered executive lies about her career on her dating profile, while her match also hides his true identity.

title: Night Guards
text: Contemporary Moscow. When eighteen-year-old Pasha rescues a beautiful young woman from a band of strangely powerful attackers, he discovers an underworld of supernatural beings living among us.

title: La La Land
text: While navigating their careers in Los Angeles, a pianist and an actress fall in love while attempting to reconcile their aspirations for the future.

title: 13th
text: An in-depth look at the prison system in the United States and how it reveals the nation's history of racial inequality.

title: London Town
text: In '70s London, a 14 year-old boy is introduced to the Clash by his estranged mother. It changes his life forever.

title: Inferno
text: When Robert Langdon wakes up in an Italian hospital with amnesia, he teams up with Dr. Sienna Brooks, and together they must race across Europe against the clock to foil a deadly global plot.

title: Keeping Up with the Joneses
text: A suburban couple becomes embroiled in an international espionage plot when they discover that their seemingly perfect new neighbors are government spies.

title: Wild Oats
text: Everything changes for Eva when she receives a life insurance check accidentally made out for five million dollars instead of the expected fifty thousand dollars. She and her best friend take the money and head out for the adventure of a lifetime.

title: The Rocky Horror Picture Show: Let's Do the Time Warp Again
text: A straitlaced, square couple, seeking shelter from a storm, find themselves in the castle of a transgender alien mad scientist intent on creating a buff bodybuilder.

title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
text: Jack Reacher must uncover the truth behind a major government conspiracy in order to clear his name while on the run as a fugitive from the law.

title: Joe Rogan: Triggered
text: Unleashing his inquisitive, intense comedic style, Rogan explores everything from raising kids and Santa Claus to pot gummies and talking to dolphins.

title: Ethel & Ernest
text: The life and times of the parents of the hailed British graphic novelist, Raymond Briggs.

title: Flowers for Algernon
text: Charlie Gordon is mentally handicapped and all he wants in life is to be a genius. Charlie takes the chance, but he must adjust emotionally when a laboratory experiment raises his IQ to amazing levels.

title: Manchester by the Sea
text: A depressed uncle is asked to take care of his teenage nephew after the boy's father dies.

title: Lion
text: A five-year-old Indian boy is adopted by an Australian couple after getting lost hundreds of kilometers from home. 25 years later, he sets out to find his lost family.

title: The Thinning
text: In a future, overcrowded, dystopian society, students with the lowest test scores are culled. Two students discover errors with the test.

title: While You Were Fighting: A Thor Mockumentary
text: The story of what the hammer-wielding Nordic god Thor was up to while the rest of the Avengers were battling each other in "Captain America: Civil War". He moves into a flat with office worker Darryl Jacobson in Australia.

title: Bad Santa 2
text: Fueled by cheap whiskey, greed and hatred, Willie teams up once again with his angry little sidekick, Marcus, to knock off a Chicago charity on Christmas Eve.

title: Ice Guardians
text: On-ice enforcers struggle to rise through the professional ranks of the world's most prestigious hockey league, only to be confronted with a new found fight for the existence of the role itself.

title: Risk
text: The story of WikiLeak's editor-in-chief Julian Assange as seen by documentary filmmaker Laura Poitras.

title: The True Memoirs of an International Assassin
text: After a publisher changes a writer's debut novel about a deadly assassin from fiction to non-fiction, the author finds himself thrust into the world of his lead character, and must take on the role of his character for his own survival.

title: Alesha Popovich and Tugarin the Dragon
text: Alesha Popovich has to catch Tugarin Zmey and bring back the stolen money money with the help of a talking Horse , a wise granny, a donkey and a beauty Lyubava.

title: HyperNormalisation
text: Adam Curtis explains how, at a time of confusing and inexplicable world events, politicians and the people they represent have retreated in to a damaging over-simplified version of what is happening.

title: The African Doctor
text: The story of Seyolo Zantoko, who as a freshly graduated doctor of Congolese descent in France, struggled with his family to integrate in a small rural village, and ended up being considered as one of the most respected doctors in the area.

title: Whiplash
text: A ferocious, bullying music teacher teaches a dedicated student.

title: Junior and Karlson
text: A Soviet cartoon adaptation of a classic Swedish tale by Astrid Lindgren about Karlsson-on-the-Roof.

title: Sapphire Blue
text: Gwen has just discovered, that she's the final member of the secret time-traveling Circle of Twelve. Now she has to juggle with constant trips to the past, her relationships with Gideon and figuring out dark secrets surrounding the Circle.

title: A Silent Voice
text: A young man is ostracized by his classmates after he bullies a deaf girl to the point where she moves away. Years later, he sets off on a path for redemption.

title: Moana
text: In Ancient Polynesia, when a terrible curse incurred by the Demigod Maui reaches Moana's island, she answers the Ocean's call to seek out the Demigod to set things right.

title: Office Christmas Party
text: When his uptight CEO sister threatens to shut down his branch, the branch manager throws an epic Christmas party in order to land a big client and save the day, but the party gets way out of hand...

title: The Space Between Us
text: The first human born on Mars travels to Earth for the first time, experiencing the wonders of the planet through fresh eyes. He embarks on an adventure with a street-smart girl to discover how he came to be.

title: Rogue One: A Star Wars Story
text: In a time of conflict, a group of unlikely heroes band together on a mission to steal the plans to the Death Star, the Empire's ultimate weapon of destruction.

title: Split
text: Three girls are kidnapped by a man with a diagnosed 23 distinct personalities. They must try to escape before the apparent emergence of a frightful new 24th.

title: Underworld: Blood Wars
text: Vampire death dealer Selene  fights to end the eternal war between the Lycan clan and the Vampire faction that betrayed her.

title: Miss Sloane
text: In the high-stakes world of political power-brokers, Elizabeth Sloane is the most sought after and formidable lobbyist in D.C. But when taking on the most powerful opponent of her career, she finds winning may come at too high a price.

title: Passengers
text: A malfunction in a sleeping pod on a spacecraft traveling to a distant colony planet wakes one passenger 90 years early.

title: Hidden Figures
text: The story of a team of female African-American mathematicians who served a vital role in NASA during the early years of the U.S. space program.

title: Fences
text: A working-class African-American father tries to raise his family in the 1950s, while coming to terms with the events of his life.

title: The Founder
text: The story of Ray Kroc, a salesman who turned two brothers' innovative fast food eatery, McDonald's, into the biggest restaurant business in the world, with a combination of ambition, persistence, and ruthlessness.

title: Why Him?
text: A holiday gathering threatens to go off the rails when Ned Fleming realizes that his daughter's Silicon Valley millionaire boyfriend is about to pop the question.

title: Sing
text: In a city of humanoid animals, a hustling theater impresario's attempt to save his theater with a singing competition becomes grander than he anticipates even as its finalists find that their lives will never be the same.

title: I Am Not Your Negro
text: Writer James Baldwin tells the story of race in modern America with his unfinished novel, Remember This House.

title: Iron Man
text: Prizefighter Mason loses his opening fight so wife Rose leaves him for Hollywood. Without her around Mason trains and starts winning. Rose comes back and wants Mason to dump his manager Regan and replace him with her secret lover Lewis.

title: Assassin's Creed
text: Callum Lynch explores the memories of his ancestor Aguilar de Nerha and gains the skills of a Master Assassin, before taking on the secret Templar society.

title: A Dog's Purpose
text: A dog looks to discover his purpose in life over the course of several lifetimes and owners.

title: Microwave Massacre
text: Fed up of his wife's bad cooking, Donald kills her and turns to cannibalism to satisfy his appetite.

title: The OA
text: Having gone missing seven years ago, the previously blind Prairie returns home, now in her twenties with her sight restored. While many believe she is a miracle, others worry that she could be dangerous.

title: Fist Fight
text: When one school teacher unwittingly causes another teacher's dismissal, he is challenged to an after-school fight.

title: Shakespeare Behind Bars
text: Twenty male inmates in a Kentucky prison form an unlikely Shakespearean acting troupe.

title: A Street Cat Named Bob
text: The true feel-good story of how James Bowen, a busker and recovering drug addict, has his life transformed when he meets a stray ginger cat. Based on the international best selling book.

title: The Lego Batman Movie
text: A cooler-than-ever Bruce Wayne must deal with the usual suspects as they plan to rule Gotham City, while discovering that he has accidentally adopted a teenage orphan who wishes to become his sidekick.

title: The Spirit of Christmas
text: Four caroling children meet Jesus and Santa Claus and learn the true meaning of Christmas.

title: The Good Boy
text: Contemporary Moscow. Ninth-grader Kolya falls in love with a beautiful young teacher at his high school. The most beautiful girl in the senior class falls in love with him. How will he make his way through this triangle?

title: Dana Carvey: Straight White Male, 60
text: Emmy-winning comedy legend Dana Carvey returns to the stage with a routine that blends pitch-perfect impressions of big personalities with so-true-it-hurts stories about being a dad of millennials, the joys of aging, and pharmaceuticals.

title: Marvel One-Shot: Agent Carter
text: Frustrated at being marginalized at work, Peggy Carter goes on an unauthorized solo field mission.

title: Kizumonogatari II: Passionate Blood
text: In the spring of his second year of high school, Koyomi Araragi met the beautiful vampire Kiss-shot Acerola-orion Heart-under-blade. Koyomi saved Kiss-shot, who was on the verge of death with all four of her limbs cut off, but only at the expense of becoming her minion and a vampire. "In order to go back to being a human again, you must take back all of Kiss-shot's limbs." After receiving advice from Meme Oshino, an expert in the supernatural, Koyomi prepares to go into battle. Awaiting him are three powerful vampire hunters-Dramaturgy, a giant vampire hunter who is a vampire himself. Episode, a half-vampire who wields an enormous cross, and Guillotinecutter, a quiet man who specializes in killing vampires. Will Koyomi be able to take back Kiss-shot's limbs from the vampire hunters? Amidst the soft spring rain, the curtain rises on this fateful blood bath.

title: Joe Rogan: Live
text: Regardless of Joe Rogan's success on television with the Ultimate Fighting Championship or hosting Fear Factor or co-starring in NewsRadio, his true love is stand-up comedy. With more than 15 years as a touring comedian, Rogan has honed an opinionated comedic style that challenges the status quo. From his unorthodox ideas for peace in the Middle East to debunking the myth of Noah's Ark and appreciating the vastness of space - all of the energy of a live Joe Rogan performance is captured on Joe Rogan: Live!

title: Jim Gaffigan: Cinco
text: The king of clean comedy returns for his fifth hour long comedy special.

title: Kizumonogatari III: Cold Blood
text: Part 3 of Kizumonogatari  trilogy, based on a light novel by Nisio Isin.

title: John Wick: Chapter Two
text: After returning to the criminal underworld to repay a debt, John Wick discovers that a large bounty has been put on his life.

title: Get Out
text: A young African-American visits his white girlfriend's parents for the weekend, where his simmering uneasiness about their reception of him eventually reaches a boiling point.

title: Logan
text: In a future where mutants are nearly extinct, an elderly and weary Logan leads a quiet life. But when Laura, a mutant child pursued by scientists, comes to him for help, he must get her to safety.

title: Kong: Skull Island
text: After the Vietnam war, a team of scientists explores an uncharted island in the Pacific, venturing into the domain of the mighty Kong, and must fight to escape a primal Eden.

title: T2: Trainspotting
text: After 20 years abroad, Mark Renton returns to Scotland and reunites with his old friends Sick Boy, Spud, and Begbie.

title: The Big Sick
text: Pakistan-born comedian Kumail Nanjiani and grad student Emily Gardner fall in love but struggle as their cultures clash. When Emily contracts a mysterious illness, Kumail finds himself forced to face her feisty parents, his family's expectations, and his true feelings.

title: 100 Streets
text: Three people, three extraordinary stories. All lived out within a hundred London streets.

title: Saturn 3
text: Two lovers stationed at a remote base in the asteroid fields of Saturn are intruded upon by a retentive technocrat from Earth and his charge: a malevolent eight foot robot.

title: Beauty and the Beast
text: A selfish Prince is cursed to become a monster for the rest of his life, unless he learns to fall in love with a beautiful young woman he keeps prisoner.

title: The Boss Baby
text: A suit-wearing, briefcase-carrying baby pairs up with his 7-year old brother to stop the dastardly plot of the CEO of Puppy Co.

title: Mercury Plains
text: A troubled man runs away to Mexico and is recruited to join a paramilitary group of teens fighting the drug cartels. He proves himself to the group, but questions their motive.

title: Call Me by Your Name
text: In 1980s Italy, romance blossoms between a seventeen-year-old student and the older man hired as his father's research assistant.

title: Mudbound
text: Two men return home from World War II to work on a farm in rural Mississippi, where they struggle to deal with racism and adjusting to life after war.

title: Ghost in the Shell
text: In the near future, Major Mira Killian is the first of her kind: A human saved from a terrible crash, who is cyber-enhanced to be a perfect soldier devoted to stopping the world's most dangerous criminals.

title: Bill Burr: Walk Your Way Out
text: Comedian Bill Burr takes the stage in Nashville and riffs on such topics as overpopulation, fast food, dictators and gorilla sign language.

title: Fifty Shades Darker
text: While Christian wrestles with his inner demons, Anastasia must confront the anger and envy of the women who came before her.

title: Neal Brennan: 3 Mics
text: Neal Brennan is taking multitasking to a whole new level in this stand up special, which features the comedian switching between three different microphones symbolizing three different styles of comedy.

title: Lemonade
text: A view of a woman's journey through life.

title: American Fable
text: After 11-year-old Gitty discovers a man who can grant wishes hiding in her family's silo, she is forced to choose between saving the man's life and protecting her family.

title: The Void
text: Shortly after delivering a patient to an understaffed hospital, a police officer experiences strange and violent occurrences seemingly linked to a group of mysterious hooded figures.

title: Guyver: Dark Hero
text: Sean Barker, unwilling host to an alien bio-armor known as the Guyver, must fight the Kronos Corporation again before they discover the secrets of the Guyver's origin.

title: Denis Leary: No Cure for Cancer
text: Ticked off comic Denis Leary talks honestly about subjects ranging from smoking, red meat, drugs, his family, rehab, and yes, cancer.

title: Buster's Mal Heart
text: A family man's chance encounter with a conspiracy-obsessed drifter leaves him on the run from the police and an impending event known as the Inversion.

title: Power Rangers
text: A group of high-school students, who are infused with unique superpowers, harness their abilities in order to save the world.

title: Alien: Covenant
text: The crew of a colony ship, bound for a remote planet, discover an uncharted paradise with a threat beyond their imagination, and must attempt a harrowing escape.

title: Free Fire
text: Set in Boston in 1978, a meeting in a deserted warehouse between two gangs turns into a shoot-out and a game of survival.

title: Species III
text: As her species decays succumbing to infections and illnesses, an alien seductress immunologically stronger becomes the only hope for them to live on.

title: Ultimate Avengers 2
text: When the Chitauri invaders are sighted in the African kingdom of Wakanda, the Avengers covertly enter the advanced nation to investigate.

title: Mulholland Dr.
text: After a car wreck, an amnesiac woman sets out to learn what happened to her with the help of a wannabe actress.

title: Dave Chappelle: The Age of Spin
text: Dave Chappelle gives his usual skewed insight into the topics of race, technology, OJ Simpson, and more in a stand up special filmed in Hollywood.

title: CHiPS
text: A rookie officer is teamed with a hardened pro at the California Highway Patrol, though the newbie soon learns his partner is really an undercover Fed investigating a heist that may involve some crooked cops.

title: Table 19
text: Eloise, having been relieved of maid of honor duties after being unceremoniously dumped by the best man via text, decides to attend the wedding anyway, only to find herself seated with five fellow unwanted guests at the dreaded Table 19.

title: Dave Chappelle: Deep in the Heart of Texas
text: Dave Chappelle gives his stand about racially charged run-ins, celebrity scandals and fatherly dilemmas in his stand-up set at Austin's Moody Theater.

title: The Quiet Family
text: A family opens a mountain inn where their first guest commits suicide. Suddenly all their guests befall horrible fates.

title: A Plasticine Crow
text: "Plasticine Crow", a re-telling of the old Aesop fable about the Fox and the Crow.

title: Gifted
text: Frank, a single man raising his child prodigy niece Mary, is drawn into a custody battle with his mother.

title: Band of Brothers
text: The story of Easy Company of the U.S. Army 101st Airborne Division and their mission in World War II Europe, from Operation Overlord to V-J Day.

title: There Once Was a Dog
text: Two lonely souls met: a dog outcast by his owners, and a poor wolf living in the woods.

title: Baywatch
text: Devoted lifeguard Mitch Buchannon butts heads with a brash new recruit, as they uncover a criminal plot that threatens the future of the bay.

title: Snatched
text: When her boyfriend dumps her before their exotic vacation, a young woman persuades her ultra-cautious mother to travel with her to paradise, with unexpected results.

title: The Mummy
text: An ancient Egyptian princess is awakened from her crypt beneath the desert, bringing with her malevolence grown over millennia, and terrors that defy human comprehension.

title: The Fate of the Furious
text: When a mysterious woman seduces Dominic Toretto into the world of terrorism and a betrayal of those closest to him, the crew face trials that will test them as never before.

title: Sandy Wexler
text: Sandy Wexler is a talent manager working in Los Angeles in the 1990s, diligently representing a group of eccentric clients on the fringes of show business.

title: Betting on Zero
text: Writer/director Ted Braun follows controversial hedge fund titan Bill Ackman as he puts a billion dollars on the line in his crusade to expose Herbalife as the largest pyramid scheme in history.

title: Win It All
text: A small-time gambler agrees to stash a bag for an acquaintance who is heading to prison. When he discovers cash in the bag, he can't resist the urge to dip into the funds.

title: Captain Underpants: The First Epic Movie
text: Two overly imaginative pranksters named George and Harold hypnotize their principal into thinking he's a ridiculously enthusiastic, incredibly dimwitted superhero named Captain Underpants.

title: It Comes at Night
text: Secure within a desolate home as an unnatural threat terrorizes the world, a man has established a tenuous domestic order with his wife and son. Then a desperate young family arrives seeking refuge.

title: Cars 3
text: Lightning McQueen sets out to prove to a new generation of racers that he's still the best race car in the world.

title: Mini's First Time
text: A rebellious girl hooks up with an escort agency, where her stepfather is a client.

title: Planet Earth II
text: Wildlife documentary series with David Attenborough, beginning with a look at the remote islands which offer sanctuary to some of the planet's rarest creatures, to the beauty of cities, which are home to humans, and animals..

title: The Hero
text: An ailing movie star comes to terms with his past and mortality.

title: Nobody Speak: Hulk Hogan, Gawker and Trials of a Free Press
text: The trial between Hulk Hogan and Gawker Media pitted privacy rights against freedom of the press, and raised important questions about how big money can silence media. This film is an examination of the perils and duties of the free press in an age of inequality.

title: Cosmos
text: Astronomer Carl Sagan leads us on an engaging guided tour of the various elements and cosmological theories of the universe.

title: Maria Bamford: Old Baby
text: Maria Bamford performs a rapid-fire, playful stand-up set for crowds at park benches, bowling alleys and LA theaters in this roving comedy special.

title: Robin Williams: Live on Broadway
text: The fourth HBO stand-up special by Robin Williams.

title: The Death of Louis XIV
text: Upon returning from a hunting expedition, King Louis XIV feels a sharp pain in his leg. He begins to die, surrounded by loyal followers in the royal chambers.

title: Death Note: Desu nôto
text: An intelligent high school student goes on a secret crusade to eliminate criminals from the world after discovering a notebook capable of killing anyone whose name is written into it.

title: Munna bhai M.B.B.S.
text: A gangster sets out to fulfill his father's dream of becoming a doctor.

title: The Beguiled
text: The unexpected arrival of a wounded Union soldier at a girls school in Virginia during the American Civil War leads to jealousy and betrayal.

title: Baby Driver
text: After being coerced into working for a crime boss, a young getaway driver finds himself taking part in a heist doomed to fail.

title: Okja
text: A young girl risks everything to prevent a powerful, multinational company from kidnapping her best friend - a fascinating beast named Okja.

title: Embassy
text: A young couple moves into a new house in Warsaw and discovers that the elevator can travel back in time to 1939, when the whole place was a German embassy.

title: Rough Night
text: Things go terribly wrong for a group of girlfriends who hire a male stripper for a bachelorette party in Miami.

title: Generation Iron 2
text: Filmmaker Vlad Yudin follows several body builders as they struggle to find success in a competitive industry.

title: Mystère à la Tour Eiffel
text: The daughter of one of the architects who built the Eiffel Tower gets framed for a murder that has taken place there, so she and her girlfriend embark on a quest across Paris to solve the mystery.

title: Stefan Zweig: Farewell to Europe
text: Before Dawn charts the years of exile in the life of famous Jewish Austrian writer Stefan Zweig, his inner struggle for the "right attitude" toward the events in war torn Europe, and his search for a new home.

title: Saved by the Bell: Hawaiian Style
text: Kelly's grandfather Harry invites the gang for a vacation at The Hawaiian Hideaway, his hotel in Honolulu, but they soon discover that a rival is threatening to put him out of business, so they scheme to help save the Hideaway.

title: Plain Clothes
text: To prove his brother's innocence, undercover officer Nick enrolls in high school again, dealing with crushes, bullies, humiliations, popularity swings, and quirky teachers and staff to find the real murderer.

title: The Prime Gig
text: A telesales con man finds the ultimate racket, but starting an affair with the girlfriend of his guru-like boss might be the wrong call.

title: The Night Before
text: A popular beauty surprisingly asks a nerd to take her to the prom. He wakes up hours later in a sleazy alley. She's missing but he remembers nothing about it.

title: Late Night with Conan O'Brien: The Best of Triumph the Insult Comic Dog
text: A hilarious collection of some of the best Triumph the Insult Comic Dog segments from "Late Night with Conan O'Brien."

title: Get Me Roger Stone
text: A documentary exploring the life and career of notorious Republican dirty trickster and longtime Trump adviser, Roger Stone, who helped create the real estate mogul's political career.

title: T2 3-D: Battle Across Time
text: Three freedom fighters attack a large corporation to prevent a future apocalypse.

title: Despicable Me 3
text: Gru meets his long-lost, charming, cheerful, and more successful twin brother Dru, who wants to team up with him for one last criminal heist.

title: Last Year's Snow Was Falling
text: Surreal misadventures of a lazy drunkard with speech impediment trying to get a New Year tree on a short notice. Loosely based on folk fairy tales.

title: Investigation Held by Kolobki
text: Two crazy brothers-detectives from a weird provincial town are searching for a rare striped elephant stolen by a suspicious foreigner.

title: Karlson Returns
text: Karlsson-on-the-Roof returns to stands against a stern housekeeper. Fun will never surrender.

title: Vacations in Prostokvashino
text: When his mom plans a vacation to a resort, little Fyodor runs away to family's cottage house instead, to visit his friends Matroskin the Cat and Sharik the Dog.

title: Winter in Prostokvashino
text: Continuing adventures of little Fyodor and his talking cat friend.

title: The Godfather Trilogy: 1972-1990
text: The multigenerational saga of the rise and fall of the Corleone crime family.

title: Priklyucheniya Kapitana Vrungelya
text: An old sea captain and his student decide to take part in the international regatta. At the same time an amateur thief steals a statue of Aphrodite from Louvre and boards their yacht by mistake. A long, fun adventure is ahead.

title: Tickling Giants
text: While the Egyptian revolution of 2011 is underway, surgeon turned comedian Bassem Youssef airs a television show that makes him popular to his countrymen but disliked by the government.

title: Vovka in the Kingdom of Far Far Away
text: A schoolboy gets into a fairy tale with the help of a librarian and DIY book. But life in the magical land is not as easy as it seems.

title: Adventures of Mowgli: The Kidnapping
text: Since Maugli saved from the trap of baby elephant from family of elephant Hatkhi, a rumor that a human baby lives in a wolfish covey, reached to banderlogists. An apish tribe arboricolous decided to do Maugli the fugleman. They steal Maugli and carry him in the neglected city in jungles.

title: A Detective Story
text: A private detective is hired to track down the computer hacker known as Trinity. But as he gets close his goal, reality takes a weird turn for him.

title: Final Flight of the Osiris
text: The crew of the hovercraft Osiris must get a message back to Zion, a message of vital importance. Easy to do, but for the armada of Sentinels between them and Zion.

title: Kid's Story
text: A teenager's dreams which conclude with him falling off a building, lead him to believe that the reality he lives in, may not be so real after all.

title: Cheburashka
text: Adventures of Cheburashka and Crocodile Gena continues.

title: War for the Planet of the Apes
text: After the apes suffer unimaginable losses, Caesar wrestles with his darker instincts and begins his own mythic quest to avenge his kind.

title: The Square
text: A prestigious Stockholm museum's chief art curator finds himself in times of both professional and personal crisis as he attempts to set up a controversial new exhibit.

title: The Meyerowitz Stories
text: An estranged family gathers together in New York City for an event celebrating the artistic work of their father.

title: War Machine
text: An idiosyncratic general confronts opposition from enemies, allies, and bureaucrats while leading a massive rebuilding operation in Afghanistan.

title: Tokyo Idols
text: Girl bands and their pop music permeate every moment of Japanese life. Following an aspiring pop singer and her fans, Tokyo Idols explores a cultural phenomenon driven by an obsession with young female sexuality, and the growing disconnect between men and women in hyper-modern societies

title: Vir Das: Abroad Understanding
text: Comedian Vir Das critics nationalism, globalism and bad politics in two performances in New York and New Delhi.

title: Norm Macdonald: Hitler's Dog, Gossip & Trickery
text: In this new stand-up special, Norm Macdonald delivers sly, deadpan observations from an older -- and perhaps even wiser -- point of view.

title: Valerian and the City of a Thousand Planets
text: A dark force threatens Alpha, a vast metropolis and home to species from a thousand planets. Special operatives Valerian and Laureline must race to identify the marauding menace and safeguard not just Alpha, but the future of the universe.

title: The Gracefield Incident
text: In Gracefield, three couples are spending a long weekend in a luxurious cabin when suddenly an uninvited guest in the form of a meteorite, comes crashing the party...

title: Shadow World
text: Based on the book of The Shadow World, this feature length documentary is an investigation into the multi-billion dollar international arms trade.

title: Wow! A Talking Fish!
text: A poor fisherman catches a talking fish, upon releasing it he summons a shape-shifting wizard by mistake.

title: Travels of an Ant
text: The story about a injured ant who travel by a hitch-hiking.

title: The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes and Doctor Watson: The Hunt for the Tiger
Fugitives
text: Jean is taken hostage at a bank by a foolish bank robber. As Jean left prison an hour earlier, the police assume he's the robber. Everything goes comically wrong. The robber's little daughter joins the fugitives.

title: Tiger Raid
text: Two cold-blooded mercenaries form an unlikely bond as they race across the desert in the dead of night.

title: Gulliver's Travels
text: An Englishman returns after nine years abroad and tells strange stories of the tiny people of Lilliput, the giants of Brobdingnag, the flying island Laputa and the Houyhnhnms, a race of intelligent horses.

title: Seven Sisters
text: In a world where families are limited to one child due to overpopulation, a set of identical septuplets must avoid being put to a long sleep by the government and dangerous infighting while investigating the disappearance of one of their own.

title: Atomic Blonde
text: An undercover MI6 agent is sent to Berlin during the Cold War to investigate the murder of a fellow agent and recover a missing list of double agents.

title: Empties
text: A comic love story about a man who refuses to accept that old age is empty of love, meaning and value to society.

title: Goon: Last of the Enforcers
text: A hockey player plagued by injuries is confronted with the possibility of retirement when a tough new player challenges his status as the league's top enforcer.

title: Dunkirk
text: Allied soldiers from Belgium, the British Commonwealth and Empire, and France are surrounded by the German Army and evacuated during a fierce battle in World War II.

title: Belladonna of Sadness
text: An evil feudal lord rapes a village girl on her wedding night and proceeds to ruin her and her husband's lives. After she's eventually banished from her village, the girl makes a pact with the devil to gain magical ability and take revenge.

title: The Putin Interviews
text: Academy Award-winning filmmaker Oliver Stone interviews the Russian president Vladimir Putin about divisive issues related to the US-Russia relations.

title: Unedited Footage of a Bear
text: An unedited shot of a bear .

title: Oh, Hello: On Broadway
text: Two delusional geriatrics reveal curious pasts, share a love of tuna and welcome a surprise guest in this filming of the popular comedy show.

title: Good Time
text: After a botched bank robbery lands his younger brother in prison, Connie Nikas embarks on a twisted odyssey through New York City's underworld to get his brother Nick out of jail.

title: Don Camillo in Moscow
text: Priest Don Camillo blackmails his friendly rival Peppone into letting him join a Communist delegation visiting the Soviet Union.

title: The House
text: After the town takes away their daughter's college scholarship, a couple start an illegal casino in their friend's house to make back the money.

title: Logan Lucky
text: Two brothers attempt to pull off a heist during a NASCAR race in North Carolina.

title: The Dark Tower
text: A boy haunted by visions of a dark tower from a parallel reality teams up with the tower's disillusioned guardian to stop an evil warlock known as the Man in Black who plans to use the boy to destroy the tower and open the gates of Hell.

title: Annabelle: Creation
text: Twelve years after the tragic death of their little girl, a doll-maker and his wife welcome a nun and several girls from a shuttered orphanage into their home, where they become the target of the doll-maker's possessed creation, Annabelle.

title: Gena the Crocodile
text: Cheburashka is a creature unknown to science. After the zoo rejects him, he becomes lonely and wants friends. Meanwhile, a crocodile named Gena is in the same boat and seeks friendship. The two meet and build a house for the lonely.

title: It
text: In the summer of 1989, a group of bullied kids band together to destroy a shape-shifting monster, which disguises itself as a clown and preys on the children of Derry, their small Maine town.

title: On the Trail of the Bremen Town Musicians
text: Sequel to the cult Russian animation Bremenskie muzykanty

title: In the blue sea, in the white foam.
text: Musical fantasy on the plots of the Armenian folk stories.

title: Wolf and Calf
text: One day, the Wolf stole the newborn Calf and brought him home to eat, but regretted it and decided not to eat it, but wait until he grows up. The Wolf becomes attached to the Calf, takes care of him, feeds milk, sings lullabies, reads books. For the sake of the Calf, the Wolf keeps cleanliness - "children - they can not grow in the mud." And the Wild Boar, which smokes a cigarette, the Wolf literally drives a rag. Gradually, the Wolf and the Calf are so used to each other that they began to live like a father and son.

title: Bobik Visiting Barbos
text: Early in the morning the grandfather walks his pet-dog Barbos. Then he leaves him alone at home, and goes until the evening, appointing Barbos "for the owner." The Barbos is bored alone, and he invites dog the Bobik to visit. The Barbos portrays himself as the owner of the apartment: unceremoniously empties the refrigerator, arranges skating on the floor, filled with the acid, stating: "And what about my grandfather? Here everything is mine. "And" And if my grandfather does not listen, then I use the broom ", trying in every possible way to impress the Bobik.

title: The Magic Ring
text: The tale that the house was not stoked throughout the century.

title: The Emoji Movie
text: Gene, a multi-expressional emoji, sets out on a journey to become a normal emoji.

title: Death Note
text: A high school student named Light Turner discovers a mysterious notebook that has the power to kill anyone whose name is written within its pages, and launches a secret crusade to rid the world of criminals.

title: Wind River
text: A veteran hunter helps an FBI agent investigate the murder of a young woman on a Wyoming Native American reservation.

title: Rory Scovel Tries Stand-Up for the First Time
text: Comedian Rory Scovel storms the stage in Atlanta, where he shares unfocused thoughts about things that mystify him, relationships and the thong song

title: Shot Caller
text: A newly released prisoner is forced by the leaders of his gang to orchestrate a major crime with a brutal rival gang on the streets of Southern California.

title: The Hitman's Bodyguard
text: The world's top bodyguard gets a new client, a hitman who must testify at the International Criminal Court. They must put their differences aside and work together to make it to the trial on time.

title: Rick and Morty: State of Georgia Vs. Denver Fenton Allen
text: A faithful, word-for-word recreation of one colorful day in the American court system.

title: Themroc
text: Made without proper language, just gibberish and grunts, this is an absurdist comedy about a man who rejects every facet of normal bourgeois life and turns his apartment into a virtual cave.

title: A German Life
text: Brunhilde Pomsel describes herself as an "apolitical girl" and a "figure on the margins," but she got closer to one of the worst criminals in world history than anyone else left alive. Today aged 104, Pomsel served as Nazi Propaganda Minister Joseph Goebbels' stenographer. Brunhilde Pomsel's life mirrors all the major breaks and continuities of the 20th century. Many people think that the dangers of war and fascism have been overcome. Brunhilde Pomsel makes it clear that this is not case. "A German Life" makes the viewer automatically ask: How would I have acted? What principles might I have betrayed to advance my career? Her extraordinary biography and personal journey into the past lead to the disturbing but timeless question: How reliable is my own moral compass?

title: Self-criticism of a Bourgeois Dog
text: A bourgeois dog and former filmmaker confesses how he became four-legged by failing in love, apple-picking and revolution. A political comedy with magic twists.

title: LEGO DC Super Hero Girls: Brain Drain
text: The DC Super Girls go LEGO® in this animated adventure brimming with brain-twisting action! The mind games are only beginning when Supergirl, Wonder Woman, and Batgirl have no recollection of a series of wrongdoings that they were responsible for. Who can the girls turn to when even Bumblebee, Katana and other members of Super Hero High are also up to no good? It will take more than super powers to untangle this mental mix-up and find out who or what is behind these mind-bending misdoings! Get up and get your cape on for the ultimate in LEGO® girl power!

title: Kingsman: The Golden Circle
text: After the Kingsman's headquarters are destroyed and the world is held hostage, an allied spy organisation in the United States is discovered. These two elite secret organisations must band together to defeat a common enemy.

title: Ari Shaffir: Double Negative
text: Comedian Ari Shaffir steps outside of his yamaka to expose the uncomfortable truth that children are trash, and becoming an adult also brings about its own greasy problems.

title: Blade Runner 2049
text: Young Blade Runner K's discovery of a long-buried secret leads him to track down former Blade Runner Rick Deckard, who's been missing for thirty years.

title: The Nut Job 2: Nutty by Nature
text: Following the events of the first movie, Surly and his friends must stop Oakton City's Mayor from destroying their home to make way for a dysfunctional amusement park.

title: Bliss
text: Two young people in Berlin, a refugee and a homeless punk, form a relationship.

title: Alles Inklusive
text: An encounter of some very diverse people, whose lives are intertwined by a fateful incident a long time ago.

title: Mother!
text: A couple's relationship is tested when uninvited guests arrive at their home, disrupting their tranquil existence.

title: Icarus
text: When Bryan sets out to uncover the truth about doping in sports, a chance meeting with a Russian scientist transforms his story from a personal experiment into a geopolitical thriller.

title: Cage Dive
text: Three friends filming an audition tape for an extreme reality-TV show find themselves stranded in shark-infested waters, turning their recording into a bloody diary of death. Do they have what it takes to survive the open water?

title: Boniface's Holiday
text: A circus lion goes on holiday to Africa, but his circus skills doesn't let him be.

title: American Made
text: The story of Barry Seal, an American pilot who became a drug-runner for the CIA in the 1980s in a clandestine operation that would be exposed as the Iran-Contra Affair.

title: Little Boxes
text: An interracial family struggles to adjust when they move from New York City to a small, predominately white town in Washington State.

title: Geostorm
